— manage isolated agent identities\\n- `bind/unbind` — route inbound channel traffic to agents\\n- `set-identity` — set name, avatar, theme\\n\\n**It does NOT execute agents or run inference turns.** No `run`, `exec`, or `invoke` subcommand exists.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 2. `openclaw agent` — Single Turn Execution (via Gateway)\\n\\nThis is the concrete command for running one agent turn from scripts:\\n\\n```bash\\nopenclaw agent --agent ops --message \\\"Summarize logs\\\"\\nopenclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \\\"status update\\\" --deliver\\nopenclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \\\"Summarize inbox\\\" --thinking medium\\n```\\n\\n**Key behavior:**\\n- Routes through a running **Gateway** (WebSocket)\\n- `--local` flag for embedded mode (no Gateway)\\n- `--deliver` to route reply to a target channel\\n- Supports `--thinking`, `--model`, `--session-id`\\n\\n**This is the primary CLI hook for external integrations (including Python scripts).**\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 3. `sessions_spawn` Tool — Programmatic Sub-Agent Spawning\\n\\nFor agent-to-agent delegation (from within an agent turn, via tool calls):\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"tool\\\": \\\"sessions_spawn\\\",\\n  \\\"params\\\": {\\n    \\\"task\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n    \\\"runtime\\\": \\\"subagent\\\",  // or \\\"acp\\\"\\n    \\\"model\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n    \\\"label\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n    \\\"runTimeoutSeconds\\\": 120\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n- `runtime: \\\"subagent\\\"` → spawns an OpenClaw sub-agent\\n- `runtime: \\\"acp\\\"` → spawns an ACP harness agent (IDE integrations)\\n- Sub-agents run in isolated sessions, can receive file attachments via `attachments[]`\\n- Controlled by `agents.list[].subagents.allowAgents`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 4. `openclaw acp` — ACP Bridge (for IDE/Python ACP harness)\\n\\nFor Python runtimes that speak the **Agent Client Protocol (ACP)** over stdio:\\n\\n```bash\\nopenclaw acp\\nopenclaw acp --url wss://gateway-host:18789 --token <token>\\nopenclaw acp --session agent:main:main\\n```\\n\\n- Bridges ACP stdio ↔ Gateway WebSocket\\n- Keeps session state mapped to Gateway session keys\\n- Supports `initialize`, `newSession`, `prompt`, `cancel`, `listSessions`\\n- Python process can act as ACP client, spawning `openclaw acp` as a subprocess\\n\\n---\\n\\n### 5. `openclaw system event` — Inject System Messages\\n\\nFor triggering agent turns via system events (useful for automated workflows):\\n\\n```bash\\nopenclaw system event --text \\\"Process new batch\\\" --mode now\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Practical Integration Pattern for Python Runtime\\n\\n**Option A — Direct turn trigger (simplest):**\\n```python\\nimport subprocess\\nresult = subprocess.run([\\n    \\\"openclaw\\\", \\\"agent\\\",\\n    \\\"--agent\\\", \\\"main\\\",\\n    \\\"--message\\\", \\\"Process video batch 42\\\",\\n    \\\"--deliver\\\"\\n], capture_output=True, text=True)\\n```\\n\\n**Option B — ACP protocol (fullest control):**\\n- Spawn `openclaw acp` as a subprocess\\n- Python runtime speaks ACP over stdio\\n- Supports session management, streaming, tool follow-along\\n- Use `sessions_spawn` with `runtime: \\\"acp\\\"` from within agent turns to invoke Python ACP harnesses\\n\\n**Option C — Gateway WebSocket directly:**\\n- Connect to `ws://localhost:18789` (default Gateway port)\\n- Use `chat.send` or `agent` messages to drive turns programmatically\\n- Subscribe to `sessions.messages.subscribe` for streaming results\\n\\n**Option D — `openclaw system event`:**\\n- Fire-and-forget injection into running agent session\\n- Good for lightweight external triggers\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Summary\\n\\nThere is **no standalone `openclaw run` or `openclaw exec`** for agents. Runtime invocation is expected via:\\n1. **`openclaw agent`** — script-friendly CLI single-turn executor\\n2. **`sessions_spawn`** tool (inside agent turns) — for sub-agent delegation\\n3. **`openclaw acp`** — for Python/IDE ACP harness integration over stdio\\n4. **Gateway WebSocket API** — for full programmatic control\\n5. **`openclaw system event`** — for injecting system prompts into running sessions\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"anthropic\",\n          \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 1,\n            \"output\": 1177,\n            \"totalTokens\": 82427,\n            \"cacheRead\": 79449,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 1800,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0.0482427\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1774984285053,\n          \"responseId\": \"msg_01DmVaEq86T3x2BnuQHPXBbB\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"962efe41\",\n            \"seq\": 27\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:subagent:7436c9b8-b2a0-46b8-9a9d-b36a20d7c96f\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"label\": \"s1-openclaw-runtime-docs\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-main-subagent-7436c9b8-b2a0-46b8-9a9d-b36a20d7c96f\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1774984329201,\n      \"sessionId\": \"7a35e7bc-361b-48ee-bd23-7410049291ef\",\n      \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 1000000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 26267,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0.1744863,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1774984210385,\n      \"endedAt\": 1774984289166,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 63245,\n      \"thinkingLevel\": \"low\",\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\main\\\\sessions\\\\7a35e7bc-361b-48ee-bd23-7410049291ef.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Here are the findings:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Research Findings: OpenClaw Agent Runtime Invocation\\n\\n### (1) Current CLI command to run an agent directly\\n\\n**Yes — `openclaw agent` exists today and is fully functional.**\\n\\n```bash\\n# Send a message to the main agent (via Gateway)\\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \\\"do something\\\"\\n\\n# Run embedded locally (requires API keys in shell env — no Gateway needed)\\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \\\"do something\\\" --local\\n\\n# Target a specific session\\nopenclaw agent --session-id <id> --message \\\"text\\\"\\n\\n# Deliver reply back to a channel\\nopenclaw agent --agent ops --message \\\"Generate report\\\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \\\"#reports\\\"\\n```\\n\\nSource: `docs/cli/agent.md` and `openclaw agent --help`\\n\\n---\\n\\n### (2) Two runtime paths exist\\n\\n| Mode | How | When |\\n|---|---|---|\\n| **Gateway-backed** (default) | Forwards to the running Gateway over WebSocket | Gateway must be running; normal operation |\\n| **Embedded/local** (`--local`) | Runs agent in-process directly | Requires provider API keys in shell env; no Gateway needed |\\n\\n---\\n\\n### (3) Sessions/subagents/APIs are the standard bridge\\n\\nYes. The intended pattern for spawning isolated agent turns programmatically is:\\n\\n- **`openclaw agent`** — CLI one-shot turn\\n- **`openclaw acp`** — ACP protocol bridge over stdio for IDE integrations (forwards to Gateway via WebSocket)\\n- **Sessions** (`openclaw sessions`) — manage stored conversation state; not themselves an execution surface\\n- **Cron jobs** (`openclaw cron`) — scheduled recurring agent turns\\n- **Hooks** — event-triggered agent turns\\n\\nThe ACP bridge (`openclaw acp`) is the intended path for programmatic IDE/code-level integration, and it routes through the Gateway session system.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### (4) Concrete supported patterns today\\n\\n```bash\\n# One-shot agent turn (Gateway mode)\\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \\\"Summarize logs\\\"\\n\\n# One-shot agent turn (embedded, no Gateway needed)\\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \\\"Summarize logs\\\" --local\\n\\n# ACP bridge (for IDE integrations - speaks ACP over stdio, forwards to Gateway)\\nopenclaw acp\\nopenclaw acp --session agent:main:main\\nopenclaw acp --url wss://gateway-host:18789 --token <token>\\n\\n# Scheduled agent turn via cron\\nopenclaw cron add --job \\\"daily-report\\\" --schedule \\\"0 9 * * *\\\" --agent main --message \\\"Generate daily report\\\"\\n\\n# Send message to channel (not agent turn, but triggers agent via channel routing)\\nopenclaw message send --channel telegram --target @user --message \\\"...\\\"\\n```\\n\\n**Key file paths:**\\n- `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\docs\\\\cli\\\\agent.md`\\n- `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\docs\\\\cli\\\\acp.md`\\n- `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\docs\\\\cli\\\\sessions.md`\\n\\n### Summary\\n\\nThe primary runtime invocation path is **`openclaw agent --agent <id> --message \\\"<text>\\\"`**. The `--local` flag bypasses the Gateway for fully embedded execution. For code-level integration, the ACP bridge (`openclaw acp`) over stdio is the intended mechanism. Sessions are storage/state constructs, not execution entry points themselves.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"anthropic\",\n          \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 1,\n            \"output\": 853,\n            \"totalTokens\": 27120,\n            \"cacheRead\": 25563,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 703,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0.02310315\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1774984270824,\n          \"responseId\": \"msg_01A6HnPnWupcTMyoUELgPHX6\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"1b0e6cbd\",\n            \"seq\": 21\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:subagent:f51d4031-7d60-444e-834b-57ca3d50d2c2\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"label\": \"s1-openclaw-community-patterns\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-main-subagent-f51d4031-7d60-444e-834b-57ca3d50d2c2\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1774984307376,\n      \"sessionId\": \"55445a18-663f-4993-bb97-5fdc1b017a28\",\n      \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 1000000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 21314,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 0.10744875000000001,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1774984211200,\n      \"endedAt\": 1774984274817,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 48060,\n      \"thinkingLevel\": \"low\",\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\main\\\\sessions\\\\55445a18-663f-4993-bb97-5fdc1b017a28.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"## Research Synthesis: How OpenClaw Users Execute Agents at Runtime\\n\\n### Confirmed Mechanisms (from official docs + local CLI inspection)\\n\\n**1. `openclaw agent` CLI command** *(primary programmatic trigger)*\\n- Runs a single agent turn via the Gateway\\n- Supports `--to <recipient>`, `--agent <id>`, `--session-id`, `--message`, `--deliver`, `--thinking`\\n- Has `--local` flag for embedded (no Gateway) mode with local API keys\\n- This is the main bridge for external systems or scripts wanting to invoke an agent programmatically\\n\\n**2. Sub-agents via `sessions_spawn` tool** *(primary in-agent parallelization pattern)*\\n- Within an agent run, spawning sub-agents is the standard pattern for parallel/background work\\n- Sub-agents get their own session (`agent:<id>:subagent:<uuid>`) and announce results back to requester\\n- Configurable model, thinking level, timeout, sandbox isolation, thread binding\\n- `mode: \\\"run\\\"` (one-shot) vs `mode: \\\"session\\\"` (persistent, requires `thread: true`)\\n- `/subagents spawn` also available as a slash command from chat\\n\\n**3. Gateway** *(infrastructure layer, not directly invoked by users)*\\n- The Gateway is the WebSocket broker that routes messages and sessions\\n- Users don't \\\"execute via gateway\\\" directly — it runs as a daemon and the CLI/channels route through it\\n- `openclaw gateway start/stop/restart` manages the service\\n\\n**4. Chat channels** *(primary user-facing runtime)*\\n- Users interact via Telegram, Discord, WhatsApp, etc.\\n- Messages to channels trigger agent runs automatically through the Gateway routing\\n- This is the most natural \\\"human-to-agent\\\" execution path\\n\\n**5. Cron jobs** (`openclaw cron`) *(scheduled agent execution)*\\n- For periodic/timed agent runs, the cron subsystem is used\\n- Runs are isolated from the main session\\n\\n**6. ACP agents** (`sessions_spawn` with `runtime: \\\"acp\\\"`) *(coding agent pattern)*\\n- For Claude Code, Codex, Gemini CLI — spawned via `sessions_spawn` with `runtime: \\\"acp\\\"` flag\\n- This is the Coding Agent skill pattern seen in the workspace\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Practical Integration Patterns\\n\\n| Pattern | Mechanism |\\n|---|---|\\n| Human triggers agent via chat | Chat channel → Gateway → agent run |\\n| Script/automation triggers agent | `openclaw agent --message \\\"...\\\" --deliver` |\\n| Agent spawns parallel task | `sessions_spawn` tool inside an agent turn |\\n| Scheduled agent work | `openclaw cron` |\\n| Persistent thread-bound sub-agent | `sessions_spawn` with `thread: true, mode: \\\"session\\\"` |\\n| Invoke coding agent (Codex/Claude Code) | `sessions_spawn` with `runtime: \\\"acp\\\"` |\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Uncertainty Flags\\n\\n- **Community patterns beyond official docs**: Limited external community content found (one meta-intelligence.tech guide, mainly summarizing official docs). No Reddit, Discord, or forum discussions surfaced — OpenClaw may have a smaller public community or most discussion is private.\\n- **`openclaw message send` as agent trigger**: The CLI has `message send` — unclear if this triggers an agent run or just sends a raw message. The changelog snippet mentions \\\"CLI/message send: write manual openclaw message send deliveries into the resolved agent session transcript\\\" — suggests it *does* thread into agent sessions.\\n- **ACP runtime specifics**: The `runtime: \\\"acp\\\"` path is mentioned in docs and skill references but full documentation wasn't fetched — behavior may differ from standard subagents.\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"anthropic\",\n          \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 1,\n            \"output\": 858,\n            \"totalTokens\": 22172,\n            \"cacheRead\": 18217,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 3096,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0.0299481\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1774984251762,\n          \"responseId\": \"msg_01Q1dcWMNrBcxBFiqvxoDqWU\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"d3808f83\",\n            \"seq\": 8\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"key\": \"agent:main:subagent:0d8719eb-b287-49cd-ae2e-5b7f7a2e2551\",\n      \"kind\": \"other\",\n      \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"spawnedBy\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"label\": \"watchdog-mvp-reconciler\",\n      \"displayName\": \"webchat:g-agent-main-subagent-0d8719eb-b287-49cd-ae2e-5b7f7a2e2551\",\n      \"parentSessionKey\": \"agent:main:main\",\n      \"deliveryContext\": {\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAt\": 1774877364780,\n      \"sessionId\": \"5011acc2-400b-4819-98ee-0dfa2ebbc124\",\n      \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n      \"contextTokens\": 1000000,\n      \"totalTokens\": 85092,\n      \"estimatedCostUsd\": 1.1475174000000001,\n      \"status\": \"done\",\n      \"startedAt\": 1774876965842,\n      \"endedAt\": 1774877319530,\n      \"runtimeMs\": 344365,\n      \"abortedLastRun\": false,\n      \"lastChannel\": \"webchat\",\n      \"transcriptPath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\main\\\\sessions\\\\5011acc2-400b-4819-98ee-0dfa2ebbc124.jsonl\",\n      \"messages\": [\n        {\n          \"role\": \"assistant\",\n          \"content\": [\n            {\n              \"type\": \"text\",\n              \"text\": \"Everything is clean. Here's the complete summary:\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Entregáveis\\n\\n### 1. Diagnóstico\\n\\n**Problema raiz:** `watchdog.py` confia 100% em `active_tasks.json` sem consultar o runtime. O campo `status` só muda se o agente que lançou a task o actualizar explicitamente — o que não acontece quando a session termina silenciosamente ou é esquecida.\\n\\n**Caso concreto:** Task `retest_claude_code_sidecar_20260328_160800` estava como `running` há +2 dias. Em `subagents/runs.json` o run correspondente (`childSessionKey: agent:main:subagent:f45bf7bf...`) tinha `endedAt`, `endedReason: subagent-complete`, `outcome.status: ok`. A task estava morta mas gerava pings a cada 10 minutos.\\n\\n### 2. Estados mínimos implementados\\n\\n`spawned → running → stalled → orphaned` (escalada por tempo, sem runtime)  \\n`running → completed / failed` (reconciliado contra `runs.json`)\\n\\n### 3. Implementação\\n\\n**Ficheiros criados:**\\n- `task_watchdog/reconciler.py` — lógica de reconciliação (225 linhas). Lê `subagents/runs.json`, pesquisa por `childSessionKey`, classifica o run, e actualiza o status da task sem inventar infra externa.\\n\\n**Ficheiros alterados:**\\n- `task_watchdog/watchdog.py` — `main()` chama `reconcile_all()` antes do `evaluate_tasks()`, com fallback silencioso se o reconciler falhar. `evaluate_tasks()` passou a suportar `spawned`, `stalled`, e `orphaned`. Deduplicação por `terminalNotifiedStatus` impede notificações repetidas.\\n\\n**Ficheiro de documentação criado:**\\n- `task_watchdog/RECONCILER_NOTES.md` — diagnóstico, arquitectura, thresholds, notas de teste.\\n\\n### 4. Validado em execução\\n\\n- Primeira run: reconciliou zombie → `completed`, notificou uma vez, arquivou em `task_history.jsonl`, removeu de `active_tasks.json`\\n- Segunda run: zero notificações falsas, `remaining: []`, `notifications: []`\"\n            }\n          ],\n          \"api\": \"anthropic-messages\",\n          \"provider\": \"anthropic\",\n          \"model\": \"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n          \"usage\": {\n            \"input\": 1,\n            \"output\": 580,\n            \"totalTokens\": 85672,\n            \"cacheRead\": 84914,\n            \"cacheWrite\": 177,\n            \"cost\": {\n              \"total\": 0.034840949999999996\n            }\n          },\n          \"stopReason\": \"stop\",\n          \"timestamp\": 1774877303444,\n          \"responseId\": \"msg_011opKNjJThTq68XsUsabBjj\",\n          \"__openclaw\": {\n            \"id\": \"5c002f29\",\n            \"seq\": 69\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"count":10,"sessions":[{"key":"agent:main:main","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","origin":{"provider":"webchat"},"displayName":"heartbeat","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1775035883612,"sessionId":"1bf752f6-670b-4c49-96b1-98f770dc0f1b","model":"gpt-5.4","contextTokens":272000,"totalTokens":23608,"estimatedCostUsd":0.3188715,"status":"running","startedAt":1775035883029,"childSessions":["agent:main:subagent:81d7b77f-33c5-424a-adbe-10888ffd1690","agent:main:subagent:e3aae318-4f32-4b3e-a743-69796c328349","agent:main:subagent:6aa0098b-64ca-4e22-ae81-7b11e92f47c9","agent:main:subagent:bce133f4-39ae-4582-9c63-4ec2d5c0522e","agent:main:subagent:1fc1a793-e351-454b-9f47-7fced2298ca5","agent:main:subagent:edcb65a3-61e3-4a11-b36c-2db4f4d0292f","agent:main:subagent:49e325a0-4b0e-4c25-87d8-cf335ff114c3","agent:main:subagent:dc24faab-3aae-482a-a304-961eabe592a2","agent:main:subagent:0d8719eb-b287-49cd-ae2e-5b7f7a2e2551","agent:main:subagent:7436c9b8-b2a0-46b8-9a9d-b36a20d7c96f","agent:main:subagent:f51d4031-7d60-444e-834b-57ca3d50d2c2","agent:main:subagent:6e766ed7-c44a-4042-8dde-13b75fef9cce","agent:main:subagent:47c9cc95-6306-4dbc-8230-de0fe8e590e3","agent:main:subagent:e05a5060-ea09-4860-8d93-b20a0212aa51","agent:main:subagent:2bf2df7c-2128-493d-aee7-f10865174752","agent:main:subagent:cf3068ff-f955-4e6c-8278-a9ba0a3d858a","agent:main:subagent:f9412e7f-e900-42a2-9831-fc8144c115d5"],"systemSent":true,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\main\\sessions\\1bf752f6-670b-4c49-96b1-98f770dc0f1b.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3xCex4AnGYTJwNk9EtWbUs6B|fc_0785557c08065f410169cce5fcced081908b4249d4f365c461","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"kinds":["subagent"],"limit":50,"activeMinutes":2880,"messageLimit":2},"partialJson":"{\"kinds\":[\"subagent\"],\"limit\":50,\"activeMinutes\":2880,\"messageLimit\":2}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":3044,"output":36,"totalTokens":27528,"cacheRead":24448,"cacheWrite":0,"cost":{"total":0.014262}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775035896706,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cce5fa5da481908224795a59b6b900","__openclaw":{"id":"437790d1","seq":27}}]},{"key":"agent:main:subagent:2bf2df7c-2128-493d-aee7-f10865174752","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","spawnedBy":"agent:main:main","label":"openclaw-worker-best-practices-1","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-main-subagent-2bf2df7c-2128-493d-aee7-f10865174752","parentSessionKey":"agent:main:main","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1774988339864,"sessionId":"64b94413-9d08-427b-9665-af85064cab1a","model":"claude-haiku-4-5","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":55360,"estimatedCostUsd":0.15500005000000003,"status":"done","startedAt":1774988163476,"endedAt":1774988304876,"runtimeMs":136843,"thinkingLevel":"low","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\main\\sessions\\64b94413-9d08-427b-9665-af85064cab1a.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now let me create a shorter, action-oriented summary for the main agent:\n\n## Research Complete: OpenClaw Agent as Deterministic Worker\n\nI've completed a comprehensive research into using `openclaw agent` as a deterministic worker/operator execution surface. Here are the **critical findings and recommendations:**\n\n---\n\n### 🔴 KEY FINDING: `--session-id` Isolation is Broken\n\n**Documented bug (GitHub #22085):** The `--session-id` flag does NOT create isolated sessions. All calls for the same agent share the same session key (`agent:<agentId>:main`), meaning:\n- Testing contaminates production\n- No true CLI-level isolation\n\n**Workaround:** Create separate agent IDs for isolated work instead of reusing `--session-id`.\n\n---\n\n### 📋 Best Practice: Use Lobster Workflows + Multi-Agent\n\nFor robust deterministic worker execution, the recommended architecture is:\n\n**Lobster workflows** (YAML-based pipeline engine):\n- Controls flow deterministically (not LLM-driven)\n- Explicit session key routing (`worker:jobId:step`)\n- Built-in loops, conditionals, retry logic\n- Survives gateway restart\n\n**Multi-agent architecture**:\n- Separate agents per role (fetcher, processor, reporter)\n- Isolated workspaces, memory, model choices\n- Peer messaging via `sessions_send` or `agentToAgent`\n- Clean separation of concerns\n\n**Example:**\n```yaml\n# pipeline.lobster\nsteps:\n  - id: fetch\n    command: openclaw.invoke --tool agent-send --args-json '{\"agentId\":\"fetcher\",\"sessionKey\":\"batch:jobId:fetch\"}'\n  - id: process\n    command: openclaw.invoke --tool agent-send --args-json '{\"agentId\":\"processor\",\"sessionKey\":\"batch:jobId:process\"}'\n    stdin: $fetch.stdout\n```\n\n---\n\n### ⚠️ Session Context & Staleness Risks\n\nSessions accumulate context across runs unless explicitly reset:\n- **Daily reset:** 4:00 AM local gateway time (can surprise workers)\n- **Context window:** Compaction auto-triggers at threshold (20K token floor by default)\n- **Memory flush:** Pre-compaction writes to `memory/` (durable across resets)\n\n**Mitigations:**\n- Use explicit session keys per job (`batch:jobId:step`)\n- Enable memory flush (default: on)\n- Monitor token usage via `/status`\n- Clean up old sessions: `openclaw sessions cleanup`\n\n---\n\n### 🏗️ File-Based Workflows\n\nOpenClaw lacks built-in job queue/file discovery. Options:\n\n1. **External orchestrator** (Redis, RabbitMQ, DB) → trigger via webhooks\n2. **Cron script** polling `/queue/*.json` → call `openclaw agent` per job\n3. **Lobster + file input** with loops\n4. **Memory files** (`memory/jobs.md`) as durable state\n\n---\n\n### 📊 Comparison Table\n\n| Aspect | `openclaw agent` CLI | `sessions_spawn` | Lobster |\n|--------|-----|-----|-----|\n| Session Isolation | ❌ Broken | ✅ Auto | ✅ Explicit |\n| Deterministic Flow | ❌ N/A | ⚠️ LLM-driven | ✅ YAML-controlled |\n| Context Staleness | ⚠️ High risk | ✅ Fresh per spawn | ✅ Controlled |\n| Best Use | Ad-hoc testing | Background helpers | **Worker pipelines** |\n\n---\n\n### 🎯 Concrete Recommendations\n\n**DO:**\n- ✅ Use separate agent IDs for isolation\n- ✅ Route via explicit session keys in Lobster\n- ✅ Write durable state to memory files\n- ✅ Trigger externally via webhooks with session routing\n- ✅ Use Lobster conditions to decide flow (not prompts)\n\n**DON'T:**\n- ❌ Reuse `--session-id` expecting isolation\n- ❌ Chain long sequences in one session\n- ❌ Let prompt drive orchestration\n- ❌ Assume session is fresh (check history)\n- ❌ Run workers across 4 AM reset without handling\n\n---\n\n### 📌 Uncertainties (Requires Testing)\n\n- **Concurrency limits:** How many `openclaw agent` CLI calls can run in parallel? (Recommend testing 4-8 before scaling)\n- **Webhook reliability:** Announces are \"best-effort\" with exponential backoff; no SLA\n- **Sub-agent announce timing:** Pending announces lost on gateway restart\n\n---\n\n### 📚 Full Research Document\n\nComplete analysis saved to:\n```\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\openclaw-worker-research.md\n```\n\nIncludes:\n- Detailed session mechanics\n- 6 best practice patterns\n- Production architecture diagram\n- Batch processing example\n- Configuration templates\n- All GitHub issue references\n\n---\n\n**Status:** Research complete. Ready for implementation if Lucca wants to build a worker pipeline using Lobster + multi-agent architecture."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-haiku-4-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":1240,"totalTokens":56600,"cacheRead":49287,"cacheWrite":6073,"cost":{"total":0.018719950000000003}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774988291123,"responseId":"msg_01Ey35m2yaamEgLfZoXyxwd1","__openclaw":{"id":"908a34a5","seq":35}}]},{"key":"agent:main:subagent:f9412e7f-e900-42a2-9831-fc8144c115d5","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","spawnedBy":"agent:main:main","label":"openclaw-worker-best-practices-3","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-main-subagent-f9412e7f-e900-42a2-9831-fc8144c115d5","parentSessionKey":"agent:main:main","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1774988284318,"sessionId":"a3bc23a9-b732-44ea-8cf2-931b72de58c0","model":"claude-haiku-4-5","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":41262,"estimatedCostUsd":0.1005012,"status":"done","startedAt":1774988165420,"endedAt":1774988255754,"runtimeMs":85658,"thinkingLevel":"low","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\main\\sessions\\a3bc23a9-b732-44ea-8cf2-931b72de58c0.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nI've completed the research task. Here's what I found:\n\n### Key Findings:\n\n1. **`--session-id` is NOT for isolation** — it targets an *existing* session, causing reuse. The docs example `--session-id 1234` targets a pre-stored session, not creating fresh isolation.\n\n2. **`--to <phone>` also reuses sessions** — if the same phone/identity runs multiple times, they share context. Not suitable for batch isolation.\n\n3. **`--local` is the answer for isolated workers** — runs embedded in the CLI with no session store interaction. Each invocation is completely isolated. Perfect for stateless batch processing.\n\n4. **Session key format is canonical** — `agent:<agentId>:scope:context`. You cannot create arbitrary session IDs; the system derives them from agent, channel, sender, etc.\n\n5. **Three isolation patterns for batch work:**\n   - **Pattern A (Recommended):** Use `--local` — simplest, zero session contamination, parallel-safe\n   - **Pattern B:** Use `sessions_spawn` from parent agent — UUID-based subagent isolation, task tracking, orchestration-aware\n   - **Pattern C:** Use cron with isolated runs — time-driven, scheduled isolation, full context\n\n6. **Avoid session reuse risk** — running the same `--to` value repeatedly reuses session context. This is the opposite of isolation.\n\n7. **For S1 operators as batch workers:**\n   - Invoke with `--local --agent s1-operator --message <item> --json`\n   - Each item gets fresh isolated context\n   - Can run in parallel safely\n   - Requires environment API keys (no Gateway dependency)\n\nI've written detailed findings to `research-openclaw-worker-sessions.md` with implementation examples, flag recommendations, and a complete reference."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-haiku-4-5","usage":{"input":5,"output":423,"totalTokens":41685,"cacheRead":37660,"cacheWrite":3597,"cost":{"total":0.01038225}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774988250011,"responseId":"msg_01L9GDSpPQ3AJpVPVrkCT9DA","__openclaw":{"id":"1cae6d83","seq":27}}]},{"key":"agent:main:subagent:cf3068ff-f955-4e6c-8278-a9ba0a3d858a","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","spawnedBy":"agent:main:main","label":"openclaw-worker-best-practices-2","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-main-subagent-cf3068ff-f955-4e6c-8278-a9ba0a3d858a","parentSessionKey":"agent:main:main","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1774988253568,"sessionId":"de5b176f-9457-4a4c-9a4a-93daf9289707","model":"claude-haiku-4-5","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":42869,"estimatedCostUsd":0.07815940000000002,"status":"done","startedAt":1774988164387,"endedAt":1774988217205,"runtimeMs":48137,"thinkingLevel":"low","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\main\\sessions\\de5b176f-9457-4a4c-9a4a-93daf9289707.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have sufficient evidence. Let me synthesize the findings.\n\n---\n\n## Research Findings: OpenClaw File-Based Workers & Stateless Execution Patterns\n\n### **Summary**\n\nOpenClaw users leverage three primary methods for file-based, stateless worker/operator execution, with strong community adoption around **coordinator-specialist patterns** and **workflow automation frameworks**.\n\n---\n\n### **Primary Execution Patterns**\n\n#### **1. Coordinator-Specialist Multi-Agent Model** (Most Mature)\n- **How it works**: One coordinator agent decomposes tasks, delegates to stateless specialists via `sessions_spawn`, and aggregates results.\n- **Key design principle**: Specialists run **without persistent memory** (`memory.enabled: false`) to ensure deterministic, repeatable execution.\n- **Real-world evidence**: LumaDock's multi-agent coordination guide (Feb 2026) explicitly positions this as \"the most reliable pattern for OpenClaw multi-agent setups.\" Specialists are ephemeral—they execute one task and terminate.\n- **File-based coordination**: Shared workspace files (`goal.md`, `plan.md`, `status.md`, `log.md`) allow agents to read/write coordination state without API calls.\n- **Cost optimization**: Stateless specialists prevent context accumulation across runs; cheaper models can be assigned to coordination while specialists focus on work quality.\n\n#### **2. Stateless Worker Subagents via `sessions_spawn`**\n- **Command**: `sessions_spawn(task, agentId?, model?, thinking?)`\n- **Behavior**: Non-blocking; returns `{status: \"accepted\", runId, childSessionKey}` immediately.\n- **Isolation**: Each sub-agent gets its own session (`agent:<id>:subagent:<uuid>`), independent workspace, and optional sandboxing.\n- **Announce pattern**: Results flow back to the parent via an announce step—parent receives a summary, not raw output.\n- **No persistent memory**: Sub-agent context only injects `AGENTS.md` + `TOOLS.md` (not `MEMORY.md`, `SOUL.md`, etc.), enforcing statelessness.\n- **Nesting support** (`maxSpawnDepth: 2`): Allows orchestrator → worker fan-out for parallel execution.\n- **Evidence**: Documented in OpenClaw Feb 2026 release; widely used in production multi-agent systems.\n\n#### **3. Direct CLI Worker Mode via `openclaw agent --local`**\n- **Command**: `openclaw agent --message \"task\" --local --deliver`\n- **Key flag**: `--local` forces embedded runtime on the current machine, skipping the Gateway entirely.\n- **Use case**: Scripted workflows, cron jobs, and deterministic one-shot tasks.\n- **Session derivation**: `--to <phone/chat-id>` derives session key; `--session-id` reuses an existing session.\n- **Output control**: `--json` returns structured metadata including session key, token usage, and runtime stats.\n- **Recent pattern**: Documented in OpenClaw agent-send docs (Feb 2026); favored for stateless scripting.\n\n---\n\n### **Deterministic Execution Mechanisms**\n\n#### **A. File-Based State Management**\n- **Shared workspace pattern**: Coordinator and all specialists read from a common workspace directory.\n  - `goal.md` → task definition and decomposition\n  - `status.md` → append-only log of subtask states (prevents race conditions)\n  - `log.md` → audit trail for debugging\n- **Idempotent writes**: Designed so writing the same value twice = same result as once.\n- **Evidence**: LumaDock guidance (Feb 2026) confirms this is production-proven for event-driven setups.\n\n#### **B. Fresh Session IDs**\n- **Per-task isolation**: Each `sessions_spawn` creates a fresh child session key.\n- **No memory leakage**: Sub-agent sessions start clean—no context from prior runs.\n- **Real evidence**: Reddit thread (Feb 2026): \"changing config requires both a gateway restart AND a fresh session on each channel\" — users actively use fresh sessions for deterministic re-execution.\n\n#### **C. Lobster Workflow Engine**\n- **Native OpenClaw workflow shell**: Typed, local-first macro engine for composable task pipelines.\n- **Determinism guarantee**: \"Reliable & Deterministic. Works every time. No scattered instructions across memory, heartbeat, and cron.\"\n- **Evidence**: Community project `clawflows` (113+ prebuilt workflows, updated 2 days ago) uses Lobster internally; all workflows are versioned and testable.\n\n---\n\n### **Recent Community Tools & Patterns**\n\n#### **ClawFlows** (nikilster/clawflows, updated 2 days ago)\n- **113 prebuilt workflows**: Email processing, meetings, finance, health, development, etc.\n- **Determinism design**: Workflows are plain-text, versioned, and scheduled via cron.\n- **Example**: `process-email` workflow (9am, 1pm, 5pm) automatically unsubscribes, archives, and summarizes.\n- **Commands**: `clawflows run <name>`, `clawflows enable`, version control via git.\n- **Community adoption**: 103 workflows from single contributor (@davehappyminion), 8+ from @march_io; contributors actively submitting new workflows.\n\n#### **ClawTeam** (win4r/ClawTeam-OpenClaw, updated 2 days ago)\n- **Multi-agent swarm coordination**: Uses OpenClaw as default agent runtime.\n- **Per-agent session isolation**: Ensures deterministic role separation.\n- **Production-hardened**: Explicit exec approval auto-config.\n\n#### **ACPX** (GitHub, updated 2 days ago)\n- **Headless CLI client** for stateful ACP sessions.\n- **Operators**: Can script agent interactions without TTY/interactive UI.\n- **Evidence**: Latest commit shows active maintenance for operator/worker use cases.\n\n---\n\n### **Practical Advice from Community**\n\n1. **Use stateless specialists by default**: Disable memory (`memory.enabled: false`) for workers; coordinator owns long-term state.\n2. **Delegate via `sessions_spawn`**: Non-blocking, isolated, provides fresh session per task.\n3. **File-based coordination beats APIs**: Shared workspace (`goal.md`, `status.md`) avoids inter-agent API overhead and is fully inspectable.\n4. **Cheap coordinator + quality specialists**: Assign a cheap model to the coordinator (classify/route/aggregate) and a better model to workers (actual work).\n5. **Fresh sessions for determinism**: Every task should start from a clean session context; avoid session reuse for different task types.\n6. **Use `--local` for scripted workflows**: Direct embedding avoids Gateway latency and is ideal for cron/batch tasks.\n7. **Leverage Lobster or ClawFlows for scheduling**: Both are production-proven, versioned, and deterministic.\n\n---\n\n### **Bottom Line**\n\nFile-based workers in OpenClaw are **not emerging—they're established practice**. The coordinator-specialist pattern with shared workspace files is the production-standard approach. `sessions_spawn` provides the isolation mechanism, and the ecosystem (ClawFlows, Lobster, ACPX) is actively matured and community-supported as of March 2026.\n\nStateless deterministic execution is achieved through: fresh sessions, disabled memory, file-based state, cron scheduling, and deliberate model assignment per role. No special flags or ACP magic required—just architectural discipline."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-haiku-4-5","usage":{"input":5,"output":1767,"totalTokens":44636,"cacheRead":37800,"cacheWrite":5064,"cost":{"total":0.01895}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774988195438,"responseId":"msg_019GADjN6iAwPhQP4U15cL7D","__openclaw":{"id":"d08e8142","seq":15}}]},{"key":"agent:main:subagent:47c9cc95-6306-4dbc-8230-de0fe8e590e3","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","spawnedBy":"agent:main:main","label":"openai-oauth-models-1","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-main-subagent-47c9cc95-6306-4dbc-8230-de0fe8e590e3","parentSessionKey":"agent:main:main","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1774986590861,"sessionId":"584ef7ca-7c9e-4d5e-ac6b-c9eb5476f71b","model":"claude-haiku-4-5","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":46405,"estimatedCostUsd":0.14162515,"status":"done","startedAt":1774986439143,"endedAt":1774986540925,"runtimeMs":97936,"thinkingLevel":"low","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\main\\sessions\\584ef7ca-7c9e-4d5e-ac6b-c9eb5476f71b.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me synthesize the findings:\n\n---\n\n## Research Summary: OpenAI Models via `openai-codex` OAuth in OpenClaw\n\n### **Key Finding: Limited Model Availability**\n\nThe `openai-codex` OAuth auth profile in OpenClaw is **currently limited to a specific subset of Codex models**, not all OpenAI models.\n\n### **What's Actually Supported (Confirmed)**\n\n**Currently working in OpenClaw:**\n- ✅ `openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex` (stable, fully integrated)\n- ✅ `openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex-spark` (research preview, Pro subscribers only)\n- ⚠️ `openai-codex/gpt-5.4` (officially documented, but **runtime integration incomplete** as of 2026.3.2)\n- ⚠️ `openai-codex/gpt-5.4-mini` (exists upstream in Codex, **status unclear in OpenClaw**)\n\n**From official Codex API** (developers.openai.com/codex):\n- gpt-5.4 ✓\n- gpt-5.4-mini ✓\n- gpt-5.3-codex ✓\n- gpt-5.3-codex-spark ✓ (Pro only)\n- Older legacy variants (5.2, 5.1, etc.) still listed but deprecated\n\n### **What Does NOT Work**\n\n- ❌ `openai-codex/gpt-5.4-nano` — **Not exposed via Codex subscription**\n  - Nano is **API-only** (via `openai/gpt-5.4-nano` with API key), not available through ChatGPT/Codex OAuth\n- ❌ Non-Codex models like `openai/gpt-5.2`, `openai/gpt-5.4` (direct API) via `openai-codex` OAuth\n  - These require `openai` provider with API key, not the `openai-codex` OAuth path\n\n### **Known Issues & Uncertainty**\n\n1. **gpt-5.4 support is incomplete** (GitHub #37623, #36817):\n   - Can be configured and appears in model list as `openai-codex/gpt-5.4`\n   - But fails at runtime with `HTTP 404` / `Unknown model`\n   - Root cause: model catalog in runtime is still hardwired to gpt-5.3-codex\n   - PR #36590 merged (feat: gpt-5.4 support), but full rollout incomplete as of 2026.3.2\n\n2. **gpt-5.4-mini status in OpenClaw is undocumented**:\n   - Exists in upstream Codex API\n   - Not confirmed working in current OpenClaw builds\n   - Likely same catalog/runtime integration gap as gpt-5.4\n\n3. **No mini/nano variants via Codex OAuth**:\n   - OpenAI only exposes gpt-5.4-mini via Codex (not nano)\n   - Nano is API-only (requires `openai/` provider + API key)\n\n### **Practical Answer**\n\n| Model | Auth Profile | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------------|--------|-------|\n| gpt-5.4 | `openai-codex` | ⚠️ Broken | Fails at runtime in 2026.3.2 |\n| gpt-5.4-mini | `openai-codex` | ❓ Unknown | Upstream available, OpenClaw support unclear |\n| gpt-5.3-codex | `openai-codex` | ✅ Works | Stable, fully integrated |\n| gpt-5.3-codex-spark | `openai-codex` | ✅ Works | Pro subscribers only |\n| gpt-5.4-nano | `openai-codex` | ❌ N/A | Not in Codex API, API-only |\n| gpt-5.4, gpt-5.4-mini, gpt-5.4-nano | `openai` (API key) | ✅ Works | Via direct OpenAI API, not OAuth |\n\n### **Evidence & Confidence Levels**\n\n| Evidence | Confidence | Source |\n|----------|-----------|--------|\n| gpt-5.3-codex works | 🟢 High | Local config, OpenClaw docs, active use |\n| gpt-5.4 fails in runtime | 🟢 High | GitHub issues #37623, #36817 (reported 2026.3.2) |\n| gpt-5.4-mini exists upstream | 🟢 High | OpenAI Codex API docs, 9to5Google |\n| gpt-5.4-mini in OpenClaw works | 🟡 Medium | Not explicitly tested; likely same gap as gpt-5.4 |\n| Nano unavailable via Codex | 🟢 High | OpenAI Codex pricing docs (nano is API-only) |\n| Future support TBD | 🟡 Medium | PR merged but no release date specified |\n\n### **Recommendation**\n\n**For now (March 2026):**\n- Use `openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex` for stable Codex OAuth work\n- If you need gpt-5.4 features, fall back to `openai/*` models with an API key (separate auth profile)\n- Watch GitHub #36817 for gpt-5.4 rollout status before upgrading\n\n---\n\nThat covers your task clearly. The evidence is strong, uncertainty is marked, and the practical answer shows exactly what works and what doesn't."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-haiku-4-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":1398,"totalTokens":47803,"cacheRead":44976,"cacheWrite":1429,"cost":{"total":0.01327385}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774986527339,"responseId":"msg_01DijLkHyQDXHvFmGE83B9oy","__openclaw":{"id":"bc47ce29","seq":47}}]},{"key":"agent:main:subagent:e05a5060-ea09-4860-8d93-b20a0212aa51","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","origin":{"provider":"heartbeat"},"spawnedBy":"agent:main:main","label":"openai-oauth-models-2","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-main-subagent-e05a5060-ea09-4860-8d93-b20a0212aa51","parentSessionKey":"agent:main:main","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1774986566383,"sessionId":"68e95f67-f5d6-459c-8e00-af96a9b488ce","model":"claude-haiku-4-5","contextTokens":200000,"totalTokens":48054,"estimatedCostUsd":0.11252625000000001,"status":"done","startedAt":1774986439901,"endedAt":1774986540284,"runtimeMs":96292,"thinkingLevel":"low","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\main\\sessions\\68e95f67-f5d6-459c-8e00-af96a9b488ce.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now I have all the information I need to compile a comprehensive answer.\n\n## Summary of Findings\n\nBased on my investigation of OpenClaw documentation, local configuration, and community evidence, here's what I found:\n\n### **How to Add Extra OpenAI Models Under Existing OAuth Auth**\n\n**Key Discovery:** `openai` and `openai-codex` are **separate, distinct auth domains** in practice, even though they both point to OpenAI's infrastructure.\n\n#### **1. Auth Domains Are Separate**\n\nFrom the configuration I examined:\n\n- **`openai` provider**: Uses `OPENAI_API_KEY` (direct API key auth) → calls `api.openai.com`\n- **`openai-codex` provider**: Uses OAuth (ChatGPT sign-in) → calls `chatgpt.com/backend-api`\n\nThey have **separate** auth profiles in `auth-profiles.json`:\n```json\n\"openai-codex:lucca2703@gmail.com\": { \"type\": \"oauth\", \"provider\": \"openai-codex\" }\n\"openai-codex:default\": { \"type\": \"oauth\", \"provider\": \"openai-codex\" }\n```\n\nEvidence from community: A Reddit user (Feb 27, 2026) reported that both auth methods **coexist in a single running gateway**, but they're treated as different providers with **different auth requirements**.\n\n---\n\n#### **2. Adding Extra Model IDs Under Existing OAuth**\n\nTo add more OpenAI/Codex models without new OAuth flows:\n\n**Option A: Extend in `openclaw.json` (Config)**\n\nEdit `agents.defaults.models` to include additional model IDs:\n\n```json5\n{\n  agents: {\n    defaults: {\n      model: { primary: \"openai-codex/gpt-5.4\" },\n      models: {\n        \"openai-codex/gpt-5.4\": {},\n        \"openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex-spark\": {},  // If entitled\n        \"openai-codex/gpt-5.2\": {}  // If available\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Option B: Extend in `models.json` (Provider Definition)**\n\nEdit the provider definition to expand the model catalog:\n\n```json5\n{\n  \"providers\": {\n    \"openai-codex\": {\n      \"baseUrl\": \"https://chatgpt.com/backend-api\",\n      \"api\": \"openai-codex-responses\",\n      \"models\": [\n        { \"id\": \"gpt-5.4\", \"name\": \"GPT-5.4\" },\n        { \"id\": \"gpt-5.3-codex-spark\", \"name\": \"Spark\" }\n      ]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Option C: CLI Helper (Recommended)**\n\nUse the built-in CLI to manage models:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw models list\nopenclaw models set openai-codex/gpt-5.4@openai-codex:lucca2703@gmail.com\n```\n\nThe `@<profileId>` syntax pins a specific OAuth profile for that session.\n\n---\n\n#### **3. How OpenClaw Discovers Models**\n\n1. **Bundled catalog** (pi-ai): OpenClaw ships with hardcoded model lists for major providers\n2. **Auth profile mapping**: When you authenticate with `openai-codex` OAuth, it discovers available models from the Codex account\n3. **Dynamic resolution**: Plugin-owned provider logic (`resolveDynamicModel`) can add models not in the static catalog\n4. **Config override**: `agents.defaults.models` allowlist becomes the runtime picker and `/model` selector\n\n---\n\n#### **4. What Models Are Available Under Codex OAuth**\n\nFrom official docs:\n\n- **`openai-codex/gpt-5.4`** — Current Codex model\n- **`openai-codex/gpt-5.3-codex-spark`** — Entitlement-dependent, experimental (if your Codex account is entitled)\n\n**Important:** `openai/gpt-5.3-codex-spark` (direct API path) is **intentionally suppressed** because the live OpenAI API rejects it. Spark is **Codex-only**.\n\n---\n\n#### **5. Practical Pattern: Using Both Auth Methods Together**\n\nThe Reddit discussion shows the pattern for mixed auth:\n\n```json5\n{\n  env: {\n    OPENAI_API_KEY: \"sk-proj-...\"  // Direct API key auth\n  },\n  auth: {\n    profiles: {\n      \"openai-codex:lucca2703@gmail.com\": {\n        \"provider\": \"openai-codex\",\n        \"mode\": \"oauth\"\n      }\n    }\n  },\n  agents: {\n    defaults: {\n      model: { primary: \"openai-codex/gpt-5.4\" },\n      models: {\n        \"openai-codex/gpt-5.4\": {},\n        \"openai/gpt-5.4\": {},        // Falls back to API key\n        \"openai/gpt-5.4-pro\": {}     // Also via API key\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nBoth coexist; the runtime chooses which auth profile to use based on the model's provider prefix.\n\n---\n\n### **Key Takeaway**\n\n✅ **You can add extra model IDs to the allowlist without extra OAuth** — just edit `agents.defaults.models` with new model IDs.\n\n✅ **`openai` and `openai-codex` require separate auth** — they're different OAuth flows and different endpoints internally.\n\n✅ **CLI is the safe path** — use `openclaw models list`, `openclaw models set`, and `/model` picker to stay within bounds."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-haiku-4-5","usage":{"input":0,"output":1385,"totalTokens":49439,"cacheRead":46198,"cacheWrite":1856,"cost":{"total":0.0138648}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774986526328,"responseId":"msg_01ChK8xZDvKRwsjwq7qfS12g","__openclaw":{"id":"25efaa52","seq":38}}]},{"key":"agent:main:subagent:6e766ed7-c44a-4042-8dde-13b75fef9cce","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","spawnedBy":"agent:main:main","label":"s1-openclaw-cli-source","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-main-subagent-6e766ed7-c44a-4042-8dde-13b75fef9cce","parentSessionKey":"agent:main:main","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1774984352257,"sessionId":"a0fc1b64-3f15-4cef-88d6-ae353d78d666","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","contextTokens":1000000,"totalTokens":81250,"estimatedCostUsd":0.5074708499999999,"status":"done","startedAt":1774984212001,"endedAt":1774984312056,"runtimeMs":84417,"thinkingLevel":"low","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\main\\sessions\\a0fc1b64-3f15-4cef-88d6-ae353d78d666.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I have enough information now. Let me also check the tools/automation docs to understand Python runtime integration better."},{"type":"text","text":"I now have enough to provide a comprehensive, evidence-based answer. Here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n## Findings: OpenClaw Agent Execution, Sessions, and Python Runtime Integration\n\n### 1. `openclaw agents` — Agent Management (NOT execution)\n\n`openclaw agents` is purely a **configuration/management** command. It handles:\n- `list`, `add`, `delete` — manage isolated agent identities\n- `bind/unbind` — route inbound channel traffic to agents\n- `set-identity` — set name, avatar, theme\n\n**It does NOT execute agents or run inference turns.** No `run`, `exec`, or `invoke` subcommand exists.\n\n---\n\n### 2. `openclaw agent` — Single Turn Execution (via Gateway)\n\nThis is the concrete command for running one agent turn from scripts:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Summarize logs\"\nopenclaw agent --to +15555550123 --message \"status update\" --deliver\nopenclaw agent --session-id 1234 --message \"Summarize inbox\" --thinking medium\n```\n\n**Key behavior:**\n- Routes through a running **Gateway** (WebSocket)\n- `--local` flag for embedded mode (no Gateway)\n- `--deliver` to route reply to a target channel\n- Supports `--thinking`, `--model`, `--session-id`\n\n**This is the primary CLI hook for external integrations (including Python scripts).**\n\n---\n\n### 3. `sessions_spawn` Tool — Programmatic Sub-Agent Spawning\n\nFor agent-to-agent delegation (from within an agent turn, via tool calls):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"tool\": \"sessions_spawn\",\n  \"params\": {\n    \"task\": \"...\",\n    \"runtime\": \"subagent\",  // or \"acp\"\n    \"model\": \"...\",\n    \"label\": \"...\",\n    \"runTimeoutSeconds\": 120\n  }\n}\n```\n\n- `runtime: \"subagent\"` → spawns an OpenClaw sub-agent\n- `runtime: \"acp\"` → spawns an ACP harness agent (IDE integrations)\n- Sub-agents run in isolated sessions, can receive file attachments via `attachments[]`\n- Controlled by `agents.list[].subagents.allowAgents`\n\n---\n\n### 4. `openclaw acp` — ACP Bridge (for IDE/Python ACP harness)\n\nFor Python runtimes that speak the **Agent Client Protocol (ACP)** over stdio:\n\n```bash\nopenclaw acp\nopenclaw acp --url wss://gateway-host:18789 --token <token>\nopenclaw acp --session agent:main:main\n```\n\n- Bridges ACP stdio ↔ Gateway WebSocket\n- Keeps session state mapped to Gateway session keys\n- Supports `initialize`, `newSession`, `prompt`, `cancel`, `listSessions`\n- Python process can act as ACP client, spawning `openclaw acp` as a subprocess\n\n---\n\n### 5. `openclaw system event` — Inject System Messages\n\nFor triggering agent turns via system events (useful for automated workflows):\n\n```bash\nopenclaw system event --text \"Process new batch\" --mode now\n```\n\n---\n\n### Practical Integration Pattern for Python Runtime\n\n**Option A — Direct turn trigger (simplest):**\n```python\nimport subprocess\nresult = subprocess.run([\n    \"openclaw\", \"agent\",\n    \"--agent\", \"main\",\n    \"--message\", \"Process video batch 42\",\n    \"--deliver\"\n], capture_output=True, text=True)\n```\n\n**Option B — ACP protocol (fullest control):**\n- Spawn `openclaw acp` as a subprocess\n- Python runtime speaks ACP over stdio\n- Supports session management, streaming, tool follow-along\n- Use `sessions_spawn` with `runtime: \"acp\"` from within agent turns to invoke Python ACP harnesses\n\n**Option C — Gateway WebSocket directly:**\n- Connect to `ws://localhost:18789` (default Gateway port)\n- Use `chat.send` or `agent` messages to drive turns programmatically\n- Subscribe to `sessions.messages.subscribe` for streaming results\n\n**Option D — `openclaw system event`:**\n- Fire-and-forget injection into running agent session\n- Good for lightweight external triggers\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\nThere is **no standalone `openclaw run` or `openclaw exec`** for agents. Runtime invocation is expected via:\n1. **`openclaw agent`** — script-friendly CLI single-turn executor\n2. **`sessions_spawn`** tool (inside agent turns) — for sub-agent delegation\n3. **`openclaw acp`** — for Python/IDE ACP harness integration over stdio\n4. **Gateway WebSocket API** — for full programmatic control\n5. **`openclaw system event`** — for injecting system prompts into running sessions"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":1177,"totalTokens":82427,"cacheRead":79449,"cacheWrite":1800,"cost":{"total":0.0482427}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774984285053,"responseId":"msg_01DmVaEq86T3x2BnuQHPXBbB","__openclaw":{"id":"962efe41","seq":27}}]},{"key":"agent:main:subagent:7436c9b8-b2a0-46b8-9a9d-b36a20d7c96f","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","spawnedBy":"agent:main:main","label":"s1-openclaw-runtime-docs","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-main-subagent-7436c9b8-b2a0-46b8-9a9d-b36a20d7c96f","parentSessionKey":"agent:main:main","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1774984329201,"sessionId":"7a35e7bc-361b-48ee-bd23-7410049291ef","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","contextTokens":1000000,"totalTokens":26267,"estimatedCostUsd":0.1744863,"status":"done","startedAt":1774984210385,"endedAt":1774984289166,"runtimeMs":63245,"thinkingLevel":"low","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\main\\sessions\\7a35e7bc-361b-48ee-bd23-7410049291ef.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here are the findings:\n\n---\n\n## Research Findings: OpenClaw Agent Runtime Invocation\n\n### (1) Current CLI command to run an agent directly\n\n**Yes — `openclaw agent` exists today and is fully functional.**\n\n```bash\n# Send a message to the main agent (via Gateway)\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \"do something\"\n\n# Run embedded locally (requires API keys in shell env — no Gateway needed)\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \"do something\" --local\n\n# Target a specific session\nopenclaw agent --session-id <id> --message \"text\"\n\n# Deliver reply back to a channel\nopenclaw agent --agent ops --message \"Generate report\" --deliver --reply-channel slack --reply-to \"#reports\"\n```\n\nSource: `docs/cli/agent.md` and `openclaw agent --help`\n\n---\n\n### (2) Two runtime paths exist\n\n| Mode | How | When |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Gateway-backed** (default) | Forwards to the running Gateway over WebSocket | Gateway must be running; normal operation |\n| **Embedded/local** (`--local`) | Runs agent in-process directly | Requires provider API keys in shell env; no Gateway needed |\n\n---\n\n### (3) Sessions/subagents/APIs are the standard bridge\n\nYes. The intended pattern for spawning isolated agent turns programmatically is:\n\n- **`openclaw agent`** — CLI one-shot turn\n- **`openclaw acp`** — ACP protocol bridge over stdio for IDE integrations (forwards to Gateway via WebSocket)\n- **Sessions** (`openclaw sessions`) — manage stored conversation state; not themselves an execution surface\n- **Cron jobs** (`openclaw cron`) — scheduled recurring agent turns\n- **Hooks** — event-triggered agent turns\n\nThe ACP bridge (`openclaw acp`) is the intended path for programmatic IDE/code-level integration, and it routes through the Gateway session system.\n\n---\n\n### (4) Concrete supported patterns today\n\n```bash\n# One-shot agent turn (Gateway mode)\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \"Summarize logs\"\n\n# One-shot agent turn (embedded, no Gateway needed)\nopenclaw agent --agent main --message \"Summarize logs\" --local\n\n# ACP bridge (for IDE integrations - speaks ACP over stdio, forwards to Gateway)\nopenclaw acp\nopenclaw acp --session agent:main:main\nopenclaw acp --url wss://gateway-host:18789 --token <token>\n\n# Scheduled agent turn via cron\nopenclaw cron add --job \"daily-report\" --schedule \"0 9 * * *\" --agent main --message \"Generate daily report\"\n\n# Send message to channel (not agent turn, but triggers agent via channel routing)\nopenclaw message send --channel telegram --target @user --message \"...\"\n```\n\n**Key file paths:**\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\agent.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\acp.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\sessions.md`\n\n### Summary\n\nThe primary runtime invocation path is **`openclaw agent --agent <id> --message \"<text>\"`**. The `--local` flag bypasses the Gateway for fully embedded execution. For code-level integration, the ACP bridge (`openclaw acp`) over stdio is the intended mechanism. Sessions are storage/state constructs, not execution entry points themselves."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":853,"totalTokens":27120,"cacheRead":25563,"cacheWrite":703,"cost":{"total":0.02310315}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774984270824,"responseId":"msg_01A6HnPnWupcTMyoUELgPHX6","__openclaw":{"id":"1b0e6cbd","seq":21}}]},{"key":"agent:main:subagent:f51d4031-7d60-444e-834b-57ca3d50d2c2","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","spawnedBy":"agent:main:main","label":"s1-openclaw-community-patterns","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-main-subagent-f51d4031-7d60-444e-834b-57ca3d50d2c2","parentSessionKey":"agent:main:main","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1774984307376,"sessionId":"55445a18-663f-4993-bb97-5fdc1b017a28","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","contextTokens":1000000,"totalTokens":21314,"estimatedCostUsd":0.10744875000000001,"status":"done","startedAt":1774984211200,"endedAt":1774984274817,"runtimeMs":48060,"thinkingLevel":"low","abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\main\\sessions\\55445a18-663f-4993-bb97-5fdc1b017a28.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Research Synthesis: How OpenClaw Users Execute Agents at Runtime\n\n### Confirmed Mechanisms (from official docs + local CLI inspection)\n\n**1. `openclaw agent` CLI command** *(primary programmatic trigger)*\n- Runs a single agent turn via the Gateway\n- Supports `--to <recipient>`, `--agent <id>`, `--session-id`, `--message`, `--deliver`, `--thinking`\n- Has `--local` flag for embedded (no Gateway) mode with local API keys\n- This is the main bridge for external systems or scripts wanting to invoke an agent programmatically\n\n**2. Sub-agents via `sessions_spawn` tool** *(primary in-agent parallelization pattern)*\n- Within an agent run, spawning sub-agents is the standard pattern for parallel/background work\n- Sub-agents get their own session (`agent:<id>:subagent:<uuid>`) and announce results back to requester\n- Configurable model, thinking level, timeout, sandbox isolation, thread binding\n- `mode: \"run\"` (one-shot) vs `mode: \"session\"` (persistent, requires `thread: true`)\n- `/subagents spawn` also available as a slash command from chat\n\n**3. Gateway** *(infrastructure layer, not directly invoked by users)*\n- The Gateway is the WebSocket broker that routes messages and sessions\n- Users don't \"execute via gateway\" directly — it runs as a daemon and the CLI/channels route through it\n- `openclaw gateway start/stop/restart` manages the service\n\n**4. Chat channels** *(primary user-facing runtime)*\n- Users interact via Telegram, Discord, WhatsApp, etc.\n- Messages to channels trigger agent runs automatically through the Gateway routing\n- This is the most natural \"human-to-agent\" execution path\n\n**5. Cron jobs** (`openclaw cron`) *(scheduled agent execution)*\n- For periodic/timed agent runs, the cron subsystem is used\n- Runs are isolated from the main session\n\n**6. ACP agents** (`sessions_spawn` with `runtime: \"acp\"`) *(coding agent pattern)*\n- For Claude Code, Codex, Gemini CLI — spawned via `sessions_spawn` with `runtime: \"acp\"` flag\n- This is the Coding Agent skill pattern seen in the workspace\n\n---\n\n### Practical Integration Patterns\n\n| Pattern | Mechanism |\n|---|---|\n| Human triggers agent via chat | Chat channel → Gateway → agent run |\n| Script/automation triggers agent | `openclaw agent --message \"...\" --deliver` |\n| Agent spawns parallel task | `sessions_spawn` tool inside an agent turn |\n| Scheduled agent work | `openclaw cron` |\n| Persistent thread-bound sub-agent | `sessions_spawn` with `thread: true, mode: \"session\"` |\n| Invoke coding agent (Codex/Claude Code) | `sessions_spawn` with `runtime: \"acp\"` |\n\n---\n\n### Uncertainty Flags\n\n- **Community patterns beyond official docs**: Limited external community content found (one meta-intelligence.tech guide, mainly summarizing official docs). No Reddit, Discord, or forum discussions surfaced — OpenClaw may have a smaller public community or most discussion is private.\n- **`openclaw message send` as agent trigger**: The CLI has `message send` — unclear if this triggers an agent run or just sends a raw message. The changelog snippet mentions \"CLI/message send: write manual openclaw message send deliveries into the resolved agent session transcript\" — suggests it *does* thread into agent sessions.\n- **ACP runtime specifics**: The `runtime: \"acp\"` path is mentioned in docs and skill references but full documentation wasn't fetched — behavior may differ from standard subagents."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":858,"totalTokens":22172,"cacheRead":18217,"cacheWrite":3096,"cost":{"total":0.0299481}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774984251762,"responseId":"msg_01Q1dcWMNrBcxBFiqvxoDqWU","__openclaw":{"id":"d3808f83","seq":8}}]},{"key":"agent:main:subagent:0d8719eb-b287-49cd-ae2e-5b7f7a2e2551","kind":"other","channel":"webchat","spawnedBy":"agent:main:main","label":"watchdog-mvp-reconciler","displayName":"webchat:g-agent-main-subagent-0d8719eb-b287-49cd-ae2e-5b7f7a2e2551","parentSessionKey":"agent:main:main","deliveryContext":{"channel":"webchat"},"updatedAt":1774877364780,"sessionId":"5011acc2-400b-4819-98ee-0dfa2ebbc124","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","contextTokens":1000000,"totalTokens":85092,"estimatedCostUsd":1.1475174000000001,"status":"done","startedAt":1774876965842,"endedAt":1774877319530,"runtimeMs":344365,"abortedLastRun":false,"lastChannel":"webchat","transcriptPath":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\main\\sessions\\5011acc2-400b-4819-98ee-0dfa2ebbc124.jsonl","messages":[{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is clean. Here's the complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## Entregáveis\n\n### 1. Diagnóstico\n\n**Problema raiz:** `watchdog.py` confia 100% em `active_tasks.json` sem consultar o runtime. O campo `status` só muda se o agente que lançou a task o actualizar explicitamente — o que não acontece quando a session termina silenciosamente ou é esquecida.\n\n**Caso concreto:** Task `retest_claude_code_sidecar_20260328_160800` estava como `running` há +2 dias. Em `subagents/runs.json` o run correspondente (`childSessionKey: agent:main:subagent:f45bf7bf...`) tinha `endedAt`, `endedReason: subagent-complete`, `outcome.status: ok`. A task estava morta mas gerava pings a cada 10 minutos.\n\n### 2. Estados mínimos implementados\n\n`spawned → running → stalled → orphaned` (escalada por tempo, sem runtime)  \n`running → completed / failed` (reconciliado contra `runs.json`)\n\n### 3. Implementação\n\n**Ficheiros criados:**\n- `task_watchdog/reconciler.py` — lógica de reconciliação (225 linhas). Lê `subagents/runs.json`, pesquisa por `childSessionKey`, classifica o run, e actualiza o status da task sem inventar infra externa.\n\n**Ficheiros alterados:**\n- `task_watchdog/watchdog.py` — `main()` chama `reconcile_all()` antes do `evaluate_tasks()`, com fallback silencioso se o reconciler falhar. `evaluate_tasks()` passou a suportar `spawned`, `stalled`, e `orphaned`. Deduplicação por `terminalNotifiedStatus` impede notificações repetidas.\n\n**Ficheiro de documentação criado:**\n- `task_watchdog/RECONCILER_NOTES.md` — diagnóstico, arquitectura, thresholds, notas de teste.\n\n### 4. Validado em execução\n\n- Primeira run: reconciliou zombie → `completed`, notificou uma vez, arquivou em `task_history.jsonl`, removeu de `active_tasks.json`\n- Segunda run: zero notificações falsas, `remaining: []`, `notifications: []`"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":580,"totalTokens":85672,"cacheRead":84914,"cacheWrite":177,"cost":{"total":0.034840949999999996}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774877303444,"responseId":"msg_011opKNjJThTq68XsUsabBjj","__openclaw":{"id":"5c002f29","seq":69}}]}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775035901848}}
