{"type":"message","id":"60ad726a","parentId":"df6be06a","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:04:53.429Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_xnUSA7qynNPPaJUUjSaVUYZA|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccedc689f4819097ba8dc2e21e2d5e","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_tts_polish_output_validator_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1\\\\s1_tts_polish_output_validator_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_595eyAaTJeoRKgjVT2VvNQc1|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccedc68a0481909ea1df685914a937","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_tts_polish_output_validator_runtime_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1\\\\s1_tts_polish_output_validator_runtime_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_L2QNXBUqaIzBlQ4rF9b3IXWt|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccedc68a0c8190bd4637c308aaca11","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\s1\\s1_tts_polish_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\s1\\\\s1_tts_polish_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_mqQ0zwbNKmEtV8Ljm5feR9aV|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccedc68a1481908f600030dbb082f7","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\tts_polish_runner.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\tts_polish_runner.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2mryE53oLb4xoA2s7rzmMInt|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccedc68a188190a0a7493152f92d65","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\tts_polish_batch_planner.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\tts_polish_batch_planner.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":940,"output":247,"cacheRead":93184,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94371,"cost":{"input":0.00235,"output":0.003705,"cacheRead":0.023295999999999997,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.029350999999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775037881007,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169ccedbf3ff481909825d224f020527c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7d44e639","parentId":"60ad726a","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:04:54.951Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_xnUSA7qynNPPaJUUjSaVUYZA|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccedc689f4819097ba8dc2e21e2d5e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 TTS Polish Output Validator Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the validation contract for per-batch `tts_polish` outputs inside S1 (Pre-Production)._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n`tts_polish_output_validator` validates one `tts_polish` batch output before that batch is allowed into the canonical `tts_polished.json` merge flow.\n\nIts job is to ensure that each polish batch result is structurally sound, preserves scene identity/order, preserves original narration reference, and does not introduce unacceptable semantic drift.\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\nThe unit of dispatch is the `tts_polish` batch.\n\nThe unit of semantic comparison remains scene-sensitive inside the batch.\n\nThe preferred unit of correction is the affected subset of scenes within the batch, when possible.\n\nOnly approved batch outputs should be passed to `tts_polish_merger`.\n\n---\n\n## Validation architecture\n\nThis validator should use a two-layer model:\n\n### Layer 1 — deterministic Python validation\nChecks structural integrity and obvious drift signals.\n\n### Layer 2 — optional semantic review\nUsed only when deterministic checks detect meaningful changes but cannot safely classify them as acceptable vs unacceptable without interpretation.\n\nThe semantic review layer is supervisory support, not autonomous final policy.\n\n---\n\n## Scope of deterministic validation\n\nFor one batch result, the deterministic layer should check:\n- JSON/object shape is valid\n- required top-level fields exist\n- `scenes` exists and is non-empty\n- expected scene count is preserved\n- scene order is preserved\n- `scene_id` mapping is preserved\n- every scene contains required fields\n- `narration_original` is preserved as the original input narration\n- `narration_tts` exists and is non-empty\n- obvious eaten words / unauthorized additions / scene mismatch signals\n- whether the batch should be approved, repaired by scene subset, regenerated, or escalated to semantic review\n\n---\n\n## Out of scope\n\n`tts_polish_output_validator` does **not**:\n- decide final retry policy by itself\n- merge batch outputs\n- rewrite polished scenes directly\n- replace downstream audio validation\n- act as a freeform stylistic reviewer\n\n---\n\n## Inputs\n\nThe validator should receive enough information to compare one polish batch output against its source polish batch.\n\n### Minimum expected input\n- run/job context sufficient for logging/reference\n- `batch_id`\n- source batch scenes\n- `tts_polish` batch output path or loaded object\n- required field specification / contract assumptions\n\n---\n\n## Output shape (draft)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"approved_for_merge\": true,\n  \"batch_id\": \"tp_004\",\n  \"classification\": \"ok\",\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": [],\n  \"stats\": {\n    \"scene_count\": 5,\n    \"changed_scene_count\": 3,\n    \"flagged_scene_count\": 0\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### Classification candidates\n- `ok`\n- `structural_patch`\n- `scene_subset_repair`\n- `batch_regenerate`\n- `needs_semantic_review`\n- `fatal_contract_error`\n\nThese are supervisory guidance categories, not autonomous retry decisions.\n\n---\n\n## Initial classification policy (v1)\n\nA practical first-pass policy for the supervisor/validator layer:\n- isolated low-risk structural issue -> `structural_patch`\n- localized clear problems in specific scenes -> `scene_subset_repair`\n- broad compromise across the batch -> `batch_regenerate`\n- meaningful but ambiguous semantic change -> `needs_semantic_review`\n- unreadable or fundamentally malformed artifact -> `fatal_contract_error`\n\nThis policy is intentionally simple and can be refined once real batch outputs are observed.\n\n---\n\n## Failure classification intent\n\n### `structural_patch`\nUse when the problem is narrow, local, and low-risk.\n\nTypical examples:\n- missing field with otherwise stable structure\n- small metadata inconsistency\n- malformed scene wrapper without meaningful semantic uncertainty\n\n### `scene_subset_repair`\nUse when specific scenes in the batch clearly need correction while the rest of the batch remains usable.\n\nTypical examples:\n- eaten words in one or two scenes\n- unauthorized additions in one or two scenes\n- one scene mapped incorrectly\n- one scene with obviously unsafe polish while the rest is sound\n\n### `batch_regenerate`\nUse when the batch output is too compromised to trust targeted repair.\n\nTypical examples:\n- widespread drift across scenes\n- many eaten/additional content failures across the batch\n- scene ordering/mapping compromised broadly\n- multiple combined failures that undermine trust in the batch as a whole\n\n### `needs_semantic_review`\nUse when deterministic checks detect meaningful changes but cannot safely determine whether the change is acceptable TTS normalization or unacceptable meaning drift.\n\nTypical examples:\n- wording changed significantly without obvious addition/deletion\n- abbreviation/ordinal/term normalization may be valid but is semantically uncertain\n- language-specific oral adaptation changed phrasing in a way that requires interpretation\n\n### `fatal_contract_error`\nUse when the artifact is too malformed for the normal repair flow.\n\nTypical examples:\n- unreadable JSON\n- missing top-level required structure\n- missing scene list\n- unusable mapping between input and output scenes\n\n---\n\n## Validation principles\n\n- deterministic checks should catch obvious breakage and drift first\n- semantic review should be used sparingly, only when needed\n- already-approved scenes should not be disturbed because another scene in the batch failed\n- the validator should help the supervisor target only the affected scenes when possible\n- semantic review informs supervisory control; it does not replace it\n\n---\n\n## Relationship to supervisor\n\nThe S1 Supervisor should:\n- run deterministic validation on each `tts_polish` batch output\n- inspect the returned classification and error list\n- invoke semantic review only when classification indicates ambiguity\n- decide whether to approve, repair a scene subset, regenerate the batch, or abort\n- only pass approved batches to `tts_polish_merger`\n\n---\n\n## Relationship to `tts_polish`\n\n`tts_polish` should not own this validator or self-manage retry policy.\n\nHowever, the supervisor may use validator findings to reinvoke `tts_polish` with structured correction feedback for only the affected scenes within the batch.\n\n---\n\n## Current status\n\nAt this stage, the contract establishes:\n- per-batch validation as the orchestration unit\n- per-scene sensitivity inside the batch\n- deterministic validation plus optional semantic review\n- scene-subset repair as the preferred correction mode when possible\n- merge only after batch approval\n\nNext step: create the real OpenClaw workspace for `tts_polish` and later implement the deterministic validator layer.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775037894775}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f713762","parentId":"7d44e639","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:04:55.122Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_595eyAaTJeoRKgjVT2VvNQc1|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccedc68a0481909ea1df685914a937","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 TTS Polish Output Validator Runtime Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the intended runtime role of the per-batch `tts_polish` validation layer inside S1._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe `tts_polish_output_validator` is the intended per-batch validation layer for `tts_polish` outputs inside S1.\n\nIts role is to validate one polish batch before that batch is accepted into canonical merge flow.\n\nThis contract exists to make the runtime architecture explicit even if the deterministic validator implementation is not yet fully extracted as a dedicated supervisor skill.\n\n---\n\n## Canonical architectural rule\n\nThe `tts_polish` lane should follow the same architectural shape as the `scene_director` lane:\n- batch planning\n- IO adapter bridge\n- operator execution\n- per-batch validation\n- optional semantic review only for ambiguous cases\n- merge only after approval\n- whole-artifact validation after merge\n\nThis means `tts_polish_output_validator` is a canonical architectural component, not an optional nice-to-have.\n\n---\n\n## Position inside S1\n\nThis component sits between:\n- `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n\nAnd may escalate ambiguous cases to:\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n\n---\n\n## Ownership\n\n### Owned by\n- S1 Supervisor as a validation layer under supervisory control\n\n### Not owned by\n- `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n- `tts_polish_merger`\n\nThe validator classifies and gates.\nThe supervisor decides.\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\nThe validator should:\n- validate batch-level structure\n- validate required fields per scene\n- validate scene identity/order preservation\n- validate preservation of `narration_original`\n- validate presence of `narration_tts`\n- detect obvious eaten words / unauthorized additions / scene mismatch signals\n- classify the batch as:\n  - approvable\n  - repairable by subset\n  - broad regenerate candidate\n  - semantically ambiguous and needing review\n  - fatally malformed\n\n---\n\n## Out of scope\n\nThe validator must **not**:\n- merge batches\n- decide final retry policy\n- rewrite polished scenes itself\n- replace downstream audio validation\n- act as a freeform stylistic reviewer\n\n---\n\n## Validation layering rule\n\n### Layer 1 — deterministic validation\nShould catch:\n- shape failures\n- identity/order failures\n- obvious drift/addition/removal failures\n- straightforward subset repair candidates\n\n### Layer 2 — optional semantic review\nShould be invoked only when deterministic checks detect meaningful changes but cannot safely classify them as acceptable vs unsafe.\n\n---\n\n## Review escalation rule\n\nThe semantic reviewer should only receive:\n- affected scenes\n- relevant ambiguity reasons\n- minimal necessary context\n\nIt should not be used as a generic second-pass reviewer for all batches.\n\n---\n\n## Merge rule\n\nOnly approved batch outputs should be passed to `tts_polish_merger`.\nRejected, ambiguous-unreviewed, or malformed outputs must not enter the canonical merge path.\n\n---\n\n## Architectural note\n\nAt the time of this contract, the conceptual contract for this component already exists in:\n- `docs/contracts/s1/s1_tts_polish_output_validator_contract.md`\n\nThis runtime contract exists to make explicit that the component is part of the canonical runtime architecture and should eventually be represented with equivalent runtime clarity to the `scene_director_output_validator` lane.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775037894952}}
{"type":"message","id":"401d14ae","parentId":"1f713762","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:04:55.296Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_L2QNXBUqaIzBlQ4rF9b3IXWt|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccedc68a0c8190bd4637c308aaca11","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# S1 TTS Polish Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the role, boundaries, and file contract of the `tts_polish` operator inside S1 (Pre-Production)._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-31_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe `tts_polish` operator is responsible for transforming original scene narration into a version optimized for Text-to-Speech while preserving meaning, information, coverage, and scene order.\n\nIts job is not to rewrite the story, but to apply only the minimum necessary oral/reading adjustments so the narration sounds better in synthetic voice output.\n\n---\n\n## Core responsibility\n\nThe central responsibility of `tts_polish` is:\n\n> Adjust the oral formulation of small ordered batches of scenes for TTS, preserving content, coverage, and scene order while improving pronunciation-readiness, readability, and speech naturalness.\n\nThis means `tts_polish` is a controlled oral-normalization operator, not a free narrative rewriter.\n\n---\n\n## Position inside S1\n\nWithin S1, `tts_polish` operates after the canonical `screenplay.json` exists and before scene bible construction.\n\nIts output is the TTS-optimized narration layer that will later be:\n- validated\n- merged into canonical `tts_polished.json`\n- consumed by downstream audio generation and scene bible construction\n\n`tts_polish` does not own sector flow. It operates under S1 Supervisor coordination and explicit file contracts.\n\n---\n\n## Batch execution model\n\n`tts_polish` operates on small ordered batches of scenes rather than on the full screenplay at once.\n\nInstead:\n- the S1 Supervisor uses `tts_polish_batch_planner` to group scenes into manageable polish batches\n- batches are emitted in stable order (`tp_001`, `tp_002`, ...)\n- each batch preserves screenplay scene order\n- the supervisor uses `tts_polish_io_adapter` to prepare an explicit payload for each batch\n- `tts_polish` operates on one polish batch at a time\n- downstream deterministic logic merges approved batch outputs into canonical `tts_polished.json`\n\n### Recommended v1 defaults\n- target scenes per batch: `5`\n- minimum scenes per batch: `3`\n- maximum scenes per batch: `6`\n- maximum words per batch: `350`\n\n---\n\n## Input contract (current draft)\n\nFor each invocation, `tts_polish` should receive a supervisor-prepared polish batch payload.\n\nThe payload should include, at minimum:\n- run/job context\n- batch identity (`tp_###`)\n- ordered batch scenes\n- for each scene: `scene_id` and `narration_original`\n- language / channel context relevant to polish behavior\n- `tts_polish_rules` injected from channel config\n- explicit output path for the batch result\n\nThe operator should receive enough context to polish the assigned scenes correctly, but should not be overloaded with unrelated upstream/downstream concerns.\n\n---\n\n## Boundaries / out of scope\n\n`tts_polish` should **not** be responsible for:\n- re-structuring the narrative\n- changing scene order\n- merging or splitting scenes\n- batching logic\n- retry policy\n- semantic validation of its own output\n- visual planning\n- audio generation\n- timestamps or alignment\n\nIt also should not drift into stylistic rewriting beyond what is necessary for TTS readiness.\n\n---\n\n## Relationship with S1 Supervisor\n\nThe S1 Supervisor is responsible for:\n- preparing the polish batch payload\n- deciding when `tts_polish` is called\n- scheduling batches with controlled parallelism\n- validating batch outputs before merge\n- deciding retry/fail/continue behavior\n- deciding whether failures should trigger subset repair, batch regeneration, semantic review, or abort\n\n`tts_polish` is responsible for producing the batch-level TTS-polished output expected by the supervisor contract.\n\n### Validation and correction loop\n- each `tts_polish` batch output is a separately validatable unit\n- semantic comparison remains scene-sensitive inside the batch\n- if one subset of scenes fails, the supervisor should prefer targeted repair of affected scenes when possible\n- validation policy belongs to the supervisor and its deterministic/semantic review layers, not to `tts_polish`\n- `tts_polish` may be reinvoked with structured correction feedback for only the affected scenes in the batch\n\n---\n\n## Output contract\n\nFor each batch, `tts_polish` should write one batch-level JSON result containing:\n- batch identity/context\n- ordered batch scenes\n- no global merge responsibility\n\n### Batch-level structure (draft)\n- `batch_id`\n- `operator`\n- `scenes`\n\n### Required scene fields\nEach scene produced by `tts_polish` should contain:\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts`\n\n### Optional scene fields\n- `changes`\n\n### Output principles\n- scene order must be preserved exactly\n- `scene_id` mapping must be preserved exactly\n- `narration_original` must remain the original scene narration\n- `narration_tts` may improve oral readability, but must not alter meaning or information\n- the output should preserve scene granularity and not collapse scenes together\n- global merge of polish batches is not the responsibility of `tts_polish`\n\n---\n\n## Quality bar\n\nA good `tts_polish` output should:\n- sound better for TTS than the original raw narration\n- preserve meaning and information fully\n- avoid eating words or adding unauthorized content\n- preserve scene order and scene identity exactly\n- make only necessary oral/reading adjustments\n- remain narrower than broad narrative rewriting\n\nLikely high-priority failure modes to guard against:\n- eaten words\n- unauthorized additions\n- meaning drift\n- scene mismatch inside batch output\n- reordered scene outputs\n- malformed or incomplete scene objects\n\n---\n\n## Current status\n\nAt this stage, the contract establishes:\n- the mission of `tts_polish`\n- its central responsibility\n- its position inside S1\n- its small-batch execution model\n- the current draft of its input/output contracts\n- the expected targeted-repair behavior for affected scene subsets\n\nThe next step is to formalize the output validator contract and then define the real OpenClaw workspace for the operator.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775037895125}}
{"type":"message","id":"8f5d9d04","parentId":"401d14ae","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:04:55.469Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_mqQ0zwbNKmEtV8Ljm5feR9aV|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccedc68a1481908f600030dbb082f7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"TTS Polish Runner — LEGACY compatibility wrapper for TTS-oriented polish.\n\nLEGACY STATUS:\n- This module remains active because the prototype entrypoint `runtime.s1.s1_start`\n  and related legacy tests still depend on it.\n- It is NOT the canonical OpenClaw runtime architecture for the S1 polish lane.\n\nCanonical architecture now expects:\n- supervisor-owned polish batch planning\n- explicit IO adapter bridge\n- OpenClaw `tts_polish` operator execution\n- per-batch validation\n- optional semantic-review escalation for ambiguous cases\n- deterministic merge into canonical `tts_polished.json`\n\nThis module remains only as a transitional compatibility path.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\nfrom openai import OpenAI\n\n\ndef run_tts_polish(\n    screenplay: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    config: dict[str, Any],\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    model: str = \"gpt-4.1-mini\",\n) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    \"\"\"Polish screenplay narrations for TTS, one scene at a time.\n\n    Args:\n        screenplay: Scene list with 'narration_original' field.\n        config: Channel config with tts_polish_rules.\n        job: PM job dict.\n        model: OpenAI model to use.\n\n    Returns:\n        List of polished scene dicts with original, polished, changes.\n    \"\"\"\n    language = job.get(\"language\", \"en\")\n    rules = config.get(\"tts_polish_rules\", [])\n\n    if not rules:\n        return [\n            {\n                \"scene_id\": s.get(\"scene_id\", f\"scene_{i+1:03d}\"),\n                \"original\": s[\"narration_original\"],\n                \"polished\": s[\"narration_original\"],\n                \"changes\": [],\n            }\n            for i, s in enumerate(screenplay)\n        ]\n\n    rules_text = \"\\n\".join(f\"- {r}\" for r in rules)\n\n    system_prompt = f\"\"\"You are a TTS text polisher for {language} narration.\n\nApply ONLY these rules:\n{rules_text}\n\nCRITICAL:\n- Do NOT change meaning.\n- Do NOT add or remove information.\n- Do NOT change verb tenses.\n- Do NOT combine or split sentences.\n- Keep numbers as digits.\n- Only apply the rules above.\n\nReturn a JSON object with:\n- \"original\": the exact input text (unchanged)\n- \"polished\": the polished version\n- \"changes\": list of changes made (brief descriptions, empty list if no changes)\"\"\"\n\n    client = OpenAI()\n    all_polished = []\n\n    for i, scene in enumerate(screenplay):\n        scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_id\", f\"scene_{i+1:03d}\")\n        narration = scene[\"narration_original\"]\n\n        try:\n            response = client.chat.completions.create(\n                model=model,\n                messages=[\n                    {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": system_prompt},\n                    {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": narration},\n                ],\n                temperature=0.2,\n                response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"},\n            )\n\n            content = response.choices[0].message.content\n            parsed = json.loads(content)\n\n            result = {\n                \"scene_id\": scene_id,\n                \"original\": parsed.get(\"original\", narration),\n                \"polished\": parsed.get(\"polished\", narration),\n                \"changes\": parsed.get(\"changes\", []),\n            }\n        except Exception:\n            # On any error, keep original text unchanged\n            result = {\n                \"scene_id\": scene_id,\n                \"original\": narration,\n                \"polished\": narration,\n                \"changes\": [],\n            }\n\n        all_polished.append(result)\n\n    return all_polished\n\n\ndef save_tts_polished(\n    polished: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    video_root: Path,\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Save tts_polished.json to b1_pre_production/.\"\"\"\n    output_dir = Path(video_root) / \"b1_pre_production\"\n    output_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    path = output_dir / \"tts_polished.json\"\n    path.write_text(\n        json.dumps(polished, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False),\n        encoding=\"utf-8\",\n    )\n    return str(path)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775037895297}}
{"type":"message","id":"9c3f6bab","parentId":"8f5d9d04","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:04:55.649Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2mryE53oLb4xoA2s7rzmMInt|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccedc68a188190a0a7493152f92d65","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef plan_tts_polish_batches(\n    screenplay: dict[str, Any],\n    *,\n    target_scenes_per_batch: int = 5,\n    min_scenes_per_batch: int = 3,\n    max_scenes_per_batch: int = 6,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 350,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    scenes = screenplay.get(\"scenes\", []) if isinstance(screenplay, dict) else []\n    if not isinstance(scenes, list) or not scenes:\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"empty_screenplay\", \"message\": \"Cannot plan polish batches without screenplay scenes\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    batches: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    current_scene_ids: list[str] = []\n    current_word_count = 0\n    batch_number = 1\n\n    def scene_word_count(scene: dict[str, Any]) -> int:\n        return len(str(scene.get(\"narration_original\", \"\")).split())\n\n    def flush_batch() -> None:\n        nonlocal current_scene_ids, current_word_count, batch_number\n        if not current_scene_ids:\n            return\n        batches.append(\n            {\n                \"batch_id\": f\"tp_{batch_number:03d}\",\n                \"scene_ids\": current_scene_ids[:],\n                \"scene_count\": len(current_scene_ids),\n                \"word_count\": current_word_count,\n            }\n        )\n        batch_number += 1\n        current_scene_ids = []\n        current_word_count = 0\n\n    for scene in scenes:\n        scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_id\")\n        if not scene_id:\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_scene_id\",\n                \"message\": \"Screenplay scene is missing 'scene_id' required for polish batching\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        words = scene_word_count(scene)\n\n        if not current_scene_ids:\n            current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\n            current_word_count = words\n            continue\n\n        next_scene_count = len(current_scene_ids) + 1\n        next_word_count = current_word_count + words\n\n        if next_scene_count <= target_scenes_per_batch and next_word_count <= max_words_per_batch:\n            current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\n            current_word_count = next_word_count\n            continue\n\n        if len(current_scene_ids) < min_scenes_per_batch and next_scene_count <= max_scenes_per_batch:\n            current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\n            current_word_count = next_word_count\n            continue\n\n        flush_batch()\n        current_scene_ids.append(scene_id)\n        current_word_count = words\n\n    if current_scene_ids:\n        flush_batch()\n\n    if batches and batches[-1][\"scene_count\"] < min_scenes_per_batch and len(batches) > 1:\n        warnings.append(\n            {\n                \"code\": \"small_final_polish_batch\",\n                \"message\": (\n                    f\"Final TTS polish batch is smaller than recommended \"\n                    f\"({batches[-1]['scene_count']} scenes)\"\n                ),\n            }\n        )\n\n    return {\n        \"ok\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"scene_count\": len(scenes),\n        \"batch_count\": len(batches),\n        \"target_scenes_per_batch\": target_scenes_per_batch,\n        \"min_scenes_per_batch\": min_scenes_per_batch,\n        \"max_scenes_per_batch\": max_scenes_per_batch,\n        \"max_words_per_batch\": max_words_per_batch,\n        \"batches\": batches,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n\n\ndef plan_tts_polish_batches_from_file(\n    screenplay_path: str | Path,\n    *,\n    target_scenes_per_batch: int = 5,\n    min_scenes_per_batch: int = 3,\n    max_scenes_per_batch: int = 6,\n    max_words_per_batch: int = 350,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    screenplay_path = Path(screenplay_path)\n    if not screenplay_path.exists():\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"batch_count\": 0,\n            \"batches\": [],\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": \"missing_screenplay_file\", \"message\": f\"Screenplay file not found: {screenplay_path}\"}],\n            \"warnings\": [],\n        }\n\n    screenplay = json.loads(screenplay_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    result = plan_tts_polish_batches(\n        screenplay,\n        target_scenes_per_batch=target_scenes_per_batch,\n        min_scenes_per_batch=min_scenes_per_batch,\n        max_scenes_per_batch=max_scenes_per_batch,\n        max_words_per_batch=max_words_per_batch,\n    )\n    result[\"screenplay_path\"] = str(screenplay_path)\n    return result\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775037895476}}
{"type":"message","id":"37bf28b8","parentId":"9c3f6bab","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:06:01.080Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_XIaUf2IX5xop24PHGPrDJqJI|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccedcd16c8819093cc3ff8946cf920","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\tts_polish_output_validator.py","content":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\nREQUIRED_TOP_LEVEL_FIELDS = {\n    \"batch_id\",\n    \"scenes\",\n}\n\nREQUIRED_SCENE_FIELDS = {\n    \"scene_id\",\n    \"narration_original\",\n    \"narration_tts\",\n}\n\nERROR_SEVERITY = {\n    \"payload_unreadable\": \"fatal_contract_error\",\n    \"output_unreadable\": \"fatal_contract_error\",\n    \"invalid_top_level_shape\": \"fatal_contract_error\",\n    \"empty_scenes\": \"fatal_contract_error\",\n    \"scene_count_mismatch\": \"batch_regenerate\",\n    \"scene_order_mismatch\": \"batch_regenerate\",\n    \"missing_required_field\": \"structural_patch\",\n    \"missing_scene_output\": \"scene_subset_repair\",\n    \"unexpected_scene_output\": \"batch_regenerate\",\n    \"narration_original_mismatch\": \"scene_subset_repair\",\n    \"empty_narration_tts\": \"scene_subset_repair\",\n    \"meaningful_change_detected\": \"needs_semantic_review\",\n}\n\nCLASSIFICATION_PRIORITY = [\n    \"fatal_contract_error\",\n    \"batch_regenerate\",\n    \"needs_semantic_review\",\n    \"scene_subset_repair\",\n    \"structural_patch\",\n    \"ok\",\n]\n\nNO_CHANGE_NORMALIZED_EQUIVALENTS = {\n    \"°c\": \"degrees celsius\",\n    \"ºc\": \"degrees celsius\",\n    \"km\": \"kilometers\",\n    \"kg\": \"kilograms\",\n    \"dr.\": \"dr\",\n}\n\n\ndef validate_tts_polish_output(\n    *,\n    batch_payload_path: str | Path,\n    batch_output_path: str | Path,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    errors: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    warnings: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    payload_result = _load_json(batch_payload_path, error_code=\"payload_unreadable\")\n    if not payload_result[\"ok\"]:\n        return _fatal_result(batch_id=None, errors=payload_result[\"errors\"], warnings=warnings)\n\n    output_result = _load_json(batch_output_path, error_code=\"output_unreadable\")\n    if not output_result[\"ok\"]:\n        payload = payload_result[\"data\"]\n        return _fatal_result(\n            batch_id=_extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload),\n            errors=output_result[\"errors\"],\n            warnings=warnings,\n        )\n\n    payload = payload_result[\"data\"]\n    output = output_result[\"data\"]\n    expected_batch_id = _extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload)\n    batch_id = _extract_batch_id(output) or expected_batch_id\n\n    source_scenes = payload.get(\"scenes\") if isinstance(payload, dict) else None\n    if not isinstance(source_scenes, list) or not source_scenes:\n        errors.append(_error(\"invalid_top_level_shape\", \"Batch payload must include non-empty 'scenes' list\"))\n        return _finalize_result(\n            batch_id=batch_id,\n            errors=errors,\n            warnings=warnings,\n            changed_scene_count=0,\n            flagged_scene_count=0,\n            source_scene_count=0,\n        )\n\n    output_scenes = _validate_top_level_output(output, errors)\n    if not output_scenes:\n        return _finalize_result(\n            batch_id=batch_id,\n            errors=errors,\n            warnings=warnings,\n            changed_scene_count=0,\n            flagged_scene_count=0,\n            source_scene_count=len(source_scenes),\n        )\n\n    source_ids = [scene.get(\"scene_id\") for scene in source_scenes if isinstance(scene, dict)]\n    output_ids = [scene.get(\"scene_id\") for scene in output_scenes if isinstance(scene, dict)]\n\n    if expected_batch_id and _extract_batch_id(output) and _extract_batch_id(output) != expected_batch_id:\n        errors.append(_error(\n            \"missing_required_field\",\n            f\"Output batch_id '{_extract_batch_id(output)}' does not match expected '{expected_batch_id}'\",\n        ))\n\n    if len(output_scenes) != len(source_scenes):\n        errors.append(_error(\n            \"scene_count_mismatch\",\n            f\"Expected {len(source_scenes)} scenes but found {len(output_scenes)}\",\n        ))\n\n    _validate_required_scene_fields(output_scenes, errors)\n    _validate_scene_mapping(source_ids, output_ids, errors)\n\n    source_map = {\n        scene.get(\"scene_id\"): scene\n        for scene in source_scenes\n        if isinstance(scene, dict) and scene.get(\"scene_id\")\n    }\n\n    changed_scene_count = 0\n    flagged_scene_ids: set[str] = set()\n\n    for scene in output_scenes:\n        scene_id = scene.get(\"scene_id\")\n        if not isinstance(scene_id, str) or scene_id not in source_map:\n            continue\n\n        source_scene = source_map[scene_id]\n        source_original = source_scene.get(\"narration_original\")\n        output_original = scene.get(\"narration_original\")\n        narration_tts = scene.get(\"narration_tts\")\n\n        if not isinstance(output_original, str) or output_original != source_original:\n            errors.append(_error(\n                \"narration_original_mismatch\",\n                f\"Scene {scene_id} narration_original does not match source payload\",\n                scene_ids=[scene_id],\n            ))\n            flagged_scene_ids.add(scene_id)\n\n        if not isinstance(narration_tts, str) or not narration_tts.strip():\n            errors.append(_error(\n                \"empty_narration_tts\",\n                f\"Scene {scene_id} must include non-empty narration_tts\",\n                scene_ids=[scene_id],\n            ))\n            flagged_scene_ids.add(scene_id)\n            continue\n\n        if isinstance(source_original, str) and _normalize_text(narration_tts) != _normalize_text(source_original):\n            changed_scene_count += 1\n            if _is_meaningfully_different(source_original, narration_tts):\n                errors.append(_error(\n                    \"meaningful_change_detected\",\n                    f\"Scene {scene_id} narration_tts differs from source in a way that may require semantic review\",\n                    scene_ids=[scene_id],\n                ))\n                flagged_scene_ids.add(scene_id)\n\n    return _finalize_result(\n        batch_id=batch_id,\n        errors=errors,\n        warnings=warnings,\n        changed_scene_count=changed_scene_count,\n        flagged_scene_count=len(flagged_scene_ids),\n        source_scene_count=len(source_scenes),\n    )\n\n\ndef _load_json(path: str | Path, *, error_code: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    path = Path(path)\n    try:\n        data = json.loads(path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\"))\n    except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\n        return {\n            \"ok\": False,\n            \"errors\": [_error(error_code, f\"Failed to read JSON from {path}: {exc}\")],\n        }\n    return {\"ok\": True, \"data\": data}\n\n\ndef _validate_top_level_output(output: Any, errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    if not isinstance(output, dict):\n        errors.append(_error(\"invalid_top_level_shape\", \"TTS polish output must be a JSON object\"))\n        return []\n\n    missing_top_level = sorted(REQUIRED_TOP_LEVEL_FIELDS - set(output.keys()))\n    if missing_top_level:\n        errors.append(_error(\n            \"invalid_top_level_shape\",\n            f\"Output is missing top-level fields: {', '.join(missing_top_level)}\",\n        ))\n\n    scenes = output.get(\"scenes\")\n    if not isinstance(scenes, list):\n        errors.append(_error(\"invalid_top_level_shape\", \"Output 'scenes' must be a list\"))\n        return []\n\n    if not scenes:\n        errors.append(_error(\"empty_scenes\", \"Output 'scenes' list is empty\"))\n        return []\n\n    valid_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n    for index, scene in enumerate(scenes, start=1):\n        if not isinstance(scene, dict):\n            errors.append(_error(\n                \"missing_required_field\",\n                f\"Scene at index {index} must be an object\",\n                scene_ids=[f\"scene_index_{index}\"],\n            ))\n            continue\n        valid_scenes.append(scene)\n\n    return valid_scenes\n\n\ndef _validate_required_scene_fields(scenes: list[dict[str, Any]], errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\n    for scene in scenes:\n        missing_fields = sorted(REQUIRED_SCENE_FIELDS - set(scene.keys()))\n        if missing_fields:\n            errors.append(_error(\n                \"missing_required_field\",\n                (\n                    f\"Scene {scene.get('scene_id', '<unknown>')} is missing required fields: \"\n                    f\"{', '.join(missing_fields)}\"\n                ),\n                scene_ids=[scene.get(\"scene_id\")],\n            ))\n\n\ndef _validate_scene_mapping(source_ids: list[Any], output_ids: list[Any], errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\n    if source_ids != output_ids:\n        errors.append(_error(\n            \"scene_order_mismatch\",\n            \"Output scene order/identity does not match input batch scene_ids\",\n            scene_ids=[str(scene_id) for scene_id in output_ids if scene_id],\n        ))\n\n    source_set = {scene_id for scene_id in source_ids if isinstance(scene_id, str)}\n    output_set = {scene_id for scene_id in output_ids if isinstance(scene_id, str)}\n\n    missing_ids = sorted(source_set - output_set)\n    unexpected_ids = sorted(output_set - source_set)\n\n    for scene_id in missing_ids:\n        errors.append(_error(\n            \"missing_scene_output\",\n            f\"Expected scene {scene_id} is missing from polish output\",\n            scene_ids=[scene_id],\n        ))\n\n    for scene_id in unexpected_ids:\n        errors.append(_error(\n            \"unexpected_scene_output\",\n            f\"Unexpected scene {scene_id} found in polish output\",\n            scene_ids=[scene_id],\n        ))\n\n\ndef _extract_batch_id(output: dict[str, Any]) -> str | None:\n    batch_id = output.get(\"batch_id\") or output.get(\"batch\", {}).get(\"batch_id\")\n    return batch_id if isinstance(batch_id, str) and batch_id.strip() else None\n\n\ndef _extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload: dict[str, Any]) -> str | None:\n    batch = payload.get(\"batch\") if isinstance(payload, dict) else None\n    if not isinstance(batch, dict):\n        return None\n    batch_id = batch.get(\"batch_id\")\n    return batch_id if isinstance(batch_id, str) and batch_id.strip() else None\n\n\ndef _normalize_text(text: str) -> str:\n    text = text.replace(\"\\r\\n\", \" \").replace(\"\\n\", \" \").replace(\"\\t\", \" \")\n    text = re.sub(r\"\\s+\", \" \", text).strip().lower()\n    return text\n\n\ndef _canonicalize_equivalents(text: str) -> str:\n    normalized = _normalize_text(text)\n    for old, new in NO_CHANGE_NORMALIZED_EQUIVALENTS.items():\n        normalized = normalized.replace(old, new)\n    normalized = normalized.replace(\"dr \", \"dr. \")\n    normalized = re.sub(r\"\\b(\\d+)\\s+kilometers\\b\", r\"\\1 km\", normalized)\n    normalized = re.sub(r\"\\b(\\d+)\\s+kilograms\\b\", r\"\\1 kg\", normalized)\n    normalized = re.sub(r\"\\b(\\d+)\\s+degrees celsius\\b\", r\"\\1 °c\", normalized)\n    return normalized\n\n\ndef _is_meaningfully_different(source: str, polished: str) -> bool:\n    return _canonicalize_equivalents(source) != _canonicalize_equivalents(polished)\n\n\ndef _error(code: str, message: str, *, scene_ids: list[str | None] | None = None) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    clean_scene_ids = [scene_id for scene_id in (scene_ids or []) if scene_id]\n    payload: dict[str, Any] = {\"code\": code, \"message\": message}\n    if clean_scene_ids:\n        payload[\"scene_ids\"] = clean_scene_ids\n    return payload\n\n\ndef _fatal_result(*, batch_id: str | None, errors: list[dict[str, Any]], warnings: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    return {\n        \"ok\": False,\n        \"approved_for_merge\": False,\n        \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n        \"classification\": \"fatal_contract_error\",\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n        \"stats\": {\n            \"scene_count\": 0,\n            \"changed_scene_count\": 0,\n            \"flagged_scene_count\": 0,\n        },\n    }\n\n\ndef _finalize_result(\n    *,\n    batch_id: str | None,\n    errors: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    warnings: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    changed_scene_count: int,\n    flagged_scene_count: int,\n    source_scene_count: int,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    classification = _classify_errors(errors)\n    return {\n        \"ok\": classification == \"ok\",\n        \"approved_for_merge\": classification == \"ok\",\n        \"batch_id\": batch_id,\n        \"classification\": classification,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n        \"stats\": {\n            \"scene_count\": source_scene_count,\n            \"changed_scene_count\": changed_scene_count,\n            \"flagged_scene_count\": flagged_scene_count,\n        },\n    }\n\n\ndef _classify_errors(errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> str:\n    if not errors:\n        return \"ok\"\n\n    severities = [ERROR_SEVERITY.get(error.get(\"code\"), \"fatal_contract_error\") for error in errors]\n    for classification in CLASSIFICATION_PRIORITY:\n        if classification in severities:\n            return classification\n    return \"fatal_contract_error\"\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\tts_polish_output_validator.py\",\"content\":\"from __future__ import annotations\\n\\nimport json\\nimport re\\nfrom pathlib import Path\\nfrom typing import Any\\n\\n\\nREQUIRED_TOP_LEVEL_FIELDS = {\\n    \\\"batch_id\\\",\\n    \\\"scenes\\\",\\n}\\n\\nREQUIRED_SCENE_FIELDS = {\\n    \\\"scene_id\\\",\\n    \\\"narration_original\\\",\\n    \\\"narration_tts\\\",\\n}\\n\\nERROR_SEVERITY = {\\n    \\\"payload_unreadable\\\": \\\"fatal_contract_error\\\",\\n    \\\"output_unreadable\\\": \\\"fatal_contract_error\\\",\\n    \\\"invalid_top_level_shape\\\": \\\"fatal_contract_error\\\",\\n    \\\"empty_scenes\\\": \\\"fatal_contract_error\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_count_mismatch\\\": \\\"batch_regenerate\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_order_mismatch\\\": \\\"batch_regenerate\\\",\\n    \\\"missing_required_field\\\": \\\"structural_patch\\\",\\n    \\\"missing_scene_output\\\": \\\"scene_subset_repair\\\",\\n    \\\"unexpected_scene_output\\\": \\\"batch_regenerate\\\",\\n    \\\"narration_original_mismatch\\\": \\\"scene_subset_repair\\\",\\n    \\\"empty_narration_tts\\\": \\\"scene_subset_repair\\\",\\n    \\\"meaningful_change_detected\\\": \\\"needs_semantic_review\\\",\\n}\\n\\nCLASSIFICATION_PRIORITY = [\\n    \\\"fatal_contract_error\\\",\\n    \\\"batch_regenerate\\\",\\n    \\\"needs_semantic_review\\\",\\n    \\\"scene_subset_repair\\\",\\n    \\\"structural_patch\\\",\\n    \\\"ok\\\",\\n]\\n\\nNO_CHANGE_NORMALIZED_EQUIVALENTS = {\\n    \\\"°c\\\": \\\"degrees celsius\\\",\\n    \\\"ºc\\\": \\\"degrees celsius\\\",\\n    \\\"km\\\": \\\"kilometers\\\",\\n    \\\"kg\\\": \\\"kilograms\\\",\\n    \\\"dr.\\\": \\\"dr\\\",\\n}\\n\\n\\ndef validate_tts_polish_output(\\n    *,\\n    batch_payload_path: str | Path,\\n    batch_output_path: str | Path,\\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    errors: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\\n    warnings: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\\n\\n    payload_result = _load_json(batch_payload_path, error_code=\\\"payload_unreadable\\\")\\n    if not payload_result[\\\"ok\\\"]:\\n        return _fatal_result(batch_id=None, errors=payload_result[\\\"errors\\\"], warnings=warnings)\\n\\n    output_result = _load_json(batch_output_path, error_code=\\\"output_unreadable\\\")\\n    if not output_result[\\\"ok\\\"]:\\n        payload = payload_result[\\\"data\\\"]\\n        return _fatal_result(\\n            batch_id=_extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload),\\n            errors=output_result[\\\"errors\\\"],\\n            warnings=warnings,\\n        )\\n\\n    payload = payload_result[\\\"data\\\"]\\n    output = output_result[\\\"data\\\"]\\n    expected_batch_id = _extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload)\\n    batch_id = _extract_batch_id(output) or expected_batch_id\\n\\n    source_scenes = payload.get(\\\"scenes\\\") if isinstance(payload, dict) else None\\n    if not isinstance(source_scenes, list) or not source_scenes:\\n        errors.append(_error(\\\"invalid_top_level_shape\\\", \\\"Batch payload must include non-empty 'scenes' list\\\"))\\n        return _finalize_result(\\n            batch_id=batch_id,\\n            errors=errors,\\n            warnings=warnings,\\n            changed_scene_count=0,\\n            flagged_scene_count=0,\\n            source_scene_count=0,\\n        )\\n\\n    output_scenes = _validate_top_level_output(output, errors)\\n    if not output_scenes:\\n        return _finalize_result(\\n            batch_id=batch_id,\\n            errors=errors,\\n            warnings=warnings,\\n            changed_scene_count=0,\\n            flagged_scene_count=0,\\n            source_scene_count=len(source_scenes),\\n        )\\n\\n    source_ids = [scene.get(\\\"scene_id\\\") for scene in source_scenes if isinstance(scene, dict)]\\n    output_ids = [scene.get(\\\"scene_id\\\") for scene in output_scenes if isinstance(scene, dict)]\\n\\n    if expected_batch_id and _extract_batch_id(output) and _extract_batch_id(output) != expected_batch_id:\\n        errors.append(_error(\\n            \\\"missing_required_field\\\",\\n            f\\\"Output batch_id '{_extract_batch_id(output)}' does not match expected '{expected_batch_id}'\\\",\\n        ))\\n\\n    if len(output_scenes) != len(source_scenes):\\n        errors.append(_error(\\n            \\\"scene_count_mismatch\\\",\\n            f\\\"Expected {len(source_scenes)} scenes but found {len(output_scenes)}\\\",\\n        ))\\n\\n    _validate_required_scene_fields(output_scenes, errors)\\n    _validate_scene_mapping(source_ids, output_ids, errors)\\n\\n    source_map = {\\n        scene.get(\\\"scene_id\\\"): scene\\n        for scene in source_scenes\\n        if isinstance(scene, dict) and scene.get(\\\"scene_id\\\")\\n    }\\n\\n    changed_scene_count = 0\\n    flagged_scene_ids: set[str] = set()\\n\\n    for scene in output_scenes:\\n        scene_id = scene.get(\\\"scene_id\\\")\\n        if not isinstance(scene_id, str) or scene_id not in source_map:\\n            continue\\n\\n        source_scene = source_map[scene_id]\\n        source_original = source_scene.get(\\\"narration_original\\\")\\n        output_original = scene.get(\\\"narration_original\\\")\\n        narration_tts = scene.get(\\\"narration_tts\\\")\\n\\n        if not isinstance(output_original, str) or output_original != source_original:\\n            errors.append(_error(\\n                \\\"narration_original_mismatch\\\",\\n                f\\\"Scene {scene_id} narration_original does not match source payload\\\",\\n                scene_ids=[scene_id],\\n            ))\\n            flagged_scene_ids.add(scene_id)\\n\\n        if not isinstance(narration_tts, str) or not narration_tts.strip():\\n            errors.append(_error(\\n                \\\"empty_narration_tts\\\",\\n                f\\\"Scene {scene_id} must include non-empty narration_tts\\\",\\n                scene_ids=[scene_id],\\n            ))\\n            flagged_scene_ids.add(scene_id)\\n            continue\\n\\n        if isinstance(source_original, str) and _normalize_text(narration_tts) != _normalize_text(source_original):\\n            changed_scene_count += 1\\n            if _is_meaningfully_different(source_original, narration_tts):\\n                errors.append(_error(\\n                    \\\"meaningful_change_detected\\\",\\n                    f\\\"Scene {scene_id} narration_tts differs from source in a way that may require semantic review\\\",\\n                    scene_ids=[scene_id],\\n                ))\\n                flagged_scene_ids.add(scene_id)\\n\\n    return _finalize_result(\\n        batch_id=batch_id,\\n        errors=errors,\\n        warnings=warnings,\\n        changed_scene_count=changed_scene_count,\\n        flagged_scene_count=len(flagged_scene_ids),\\n        source_scene_count=len(source_scenes),\\n    )\\n\\n\\ndef _load_json(path: str | Path, *, error_code: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    path = Path(path)\\n    try:\\n        data = json.loads(path.read_text(encoding=\\\"utf-8\\\"))\\n    except Exception as exc:  # noqa: BLE001\\n        return {\\n            \\\"ok\\\": False,\\n            \\\"errors\\\": [_error(error_code, f\\\"Failed to read JSON from {path}: {exc}\\\")],\\n        }\\n    return {\\\"ok\\\": True, \\\"data\\\": data}\\n\\n\\ndef _validate_top_level_output(output: Any, errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\\n    if not isinstance(output, dict):\\n        errors.append(_error(\\\"invalid_top_level_shape\\\", \\\"TTS polish output must be a JSON object\\\"))\\n        return []\\n\\n    missing_top_level = sorted(REQUIRED_TOP_LEVEL_FIELDS - set(output.keys()))\\n    if missing_top_level:\\n        errors.append(_error(\\n            \\\"invalid_top_level_shape\\\",\\n            f\\\"Output is missing top-level fields: {', '.join(missing_top_level)}\\\",\\n        ))\\n\\n    scenes = output.get(\\\"scenes\\\")\\n    if not isinstance(scenes, list):\\n        errors.append(_error(\\\"invalid_top_level_shape\\\", \\\"Output 'scenes' must be a list\\\"))\\n        return []\\n\\n    if not scenes:\\n        errors.append(_error(\\\"empty_scenes\\\", \\\"Output 'scenes' list is empty\\\"))\\n        return []\\n\\n    valid_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\\n    for index, scene in enumerate(scenes, start=1):\\n        if not isinstance(scene, dict):\\n            errors.append(_error(\\n                \\\"missing_required_field\\\",\\n                f\\\"Scene at index {index} must be an object\\\",\\n                scene_ids=[f\\\"scene_index_{index}\\\"],\\n            ))\\n            continue\\n        valid_scenes.append(scene)\\n\\n    return valid_scenes\\n\\n\\ndef _validate_required_scene_fields(scenes: list[dict[str, Any]], errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\\n    for scene in scenes:\\n        missing_fields = sorted(REQUIRED_SCENE_FIELDS - set(scene.keys()))\\n        if missing_fields:\\n            errors.append(_error(\\n                \\\"missing_required_field\\\",\\n                (\\n                    f\\\"Scene {scene.get('scene_id', '<unknown>')} is missing required fields: \\\"\\n                    f\\\"{', '.join(missing_fields)}\\\"\\n                ),\\n                scene_ids=[scene.get(\\\"scene_id\\\")],\\n            ))\\n\\n\\ndef _validate_scene_mapping(source_ids: list[Any], output_ids: list[Any], errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> None:\\n    if source_ids != output_ids:\\n        errors.append(_error(\\n            \\\"scene_order_mismatch\\\",\\n            \\\"Output scene order/identity does not match input batch scene_ids\\\",\\n            scene_ids=[str(scene_id) for scene_id in output_ids if scene_id],\\n        ))\\n\\n    source_set = {scene_id for scene_id in source_ids if isinstance(scene_id, str)}\\n    output_set = {scene_id for scene_id in output_ids if isinstance(scene_id, str)}\\n\\n    missing_ids = sorted(source_set - output_set)\\n    unexpected_ids = sorted(output_set - source_set)\\n\\n    for scene_id in missing_ids:\\n        errors.append(_error(\\n            \\\"missing_scene_output\\\",\\n            f\\\"Expected scene {scene_id} is missing from polish output\\\",\\n            scene_ids=[scene_id],\\n        ))\\n\\n    for scene_id in unexpected_ids:\\n        errors.append(_error(\\n            \\\"unexpected_scene_output\\\",\\n            f\\\"Unexpected scene {scene_id} found in polish output\\\",\\n            scene_ids=[scene_id],\\n        ))\\n\\n\\ndef _extract_batch_id(output: dict[str, Any]) -> str | None:\\n    batch_id = output.get(\\\"batch_id\\\") or output.get(\\\"batch\\\", {}).get(\\\"batch_id\\\")\\n    return batch_id if isinstance(batch_id, str) and batch_id.strip() else None\\n\\n\\ndef _extract_batch_id_from_payload(payload: dict[str, Any]) -> str | None:\\n    batch = payload.get(\\\"batch\\\") if isinstance(payload, dict) else None\\n    if not isinstance(batch, dict):\\n        return None\\n    batch_id = batch.get(\\\"batch_id\\\")\\n    return batch_id if isinstance(batch_id, str) and batch_id.strip() else None\\n\\n\\ndef _normalize_text(text: str) -> str:\\n    text = text.replace(\\\"\\\\r\\\\n\\\", \\\" \\\").replace(\\\"\\\\n\\\", \\\" \\\").replace(\\\"\\\\t\\\", \\\" \\\")\\n    text = re.sub(r\\\"\\\\s+\\\", \\\" \\\", text).strip().lower()\\n    return text\\n\\n\\ndef _canonicalize_equivalents(text: str) -> str:\\n    normalized = _normalize_text(text)\\n    for old, new in NO_CHANGE_NORMALIZED_EQUIVALENTS.items():\\n        normalized = normalized.replace(old, new)\\n    normalized = normalized.replace(\\\"dr \\\", \\\"dr. \\\")\\n    normalized = re.sub(r\\\"\\\\b(\\\\d+)\\\\s+kilometers\\\\b\\\", r\\\"\\\\1 km\\\", normalized)\\n    normalized = re.sub(r\\\"\\\\b(\\\\d+)\\\\s+kilograms\\\\b\\\", r\\\"\\\\1 kg\\\", normalized)\\n    normalized = re.sub(r\\\"\\\\b(\\\\d+)\\\\s+degrees celsius\\\\b\\\", r\\\"\\\\1 °c\\\", normalized)\\n    return normalized\\n\\n\\ndef _is_meaningfully_different(source: str, polished: str) -> bool:\\n    return _canonicalize_equivalents(source) != _canonicalize_equivalents(polished)\\n\\n\\ndef _error(code: str, message: str, *, scene_ids: list[str | None] | None = None) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    clean_scene_ids = [scene_id for scene_id in (scene_ids or []) if scene_id]\\n    payload: dict[str, Any] = {\\\"code\\\": code, \\\"message\\\": message}\\n    if clean_scene_ids:\\n        payload[\\\"scene_ids\\\"] = clean_scene_ids\\n    return payload\\n\\n\\ndef _fatal_result(*, batch_id: str | None, errors: list[dict[str, Any]], warnings: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    return {\\n        \\\"ok\\\": False,\\n        \\\"approved_for_merge\\\": False,\\n        \\\"batch_id\\\": batch_id,\\n        \\\"classification\\\": \\\"fatal_contract_error\\\",\\n        \\\"errors\\\": errors,\\n        \\\"warnings\\\": warnings,\\n        \\\"stats\\\": {\\n            \\\"scene_count\\\": 0,\\n            \\\"changed_scene_count\\\": 0,\\n            \\\"flagged_scene_count\\\": 0,\\n        },\\n    }\\n\\n\\ndef _finalize_result(\\n    *,\\n    batch_id: str | None,\\n    errors: list[dict[str, Any]],\\n    warnings: list[dict[str, Any]],\\n    changed_scene_count: int,\\n    flagged_scene_count: int,\\n    source_scene_count: int,\\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    classification = _classify_errors(errors)\\n    return {\\n        \\\"ok\\\": classification == \\\"ok\\\",\\n        \\\"approved_for_merge\\\": classification == \\\"ok\\\",\\n        \\\"batch_id\\\": batch_id,\\n        \\\"classification\\\": classification,\\n        \\\"errors\\\": errors,\\n        \\\"warnings\\\": warnings,\\n        \\\"stats\\\": {\\n            \\\"scene_count\\\": source_scene_count,\\n            \\\"changed_scene_count\\\": changed_scene_count,\\n            \\\"flagged_scene_count\\\": flagged_scene_count,\\n        },\\n    }\\n\\n\\ndef _classify_errors(errors: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> str:\\n    if not errors:\\n        return \\\"ok\\\"\\n\\n    severities = [ERROR_SEVERITY.get(error.get(\\\"code\\\"), \\\"fatal_contract_error\\\") for error in errors]\\n    for classification in CLASSIFICATION_PRIORITY:\\n        if classification in severities:\\n            return classification\\n    return \\\"fatal_contract_error\\\"\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":5437,"output":3400,"cacheRead":94208,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":103045,"cost":{"input":0.0135925,"output":0.051000000000000004,"cacheRead":0.023552,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0881445}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775037896169,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169ccedca811081908fa071f0b241a51a"}}
