{"type":"message","id":"c9452595","parentId":"6b63436b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:11:00.088Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_QDilIMyzJm4SIorrNCHn9PXp|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccef34d0788190a53d15a0fe94e080","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# RULES.md\n\n## Non-Negotiable Rules\n\n1. **Never change meaning**\n   - Do not alter the meaning, implication, factual content, or narrative intention of the original scene.\n\n2. **Never add or remove information**\n   - Do not eat words, compress ideas, expand ideas, embellish, summarize, or paraphrase beyond what is strictly necessary for TTS normalization.\n\n3. **Preserve scene identity and order**\n   - Keep the same `scene_id` mapping.\n   - Keep the same scene order.\n   - Do not merge or split scenes.\n\n4. **Preserve original reference**\n   - `narration_original` must remain the original source narration for the scene.\n\n5. **Optimize narrowly for TTS**\n   - Apply only the minimum necessary changes for pronunciation, readability, oral clarity, abbreviations, ordinals, units, and similar TTS concerns.\n\n6. **Do not absorb another layer's job**\n   - Do not re-decide scene structure.\n   - Do not validate your own output.\n   - Do not generate audio.\n   - Do not create timestamps/alignment.\n\n7. **Respect batch discipline**\n   - Operate only on the scenes provided in the assigned batch.\n   - Do not act as if you own the whole screenplay.\n\n8. **Prefer safe minimalism**\n   - If a change is not clearly necessary for TTS improvement, prefer not to make it.\n\n## Output Fields Required Per Scene\n\n- `scene_id`\n- `narration_original`\n- `narration_tts`\n\n## Optional Fields\n\n- `changes`\n\n## Quality Standard\n\nA good output should:\n- sound better in TTS than the original raw narration\n- preserve meaning fully\n- preserve scene order and scene identity exactly\n- make only necessary oral/reading adjustments\n- remain narrow rather than becoming stylistic rewriting\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775038259988}}
{"type":"message","id":"29c4e446","parentId":"c9452595","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:11:00.189Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_v6oS5L4feF0UDJ7HbqYukoHI|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccef34d084819085f32321ba9b002d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md\n\n## Notes\n\nThis operator does not own broad system tooling decisions.\nIts operational contract is mostly defined by:\n- the supervisor-prepared payload\n- S1 contracts\n- workspace rules/prompt/examples\n\n## Important Structural Notes\n\n- Dispatch unit: small ordered scene batches\n- Comparison sensitivity: scene-by-scene inside the batch\n- Validation is supervisor-owned\n- `tts_polish_output_validator` is the canonical batch gate before merge\n- Semantic review is optional and only for ambiguous cases\n- Preferred correction mode: affected scene subset when possible\n- Approved batches, not just completed batches, should flow into merge\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775038260088}}
{"type":"message","id":"99b94436","parentId":"29c4e446","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:11:00.290Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_HnQVMLMAt6dqsjJbjpv8992E|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccef34d090819080c2aec9a86983bc","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - op_s1_tts_polish\n\n## Purpose of This Workspace\n\nThis workspace exists to give `op_s1_tts_polish` the minimum operational context needed to perform safe, controlled TTS polish on small ordered scene batches.\n\n## What This Agent Should Read\n\nAt minimum:\n1. `IDENTITY.md`\n2. `CONTEXT.md`\n3. `RULES.md`\n4. `PROMPT.md`\n5. `EXAMPLES.md`\n\n## Operating Principle\n\nThis agent should be narrow, disciplined, and fidelity-first.\nIt should not behave like a supervisor, semantic reviewer, or narrative rewriter.\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Do not change meaning.\n- Do not add/remove information.\n- Do not absorb downstream audio or upstream narrative-structure responsibilities.\n- Do not improvise around broken contracts; surface the conflict through the proper supervisory loop.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775038260189}}
{"type":"message","id":"a8d57390","parentId":"99b94436","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:11:10.172Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_OeLVea0PIkFLj0UlekhdB7Ml|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccef39f7fc81908af5187e103ea319","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_tts_polish\\AGENTS.md","oldText":"## Operating Principle\n\nThis agent should be narrow, disciplined, and fidelity-first.\nIt should not behave like a supervisor, semantic reviewer, or narrative rewriter.\n\n## Red Lines\n","newText":"## Operating Principle\n\nThis agent should be narrow, disciplined, and fidelity-first.\nIt should not behave like a supervisor, semantic reviewer, or narrative rewriter.\n\n## Runtime Worker Protocol\n\nWhen invoked as an execution worker by the S1 runtime:\n1. Read the payload file/path explicitly referenced in the incoming instruction.\n2. Treat the payload as the source of truth for:\n   - batch identity\n   - ordered input scenes\n   - output path\n   - required constraints\n3. Produce the final batch result as valid JSON.\n4. Write the result to the declared `output_path`.\n5. The top-level output shape must be:\n   - `batch_id`\n   - `operator`\n   - `scenes`\n6. Prefer artifact creation over conversational explanation.\n7. If execution fails, write a structured error JSON to the expected output path when possible.\n8. Do not stop at analysis-only if you have enough information to write the output artifact.\n\n## Red Lines\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_tts_polish\\\\AGENTS.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Operating Principle\\n\\nThis agent should be narrow, disciplined, and fidelity-first.\\nIt should not behave like a supervisor, semantic reviewer, or narrative rewriter.\\n\\n## Red Lines\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Operating Principle\\n\\nThis agent should be narrow, disciplined, and fidelity-first.\\nIt should not behave like a supervisor, semantic reviewer, or narrative rewriter.\\n\\n## Runtime Worker Protocol\\n\\nWhen invoked as an execution worker by the S1 runtime:\\n1. Read the payload file/path explicitly referenced in the incoming instruction.\\n2. Treat the payload as the source of truth for:\\n   - batch identity\\n   - ordered input scenes\\n   - output path\\n   - required constraints\\n3. Produce the final batch result as valid JSON.\\n4. Write the result to the declared `output_path`.\\n5. The top-level output shape must be:\\n   - `batch_id`\\n   - `operator`\\n   - `scenes`\\n6. Prefer artifact creation over conversational explanation.\\n7. If execution fails, write a structured error JSON to the expected output path when possible.\\n8. Do not stop at analysis-only if you have enough information to write the output artifact.\\n\\n## Red Lines\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":825,"output":305,"cacheRead":121984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123114,"cost":{"input":0.0020625,"output":0.004575,"cacheRead":0.030496,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0371335}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775038260937,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169ccef36fc308190baf8a1a24a343ab4"}}
