{"type":"message","id":"d406d90a","parentId":"195267b5","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:19:47.757Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Progresso real: já destravei os dois bloqueios iniciais — config path e worker `tts_polish`. O teste integrado agora entra no lane de TTS polish de verdade e falha num ponto mais avançado: o validator está a sinalizar a mudança `km -> kilometers` numa cena real como needing semantic review. Ou seja, o sistema já está a correr mais fundo; o próximo ajuste é refinar o critério de equivalência segura no validator ou adicionar a via de reviewer/orchestration.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169ccf12c4fbc81909f08ec08bec0de3f\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Boa — avancei de verdade.\n\n# O que destravei agora\n\n## 1. Corrigi o problema de config path\nO supervisor estava a procurar `accounts/004/fr.yaml` no lugar errado por causa de como o `run_root` de teste estava fora do repo.\n\nAjustei:\n- `s1_preflight_checker.py`\n- `_load_config(...)` em `supervisor_runtime.py`\n\npara procurar a config também a partir do **repo real**.\n\n### Resultado\nO teste integrado **já não morre mais no preflight/config**.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Tornei o `op_s1_tts_polish` confiável como worker\nAjustei o workspace dele para reforçar:\n\n- worker protocol explícito\n- prioridade em escrever artefacto\n- proibição prática de cair em `NO_REPLY` quando tem payload/output_path válidos\n- output contract top-level esperado\n\n### Resultado\nRe-testei o agent.\n\nAgora ele escreveu correctamente:\n\n- `batch_id`\n- `operator`\n- `scenes`\n\ne já não caiu no `NO_REPLY`.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Fiz o validator do `tts_polish` passar no teste controlado\nRefinei o `tts_polish_output_validator` para aceitar equivalências seguras como:\n\n- `km` ↔ `kilometers`\n- `m` ↔ `meters`\n- `°C` / encoding quebrado ↔ `degrees celsius`\n- `dr` ↔ `dr.`\n\n### Resultado\nO teste controlado do `tts_polish` agora dá:\n\n- `approved_for_merge: true`\n- `classification: ok`\n\n---\n\n# Onde o teste integrado parou agora\n\nIsto é a parte mais importante:\n\n## O teste integrado do supervisor já entra no lane de TTS polish de verdade\nOu seja:\n- passou do preflight\n- passou do problema de config\n- passou da fase “agent não escreve”\n- e agora falha **num ponto semântico mais avançado**\n\n### Falha actual\nNo run real integrado, apareceu:\n\n- `meaningful_change_detected` para `scene_001`\n- seguido de:\n  - `tts_polish_lane_incomplete`\n  - pedindo retry/reviewer orchestration\n\n---\n\n# Tradução bem leiga\nAntes estávamos travados em problemas de “encanamento”:\n\n- caminho errado\n- agent não obedecendo como worker\n\nAgora o sistema já está a rodar mais fundo, e o bloqueio ficou mais nobre:\n\n> o validator do TTS polish ainda está conservador demais para algumas normalizações que provavelmente são seguras\n\nPor exemplo, uma expansão tipo:\n- `km` → `kilometers`\n\nou algo semelhante numa cena real do run integrado.\n\n---\n\n# O que isso significa estrategicamente\n\n## Boa notícia\nIsto é **progresso real**.\n\nPorque agora o gargalo não é mais:\n- arquitetura\n- registry\n- invocation\n- config\n- worker protocol básico\n\nAgora o gargalo está em:\n\n### política de validação / equivalência segura no `tts_polish`\nOu seja:\n- o sistema já funciona o suficiente para o problema ficar mais fino\n\n---\n\n# Estado actual do S1\n\n## Já destravado\n- `scene_director` canónico funcional\n- `tts_polish` invocável no runtime\n- `tts_polish` a escrever artefacto de forma confiável\n- config path corrigido\n- teste integrado a correr mais fundo que antes\n\n## Bloqueio actual real\n- validator do `tts_polish` ainda marca pelo menos uma mudança real do run como:\n  - `needs_semantic_review`\n\nEntão faltam 2 caminhos possíveis:\n\n### Opção A — refinar melhor o validator\nAdicionar mais equivalências seguras e reduzir falso positivo.\n\n### Opção B — implementar a via de semantic reviewer/orchestration\nOu seja:\n- quando cair em ambiguidade\n- mandar só as cenas afectadas para review\n- em vez de falhar o lane\n\n---\n\n# Minha recomendação objectiva\n**Primeiro eu tentaria a Opção A.**\n\nPorque neste momento parece bem provável que o bloqueio seja:\n- um falso positivo conservador\n- não um problema estrutural real do TTS polish\n\nSe depois disso ainda falhar, aí sim faz sentido abrir a via:\n- `tts_polish_semantic_reviewer`\n\n---\n\n# Resumo brutal\n**Sim, tivemos progresso importante.**\nEu já destravei os dois gargalos que estavam mais em baixo nível.\n\n## Agora o S1 está preso num ponto mais alto:\n**o critério de validação semântica do TTS polish ainda está conservador demais no teste integrado real.**\n\nSe quiser, eu continuo agora exactamente desse ponto:\n- inspeccionar a `scene_001` real que disparou\n- entender qual mudança causou o alerta\n- ajustar o validator ou a política do lane\n- e tentar buscar o primeiro teste integrado verde.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169ccf12edcd48190a8f315ebf740f93f\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":440,"output":1147,"cacheRead":121984,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":123571,"cost":{"input":0.0011,"output":0.017205,"cacheRead":0.030496,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.048801}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775038755350,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169ccf1296d308190a8cd5e2b68f4beee"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ba7d89e8","parentId":"d406d90a","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:26:03.472Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-04-01 07:26 GMT-3] Perfeito Tobias. Eu vou precisar sair agora e volto daqui mais ou menos uma hora e meia. Gostaria muito que você seguisse trabalhando enquanto estou fora. Sim concordo totalmente com a tua recomendação objetiva e vc me parece estar indo muito bem. Nesta uma hora e meia enquanto estou fora, obviamente a prioridade máxima é agrantir que o S1 funcione perfeitamente da maneira que estamos montando. Depois disso, acredito que a prioridade seja o PM e VO, que precisa fazer o wiring entre eles e, além disso, o PM e o VO, ainda não são agentes reais no nosso openclaw e acredito que eles ainda não possuem seu workspace próprio no openclaw. Gostaria que os dois também rodassem com o modelo gpt 5.4 mini. Como podes me garantir que vais ficart trbalhando durante esta uma hora e meia que estarei fora, para garantir que o S1 funcione da mlehor maneira possível e, sem seguida, fazer tudo que fizemos no S1 mas para PM e VO? C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm. Já temos criadas alguns contract e skills para o PM principalmente, mas deve estar bem desatuializado pois estavamos seguindo aquele processo de paenas adequar a arquitetura, mas ai migramos para o processo de passar por cada um dos agentes/setores do workflow e deixando cada um deles 100%. Eu ficaria muito feliz se eu voltasse daqui uma e hroa e meia e tu me dissesse que conseguisse fazer rodar um workflow completo PM -> VO -> S1 e que o output do S1 ta perfeito. Porém nas ultimas vezes que te pedi pra trabalhar sem minha presença, você acabou não fazenod nada, então temos que pensar como que vamos estruturar essa sua jornada de trabalho"}],"timestamp":1775039163363}}
{"type":"message","id":"4176d996","parentId":"ba7d89e8","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:26:09.703Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4z498YUVuKxOBFuQoage09mE|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccf2c2408481909294fcb71e045b6a","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\index.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\docs\\\\index.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":121467,"output":43,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":124070,"cost":{"input":0.30366750000000003,"output":0.0006450000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0006399999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.3049525}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775039164678,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169ccf2bebbc48190955b47ec931ca0de"}}
{"type":"message","id":"bf3a9abf","parentId":"4176d996","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:26:10.525Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4z498YUVuKxOBFuQoage09mE|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccf2c2408481909294fcb71e045b6a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nsummary: \"OpenClaw is a multi-channel gateway for AI agents that runs on any OS.\"\nread_when:\n  - Introducing OpenClaw to newcomers\ntitle: \"OpenClaw\"\n---\n\n# OpenClaw 🦞\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n    <img\n        src=\"/assets/openclaw-logo-text-dark.png\"\n        alt=\"OpenClaw\"\n        width=\"500\"\n        class=\"dark:hidden\"\n    />\n    <img\n        src=\"/assets/openclaw-logo-text.png\"\n        alt=\"OpenClaw\"\n        width=\"500\"\n        class=\"hidden dark:block\"\n    />\n</p>\n\n> _\"EXFOLIATE! EXFOLIATE!\"_ — A space lobster, probably\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n  <strong>Any OS gateway for AI agents across WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, iMessage, and more.</strong><br />\n  Send a message, get an agent response from your pocket. Plugins add Mattermost and more.\n</p>\n\n<Columns>\n  <Card title=\"Get Started\" href=\"/start/getting-started\" icon=\"rocket\">\n    Install OpenClaw and bring up the Gateway in minutes.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Run Onboarding\" href=\"/start/wizard\" icon=\"sparkles\">\n    Guided setup with `openclaw onboard` and pairing flows.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Open the Control UI\" href=\"/web/control-ui\" icon=\"layout-dashboard\">\n    Launch the browser dashboard for chat, config, and sessions.\n  </Card>\n</Columns>\n\n## What is OpenClaw?\n\nOpenClaw is a **self-hosted gateway** that connects your favorite chat apps — WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, iMessage, and more — to AI coding agents like Pi. You run a single Gateway process on your own machine (or a server), and it becomes the bridge between your messaging apps and an always-available AI assistant.\n\n**Who is it for?** Developers and power users who want a personal AI assistant they can message from anywhere — without giving up control of their data or relying on a hosted service.\n\n**What makes it different?**\n\n- **Self-hosted**: runs on your hardware, your rules\n- **Multi-channel**: one Gateway serves WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, and more simultaneously\n- **Agent-native**: built for coding agents with tool use, sessions, memory, and multi-agent routing\n- **Open source**: MIT licensed, community-driven\n\n**What do you need?** Node 24 (recommended), or Node 22 LTS (`22.14+`) for compatibility, an API key from your chosen provider, and 5 minutes. For best quality and security, use the strongest latest-generation model available.\n\n## How it works\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart LR\n  A[\"Chat apps + plugins\"] --> B[\"Gateway\"]\n  B --> C[\"Pi agent\"]\n  B --> D[\"CLI\"]\n  B --> E[\"Web Control UI\"]\n  B --> F[\"macOS app\"]\n  B --> G[\"iOS and Android nodes\"]\n```\n\nThe Gateway is the single source of truth for sessions, routing, and channel connections.\n\n## Key capabilities\n\n<Columns>\n  <Card title=\"Multi-channel gateway\" icon=\"network\">\n    WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, and iMessage with a single Gateway process.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Plugin channels\" icon=\"plug\">\n    Add Mattermost and more with extension packages.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Multi-agent routing\" icon=\"route\">\n    Isolated sessions per agent, workspace, or sender.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Media support\" icon=\"image\">\n    Send and receive images, audio, and documents.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Web Control UI\" icon=\"monitor\">\n    Browser dashboard for chat, config, sessions, and nodes.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Mobile nodes\" icon=\"smartphone\">\n    Pair iOS and Android nodes for Canvas, camera, and voice-enabled workflows.\n  </Card>\n</Columns>\n\n## Quick start\n\n<Steps>\n  <Step title=\"Install OpenClaw\">\n    ```bash\n    npm install -g openclaw@latest\n    ```\n  </Step>\n  <Step title=\"Onboard and install the service\">\n    ```bash\n    openclaw onboard --install-daemon\n    ```\n  </Step>\n  <Step title=\"Chat\">\n    Open the Control UI in your browser and send a message:\n\n    ```bash\n    openclaw dashboard\n    ```\n\n    Or connect a channel ([Telegram](/channels/telegram) is fastest) and chat from your phone.\n\n  </Step>\n</Steps>\n\nNeed the full install and dev setup? See [Getting Started](/start/getting-started).\n\n## Dashboard\n\nOpen the browser Control UI after the Gateway starts.\n\n- Local default: [http://127.0.0.1:18789/](http://127.0.0.1:18789/)\n- Remote access: [Web surfaces](/web) and [Tailscale](/gateway/tailscale)\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n  <img src=\"/whatsapp-openclaw.jpg\" alt=\"OpenClaw\" width=\"420\" />\n</p>\n\n## Configuration (optional)\n\nConfig lives at `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`.\n\n- If you **do nothing**, OpenClaw uses the bundled Pi binary in RPC mode with per-sender sessions.\n- If you want to lock it down, start with `channels.whatsapp.allowFrom` and (for groups) mention rules.\n\nExample:\n\n```json5\n{\n  channels: {\n    whatsapp: {\n      allowFrom: [\"+15555550123\"],\n      groups: { \"*\": { requireMention: true } },\n    },\n  },\n  messages: { groupChat: { mentionPatterns: [\"@openclaw\"] } },\n}\n```\n\n## Start here\n\n<Columns>\n  <Card title=\"Docs hubs\" href=\"/start/hubs\" icon=\"book-open\">\n    All docs and guides, organized by use case.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Configuration\" href=\"/gateway/configuration\" icon=\"settings\">\n    Core Gateway settings, tokens, and provider config.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Remote access\" href=\"/gateway/remote\" icon=\"globe\">\n    SSH and tailnet access patterns.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Channels\" href=\"/channels/telegram\" icon=\"message-square\">\n    Channel-specific setup for WhatsApp, Telegram, Discord, and more.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Nodes\" href=\"/nodes\" icon=\"smartphone\">\n    iOS and Android nodes with pairing, Canvas, camera, and device actions.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Help\" href=\"/help\" icon=\"life-buoy\">\n    Common fixes and troubleshooting entry point.\n  </Card>\n</Columns>\n\n## Learn more\n\n<Columns>\n  <Card title=\"Full feature list\" href=\"/concepts/features\" icon=\"list\">\n    Complete channel, routing, and media capabilities.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Multi-agent routing\" href=\"/concepts/multi-agent\" icon=\"route\">\n    Workspace isolation and per-agent sessions.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Security\" href=\"/gateway/security\" icon=\"shield\">\n    Tokens, allowlists, and safety controls.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"Troubleshooting\" href=\"/gateway/troubleshooting\" icon=\"wrench\">\n    Gateway diagnostics and common errors.\n  </Card>\n  <Card title=\"About and credits\" href=\"/reference/credits\" icon=\"info\">\n    Project origins, contributors, and license.\n  </Card>\n</Columns>\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775039170339}}
{"type":"message","id":"907c3963","parentId":"bf3a9abf","timestamp":"2026-04-01T10:26:29.915Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfeito — para garantir trabalho enquanto tu estiver fora, não posso depender só de “lembrar”. Vou transformar isso em mecanismo persistente: registrar a missão em ficheiro e lançar uma sessão persistente/subagente para continuar a execução enquanto tu estiver ausente.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169ccf2cb9f348190b70c24d24bfea62e\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_V9a6v7IJCDbNFBWZJTaJgQA5|fc_0785557c08065f410169ccf2cdfc5081909b61e376fa0ca389","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\TASKS.md","content":"# TASKS.md\n\n## Active Mission — 2026-04-01\n\n### Priority 1 — Make S1 canonical flow work end-to-end\nGoal: get the canonical S1 runtime working as robustly as possible.\n\nSuccess target:\n- `run_s1_supervisor_runtime(...)` completes successfully on a controlled run\n- flow reaches `b1_complete`\n- `scene_director` + `tts_polish` + scene bible lane all work together\n- S1 output quality/validation is strong, not just barely passing\n\nCurrent known blockers to resolve:\n- refine `tts_polish` validator/review policy so safe TTS equivalences do not trigger false failures\n- keep `op_s1_tts_polish` reliable as a worker that always writes artifacts\n- continue integrated testing until S1 run is green\n\n### Priority 2 — PM and VO after S1 is stable\nAfter S1 is stable, move to PM and VO.\n\nDesired outcome:\n- PM and VO become real OpenClaw agents\n- PM and VO have proper workspaces in OpenClaw\n- PM and VO run on `gpt-5.4-mini`\n- PM -> VO -> S1 canonical workflow runs end-to-end on a controlled test\n\nLikely areas to inspect:\n- `docs/contracts/`\n- `runtime/pm`\n- current PM/VO contracts, skills, runtime wiring, and OpenClaw registration state\n\n## Execution rule\nDo not rely on chat memory for this mission. Continue from this file + repo state until the human returns or a hard blocker is reached.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\TASKS.md\",\"content\":\"# TASKS.md\\n\\n## Active Mission — 2026-04-01\\n\\n### Priority 1 — Make S1 canonical flow work end-to-end\\nGoal: get the canonical S1 runtime working as robustly as possible.\\n\\nSuccess target:\\n- `run_s1_supervisor_runtime(...)` completes successfully on a controlled run\\n- flow reaches `b1_complete`\\n- `scene_director` + `tts_polish` + scene bible lane all work together\\n- S1 output quality/validation is strong, not just barely passing\\n\\nCurrent known blockers to resolve:\\n- refine `tts_polish` validator/review policy so safe TTS equivalences do not trigger false failures\\n- keep `op_s1_tts_polish` reliable as a worker that always writes artifacts\\n- continue integrated testing until S1 run is green\\n\\n### Priority 2 — PM and VO after S1 is stable\\nAfter S1 is stable, move to PM and VO.\\n\\nDesired outcome:\\n- PM and VO become real OpenClaw agents\\n- PM and VO have proper workspaces in OpenClaw\\n- PM and VO run on `gpt-5.4-mini`\\n- PM -> VO -> S1 canonical workflow runs end-to-end on a controlled test\\n\\nLikely areas to inspect:\\n- `docs/contracts/`\\n- `runtime/pm`\\n- current PM/VO contracts, skills, runtime wiring, and OpenClaw registration state\\n\\n## Execution rule\\nDo not rely on chat memory for this mission. Continue from this file + repo state until the human returns or a hard blocker is reached.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":123136,"output":441,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":126137,"cost":{"input":0.30784,"output":0.006615,"cacheRead":0.0006399999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.31509499999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775039171188,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169ccf2c54300819094cbfc6f85eb9af0"}}
