{"type":"message","id":"1c5a8896","parentId":"a215471b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T12:59:00.688Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_rOLFVc0galtQrFBsBO9Wh9DR|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1695b8b48190acbdfc8a4b939c49","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -Recurse -File docs\\contracts | Where-Object { $_.FullName -match 'pm|vo' } | Select-Object -ExpandProperty FullName","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"Get-ChildItem -Recurse -File docs\\\\contracts | Where-Object { $_.FullName -match 'pm|vo' } | Select-Object -ExpandProperty FullName\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":30}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_hLKd0vrZs7KkLurdk9ZApPeg|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1695b8c48190a3dda16787c3114c","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\vo_start.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\vo\\\\vo_start.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_AKMNjfSIrCQnKwxw461qi8S5|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1695b8cc8190878edd29a21b3aa9","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm\\selection_engine.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\pm\\\\selection_engine.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_kE6BYaKUfBXXh6lf0ktook0H|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1695b8e08190b326e47f0edfeb16","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm\\job_builder.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\pm\\\\job_builder.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_GEprW2y8qaZNmFFlyEMrr1vv|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1695b8ec8190bb46fb023e0bc4b8","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\job_input_validator.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\vo\\\\job_input_validator.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":118980,"output":250,"cacheRead":20992,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":140222,"cost":{"input":0.29745000000000005,"output":0.0037500000000000003,"cacheRead":0.005248,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.306448}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775048332603,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd168f07088190ac5bf0df416024fe"}}
{"type":"message","id":"396f50b3","parentId":"1c5a8896","timestamp":"2026-04-01T12:59:02.511Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_rOLFVc0galtQrFBsBO9Wh9DR|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1695b8b48190acbdfc8a4b939c49","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm_override_contract.md\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm_read_pub_contract.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":734,"aggregated":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm_override_contract.md\r\nC:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm_read_pub_contract.md","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775048342326}}
{"type":"message","id":"ff3f9feb","parentId":"396f50b3","timestamp":"2026-04-01T12:59:02.698Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_hLKd0vrZs7KkLurdk9ZApPeg|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1695b8c48190a3dda16787c3114c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"VO Start — entry point for Video Orchestrator bootstrap.\n\nOrchestrates:\n1. Validate job (job_input_validator)\n2. Initialize directory (video_dir_initializer)\n3. Write job.json (done inside video_dir_initializer)\n4. Write run_metadata.json\n5. Write checkpoints/vo_init.json\n6. Return structured result\n\nIf job is invalid: returns success=false, errors, NO directory created.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nfrom runtime.vo.job_input_validator import validate_job_input\nfrom runtime.vo.video_dir_initializer import initialize_video_dir\nfrom runtime.vo.run_metadata_writer import write_run_metadata\nfrom runtime.vo.checkpoint_initializer import write_initial_checkpoint\n\n\ndef start_video_run(\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    production_root: Path | None = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Bootstrap a video production run from a PM job.\n\n    Args:\n        job: PM job dict to initialize.\n        production_root: Override for production root (used in tests).\n\n    Returns:\n        Structured result dict with success, paths, status, errors, warnings.\n    \"\"\"\n    warnings: list[str] = []\n\n    # Step 1: Validate job\n    validation = validate_job_input(job)\n    if not validation[\"valid\"]:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"job_id\": job.get(\"job_id\", \"unknown\"),\n            \"video_root\": None,\n            \"paths\": {},\n            \"status\": \"validation_failed\",\n            \"next_step\": None,\n            \"errors\": validation[\"errors\"],\n            \"warnings\": warnings,\n        }\n\n    # Step 2-3: Initialize directory + write job.json\n    try:\n        dir_result = initialize_video_dir(job, production_root=production_root)\n    except FileExistsError as e:\n        return {\n            \"success\": False,\n            \"job_id\": job[\"job_id\"],\n            \"video_root\": None,\n            \"paths\": {},\n            \"status\": \"run_already_exists\",\n            \"next_step\": None,\n            \"errors\": [{\n                \"code\": \"run_already_exists\",\n                \"field\": \"video_root\",\n                \"message\": str(e),\n            }],\n            \"warnings\": warnings,\n        }\n\n    video_root = Path(dir_result[\"video_root\"])\n\n    # Step 4: Write run_metadata.json\n    metadata_path = write_run_metadata(video_root, job)\n\n    # Step 5: Write checkpoints/vo_init.json\n    checkpoint_path = write_initial_checkpoint(video_root, job)\n\n    # Step 6: Return structured result\n    return {\n        \"success\": True,\n        \"job_id\": job[\"job_id\"],\n        \"video_root\": str(video_root),\n        \"paths\": {\n            \"job_json\": dir_result[\"job_json_path\"],\n            \"run_metadata\": metadata_path,\n            \"checkpoint_init\": checkpoint_path,\n        },\n        \"status\": \"initialized\",\n        \"next_step\": \"ready_for_script_fetch\",\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": warnings,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775048342513}}
{"type":"message","id":"60622ff1","parentId":"ff3f9feb","timestamp":"2026-04-01T12:59:02.886Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_AKMNjfSIrCQnKwxw461qi8S5|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1695b8cc8190878edd29a21b3aa9","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"PM Selection Engine — mode-aware channel selection.\n\nSupports 3 modes:\n- auto_select: PM decides by runway\n- filtered_select: PM decides by runway within upstream constraints\n- direct_select: Tobias decides the target, PM resolves and validates\n\nFollows the contract in docs/contracts/pm_override_contract.md.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom datetime import date\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\n\nfrom runtime.pm.override_validator import validate_override\nfrom runtime.pm.read_pub import read_pub\nfrom runtime.pm.job_builder import build_job\nfrom runtime.pm.job_validator import validate_job\n\n\ndef select_and_build_job(\n    override: dict[str, Any],\n    credential_path: Optional[Path] = None,\n    today: Optional[date] = None,\n    job_sequence: int = 1,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Execute PM selection with override mode awareness.\n\n    Args:\n        override: Override payload with mode, constraints, direct_target.\n        credential_path: Optional path to Google SA credentials.\n        today: Reference date for runway calculation.\n        job_sequence: Sequence number for same-day jobs.\n\n    Returns:\n        {\n            \"success\": bool,\n            \"mode\": str,\n            \"job\": dict | None,\n            \"validation\": dict | None,\n            \"selection_reasoning\": str,\n            \"pub_summary\": dict | None,\n            \"warnings\": list,\n            \"errors\": list,\n        }\n    \"\"\"\n    # Step 1: Validate override payload\n    ov_result = validate_override(override)\n    if not ov_result[\"valid\"]:\n        return _result(\n            success=False,\n            mode=override.get(\"mode\", \"unknown\"),\n            errors=ov_result[\"errors\"],\n            warnings=ov_result.get(\"warnings\", []),\n            reasoning=\"Override validation failed\",\n        )\n\n    mode = override[\"mode\"]\n    warnings = list(ov_result.get(\"warnings\", []))\n\n    # Step 2: Route by mode\n    if mode == \"direct_select\":\n        return _direct_select(override, credential_path, today, job_sequence, warnings)\n    elif mode == \"filtered_select\":\n        return _filtered_select(override, credential_path, today, job_sequence, warnings)\n    else:  # auto_select\n        return _auto_select(override, credential_path, today, job_sequence, warnings)\n\n\ndef _auto_select(\n    override: dict, credential_path, today, job_sequence, warnings\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Normal PM selection by runway.\"\"\"\n    pub = _read_pub_safe(credential_path, today)\n    if pub is None:\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=\"auto_select\",\n            errors=[{\"code\": \"pub_read_failed\", \"message\": \"Could not read PUB sheet\"}],\n            warnings=warnings, reasoning=\"PUB read failed\",\n        )\n\n    if pub[\"errors\"]:\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=\"auto_select\",\n            errors=pub[\"errors\"], warnings=warnings,\n            reasoning=\"PUB read returned errors\",\n            pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\"),\n        )\n\n    eligible = pub[\"eligible_channels\"]\n    if not eligible:\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=\"auto_select\",\n            errors=[{\"code\": \"no_eligible_channels\", \"message\": \"No eligible channels in PUB\"}],\n            warnings=warnings, reasoning=\"No eligible channels found\",\n            pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\"),\n        )\n\n    chosen = eligible[0]  # Already sorted by runway\n    return _build_and_validate(\n        chosen, override, job_sequence, warnings,\n        reasoning=f\"auto_select: chose {chosen['channel_name']} (runway={chosen['runway_days']})\",\n        pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\"),\n    )\n\n\ndef _filtered_select(\n    override: dict, credential_path, today, job_sequence, warnings\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"PM selection within upstream constraints.\"\"\"\n    constraints = override.get(\"constraints\", {})\n\n    # Build filter params from constraints\n    allowed_accounts = constraints.get(\"allowed_accounts\")\n    allowed_languages = constraints.get(\"allowed_languages\")\n    excluded_accounts = constraints.get(\"excluded_accounts\")\n    excluded_languages = constraints.get(\"excluded_languages\")\n\n    # Read PUB with allowed filters (read_pub supports these natively)\n    pub = _read_pub_safe(\n        credential_path, today,\n        allowed_accounts=allowed_accounts,\n        allowed_languages=allowed_languages,\n    )\n    if pub is None:\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=\"filtered_select\",\n            errors=[{\"code\": \"pub_read_failed\", \"message\": \"Could not read PUB sheet\"}],\n            warnings=warnings, reasoning=\"PUB read failed\",\n        )\n\n    if pub[\"errors\"]:\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=\"filtered_select\",\n            errors=pub[\"errors\"], warnings=warnings,\n            reasoning=\"PUB read returned errors\",\n            pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\"),\n        )\n\n    eligible = pub[\"eligible_channels\"]\n\n    # Apply excluded filters (not natively supported by read_pub)\n    if excluded_accounts:\n        eligible = [c for c in eligible if c[\"account\"] not in excluded_accounts]\n    if excluded_languages:\n        eligible = [c for c in eligible if c[\"language\"] not in excluded_languages]\n\n    # CRITICAL: filtered_select must NOT fall back to auto_select\n    if not eligible:\n        filter_desc = _describe_constraints(constraints)\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=\"filtered_select\",\n            errors=[{\n                \"code\": \"no_eligible_in_subset\",\n                \"message\": f\"No eligible channels within constraints: {filter_desc}\",\n            }],\n            warnings=warnings,\n            reasoning=f\"filtered_select produced 0 candidates with constraints: {filter_desc}\",\n            pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\"),\n        )\n\n    chosen = eligible[0]\n    filter_desc = _describe_constraints(constraints)\n    return _build_and_validate(\n        chosen, override, job_sequence, warnings,\n        reasoning=f\"filtered_select: chose {chosen['channel_name']} (runway={chosen['runway_days']}) within {filter_desc}\",\n        pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\"),\n    )\n\n\ndef _direct_select(\n    override: dict, credential_path, today, job_sequence, warnings\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Direct target resolution — Tobias chose, PM validates.\"\"\"\n    target = override[\"direct_target\"]\n    account = target[\"account\"]\n    language = target[\"language\"]\n\n    # Read PUB to get operational state (even for direct, we want warnings)\n    pub = _read_pub_safe(credential_path, today)\n\n    # Find the channel in PUB data (for operational awareness)\n    channel_data = None\n    if pub and not pub.get(\"errors\"):\n        all_channels = pub.get(\"eligible_channels\", []) + [\n            _excluded_to_channel(ex) for ex in pub.get(\"excluded_rows\", [])\n        ]\n        for ch in all_channels:\n            if ch.get(\"account\") == account and ch.get(\"language\") == language:\n                channel_data = ch\n                break\n\n    # Build channel dict for job_builder (from PUB data or minimal)\n    if channel_data:\n        chosen = channel_data\n        # Add operational warnings\n        if not channel_data.get(\"eligible\", True):\n            warnings.append({\n                \"code\": \"target_not_eligible\",\n                \"message\": f\"Direct target {account}/{language} is not eligible in PUB \"\n                           f\"(prod={channel_data.get('prod', '?')}, \"\n                           f\"scripts_remaining={channel_data.get('scripts_remaining', '?')})\",\n            })\n        if channel_data.get(\"scripts_remaining\", 1) <= 0:\n            warnings.append({\n                \"code\": \"target_no_scripts\",\n                \"message\": f\"Direct target {account}/{language} has 0 scripts remaining\",\n            })\n    else:\n        # Channel not found in PUB — try to build from config only\n        try:\n            from runtime.pm.job_builder import _load_channel_config\n            config = _load_channel_config(account, language)\n        except FileNotFoundError:\n            # CRITICAL: direct_select must NOT choose another target\n            return _result(\n                success=False, mode=\"direct_select\",\n                errors=[{\n                    \"code\": \"target_not_found\",\n                    \"message\": f\"Direct target {account}/{language} has no local config\",\n                }],\n                warnings=warnings,\n                reasoning=f\"direct_select: target {account}/{language} cannot be resolved\",\n            )\n\n        chosen = {\n            \"account\": account,\n            \"language\": language,\n            \"channel_name\": config.get(\"channel_name\", f\"C{account} {language.upper()}\"),\n            \"pub_row\": config.get(\"pub_row\"),\n            \"runway_days\": None,\n            \"scripts_remaining\": None,\n            \"reason\": f\"Direct select by {override.get('requested_by', 'unknown')}\",\n        }\n        warnings.append({\n            \"code\": \"target_not_in_pub\",\n            \"message\": f\"Direct target {account}/{language} was not found in PUB data — operational state unknown\",\n        })\n\n    return _build_and_validate(\n        chosen, override, job_sequence, warnings,\n        reasoning=f\"direct_select: target {account}/{language} resolved by {override.get('requested_by', 'unknown')}\",\n        pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\") if pub else None,\n    )\n\n\ndef _build_and_validate(\n    chosen: dict, override: dict, job_sequence: int,\n    warnings: list, reasoning: str, pub_summary: dict = None,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Build and validate job from chosen channel.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        job = build_job(\n            chosen,\n            priority_override=override.get(\"reason\"),\n            job_sequence=job_sequence,\n        )\n    except FileNotFoundError as e:\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=override[\"mode\"],\n            errors=[{\"code\": \"config_not_found\", \"message\": str(e)}],\n            warnings=warnings, reasoning=reasoning,\n            pub_summary=pub_summary,\n        )\n\n    validation = validate_job(job)\n\n    # For direct_select, a validation failure on scripts_remaining is a warning, not a blocker\n    if override[\"mode\"] == \"direct_select\" and not validation[\"valid\"]:\n        non_blocking = all(\n            e[\"code\"] in (\"no_scripts_remaining\",) for e in validation[\"errors\"]\n        )\n        if non_blocking:\n            for e in validation[\"errors\"]:\n                warnings.append({\n                    \"code\": f\"validation_warning_{e['code']}\",\n                    \"message\": e[\"message\"],\n                })\n            validation = {\"valid\": True, \"errors\": []}\n\n    return _result(\n        success=validation[\"valid\"],\n        mode=override[\"mode\"],\n        job=job if validation[\"valid\"] else None,\n        validation=validation,\n        warnings=warnings,\n        reasoning=reasoning,\n        pub_summary=pub_summary,\n    )\n\n\ndef _read_pub_safe(credential_path, today, **kwargs) -> Optional[dict]:\n    \"\"\"Read PUB with error handling.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        return read_pub(credential_path=credential_path, today=today, **kwargs)\n    except Exception:\n        return None\n\n\ndef _excluded_to_channel(excluded: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Convert an excluded_rows entry to a channel-like dict.\"\"\"\n    return {\n        \"account\": excluded.get(\"account\", \"\"),\n        \"language\": excluded.get(\"language\", \"\"),\n        \"channel_name\": excluded.get(\"channel_name\", \"\"),\n        \"pub_row\": excluded.get(\"pub_row\"),\n        \"eligible\": False,\n        \"prod\": excluded.get(\"raw_prod\", \"\"),\n        \"scripts_remaining\": 0,\n        \"runway_days\": None,\n    }\n\n\ndef _describe_constraints(constraints: dict) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Human-readable constraint summary.\"\"\"\n    parts = []\n    for key in (\"allowed_accounts\", \"allowed_languages\", \"excluded_accounts\", \"excluded_languages\"):\n        val = constraints.get(key)\n        if val:\n            parts.append(f\"{key}={val}\")\n    if constraints.get(\"monetized_only\"):\n        parts.append(\"monetized_only=true\")\n    return \", \".join(parts) if parts else \"no active constraints\"\n\n\ndef _result(\n    success: bool, mode: str, job: dict = None, validation: dict = None,\n    warnings: list = None, errors: list = None, reasoning: str = \"\",\n    pub_summary: dict = None,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Build standardized result.\"\"\"\n    return {\n        \"success\": success,\n        \"mode\": mode,\n        \"job\": job,\n        \"validation\": validation,\n        \"selection_reasoning\": reasoning,\n        \"pub_summary\": pub_summary,\n        \"warnings\": warnings or [],\n        \"errors\": errors or [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775048342698}}
{"type":"message","id":"619d75dd","parentId":"60622ff1","timestamp":"2026-04-01T12:59:03.111Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_kE6BYaKUfBXXh6lf0ktook0H|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1695b8e08190b326e47f0edfeb16","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"PM Job Builder — mounts canonical job JSON for the VO.\n\nTakes the chosen channel from read_pub output + local YAML config\nand builds the job artifact with everything the VO needs.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\nimport yaml\n\nACCOUNTS_DIR = Path(__file__).parent.parent.parent / \"accounts\"\n\n\ndef build_job(\n    channel: dict[str, Any],\n    priority_override: Optional[str] = None,\n    job_sequence: int = 1,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Build canonical PM job from chosen channel + local config.\n\n    Args:\n        channel: A single eligible_channel dict from read_pub output.\n        priority_override: Optional override reason (e.g. \"Lucca: so conta 03\").\n        job_sequence: Sequence number for same-day jobs (default 1).\n\n    Returns:\n        Canonical job JSON ready for validation and VO handoff.\n    \"\"\"\n    account = channel[\"account\"]\n    language = channel[\"language\"]\n    today_str = datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n\n    # Load local YAML config\n    config = _load_channel_config(account, language)\n\n    job_id = f\"{today_str}_{account}_{language}_{job_sequence:03d}\"\n\n    return {\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"account\": account,\n        \"language\": language,\n        \"channel_name\": channel.get(\"channel_name\", config.get(\"channel_name\", \"\")),\n        # Sheet/Drive IDs from local config (source of truth for IDs)\n        \"sheet_scripts_id\": config.get(\"sheet_scripts_id\", \"\"),\n        \"sheet_scripts_name\": config.get(\"sheet_scripts_name\", \"\"),\n        \"sheet_tracking_id\": config.get(\"sheet_tracking_id\", \"\"),\n        \"drive_folder_id\": config.get(\"drive_folder_id\", \"\"),\n        \"channel_url\": config.get(\"channel_url\", \"\"),\n        \"v3_config\": config.get(\"v3_config\", \"\"),\n        # PUB state at decision time\n        \"runway_days\": channel.get(\"runway_days\"),\n        \"scripts_remaining\": channel.get(\"scripts_remaining\"),\n        \"reason\": channel.get(\"reason\", \"\"),\n        \"priority_override\": priority_override,\n        # Metadata\n        \"created_at\": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),\n        \"pub_row\": channel.get(\"pub_row\"),\n    }\n\n\ndef _load_channel_config(account: str, language: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Load the YAML config for a specific account/language.\"\"\"\n    config_path = ACCOUNTS_DIR / account / f\"{language}.yaml\"\n    if not config_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(\n            f\"Channel config not found: {config_path}\"\n        )\n    with open(config_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        return yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775048342886}}
{"type":"message","id":"5a8dedec","parentId":"619d75dd","timestamp":"2026-04-01T12:59:03.296Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_GEprW2y8qaZNmFFlyEMrr1vv|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1695b8ec8190bb46fb023e0bc4b8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"VO Job Input Validator — validates PM job from VO perspective.\n\nIf validation fails, VO must NOT create any run directory.\nReturns structured errors for debugging.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\n# Fields that must exist and be non-empty strings\nREQUIRED_STRING_FIELDS = [\n    \"job_id\",\n    \"account\",\n    \"language\",\n    \"channel_name\",\n    \"sheet_scripts_id\",\n    \"sheet_tracking_id\",\n    \"drive_folder_id\",\n    \"v3_config\",\n    \"created_at\",\n]\n\n# All required fields (pub_row can be int or None)\nREQUIRED_FIELDS = REQUIRED_STRING_FIELDS + [\"pub_row\"]\n\n\ndef validate_job_input(job: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Validate a PM job as VO input.\n\n    Returns:\n        {\n            \"valid\": bool,\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": str, \"field\": str, \"message\": str}, ...]\n        }\n    \"\"\"\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    # Check required fields exist\n    for field in REQUIRED_FIELDS:\n        if field not in job:\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_field\",\n                \"field\": field,\n                \"message\": f\"Required field '{field}' is missing\",\n            })\n\n    # If critical fields missing, return early\n    if errors:\n        return {\"valid\": False, \"errors\": errors}\n\n    # Check required string fields are non-empty strings\n    for field in REQUIRED_STRING_FIELDS:\n        val = job.get(field)\n        if not isinstance(val, str) or not val.strip():\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"empty_or_invalid_type\",\n                \"field\": field,\n                \"message\": f\"Field '{field}' must be a non-empty string, got: {type(val).__name__}={val!r}\",\n            })\n\n    # pub_row type check (must be int if present, can be None)\n    pub_row = job.get(\"pub_row\")\n    if pub_row is not None and not isinstance(pub_row, int):\n        errors.append({\n            \"code\": \"invalid_type\",\n            \"field\": \"pub_row\",\n            \"message\": f\"pub_row must be int or None, got: {type(pub_row).__name__}\",\n        })\n\n    return {\n        \"valid\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775048343112}}
{"type":"message","id":"51e2415b","parentId":"5a8dedec","timestamp":"2026-04-01T12:59:13.043Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_O4jri3C8knfQmCqyR6JsqEZ7|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd16a25f8c819092edea98c58c5ccc","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\script_fetch_and_lock.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\vo\\\\script_fetch_and_lock.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ZaXDoyVZch4uuouw1Da3bgp6|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd16a25f9c8190959f666636b7a251","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm\\read_pub.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\pm\\\\read_pub.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c1q7Sf9AtQlNTYPKLlCcEiOp|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd16a25fe88190b3bcbc1517af57b4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm_override_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm_override_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_pPSG2bCvRIRa7pQEMuc80HGM|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd16a25ff081909a0058338d897ef8","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm_read_pub_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm_read_pub_contract.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":115027,"output":173,"cacheRead":24064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":139264,"cost":{"input":0.28756750000000003,"output":0.002595,"cacheRead":0.006016,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.29617850000000007}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775048343990,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd169a144c81908d1fd97a410ee5ef"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6dd8d81b","parentId":"51e2415b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T12:59:14.518Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_O4jri3C8knfQmCqyR6JsqEZ7|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd16a25f8c819092edea98c58c5ccc","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"VO Script Fetch and Lock — orchestrates fetch + lock + persist.\n\nReceives an initialized run, fetches the next eligible script from\nthe scripts sheet, locks it, and persists everything locally.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\n\nfrom runtime.vo.script_fetcher import fetch_eligible_script\nfrom runtime.vo.script_locker import lock_script_row\nfrom runtime.vo.script_metadata_writer import write_script_artifacts\nfrom runtime.vo.script_checkpoint_writer import write_script_checkpoint\n\n\ndef fetch_and_lock_script(\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    video_root: str | Path,\n    credential_path: Optional[Path] = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Fetch next eligible script, lock it, persist locally.\n\n    Args:\n        job: Validated PM job dict.\n        video_root: Path to the initialized run directory.\n        credential_path: Optional SA credential path override.\n\n    Returns:\n        Structured result with success, paths, next_step.\n    \"\"\"\n    video_root = Path(video_root)\n    job_id = job.get(\"job_id\", \"\")\n    sheet_id = job.get(\"sheet_scripts_id\", \"\")\n    sheet_name = job.get(\"sheet_scripts_name\", \"\")\n\n    # Step 1: Fetch eligible script\n    try:\n        script_data = fetch_eligible_script(\n            sheet_scripts_id=sheet_id,\n            sheet_scripts_name=sheet_name,\n            credential_path=credential_path,\n        )\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _error_result(job_id, f\"Script fetch failed: {e}\")\n\n    if not script_data.get(\"found\"):\n        return _error_result(\n            job_id,\n            f\"No eligible scripts (Status='to do') in sheet {sheet_id}/{sheet_name}\",\n            code=\"no_eligible_scripts\",\n        )\n\n    # Step 2: Lock the script row in the sheet\n    try:\n        lock_data = lock_script_row(\n            sheet_scripts_id=sheet_id,\n            sheet_scripts_name=sheet_name,\n            row_number=script_data[\"row_number\"],\n            credential_path=credential_path,\n        )\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _error_result(job_id, f\"Script lock failed: {e}\")\n\n    if not lock_data.get(\"locked\"):\n        return _error_result(\n            job_id,\n            f\"Could not lock script row {script_data['row_number']}: {lock_data.get('error', 'unknown')}\",\n            code=\"lock_failed\",\n        )\n\n    # Step 3: Persist script artifacts locally\n    try:\n        paths = write_script_artifacts(\n            video_root=video_root,\n            job=job,\n            script_data=script_data,\n            lock_data=lock_data,\n        )\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _error_result(job_id, f\"Could not write script artifacts: {e}\")\n\n    # Step 4: Write checkpoint (only after everything succeeded)\n    try:\n        checkpoint_path = write_script_checkpoint(\n            video_root=video_root,\n            job=job,\n            script_data=script_data,\n            paths=paths,\n        )\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _error_result(job_id, f\"Could not write checkpoint: {e}\")\n\n    paths[\"checkpoint_path\"] = checkpoint_path\n\n    return {\n        \"success\": True,\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"status\": \"script_ready\",\n        \"current_stage\": \"vo_script_fetch\",\n        \"script_row\": script_data[\"row_number\"],\n        \"title\": script_data.get(\"title\", \"\"),\n        \"script_path\": paths[\"script_path\"],\n        \"metadata_path\": paths[\"metadata_path\"],\n        \"lock_path\": paths[\"lock_path\"],\n        \"checkpoint_path\": checkpoint_path,\n        \"next_step\": \"ready_for_s1\",\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n\n\ndef _error_result(job_id: str, message: str, code: str = \"script_fetch_error\") -> dict:\n    return {\n        \"success\": False,\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"status\": \"failed\",\n        \"current_stage\": \"vo_script_fetch\",\n        \"script_row\": None,\n        \"title\": \"\",\n        \"script_path\": \"\",\n        \"metadata_path\": \"\",\n        \"lock_path\": \"\",\n        \"checkpoint_path\": \"\",\n        \"next_step\": None,\n        \"errors\": [{\"code\": code, \"message\": message}],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775048354343}}
{"type":"message","id":"d9f3504b","parentId":"6dd8d81b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T12:59:14.697Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ZaXDoyVZch4uuouw1Da3bgp6|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd16a25f9c8190959f666636b7a251","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"PM read_pub -- reads PUB sheet, normalizes, filters, ranks.\n\nFollows the contract in docs/contracts/pm_read_pub_contract.md.\nDoes NOT create the job artifact (that's job_builder).\nDoes NOT apply complex NL overrides.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom datetime import date, datetime, timezone\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Optional\nimport yaml\n\nfrom runtime.integrations.google_sheets import GoogleSheetsClient\nfrom runtime.pm.pub_row_normalizer import normalize_pub_row\n\n\n# Defaults from contract\nDEFAULT_SHEET_ID = \"1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc\"\nDEFAULT_TAB = \"PUB\"\nACCOUNTS_DIR = Path(__file__).parent.parent.parent / \"accounts\"\n\n\ndef read_pub(\n    credential_path: Optional[Path] = None,\n    sheet_id: str = DEFAULT_SHEET_ID,\n    tab_name: str = DEFAULT_TAB,\n    today: Optional[date] = None,\n    allowed_accounts: Optional[list[str]] = None,\n    allowed_languages: Optional[list[str]] = None,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Read PUB sheet, normalize, filter eligible, rank by runway.\n\n    Returns:\n        Contract-compliant dict with eligible_channels, excluded_rows, errors.\n    \"\"\"\n    if today is None:\n        today = date.today()\n\n    errors: list[dict] = []\n\n    # Load channel configs from registry + individual YAMLs\n    try:\n        channels = _load_channel_configs()\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _fatal_error(\"registry_load_failed\", str(e))\n\n    # Read PUB sheet\n    try:\n        client = GoogleSheetsClient(credential_path=credential_path)\n        raw_rows = client.read_worksheet_raw(sheet_id, tab_name)\n    except FileNotFoundError as e:\n        return _fatal_error(\"credential_missing\", str(e))\n    except ValueError as e:\n        return _fatal_error(\"sheet_not_found\", str(e))\n    except ConnectionError as e:\n        return _fatal_error(\"api_error\", str(e))\n    except Exception as e:\n        return _fatal_error(\"unexpected_error\", str(e))\n\n    # Normalize each channel's row\n    eligible_channels = []\n    excluded_rows = []\n\n    for ch in channels:\n        pub_row = ch[\"pub_row\"]\n\n        # Apply filters\n        if allowed_accounts and ch[\"account\"] not in allowed_accounts:\n            excluded_rows.append({\n                \"pub_row\": pub_row,\n                \"account\": ch[\"account\"],\n                \"language\": ch[\"language\"],\n                \"excluded_reason\": f\"Account {ch['account']} not in allowed_accounts filter\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        if allowed_languages and ch[\"language\"] not in allowed_languages:\n            excluded_rows.append({\n                \"pub_row\": pub_row,\n                \"account\": ch[\"account\"],\n                \"language\": ch[\"language\"],\n                \"excluded_reason\": f\"Language {ch['language']} not in allowed_languages filter\",\n            })\n            continue\n\n        # Get row values (1-indexed in sheet, 0-indexed in list)\n        if pub_row > len(raw_rows):\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"row_out_of_range\",\n                \"message\": f\"Row {pub_row} does not exist in sheet ({len(raw_rows)} rows total)\",\n                \"scope\": \"row\",\n                \"pub_row\": pub_row,\n            })\n            continue\n\n        row_values = raw_rows[pub_row - 1]  # Convert to 0-indexed\n\n        # Normalize\n        normalized = normalize_pub_row(\n            row_values=row_values,\n            pub_row=pub_row,\n            account=ch[\"account\"],\n            language=ch[\"language\"],\n            channel_name=ch[\"channel_name\"],\n            today=today,\n        )\n\n        if normalized[\"eligible\"]:\n            eligible_channels.append(normalized)\n        else:\n            reason = \"Not eligible\"\n            if normalized[\"prod\"] != \"SIM\":\n                reason = \"PROD != SIM\"\n            elif normalized[\"scripts_remaining\"] <= 0:\n                reason = \"No scripts remaining\"\n            elif normalized[\"normalization_errors\"]:\n                reason = \"; \".join(normalized[\"normalization_errors\"])\n\n            excluded_rows.append({\n                \"pub_row\": pub_row,\n                \"account\": ch[\"account\"],\n                \"language\": ch[\"language\"],\n                \"channel_name\": ch[\"channel_name\"],\n                \"excluded_reason\": reason,\n                \"raw_prod\": normalized[\"prod\"],\n                \"raw_scripts\": normalized[\"scripts_raw\"],\n            })\n\n    # Sort eligible by runway (lowest first), then by account number\n    eligible_channels.sort(\n        key=lambda c: (c[\"runway_days\"], c[\"account\"], c[\"language\"])\n    )\n\n    # Add reason field to eligible channels\n    for ch in eligible_channels:\n        ch[\"reason\"] = (\n            f\"PROD=SIM, scripts_remaining={ch['scripts_remaining']}, \"\n            f\"runway={ch['runway_days']}\"\n        )\n\n    return {\n        \"source\": {\n            \"sheet_id\": sheet_id,\n            \"tab_name\": tab_name,\n            \"read_at\": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),\n        },\n        \"today\": today.isoformat(),\n        \"eligible_channels\": eligible_channels,\n        \"excluded_rows\": excluded_rows,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n        \"summary\": {\n            \"total_channels_configured\": len(channels),\n            \"eligible\": len(eligible_channels),\n            \"excluded\": len(excluded_rows),\n            \"errors\": len(errors),\n        },\n    }\n\n\ndef _load_channel_configs() -> list[dict]:\n    \"\"\"Load all channel configs from registry + individual YAMLs.\"\"\"\n    registry_path = ACCOUNTS_DIR / \"registry.yaml\"\n    if not registry_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Registry not found: {registry_path}\")\n\n    with open(registry_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        registry = yaml.safe_load(f)\n\n    channels = []\n    for entry in registry.get(\"channels\", []):\n        config_path = ACCOUNTS_DIR / entry[\"config\"]\n        if not config_path.exists():\n            continue\n\n        with open(config_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n            cfg = yaml.safe_load(f)\n\n        channels.append({\n            \"account\": str(cfg.get(\"account\", \"\")),\n            \"language\": cfg.get(\"language\", \"\"),\n            \"channel_name\": cfg.get(\"channel_name\", \"\"),\n            \"pub_row\": cfg.get(\"pub_row\"),\n            \"config_path\": str(config_path),\n            \"sheet_scripts_id\": cfg.get(\"sheet_scripts_id\", \"\"),\n            \"sheet_scripts_name\": cfg.get(\"sheet_scripts_name\", \"\"),\n            \"sheet_tracking_id\": cfg.get(\"sheet_tracking_id\", \"\"),\n            \"drive_folder_id\": cfg.get(\"drive_folder_id\", \"\"),\n            \"channel_url\": cfg.get(\"channel_url\", \"\"),\n            \"v3_config\": cfg.get(\"v3_config\", \"\"),\n        })\n\n    # Filter out channels without pub_row\n    channels = [c for c in channels if c.get(\"pub_row\") is not None]\n\n    return channels\n\n\ndef _fatal_error(code: str, message: str) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Build a fatal error response.\"\"\"\n    return {\n        \"source\": {\"sheet_id\": \"\", \"tab_name\": \"\", \"read_at\": \"\"},\n        \"today\": \"\",\n        \"eligible_channels\": [],\n        \"excluded_rows\": [],\n        \"errors\": [{\n            \"code\": code,\n            \"message\": message,\n            \"scope\": \"fatal\",\n        }],\n        \"summary\": {\n            \"total_channels_configured\": 0,\n            \"eligible\": 0,\n            \"excluded\": 0,\n            \"errors\": 1,\n        },\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775048354518}}
{"type":"message","id":"da2fc93c","parentId":"d9f3504b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T12:59:14.891Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_c1q7Sf9AtQlNTYPKLlCcEiOp|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd16a25fe88190b3bcbc1517af57b4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PM Override Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines how Tobias constrains or directs the Production Manager's selection behavior._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis contract defines the upstream override layer for the Production Manager (PM).\n\nThe PM should not treat PUB/runway as the absolute sovereign decision source.\nPUB is the operational state input. Final production intent can be constrained or directed by Tobias.\n\nThis contract exists to make that explicit and implementation-safe.\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### PUB is operational truth, not strategic sovereignty\n\nThe PM uses PUB to understand production reality:\n- which channels are active\n- how many scripts remain\n- how much runway each channel has\n- which channels are operationally urgent\n\nBut Tobias remains the higher-level decision layer.\n\nThat means the PM must support three operating modes:\n1. `auto_select`\n2. `filtered_select`\n3. `direct_select`\n\n---\n\n## Operating modes\n\n## 1. `auto_select`\n\n### Meaning\nThe PM is asked to choose the best production target using its normal operational logic.\n\n### Behavior\n- read PUB\n- normalize rows\n- filter eligible channels\n- compute runway\n- sort by urgency\n- choose the top candidate using the default prioritization rules\n\n### When to use\nUse this when Tobias says things like:\n- \"escolhe o mais urgente\"\n- \"decide o próximo vídeo\"\n- \"vê o que deve entrar em produção\"\n\n### Decision authority\nPM decides within its normal rules.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `filtered_select`\n\n### Meaning\nThe PM must still choose using PUB/runway logic, but only inside a constrained subset imposed by Tobias.\n\n### Behavior\n- read PUB\n- normalize rows\n- apply upstream constraints first\n- compute runway only within the allowed subset\n- choose the best candidate inside that subset\n\n### Example constraints\n- allowed accounts only\n- allowed languages only\n- excluded accounts\n- excluded languages\n- monetized channels only\n- specific strategic cohort only\n\n### When to use\nUse this when Tobias says things like:\n- \"só conta 03 hoje\"\n- \"prioriza 05 en e 03 fr\"\n- \"foca só monetizados\"\n- \"ignora os canais X e Y\"\n\n### Decision authority\nTobias defines the selection frame.\nPM decides inside that frame.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `direct_select`\n\n### Meaning\nThe PM is not being asked to choose strategically.\nIt is being asked to materialize and validate a direct production target.\n\n### Behavior\n- resolve the requested account/language directly\n- validate that the target exists\n- validate that the target is still operationally viable if possible\n- build the canonical PM job for that target\n- report relevant warnings if the direct target is unusual or operationally weak\n\n### When to use\nUse this when Tobias says things like:\n- \"produz 003 fr\"\n- \"faz 005 en agora\"\n- \"quero este canal específico\"\n\n### Decision authority\nTobias decides the target.\nPM validates and materializes it.\n\n---\n\n## Priority order\n\nIf override information exists, the PM should resolve authority in this order:\n\n1. `direct_select`\n2. `filtered_select`\n3. `auto_select`\n\nThat means:\n- a direct order beats a filtered order\n- a filtered order beats default runway autonomy\n\n---\n\n## Contract shape\n\nThe override layer should be represented as a structured object before final PM selection runs.\n\n### Suggested shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"auto_select\",\n  \"reason\": \"Default PM selection\",\n  \"constraints\": null,\n  \"direct_target\": null,\n  \"requested_by\": \"tobias\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T12:00:00-03:00\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## `auto_select` shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"auto_select\",\n  \"reason\": \"Choose the most urgent channel by runway\",\n  \"constraints\": null,\n  \"direct_target\": null,\n  \"requested_by\": \"tobias\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T12:00:00-03:00\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## `filtered_select` shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"filtered_select\",\n  \"reason\": \"Focus production on account 003 today\",\n  \"constraints\": {\n    \"allowed_accounts\": [\"003\"],\n    \"allowed_languages\": null,\n    \"excluded_accounts\": null,\n    \"excluded_languages\": null,\n    \"monetized_only\": false\n  },\n  \"direct_target\": null,\n  \"requested_by\": \"tobias\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T12:00:00-03:00\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## `direct_select` shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"direct_select\",\n  \"reason\": \"Lucca requested specific production target\",\n  \"constraints\": null,\n  \"direct_target\": {\n    \"account\": \"003\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"requested_by\": \"tobias\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T12:00:00-03:00\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Expected PM behavior by mode\n\n### In `auto_select`\nThe PM should return:\n- top candidate\n- supporting ranked list if useful\n- operational reasoning based on runway\n\n### In `filtered_select`\nThe PM should return:\n- best candidate inside constraints\n- explanation of applied filters\n- warning if the filtered pool is empty\n\n### In `direct_select`\nThe PM should return:\n- the requested target if valid\n- warnings if the target has no scripts / invalid config / inactive production / bad mapping\n- failure if the target cannot be resolved safely\n\n---\n\n## Validation rules\n\n### General\nEvery override object should validate:\n- supported `mode`\n- valid shape for that mode\n- no conflicting mode payloads\n- timestamps and metadata well-formed where required\n\n### `filtered_select`\n- reject malformed account/language lists\n- reject empty constraints if mode is `filtered_select`\n- allow future expansion of constraints without breaking current structure\n\n### `direct_select`\n- require `account`\n- require `language`\n- reject missing direct target\n\n---\n\n## Failure behavior\n\n### `auto_select`\nIf PUB cannot be read, PM fails normally.\n\n### `filtered_select`\nIf the constraints produce zero eligible candidates:\n- PM should fail clearly or return no selection with structured reason\n- PM must not silently fall back to unrestricted `auto_select`\n\n### `direct_select`\nIf the requested target is invalid/unresolvable:\n- PM should fail explicitly\n- PM must not silently choose another channel\n\nThis rule is critical.\nA direct order must never degrade into \"I picked something else\" without explicit Tobias approval.\n\n---\n\n## Non-goals for v1\n\nThis contract does not yet define:\n- natural-language parsing of overrides\n- persistence lifetime / expiry of overrides\n- multi-step campaign scheduling\n- weighted strategic scoring beyond simple mode selection\n- direct Lucca-to-PM conversation protocol\n\nThose can be added later.\n\n---\n\n## Recommended implementation split\n\nLikely implementation pieces:\n- `runtime/pm/override_parser.py` (later)\n- `runtime/pm/selection_engine.py` or equivalent mode-aware selection layer\n- integration with existing `read_pub`, `job_builder`, and `job_validator`\n\nFor now, the important thing is that the PM substrate and future VO work do not assume runway autonomy is the only valid operating model.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775048354698}}
{"type":"message","id":"50eff899","parentId":"da2fc93c","timestamp":"2026-04-01T12:59:15.120Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_pPSG2bCvRIRa7pQEMuc80HGM|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd16a25ff081909a0058338d897ef8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PM `read_pub` Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft based on current PM documentation. This is a contract draft for implementation, not a claim that all operational choices are fully frozen._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n`read_pub` is the Production Manager's deterministic ingestion layer for the canonical PUB spreadsheet.\n\nIts job is to:\n- authenticate with the canonical Google service account\n- read the `PUB` tab from the canonical spreadsheet\n- normalize the rows relevant to production prioritization\n- filter out channels that are not eligible for production\n- compute runway per eligible channel\n- return a stable, machine-consumable structure for PM decision-making\n\n`read_pub` does **not**:\n- choose the final production target on its own if an explicit direct order was given upstream\n- generate the PM -> VO job artifact\n- apply complex business overrides beyond the explicitly supported filter contract\n- mutate Sheets or Drive\n\n---\n\n## Canonical source\n\n### Spreadsheet\n- **Sheet ID**: `1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc`\n- **Tab**: `PUB`\n\n### Credentials\n- **Credential model**: Google service account\n- **Canonical credential path**: `C:\\secrets\\content_factory\\google_service_account.json`\n\n### Dependencies\n- Google Sheets API must be enabled\n- The service account must have at least read access to the canonical spreadsheet\n\n---\n\n## Inputs\n\n### Required runtime inputs\n1. `credential_path`\n   - default canonical value: `C:\\secrets\\content_factory\\google_service_account.json`\n2. `sheet_id`\n   - default canonical value: `1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc`\n3. `tab_name`\n   - default canonical value: `PUB`\n4. `today`\n   - ISO date or runtime-local current date used to compute runway\n\n### Optional runtime inputs\n5. `allowed_accounts`\n   - list of account IDs to restrict evaluation\n6. `allowed_languages`\n   - list of languages to restrict evaluation\n7. `pub_row_subset`\n   - optional row subset for testing/debugging\n8. `override_filter`\n   - structured upstream filter contract, if already resolved by PM/override parser\n\n---\n\n## Required columns from PUB\n\nThe current PM documentation defines these columns as the minimum required fields:\n\n| Column | Header | Meaning |\n|--------|--------|---------|\n| B | `ULT PUB` | Date of last already-scheduled publication |\n| F | `PROGRAMAR` | Videos ready but not yet uploaded/scheduled |\n| J | `PROD` | Whether production is active for the channel (`SIM` / `NÃO`) |\n| O | `SCRIPTS` | Script usage in `used/total` format |\n\n### Additional identification data\n`read_pub` must also retain enough row identity to map a row to:\n- `pub_row`\n- `account`\n- `language`\n- `channel_name`\n\nThe current contract assumes those mappings are resolved via the local account registry and/or documented row mapping already defined by PM docs.\n\n---\n\n## Eligibility rules\n\nA row is eligible for PM prioritization only if all of the following are true:\n\n1. `PROD = SIM`\n2. `scripts_remaining > 0`\n3. the row can be mapped to a valid local account/language/config entry\n4. required fields for runway calculation can be parsed successfully\n\nRows that fail any of the above must not be included in the eligible result set.\n\nThey should instead be returned in a structured `excluded_rows` or `errors` section.\n\n---\n\n## Parsing and normalization rules\n\n### `ULT PUB`\n- Expected format: date value representing the last scheduled publication date\n- Minimum v1 behavior:\n  - parse documented date format reliably\n  - normalize to ISO date in output\n- If unparsable:\n  - mark row invalid\n  - exclude from eligible set\n  - emit structured error\n\n### `PROGRAMAR`\n- Expected semantic: integer count of already-produced but not-yet-scheduled videos\n- Normalize to integer\n- If missing or invalid:\n  - mark row invalid\n  - exclude from eligible set\n  - emit structured error\n\n### `PROD`\n- Expected semantic: active production flag\n- Minimum supported positive value in v1: `SIM`\n- Any non-`SIM` value is treated as inactive\n\n### `SCRIPTS`\n- Expected format: `used/total`, e.g. `38/57`\n- Parse into:\n  - `scripts_used`\n  - `scripts_total`\n  - `scripts_remaining = scripts_total - scripts_used`\n- If malformed:\n  - mark row invalid\n  - exclude from eligible set\n  - emit structured error\n\n---\n\n## Runway calculation\n\nCanonical formula from PM documentation:\n\n```text\nrunway_days = PROGRAMAR + days_until_last_scheduled_publication\n```\n\nWhere:\n- `PROGRAMAR` = count from column F\n- `days_until_last_scheduled_publication = ULT_PUB - today`\n\n### Notes\n- Negative runway is valid and indicates urgency/deficit\n- Zero runway is valid\n- Higher runway means more content buffer\n- Lower runway means higher urgency\n\n---\n\n## Sorting / prioritization output\n\nFor the base `read_pub` contract, the output list should be sorted by:\n\n1. lowest `runway_days`\n2. lower account number as tiebreaker, based on current PM documentation\n\n### Important boundary\n`read_pub` should compute and sort.\nFinal PM decision logic that applies richer overrides may happen one layer above unless explicitly folded into this skill later.\n\n---\n\n## Output contract\n\nThe primary output should be a stable JSON-serializable structure.\n\n### Suggested top-level shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"source\": {\n    \"sheet_id\": \"1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc\",\n    \"tab_name\": \"PUB\",\n    \"read_at\": \"2026-03-30T11:00:00-03:00\"\n  },\n  \"eligible_channels\": [],\n  \"excluded_rows\": [],\n  \"errors\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Required fields for each eligible channel\n\n```json\n{\n  \"pub_row\": 16,\n  \"account\": \"003\",\n  \"language\": \"fr\",\n  \"channel_name\": \"C003 FRA\",\n  \"ult_pub_raw\": \"27/03/2026\",\n  \"ult_pub_iso\": \"2026-03-27\",\n  \"programar\": 0,\n  \"prod\": \"SIM\",\n  \"scripts_raw\": \"38/57\",\n  \"scripts_used\": 38,\n  \"scripts_total\": 57,\n  \"scripts_remaining\": 19,\n  \"runway_days\": 1,\n  \"eligible\": true,\n  \"reason\": \"PROD=SIM, scripts_remaining>0, runway=1\"\n}\n```\n\n### Required fields for excluded rows\nAt minimum:\n- `pub_row`\n- row identity if available\n- `excluded_reason`\n- `raw_values` or safe debugging fields when useful\n\n### Required fields for errors\nAt minimum:\n- `code`\n- `message`\n- `scope` (`sheet`, `row`, `auth`, `parse`, etc.)\n- `pub_row` when applicable\n\n---\n\n## Error handling\n\n### Fatal errors\nThese should fail the whole call:\n- credential file missing\n- credential file unreadable\n- authentication failure\n- spreadsheet not found\n- tab not found\n- Google API unavailable for the whole request\n\n### Row-level errors\nThese should not fail the entire call if partial read is still meaningful:\n- invalid date in `ULT PUB`\n- malformed `SCRIPTS`\n- invalid `PROGRAMAR`\n- unmapped row/account/language\n\n### Partial success rule\nIf the sheet is readable and at least one valid eligible row exists, `read_pub` may return partial success with row-level errors attached.\n\n---\n\n## Non-goals for v1\n\nThe following are intentionally outside the initial `read_pub` contract unless later promoted:\n- caching / snapshot fallback\n- write-back to Sheets\n- direct job creation\n- script locking\n- advanced override semantics in natural language\n- historical analytics / trend reporting\n\n---\n\n## Open questions to confirm later\n\nThese are not frozen by this v1 contract:\n\n1. What is the final source of truth if PUB and local YAML diverge?\n2. Should `read_pub` support cache/last-known-good snapshot on API failure?\n3. What exact upstream component resolves natural-language overrides into structured filters?\n4. What exact row/account/language mapping logic should be canonical if the sheet identity layer is ambiguous?\n5. Should inactive/malformed rows be returned with full debug payloads or only sanitized summaries?\n\n---\n\n## Recommended implementation split\n\nTo keep responsibilities clean, implementation should likely be split into:\n\n- `runtime/integrations/google_sheets.py`\n- `runtime/pm/read_pub.py`\n- `runtime/pm/pub_row_normalizer.py`\n- `runtime/pm/job_builder.py`\n- `runtime/pm/job_validator.py`\n\n`read_pub` should remain the deterministic ingestion layer, not absorb the whole PM.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775048354893}}
{"type":"message","id":"0965f599","parentId":"50eff899","timestamp":"2026-04-01T12:59:53.802Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Sim — lembro onde paramos, e já fiz a primeira verificação real.\n\nVou-te dar o diagnóstico **bem executivo** e separado nas 4 camadas que combinámos:\n\n- contracts\n- runtime/implementação\n- workspace OpenClaw\n- registry/agent reality\n\n---\n\n# Diagnóstico executivo\n\n## PM\n\n### 1. Contracts\n**Existe alguma base, mas está incompleta.**\n\nEncontrei contracts para PM:\n- `docs/contracts/pm_override_contract.md`\n- `docs/contracts/pm_read_pub_contract.md`\n\n### O que isso cobre bem\n- leitura da PUB sheet\n- modos do PM:\n  - `auto_select`\n  - `filtered_select`\n  - `direct_select`\n- regra de autoridade do override\n- boundary entre PUB como verdade operacional vs Tobias como camada estratégica\n\n### O que ainda não encontrei\nNão encontrei, pelo menos nesta primeira passada:\n- um **PM supervisor contract canónico completo**\n- um contrato claro do **handoff PM -> VO**\n- um contract dedicado de “PM as OpenClaw agent”\n\n### Leitura\nO PM está **mais maduro em contrato do que o VO**, mas ainda parece estar numa fase:\n> “substrate determinístico + rules fortes”, não ainda “agent OpenClaw fully aterrado”\n\n---\n\n### 2. Runtime / implementação\n**Existe bastante substrate determinístico.**\n\nEncontrei em `runtime/pm/`:\n- `read_pub.py`\n- `pub_row_normalizer.py`\n- `selection_engine.py`\n- `override_validator.py`\n- `job_builder.py`\n- `job_validator.py`\n\n### O que isso significa\nO PM já tem:\n- ingestão real da PUB\n- normalização\n- filtragem\n- seleção por modos\n- construção de job\n- validação do job\n\n### Leitura honesta\nIsto é **bom e útil**.  \nMas ainda parece um PM como **motor determinístico/orquestrador parcial**, não como **agent OpenClaw real com workspace próprio**.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Workspace OpenClaw\n**Não existe ainda, pelo que verifiquei agora.**\n\nNa pasta:\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents`\n\nnão encontrei nada como:\n- `pm`\n- `sm_pm`\n- `production_manager`\n\nSó existem os agents do S1 e o `main`.\n\n### Conclusão\nPM **ainda não tem workspace OpenClaw real**.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Registry / agent reality\nTambém confirmei com:\n\n- `openclaw agents list`\n\nE **não existe PM registado como agent**.\n\n### Conclusão final sobre PM\nO PM está assim:\n\n#### Forte em:\n- contracts parciais relevantes\n- substrate determinístico útil\n- lógica operacional real de seleção e montagem de job\n\n#### Fraco / faltando:\n- workspace OpenClaw\n- agent id real\n- identidade operacional canónica como supervisor/agent\n- wiring explícito PM -> VO dentro do mundo OpenClaw\n\n---\n\n# VO\n\n## 1. Contracts\n**Muito mais fraco em documentação contratual explícita.**\n\nNa primeira verificação, eu **não encontrei contracts de VO** equivalentes aos do PM.\n\nIsso já é um sinal importante.\n\n### Leitura\nO VO parece estar mais:\n- implementado no runtime\n- menos formalizado em contracts\n\n---\n\n## 2. Runtime / implementação\n**Existe substrate concreto e relativamente sólido.**\n\nEncontrei em `runtime/vo/`:\n- `vo_start.py`\n- `job_input_validator.py`\n- `video_dir_initializer.py`\n- `run_metadata_writer.py`\n- `checkpoint_initializer.py`\n- `script_fetcher.py`\n- `script_locker.py`\n- `script_metadata_writer.py`\n- `script_checkpoint_writer.py`\n- `script_fetch_and_lock.py`\n\n### O que isso mostra\nO VO já sabe fazer bastante coisa real:\n- validar job vindo do PM\n- criar run root\n- escrever `job.json`\n- escrever `run_metadata.json`\n- criar checkpoint inicial\n- ir buscar script\n- lockar script\n- persistir artefactos locais\n- escrever `vo_script_ready`\n\n### Em termos de pipeline\nIsto é importante:\no VO já parece ser a camada que prepara exactamente os artefactos que o S1 espera receber depois.\n\n### Leitura honesta\nO VO está **operacionalmente promissor**, talvez até mais “pipeline-real” que o PM.  \nMas continua a parecer um **runtime Python funcional**, não ainda um **agent OpenClaw aterrado**.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Workspace OpenClaw\n**Não existe ainda.**\n\nTal como no PM, não há nada em:\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents`\n\nque pareça:\n- `vo`\n- `sm_vo`\n- `video_orchestrator`\n\n### Conclusão\nVO **ainda não tem workspace OpenClaw real**.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Registry / agent reality\nTambém não apareceu nenhum VO em:\n\n- `openclaw agents list`\n\n### Conclusão final sobre VO\nO VO está assim:\n\n#### Forte em:\n- runtime Python concreto\n- handoff material para preparar o terreno do S1\n- artefactos/run bootstrap com forma relativamente clara\n\n#### Fraco / faltando:\n- contracts dedicados claros\n- workspace OpenClaw\n- agent id real\n- identidade operacional canónica como agent/supervisor OpenClaw\n\n---\n\n# Gaps principais\n\n## PM — gaps\n1. **falta virar agent OpenClaw real**\n2. falta workspace próprio\n3. falta definição canónica de identidade/autoridade do PM no OpenClaw\n4. falta contract claro do handoff PM -> VO\n5. falta registry/configuração real em `openclaw agents`\n\n## VO — gaps\n1. **falta virar agent OpenClaw real**\n2. falta workspace próprio\n3. falta contract dedicado de VO\n4. falta clarificação do papel exacto:\n   - VO como supervisor?\n   - VO como bootstrap operator?\n   - VO como runtime agent intermédio?\n5. falta registry/configuração real em `openclaw agents`\n\n---\n\n# Minha leitura estratégica\n## PM\nEstá mais maduro em **governança e lógica de decisão**.\n\n## VO\nEstá mais maduro em **execução operacional concreta do run**.\n\n## Os dois\nNenhum dos dois ainda está “encarnado” no OpenClaw como o S1 já está.\n\n---\n\n# Próximo passo recomendado\n\n## Ordem mais inteligente\nEu recomendo esta sequência exacta:\n\n### 1. PM primeiro — mas só no nível estrutural\nPorque o PM é upstream e define o job.\n\nFazer:\n- definir/confirmar contrato canónico do PM como agent\n- mapear identidade, inputs, outputs e autoridade\n- criar workspace OpenClaw do PM\n- configurar modelo `gpt-5.4-mini`\n\n### 2. VO logo depois\nPorque o VO é a ponte operacional real entre PM e S1.\n\nFazer:\n- definir/confirmar contrato canónico do VO\n- clarificar inputs/outputs do VO\n- criar workspace OpenClaw do VO\n- configurar modelo `gpt-5.4-mini`\n\n### 3. Só depois wiring integrado\n- PM gera/valida job\n- VO consome job e cria run\n- VO prepara script e `vo_script_ready`\n- S1 entra\n\n---\n\n# Em uma frase\n## Estado actual:\n- **PM e VO têm substrate útil**\n- **PM e VO ainda não são agents OpenClaw reais**\n- **o missing link agora não é lógica base, é encarnação operacional no OpenClaw + handoff explícito**\n\n---\n\n# Recomendação operacional imediata\nSe concordares, o passo certo agora é:\n\n## Fase seguinte\n**desenhar primeiro o contrato/identidade canónica do PM como agent OpenClaw**,  \nporque isso vai dar a peça upstream certa antes de aterrarmos o VO.\n\nSe quiser, eu sigo já com isso e te entrego:\n- **PM agent blueprint**\n- depois **VO agent blueprint**\n- e só então vamos para criação real dos workspaces.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169cd16a939948190a18f3211acde58fa\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":112153,"output":1720,"cacheRead":27136,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":141009,"cost":{"input":0.28038250000000003,"output":0.0258,"cacheRead":0.006784,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.31296650000000004}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775048355838,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd16a5f14481909f9e92aef6140823"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6944359a","parentId":"0965f599","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:04:08.145Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-04-01 10:04 GMT-3] fechado, também temos que oprganizar os contracts em subdiretorios de cada agente como fizemos pro s1 aqui: C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts. Já tem alguns contracts lá mas não sei como estão devem estar desatualizados. C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm aqui tbm já tem algumas skills prontas dele. Lembro que quando eu pazssei por ele com o claude code no processo anterior que estavamos seguindo, estava funcionando a visualização da pagina PUB da planilha perfis. Enfim vamos começar pelo PM garantir que ele ta 100% depois vamos de VO, fazemos o wiring completo e testamos PM -> VO -> S1 pra ver o que acontece"}],"timestamp":1775048648032}}
{"type":"message","id":"cc011a18","parentId":"6944359a","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:04:51.469Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Perfeito. Concordo com a sequência.\n\n# Direção fechada então\n## Ordem oficial agora:\n1. **PM**\n2. **VO**\n3. **wiring PM -> VO**\n4. **teste PM -> VO -> S1**\n\nE sim — também concordo totalmente com o ponto dos contracts:\n\n## Precisamos organizar `docs/contracts` por agente/setor\nTal como fizemos com S1.\n\nPorque hoje o problema não é só “falta código”:\né também **falta de estrutura documental canónica**.\n\n---\n\n# Minha leitura do PM agora\nO PM parece estar numa situação parecida com o que o S1 estava antes de ser consolidado:\n\n### Já tem:\n- substrate útil\n- algumas peças a funcionar\n- algum contrato\n- algum comportamento real já validado\n- memória tua de que a visualização da página PUB já funcionava\n\n### Mas ainda falta:\n- separar claramente o que é:\n  - contract\n  - runtime determinístico\n  - workspace OpenClaw\n  - agent reality\n- transformar isso numa peça canónica e durável\n\n---\n\n# O que eu faria agora no PM\n\n## Fase 1 — Diagnóstico documental e estrutural\n### Objetivo\nDescobrir:\n- o que existe\n- o que está desatualizado\n- o que pode ser reaproveitado\n- o que precisa ser reescrito\n\n### Áreas\n- `docs/contracts`\n- `runtime/pm`\n\n---\n\n## Fase 2 — Organizar contracts do PM em subdiretório próprio\nHoje eu esperaria algo como:\n\n- `docs/contracts/pm/`\n\nE dentro:\n- supervisor/agent contract do PM\n- read_pub contract\n- override contract\n- job_builder contract\n- job_validator contract\n- talvez selection_engine contract\n\n### Regra\nTal como no S1:\n- um sítio claro\n- sem contracts espalhados soltos na raiz de `docs/contracts`\n\n---\n\n## Fase 3 — Definir o PM como agent OpenClaw real\nAntes de criar ficheiros, precisamos deixar claro:\n\n### PM é o quê, exactamente?\nProvavelmente:\n- **supervisor/manager agent**\n- não só skill determinística\n- não só script Python\n- não só helper de sheet\n\n### O que ele deve fazer\n- receber um pedido/override\n- ler estado operacional da PUB\n- decidir ou materializar o target\n- construir job canónico\n- entregar handoff para VO\n\n---\n\n## Fase 4 — Criar o workspace real do PM\nDepois da clareza:\n- workspace OpenClaw\n- identidade\n- contexto\n- workflow\n- ferramentas/notas\n- modelo `gpt-5.4-mini`\n- registry real no OpenClaw\n\n---\n\n## Fase 5 — Só depois ir para VO\nPorque aí o VO já nasce com o PM definido a montante.\n\n---\n\n# O que eu acho importante não fazer\n## Não fazer isto:\nsair criando workspace do PM agora só porque “já sabemos mais ou menos”\n\n### Porque?\nPorque tu já disseste várias vezes — e tens razão:\n- **component-first**\n- **discussion-first**\n- **boundary-first**\n\nEntão o caminho certo é:\n1. destrinchar o PM\n2. organizar contracts\n3. só depois criar o agent real\n\n---\n\n# Próximo passo imediato que eu recomendo\nEu seguiria agora com este bloco:\n\n## PM — ronda 1\n1. inventário dos contracts actuais do PM\n2. inventário do runtime/skills actuais do PM\n3. leitura do que está reaproveitável\n4. proposta da estrutura nova em:\n   - `docs/contracts/pm/`\n5. diagnóstico claro:\n   - o que manter\n   - o que mover\n   - o que reescrever\n   - o que ainda falta criar\n\n---\n\n# Resposta curta\n## Sim:\n- começamos pelo **PM**\n- deixamos o **PM 100%**\n- depois **VO**\n- depois fazemos o **wiring completo**\n- e testamos **PM -> VO -> S1**\n\n## E sim também:\n- vamos **organizar os contracts por subdiretório próprio**, como fizemos no S1\n\n---\n\nSe quiser, eu já avanço agora para a próxima etapa concreta:\n\n### **inventário completo do PM**\n- contracts actuais\n- runtime actual\n- o que está desactualizado\n- proposta da nova estrutura canónica do PM\n\ne depois te trago isso bem mastigado.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169cd17d39dd08190bc6564f59c19c55e\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":145005,"output":945,"cacheRead":4608,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":150558,"cost":{"input":0.3625125,"output":0.014175,"cacheRead":0.001152,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.3778395}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775048649252,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd17cba0f08190b818d03e02e7f859"}}
