{"type":"message","id":"f4abeee1","parentId":"bf54f4af","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:10:03.797Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou criar a estrutura canónica de contracts do PM agora, reaproveitando o que existe e fechando as peças que faltam.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169cd19285308819097de12326efc33d2\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Wys7MUThXtc1DSoHLUqWHSiv|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd192caa2481908bacc4ae77aeb717","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm\\selection_engine.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\pm\\\\selection_engine.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_O9UNoSjTdEhacaaSjEnGrbJ6|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd192caa38819095b891554cb1cd3b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm\\job_builder.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\pm\\\\job_builder.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_uG32FfeXsqnSWx4BeBXGy7FX|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd192caa408190b86d11fc1c4f66c9","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm\\job_validator.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\pm\\\\job_validator.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_QLhnrAGSwDWxYUm1g1TRP5rD|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd192caa488190b194a7b704ea8eb5","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm_override_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm_override_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_uZWZMWmhhzOuVjmUQVuzJjHT|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd192caa508190a864ce0ab119119b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm_read_pub_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm_read_pub_contract.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":212,"output":242,"cacheRead":148864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":149318,"cost":{"input":0.0005300000000000001,"output":0.00363,"cacheRead":0.037216,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.041375999999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775048992962,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd1923f1c88190a6ff3f9cd4cda784"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0214ee3c","parentId":"f4abeee1","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:10:05.475Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Wys7MUThXtc1DSoHLUqWHSiv|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd192caa2481908bacc4ae77aeb717","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"PM Selection Engine — mode-aware channel selection.\n\nSupports 3 modes:\n- auto_select: PM decides by runway\n- filtered_select: PM decides by runway within upstream constraints\n- direct_select: Tobias decides the target, PM resolves and validates\n\nFollows the contract in docs/contracts/pm_override_contract.md.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom datetime import date\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\n\nfrom runtime.pm.override_validator import validate_override\nfrom runtime.pm.read_pub import read_pub\nfrom runtime.pm.job_builder import build_job\nfrom runtime.pm.job_validator import validate_job\n\n\ndef select_and_build_job(\n    override: dict[str, Any],\n    credential_path: Optional[Path] = None,\n    today: Optional[date] = None,\n    job_sequence: int = 1,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Execute PM selection with override mode awareness.\n\n    Args:\n        override: Override payload with mode, constraints, direct_target.\n        credential_path: Optional path to Google SA credentials.\n        today: Reference date for runway calculation.\n        job_sequence: Sequence number for same-day jobs.\n\n    Returns:\n        {\n            \"success\": bool,\n            \"mode\": str,\n            \"job\": dict | None,\n            \"validation\": dict | None,\n            \"selection_reasoning\": str,\n            \"pub_summary\": dict | None,\n            \"warnings\": list,\n            \"errors\": list,\n        }\n    \"\"\"\n    # Step 1: Validate override payload\n    ov_result = validate_override(override)\n    if not ov_result[\"valid\"]:\n        return _result(\n            success=False,\n            mode=override.get(\"mode\", \"unknown\"),\n            errors=ov_result[\"errors\"],\n            warnings=ov_result.get(\"warnings\", []),\n            reasoning=\"Override validation failed\",\n        )\n\n    mode = override[\"mode\"]\n    warnings = list(ov_result.get(\"warnings\", []))\n\n    # Step 2: Route by mode\n    if mode == \"direct_select\":\n        return _direct_select(override, credential_path, today, job_sequence, warnings)\n    elif mode == \"filtered_select\":\n        return _filtered_select(override, credential_path, today, job_sequence, warnings)\n    else:  # auto_select\n        return _auto_select(override, credential_path, today, job_sequence, warnings)\n\n\ndef _auto_select(\n    override: dict, credential_path, today, job_sequence, warnings\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Normal PM selection by runway.\"\"\"\n    pub = _read_pub_safe(credential_path, today)\n    if pub is None:\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=\"auto_select\",\n            errors=[{\"code\": \"pub_read_failed\", \"message\": \"Could not read PUB sheet\"}],\n            warnings=warnings, reasoning=\"PUB read failed\",\n        )\n\n    if pub[\"errors\"]:\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=\"auto_select\",\n            errors=pub[\"errors\"], warnings=warnings,\n            reasoning=\"PUB read returned errors\",\n            pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\"),\n        )\n\n    eligible = pub[\"eligible_channels\"]\n    if not eligible:\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=\"auto_select\",\n            errors=[{\"code\": \"no_eligible_channels\", \"message\": \"No eligible channels in PUB\"}],\n            warnings=warnings, reasoning=\"No eligible channels found\",\n            pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\"),\n        )\n\n    chosen = eligible[0]  # Already sorted by runway\n    return _build_and_validate(\n        chosen, override, job_sequence, warnings,\n        reasoning=f\"auto_select: chose {chosen['channel_name']} (runway={chosen['runway_days']})\",\n        pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\"),\n    )\n\n\ndef _filtered_select(\n    override: dict, credential_path, today, job_sequence, warnings\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"PM selection within upstream constraints.\"\"\"\n    constraints = override.get(\"constraints\", {})\n\n    # Build filter params from constraints\n    allowed_accounts = constraints.get(\"allowed_accounts\")\n    allowed_languages = constraints.get(\"allowed_languages\")\n    excluded_accounts = constraints.get(\"excluded_accounts\")\n    excluded_languages = constraints.get(\"excluded_languages\")\n\n    # Read PUB with allowed filters (read_pub supports these natively)\n    pub = _read_pub_safe(\n        credential_path, today,\n        allowed_accounts=allowed_accounts,\n        allowed_languages=allowed_languages,\n    )\n    if pub is None:\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=\"filtered_select\",\n            errors=[{\"code\": \"pub_read_failed\", \"message\": \"Could not read PUB sheet\"}],\n            warnings=warnings, reasoning=\"PUB read failed\",\n        )\n\n    if pub[\"errors\"]:\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=\"filtered_select\",\n            errors=pub[\"errors\"], warnings=warnings,\n            reasoning=\"PUB read returned errors\",\n            pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\"),\n        )\n\n    eligible = pub[\"eligible_channels\"]\n\n    # Apply excluded filters (not natively supported by read_pub)\n    if excluded_accounts:\n        eligible = [c for c in eligible if c[\"account\"] not in excluded_accounts]\n    if excluded_languages:\n        eligible = [c for c in eligible if c[\"language\"] not in excluded_languages]\n\n    # CRITICAL: filtered_select must NOT fall back to auto_select\n    if not eligible:\n        filter_desc = _describe_constraints(constraints)\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=\"filtered_select\",\n            errors=[{\n                \"code\": \"no_eligible_in_subset\",\n                \"message\": f\"No eligible channels within constraints: {filter_desc}\",\n            }],\n            warnings=warnings,\n            reasoning=f\"filtered_select produced 0 candidates with constraints: {filter_desc}\",\n            pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\"),\n        )\n\n    chosen = eligible[0]\n    filter_desc = _describe_constraints(constraints)\n    return _build_and_validate(\n        chosen, override, job_sequence, warnings,\n        reasoning=f\"filtered_select: chose {chosen['channel_name']} (runway={chosen['runway_days']}) within {filter_desc}\",\n        pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\"),\n    )\n\n\ndef _direct_select(\n    override: dict, credential_path, today, job_sequence, warnings\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Direct target resolution — Tobias chose, PM validates.\"\"\"\n    target = override[\"direct_target\"]\n    account = target[\"account\"]\n    language = target[\"language\"]\n\n    # Read PUB to get operational state (even for direct, we want warnings)\n    pub = _read_pub_safe(credential_path, today)\n\n    # Find the channel in PUB data (for operational awareness)\n    channel_data = None\n    if pub and not pub.get(\"errors\"):\n        all_channels = pub.get(\"eligible_channels\", []) + [\n            _excluded_to_channel(ex) for ex in pub.get(\"excluded_rows\", [])\n        ]\n        for ch in all_channels:\n            if ch.get(\"account\") == account and ch.get(\"language\") == language:\n                channel_data = ch\n                break\n\n    # Build channel dict for job_builder (from PUB data or minimal)\n    if channel_data:\n        chosen = channel_data\n        # Add operational warnings\n        if not channel_data.get(\"eligible\", True):\n            warnings.append({\n                \"code\": \"target_not_eligible\",\n                \"message\": f\"Direct target {account}/{language} is not eligible in PUB \"\n                           f\"(prod={channel_data.get('prod', '?')}, \"\n                           f\"scripts_remaining={channel_data.get('scripts_remaining', '?')})\",\n            })\n        if channel_data.get(\"scripts_remaining\", 1) <= 0:\n            warnings.append({\n                \"code\": \"target_no_scripts\",\n                \"message\": f\"Direct target {account}/{language} has 0 scripts remaining\",\n            })\n    else:\n        # Channel not found in PUB — try to build from config only\n        try:\n            from runtime.pm.job_builder import _load_channel_config\n            config = _load_channel_config(account, language)\n        except FileNotFoundError:\n            # CRITICAL: direct_select must NOT choose another target\n            return _result(\n                success=False, mode=\"direct_select\",\n                errors=[{\n                    \"code\": \"target_not_found\",\n                    \"message\": f\"Direct target {account}/{language} has no local config\",\n                }],\n                warnings=warnings,\n                reasoning=f\"direct_select: target {account}/{language} cannot be resolved\",\n            )\n\n        chosen = {\n            \"account\": account,\n            \"language\": language,\n            \"channel_name\": config.get(\"channel_name\", f\"C{account} {language.upper()}\"),\n            \"pub_row\": config.get(\"pub_row\"),\n            \"runway_days\": None,\n            \"scripts_remaining\": None,\n            \"reason\": f\"Direct select by {override.get('requested_by', 'unknown')}\",\n        }\n        warnings.append({\n            \"code\": \"target_not_in_pub\",\n            \"message\": f\"Direct target {account}/{language} was not found in PUB data — operational state unknown\",\n        })\n\n    return _build_and_validate(\n        chosen, override, job_sequence, warnings,\n        reasoning=f\"direct_select: target {account}/{language} resolved by {override.get('requested_by', 'unknown')}\",\n        pub_summary=pub.get(\"summary\") if pub else None,\n    )\n\n\ndef _build_and_validate(\n    chosen: dict, override: dict, job_sequence: int,\n    warnings: list, reasoning: str, pub_summary: dict = None,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Build and validate job from chosen channel.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        job = build_job(\n            chosen,\n            priority_override=override.get(\"reason\"),\n            job_sequence=job_sequence,\n        )\n    except FileNotFoundError as e:\n        return _result(\n            success=False, mode=override[\"mode\"],\n            errors=[{\"code\": \"config_not_found\", \"message\": str(e)}],\n            warnings=warnings, reasoning=reasoning,\n            pub_summary=pub_summary,\n        )\n\n    validation = validate_job(job)\n\n    # For direct_select, a validation failure on scripts_remaining is a warning, not a blocker\n    if override[\"mode\"] == \"direct_select\" and not validation[\"valid\"]:\n        non_blocking = all(\n            e[\"code\"] in (\"no_scripts_remaining\",) for e in validation[\"errors\"]\n        )\n        if non_blocking:\n            for e in validation[\"errors\"]:\n                warnings.append({\n                    \"code\": f\"validation_warning_{e['code']}\",\n                    \"message\": e[\"message\"],\n                })\n            validation = {\"valid\": True, \"errors\": []}\n\n    return _result(\n        success=validation[\"valid\"],\n        mode=override[\"mode\"],\n        job=job if validation[\"valid\"] else None,\n        validation=validation,\n        warnings=warnings,\n        reasoning=reasoning,\n        pub_summary=pub_summary,\n    )\n\n\ndef _read_pub_safe(credential_path, today, **kwargs) -> Optional[dict]:\n    \"\"\"Read PUB with error handling.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        return read_pub(credential_path=credential_path, today=today, **kwargs)\n    except Exception:\n        return None\n\n\ndef _excluded_to_channel(excluded: dict) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Convert an excluded_rows entry to a channel-like dict.\"\"\"\n    return {\n        \"account\": excluded.get(\"account\", \"\"),\n        \"language\": excluded.get(\"language\", \"\"),\n        \"channel_name\": excluded.get(\"channel_name\", \"\"),\n        \"pub_row\": excluded.get(\"pub_row\"),\n        \"eligible\": False,\n        \"prod\": excluded.get(\"raw_prod\", \"\"),\n        \"scripts_remaining\": 0,\n        \"runway_days\": None,\n    }\n\n\ndef _describe_constraints(constraints: dict) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Human-readable constraint summary.\"\"\"\n    parts = []\n    for key in (\"allowed_accounts\", \"allowed_languages\", \"excluded_accounts\", \"excluded_languages\"):\n        val = constraints.get(key)\n        if val:\n            parts.append(f\"{key}={val}\")\n    if constraints.get(\"monetized_only\"):\n        parts.append(\"monetized_only=true\")\n    return \", \".join(parts) if parts else \"no active constraints\"\n\n\ndef _result(\n    success: bool, mode: str, job: dict = None, validation: dict = None,\n    warnings: list = None, errors: list = None, reasoning: str = \"\",\n    pub_summary: dict = None,\n) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Build standardized result.\"\"\"\n    return {\n        \"success\": success,\n        \"mode\": mode,\n        \"job\": job,\n        \"validation\": validation,\n        \"selection_reasoning\": reasoning,\n        \"pub_summary\": pub_summary,\n        \"warnings\": warnings or [],\n        \"errors\": errors or [],\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775049005297}}
{"type":"message","id":"5a0237e9","parentId":"0214ee3c","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:10:05.660Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_O9UNoSjTdEhacaaSjEnGrbJ6|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd192caa38819095b891554cb1cd3b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"PM Job Builder — mounts canonical job JSON for the VO.\n\nTakes the chosen channel from read_pub output + local YAML config\nand builds the job artifact with everything the VO needs.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\nimport yaml\n\nACCOUNTS_DIR = Path(__file__).parent.parent.parent / \"accounts\"\n\n\ndef build_job(\n    channel: dict[str, Any],\n    priority_override: Optional[str] = None,\n    job_sequence: int = 1,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Build canonical PM job from chosen channel + local config.\n\n    Args:\n        channel: A single eligible_channel dict from read_pub output.\n        priority_override: Optional override reason (e.g. \"Lucca: so conta 03\").\n        job_sequence: Sequence number for same-day jobs (default 1).\n\n    Returns:\n        Canonical job JSON ready for validation and VO handoff.\n    \"\"\"\n    account = channel[\"account\"]\n    language = channel[\"language\"]\n    today_str = datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime(\"%Y-%m-%d\")\n\n    # Load local YAML config\n    config = _load_channel_config(account, language)\n\n    job_id = f\"{today_str}_{account}_{language}_{job_sequence:03d}\"\n\n    return {\n        \"job_id\": job_id,\n        \"account\": account,\n        \"language\": language,\n        \"channel_name\": channel.get(\"channel_name\", config.get(\"channel_name\", \"\")),\n        # Sheet/Drive IDs from local config (source of truth for IDs)\n        \"sheet_scripts_id\": config.get(\"sheet_scripts_id\", \"\"),\n        \"sheet_scripts_name\": config.get(\"sheet_scripts_name\", \"\"),\n        \"sheet_tracking_id\": config.get(\"sheet_tracking_id\", \"\"),\n        \"drive_folder_id\": config.get(\"drive_folder_id\", \"\"),\n        \"channel_url\": config.get(\"channel_url\", \"\"),\n        \"v3_config\": config.get(\"v3_config\", \"\"),\n        # PUB state at decision time\n        \"runway_days\": channel.get(\"runway_days\"),\n        \"scripts_remaining\": channel.get(\"scripts_remaining\"),\n        \"reason\": channel.get(\"reason\", \"\"),\n        \"priority_override\": priority_override,\n        # Metadata\n        \"created_at\": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),\n        \"pub_row\": channel.get(\"pub_row\"),\n    }\n\n\ndef _load_channel_config(account: str, language: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Load the YAML config for a specific account/language.\"\"\"\n    config_path = ACCOUNTS_DIR / account / f\"{language}.yaml\"\n    if not config_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(\n            f\"Channel config not found: {config_path}\"\n        )\n    with open(config_path, \"r\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n        return yaml.safe_load(f) or {}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775049005478}}
{"type":"message","id":"5308a13f","parentId":"5a0237e9","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:10:05.844Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_uG32FfeXsqnSWx4BeBXGy7FX|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd192caa408190b86d11fc1c4f66c9","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"PM Job Validator — deterministic validation of job artifact.\n\nIf validation fails, the job MUST NOT proceed to the VO.\nReturns structured errors for debugging.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\nACCOUNTS_DIR = Path(__file__).parent.parent.parent / \"accounts\"\n\n# Fields that must exist and be non-empty strings\nREQUIRED_STRING_FIELDS = [\n    \"job_id\",\n    \"account\",\n    \"language\",\n    \"channel_name\",\n    \"sheet_scripts_id\",\n    \"sheet_tracking_id\",\n    \"drive_folder_id\",\n    \"v3_config\",\n    \"created_at\",\n]\n\n# Fields that must exist (can be None for nullable fields)\nREQUIRED_FIELDS = REQUIRED_STRING_FIELDS + [\n    \"runway_days\",\n    \"scripts_remaining\",\n    \"pub_row\",\n]\n\n\ndef validate_job(job: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Validate a PM job artifact.\n\n    Returns:\n        {\n            \"valid\": bool,\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": str, \"field\": str, \"message\": str}, ...]\n        }\n    \"\"\"\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    # Check required fields exist\n    for field in REQUIRED_FIELDS:\n        if field not in job:\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_field\",\n                \"field\": field,\n                \"message\": f\"Required field '{field}' is missing\",\n            })\n\n    # If critical fields missing, return early\n    if errors:\n        return {\"valid\": False, \"errors\": errors}\n\n    # Check required string fields are non-empty\n    for field in REQUIRED_STRING_FIELDS:\n        val = job.get(field)\n        if not isinstance(val, str) or not val.strip():\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"empty_or_invalid_type\",\n                \"field\": field,\n                \"message\": f\"Field '{field}' must be a non-empty string, got: {type(val).__name__}={val!r}\",\n            })\n\n    # Type checks for numeric fields\n    runway = job.get(\"runway_days\")\n    if runway is not None and not isinstance(runway, (int, float)):\n        errors.append({\n            \"code\": \"invalid_type\",\n            \"field\": \"runway_days\",\n            \"message\": f\"runway_days must be numeric, got: {type(runway).__name__}\",\n        })\n\n    scripts = job.get(\"scripts_remaining\")\n    if scripts is not None and not isinstance(scripts, int):\n        errors.append({\n            \"code\": \"invalid_type\",\n            \"field\": \"scripts_remaining\",\n            \"message\": f\"scripts_remaining must be int, got: {type(scripts).__name__}\",\n        })\n\n    pub_row = job.get(\"pub_row\")\n    if pub_row is not None and not isinstance(pub_row, int):\n        errors.append({\n            \"code\": \"invalid_type\",\n            \"field\": \"pub_row\",\n            \"message\": f\"pub_row must be int, got: {type(pub_row).__name__}\",\n        })\n\n    # Coherence checks\n    account = job.get(\"account\", \"\")\n    language = job.get(\"language\", \"\")\n\n    # job_id format check\n    job_id = job.get(\"job_id\", \"\")\n    if isinstance(job_id, str) and account and language:\n        if f\"_{account}_{language}_\" not in job_id:\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"incoherent_job_id\",\n                \"field\": \"job_id\",\n                \"message\": f\"job_id '{job_id}' does not contain account '{account}' and language '{language}'\",\n            })\n\n    # Config file exists check\n    v3_config = job.get(\"v3_config\", \"\")\n    if isinstance(v3_config, str) and v3_config:\n        # Check local account YAML exists\n        config_path = ACCOUNTS_DIR / account / f\"{language}.yaml\"\n        if not config_path.exists():\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"config_not_found\",\n                \"field\": \"v3_config\",\n                \"message\": f\"Local config not found: {config_path}\",\n            })\n\n    # scripts_remaining coherence\n    if isinstance(scripts, int) and scripts <= 0:\n        errors.append({\n            \"code\": \"no_scripts_remaining\",\n            \"field\": \"scripts_remaining\",\n            \"message\": f\"scripts_remaining is {scripts} — job should not have been created\",\n        })\n\n    return {\n        \"valid\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775049005661}}
{"type":"message","id":"69f4d632","parentId":"5308a13f","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:10:06.073Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_QLhnrAGSwDWxYUm1g1TRP5rD|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd192caa488190b194a7b704ea8eb5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PM Override Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines how Tobias constrains or directs the Production Manager's selection behavior._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis contract defines the upstream override layer for the Production Manager (PM).\n\nThe PM should not treat PUB/runway as the absolute sovereign decision source.\nPUB is the operational state input. Final production intent can be constrained or directed by Tobias.\n\nThis contract exists to make that explicit and implementation-safe.\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### PUB is operational truth, not strategic sovereignty\n\nThe PM uses PUB to understand production reality:\n- which channels are active\n- how many scripts remain\n- how much runway each channel has\n- which channels are operationally urgent\n\nBut Tobias remains the higher-level decision layer.\n\nThat means the PM must support three operating modes:\n1. `auto_select`\n2. `filtered_select`\n3. `direct_select`\n\n---\n\n## Operating modes\n\n## 1. `auto_select`\n\n### Meaning\nThe PM is asked to choose the best production target using its normal operational logic.\n\n### Behavior\n- read PUB\n- normalize rows\n- filter eligible channels\n- compute runway\n- sort by urgency\n- choose the top candidate using the default prioritization rules\n\n### When to use\nUse this when Tobias says things like:\n- \"escolhe o mais urgente\"\n- \"decide o próximo vídeo\"\n- \"vê o que deve entrar em produção\"\n\n### Decision authority\nPM decides within its normal rules.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `filtered_select`\n\n### Meaning\nThe PM must still choose using PUB/runway logic, but only inside a constrained subset imposed by Tobias.\n\n### Behavior\n- read PUB\n- normalize rows\n- apply upstream constraints first\n- compute runway only within the allowed subset\n- choose the best candidate inside that subset\n\n### Example constraints\n- allowed accounts only\n- allowed languages only\n- excluded accounts\n- excluded languages\n- monetized channels only\n- specific strategic cohort only\n\n### When to use\nUse this when Tobias says things like:\n- \"só conta 03 hoje\"\n- \"prioriza 05 en e 03 fr\"\n- \"foca só monetizados\"\n- \"ignora os canais X e Y\"\n\n### Decision authority\nTobias defines the selection frame.\nPM decides inside that frame.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `direct_select`\n\n### Meaning\nThe PM is not being asked to choose strategically.\nIt is being asked to materialize and validate a direct production target.\n\n### Behavior\n- resolve the requested account/language directly\n- validate that the target exists\n- validate that the target is still operationally viable if possible\n- build the canonical PM job for that target\n- report relevant warnings if the direct target is unusual or operationally weak\n\n### When to use\nUse this when Tobias says things like:\n- \"produz 003 fr\"\n- \"faz 005 en agora\"\n- \"quero este canal específico\"\n\n### Decision authority\nTobias decides the target.\nPM validates and materializes it.\n\n---\n\n## Priority order\n\nIf override information exists, the PM should resolve authority in this order:\n\n1. `direct_select`\n2. `filtered_select`\n3. `auto_select`\n\nThat means:\n- a direct order beats a filtered order\n- a filtered order beats default runway autonomy\n\n---\n\n## Contract shape\n\nThe override layer should be represented as a structured object before final PM selection runs.\n\n### Suggested shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"auto_select\",\n  \"reason\": \"Default PM selection\",\n  \"constraints\": null,\n  \"direct_target\": null,\n  \"requested_by\": \"tobias\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T12:00:00-03:00\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## `auto_select` shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"auto_select\",\n  \"reason\": \"Choose the most urgent channel by runway\",\n  \"constraints\": null,\n  \"direct_target\": null,\n  \"requested_by\": \"tobias\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T12:00:00-03:00\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## `filtered_select` shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"filtered_select\",\n  \"reason\": \"Focus production on account 003 today\",\n  \"constraints\": {\n    \"allowed_accounts\": [\"003\"],\n    \"allowed_languages\": null,\n    \"excluded_accounts\": null,\n    \"excluded_languages\": null,\n    \"monetized_only\": false\n  },\n  \"direct_target\": null,\n  \"requested_by\": \"tobias\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T12:00:00-03:00\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## `direct_select` shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"direct_select\",\n  \"reason\": \"Lucca requested specific production target\",\n  \"constraints\": null,\n  \"direct_target\": {\n    \"account\": \"003\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"requested_by\": \"tobias\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T12:00:00-03:00\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Expected PM behavior by mode\n\n### In `auto_select`\nThe PM should return:\n- top candidate\n- supporting ranked list if useful\n- operational reasoning based on runway\n\n### In `filtered_select`\nThe PM should return:\n- best candidate inside constraints\n- explanation of applied filters\n- warning if the filtered pool is empty\n\n### In `direct_select`\nThe PM should return:\n- the requested target if valid\n- warnings if the target has no scripts / invalid config / inactive production / bad mapping\n- failure if the target cannot be resolved safely\n\n---\n\n## Validation rules\n\n### General\nEvery override object should validate:\n- supported `mode`\n- valid shape for that mode\n- no conflicting mode payloads\n- timestamps and metadata well-formed where required\n\n### `filtered_select`\n- reject malformed account/language lists\n- reject empty constraints if mode is `filtered_select`\n- allow future expansion of constraints without breaking current structure\n\n### `direct_select`\n- require `account`\n- require `language`\n- reject missing direct target\n\n---\n\n## Failure behavior\n\n### `auto_select`\nIf PUB cannot be read, PM fails normally.\n\n### `filtered_select`\nIf the constraints produce zero eligible candidates:\n- PM should fail clearly or return no selection with structured reason\n- PM must not silently fall back to unrestricted `auto_select`\n\n### `direct_select`\nIf the requested target is invalid/unresolvable:\n- PM should fail explicitly\n- PM must not silently choose another channel\n\nThis rule is critical.\nA direct order must never degrade into \"I picked something else\" without explicit Tobias approval.\n\n---\n\n## Non-goals for v1\n\nThis contract does not yet define:\n- natural-language parsing of overrides\n- persistence lifetime / expiry of overrides\n- multi-step campaign scheduling\n- weighted strategic scoring beyond simple mode selection\n- direct Lucca-to-PM conversation protocol\n\nThose can be added later.\n\n---\n\n## Recommended implementation split\n\nLikely implementation pieces:\n- `runtime/pm/override_parser.py` (later)\n- `runtime/pm/selection_engine.py` or equivalent mode-aware selection layer\n- integration with existing `read_pub`, `job_builder`, and `job_validator`\n\nFor now, the important thing is that the PM substrate and future VO work do not assume runway autonomy is the only valid operating model.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775049005844}}
{"type":"message","id":"6230705f","parentId":"69f4d632","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:10:06.262Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_uZWZMWmhhzOuVjmUQVuzJjHT|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd192caa508190a864ce0ab119119b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PM `read_pub` Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft based on current PM documentation. This is a contract draft for implementation, not a claim that all operational choices are fully frozen._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-03-30_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n`read_pub` is the Production Manager's deterministic ingestion layer for the canonical PUB spreadsheet.\n\nIts job is to:\n- authenticate with the canonical Google service account\n- read the `PUB` tab from the canonical spreadsheet\n- normalize the rows relevant to production prioritization\n- filter out channels that are not eligible for production\n- compute runway per eligible channel\n- return a stable, machine-consumable structure for PM decision-making\n\n`read_pub` does **not**:\n- choose the final production target on its own if an explicit direct order was given upstream\n- generate the PM -> VO job artifact\n- apply complex business overrides beyond the explicitly supported filter contract\n- mutate Sheets or Drive\n\n---\n\n## Canonical source\n\n### Spreadsheet\n- **Sheet ID**: `1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc`\n- **Tab**: `PUB`\n\n### Credentials\n- **Credential model**: Google service account\n- **Canonical credential path**: `C:\\secrets\\content_factory\\google_service_account.json`\n\n### Dependencies\n- Google Sheets API must be enabled\n- The service account must have at least read access to the canonical spreadsheet\n\n---\n\n## Inputs\n\n### Required runtime inputs\n1. `credential_path`\n   - default canonical value: `C:\\secrets\\content_factory\\google_service_account.json`\n2. `sheet_id`\n   - default canonical value: `1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc`\n3. `tab_name`\n   - default canonical value: `PUB`\n4. `today`\n   - ISO date or runtime-local current date used to compute runway\n\n### Optional runtime inputs\n5. `allowed_accounts`\n   - list of account IDs to restrict evaluation\n6. `allowed_languages`\n   - list of languages to restrict evaluation\n7. `pub_row_subset`\n   - optional row subset for testing/debugging\n8. `override_filter`\n   - structured upstream filter contract, if already resolved by PM/override parser\n\n---\n\n## Required columns from PUB\n\nThe current PM documentation defines these columns as the minimum required fields:\n\n| Column | Header | Meaning |\n|--------|--------|---------|\n| B | `ULT PUB` | Date of last already-scheduled publication |\n| F | `PROGRAMAR` | Videos ready but not yet uploaded/scheduled |\n| J | `PROD` | Whether production is active for the channel (`SIM` / `NÃO`) |\n| O | `SCRIPTS` | Script usage in `used/total` format |\n\n### Additional identification data\n`read_pub` must also retain enough row identity to map a row to:\n- `pub_row`\n- `account`\n- `language`\n- `channel_name`\n\nThe current contract assumes those mappings are resolved via the local account registry and/or documented row mapping already defined by PM docs.\n\n---\n\n## Eligibility rules\n\nA row is eligible for PM prioritization only if all of the following are true:\n\n1. `PROD = SIM`\n2. `scripts_remaining > 0`\n3. the row can be mapped to a valid local account/language/config entry\n4. required fields for runway calculation can be parsed successfully\n\nRows that fail any of the above must not be included in the eligible result set.\n\nThey should instead be returned in a structured `excluded_rows` or `errors` section.\n\n---\n\n## Parsing and normalization rules\n\n### `ULT PUB`\n- Expected format: date value representing the last scheduled publication date\n- Minimum v1 behavior:\n  - parse documented date format reliably\n  - normalize to ISO date in output\n- If unparsable:\n  - mark row invalid\n  - exclude from eligible set\n  - emit structured error\n\n### `PROGRAMAR`\n- Expected semantic: integer count of already-produced but not-yet-scheduled videos\n- Normalize to integer\n- If missing or invalid:\n  - mark row invalid\n  - exclude from eligible set\n  - emit structured error\n\n### `PROD`\n- Expected semantic: active production flag\n- Minimum supported positive value in v1: `SIM`\n- Any non-`SIM` value is treated as inactive\n\n### `SCRIPTS`\n- Expected format: `used/total`, e.g. `38/57`\n- Parse into:\n  - `scripts_used`\n  - `scripts_total`\n  - `scripts_remaining = scripts_total - scripts_used`\n- If malformed:\n  - mark row invalid\n  - exclude from eligible set\n  - emit structured error\n\n---\n\n## Runway calculation\n\nCanonical formula from PM documentation:\n\n```text\nrunway_days = PROGRAMAR + days_until_last_scheduled_publication\n```\n\nWhere:\n- `PROGRAMAR` = count from column F\n- `days_until_last_scheduled_publication = ULT_PUB - today`\n\n### Notes\n- Negative runway is valid and indicates urgency/deficit\n- Zero runway is valid\n- Higher runway means more content buffer\n- Lower runway means higher urgency\n\n---\n\n## Sorting / prioritization output\n\nFor the base `read_pub` contract, the output list should be sorted by:\n\n1. lowest `runway_days`\n2. lower account number as tiebreaker, based on current PM documentation\n\n### Important boundary\n`read_pub` should compute and sort.\nFinal PM decision logic that applies richer overrides may happen one layer above unless explicitly folded into this skill later.\n\n---\n\n## Output contract\n\nThe primary output should be a stable JSON-serializable structure.\n\n### Suggested top-level shape\n\n```json\n{\n  \"source\": {\n    \"sheet_id\": \"1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc\",\n    \"tab_name\": \"PUB\",\n    \"read_at\": \"2026-03-30T11:00:00-03:00\"\n  },\n  \"eligible_channels\": [],\n  \"excluded_rows\": [],\n  \"errors\": []\n}\n```\n\n### Required fields for each eligible channel\n\n```json\n{\n  \"pub_row\": 16,\n  \"account\": \"003\",\n  \"language\": \"fr\",\n  \"channel_name\": \"C003 FRA\",\n  \"ult_pub_raw\": \"27/03/2026\",\n  \"ult_pub_iso\": \"2026-03-27\",\n  \"programar\": 0,\n  \"prod\": \"SIM\",\n  \"scripts_raw\": \"38/57\",\n  \"scripts_used\": 38,\n  \"scripts_total\": 57,\n  \"scripts_remaining\": 19,\n  \"runway_days\": 1,\n  \"eligible\": true,\n  \"reason\": \"PROD=SIM, scripts_remaining>0, runway=1\"\n}\n```\n\n### Required fields for excluded rows\nAt minimum:\n- `pub_row`\n- row identity if available\n- `excluded_reason`\n- `raw_values` or safe debugging fields when useful\n\n### Required fields for errors\nAt minimum:\n- `code`\n- `message`\n- `scope` (`sheet`, `row`, `auth`, `parse`, etc.)\n- `pub_row` when applicable\n\n---\n\n## Error handling\n\n### Fatal errors\nThese should fail the whole call:\n- credential file missing\n- credential file unreadable\n- authentication failure\n- spreadsheet not found\n- tab not found\n- Google API unavailable for the whole request\n\n### Row-level errors\nThese should not fail the entire call if partial read is still meaningful:\n- invalid date in `ULT PUB`\n- malformed `SCRIPTS`\n- invalid `PROGRAMAR`\n- unmapped row/account/language\n\n### Partial success rule\nIf the sheet is readable and at least one valid eligible row exists, `read_pub` may return partial success with row-level errors attached.\n\n---\n\n## Non-goals for v1\n\nThe following are intentionally outside the initial `read_pub` contract unless later promoted:\n- caching / snapshot fallback\n- write-back to Sheets\n- direct job creation\n- script locking\n- advanced override semantics in natural language\n- historical analytics / trend reporting\n\n---\n\n## Open questions to confirm later\n\nThese are not frozen by this v1 contract:\n\n1. What is the final source of truth if PUB and local YAML diverge?\n2. Should `read_pub` support cache/last-known-good snapshot on API failure?\n3. What exact upstream component resolves natural-language overrides into structured filters?\n4. What exact row/account/language mapping logic should be canonical if the sheet identity layer is ambiguous?\n5. Should inactive/malformed rows be returned with full debug payloads or only sanitized summaries?\n\n---\n\n## Recommended implementation split\n\nTo keep responsibilities clean, implementation should likely be split into:\n\n- `runtime/integrations/google_sheets.py`\n- `runtime/pm/read_pub.py`\n- `runtime/pm/pub_row_normalizer.py`\n- `runtime/pm/job_builder.py`\n- `runtime/pm/job_validator.py`\n\n`read_pub` should remain the deterministic ingestion layer, not absorb the whole PM.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775049006073}}
{"type":"message","id":"a1966278","parentId":"6230705f","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:10:13.427Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_jLP47PIe4PAvZGJ7F6pVUL1d|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1935de488190a77141f2b44036b5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path 'docs\\contracts\\pm' | Out-Null","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"New-Item -ItemType Directory -Force -Path 'docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm' | Out-Null\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":30}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":105273,"output":69,"cacheRead":45568,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":150910,"cost":{"input":0.26318250000000004,"output":0.0010350000000000001,"cacheRead":0.011392,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.27560950000000006}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775049006935,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd19314440819084c903630218b26b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"458c7083","parentId":"a1966278","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:10:14.314Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_jLP47PIe4PAvZGJ7F6pVUL1d|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1935de488190a77141f2b44036b5","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"(no output)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":399,"aggregated":"","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775049014128}}
{"type":"message","id":"ae6ca22d","parentId":"458c7083","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:12:59.088Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_uBV45A4lH3amUPXhgdVu3C7X|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd19dbf6448190b4fac5d72108b6f5","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\pm_supervisor_contract.md","content":"# PM Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the canonical role, authority, workflow, and component boundaries of the Production Manager._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Production Manager (PM) is the canonical upstream production-selection supervisor in the editing pipeline.\n\nIts job is to:\n- understand operational production state from the PUB sheet\n- interpret strategic constraints or direct orders from Tobias\n- choose or materialize the correct production target\n- build a canonical production job\n- validate that job before handoff\n- hand the validated job to the Video Orchestrator (VO)\n\nThe PM is an **OpenClaw supervisor/manager agent**.\nIt is not:\n- just a spreadsheet reader\n- just a deterministic script folder\n- the final owner of run bootstrap or script locking\n- a downstream sector executor\n\n---\n\n## Canonical authority\n\n### PM owns\n- production target selection within its authority frame\n- interpretation of PUB as operational truth\n- application of override mode rules\n- creation of canonical PM job artifacts\n- validation of those job artifacts before VO handoff\n- refusal to hand off invalid jobs\n\n### PM does not own\n- script fetching/locking\n- run directory initialization\n- S1 supervision\n- downstream sector execution\n- strategic sovereignty above Tobias\n\n### Core principle\nPUB is operational truth, not strategic sovereignty.\n\nThat means:\n- PM uses PUB to understand reality\n- Tobias can constrain or directly target production\n- PM obeys valid upstream authority while preserving operational safety\n\n---\n\n## Canonical operating model\n\nThe canonical PM model is:\n- **PM supervisor = decision brain of production target selection**\n- **deterministic PM runtime components = operational substrate**\n- **validated PM job artifact = handoff truth to VO**\n\nThe PM should reason over persisted/configured reality and structured override inputs, not hidden ad-hoc assumptions.\n\n---\n\n## Component classes inside PM\n\nThe PM sector is currently composed of three practical component classes.\n\n### 1. Canonical PM supervisor\n- future OpenClaw PM agent/workspace (not yet created at the time of this draft)\n\n### 2. Deterministic PM runtime components\n- `read_pub`\n- `pub_row_normalizer`\n- `override_validator`\n- `selection_engine`\n- `job_builder`\n- `job_validator`\n\n### 3. External integrations / supporting substrate\n- `runtime.integrations.google_sheets.GoogleSheetsClient`\n- local `accounts/registry.yaml`\n- per-channel YAML config files under `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n\n---\n\n## Canonical input model\n\nThe PM may be invoked with a structured override object that defines its authority frame.\n\n### Supported modes\n1. `auto_select`\n2. `filtered_select`\n3. `direct_select`\n\n### Priority order\nIf override information exists, the PM should resolve authority in this order:\n1. `direct_select`\n2. `filtered_select`\n3. `auto_select`\n\n---\n\n## Canonical output model\n\nThe canonical PM output is a **validated PM job artifact** suitable for VO handoff.\n\nAt minimum the PM should return:\n- selection success/failure\n- mode used\n- job artifact when successful\n- validation result\n- selection reasoning\n- warnings/errors\n- PUB summary when relevant\n\nThe PM should not claim success if the job fails validation.\n\n---\n\n## Authority map\n\n### Tobias owns\n- strategic production intent\n- high-level prioritization frame\n- direct target orders when desired\n\n### PM owns\n- operational interpretation of PUB\n- production target resolution within the active authority mode\n- job construction and validation\n- safe refusal when the requested result is structurally invalid or unresolvable\n\n### VO owns\n- run bootstrap after receiving a valid PM job\n- run directory initialization\n- script fetch/lock/persist\n- producing `ready_for_s1` state\n\n---\n\n## Canonical PM workflow\n\nThe canonical PM flow is:\n\n1. Receive structured override / production request\n2. Validate override payload via `override_validator`\n3. Read PUB via `read_pub`\n4. Apply mode-aware selection logic via `selection_engine`\n5. Resolve chosen production target\n6. Build canonical job via `job_builder`\n7. Validate canonical job via `job_validator`\n8. If valid, hand off to VO\n9. If invalid, fail explicitly with structured errors\n\n---\n\n## Failure behavior\n\n### PM must fail explicitly when:\n- override payload is invalid\n- PUB cannot be read and no safe fallback exists\n- filtered constraints produce zero candidates\n- direct target is unresolvable\n- job artifact fails blocking validation\n\n### PM must not:\n- silently fall back from `filtered_select` to unrestricted auto mode\n- silently choose another target when `direct_select` fails\n- hand off an invalid job to VO\n\n---\n\n## Current implementation reality\n\nAt the time of this draft:\n- deterministic PM substrate exists and is materially implemented\n- PM contracts exist only partially\n- PM is not yet realized as a real OpenClaw workspace/agent\n- the job artifact and mode logic are ahead of the agent embodiment\n\nThis means the PM is currently stronger as substrate than as OpenClaw runtime entity.\n\n---\n\n## Immediate implication for future work\n\nThe next correct move is:\n- complete PM contract coverage\n- create PM workspace/agent reality in OpenClaw\n- bind the deterministic substrate to the PM supervisor identity\n- then wire PM into VO through the canonical handoff contract\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm\\\\pm_supervisor_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# PM Supervisor Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the canonical role, authority, workflow, and component boundaries of the Production Manager._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThe Production Manager (PM) is the canonical upstream production-selection supervisor in the editing pipeline.\\n\\nIts job is to:\\n- understand operational production state from the PUB sheet\\n- interpret strategic constraints or direct orders from Tobias\\n- choose or materialize the correct production target\\n- build a canonical production job\\n- validate that job before handoff\\n- hand the validated job to the Video Orchestrator (VO)\\n\\nThe PM is an **OpenClaw supervisor/manager agent**.\\nIt is not:\\n- just a spreadsheet reader\\n- just a deterministic script folder\\n- the final owner of run bootstrap or script locking\\n- a downstream sector executor\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical authority\\n\\n### PM owns\\n- production target selection within its authority frame\\n- interpretation of PUB as operational truth\\n- application of override mode rules\\n- creation of canonical PM job artifacts\\n- validation of those job artifacts before VO handoff\\n- refusal to hand off invalid jobs\\n\\n### PM does not own\\n- script fetching/locking\\n- run directory initialization\\n- S1 supervision\\n- downstream sector execution\\n- strategic sovereignty above Tobias\\n\\n### Core principle\\nPUB is operational truth, not strategic sovereignty.\\n\\nThat means:\\n- PM uses PUB to understand reality\\n- Tobias can constrain or directly target production\\n- PM obeys valid upstream authority while preserving operational safety\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical operating model\\n\\nThe canonical PM model is:\\n- **PM supervisor = decision brain of production target selection**\\n- **deterministic PM runtime components = operational substrate**\\n- **validated PM job artifact = handoff truth to VO**\\n\\nThe PM should reason over persisted/configured reality and structured override inputs, not hidden ad-hoc assumptions.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Component classes inside PM\\n\\nThe PM sector is currently composed of three practical component classes.\\n\\n### 1. Canonical PM supervisor\\n- future OpenClaw PM agent/workspace (not yet created at the time of this draft)\\n\\n### 2. Deterministic PM runtime components\\n- `read_pub`\\n- `pub_row_normalizer`\\n- `override_validator`\\n- `selection_engine`\\n- `job_builder`\\n- `job_validator`\\n\\n### 3. External integrations / supporting substrate\\n- `runtime.integrations.google_sheets.GoogleSheetsClient`\\n- local `accounts/registry.yaml`\\n- per-channel YAML config files under `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical input model\\n\\nThe PM may be invoked with a structured override object that defines its authority frame.\\n\\n### Supported modes\\n1. `auto_select`\\n2. `filtered_select`\\n3. `direct_select`\\n\\n### Priority order\\nIf override information exists, the PM should resolve authority in this order:\\n1. `direct_select`\\n2. `filtered_select`\\n3. `auto_select`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical output model\\n\\nThe canonical PM output is a **validated PM job artifact** suitable for VO handoff.\\n\\nAt minimum the PM should return:\\n- selection success/failure\\n- mode used\\n- job artifact when successful\\n- validation result\\n- selection reasoning\\n- warnings/errors\\n- PUB summary when relevant\\n\\nThe PM should not claim success if the job fails validation.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Authority map\\n\\n### Tobias owns\\n- strategic production intent\\n- high-level prioritization frame\\n- direct target orders when desired\\n\\n### PM owns\\n- operational interpretation of PUB\\n- production target resolution within the active authority mode\\n- job construction and validation\\n- safe refusal when the requested result is structurally invalid or unresolvable\\n\\n### VO owns\\n- run bootstrap after receiving a valid PM job\\n- run directory initialization\\n- script fetch/lock/persist\\n- producing `ready_for_s1` state\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical PM workflow\\n\\nThe canonical PM flow is:\\n\\n1. Receive structured override / production request\\n2. Validate override payload via `override_validator`\\n3. Read PUB via `read_pub`\\n4. Apply mode-aware selection logic via `selection_engine`\\n5. Resolve chosen production target\\n6. Build canonical job via `job_builder`\\n7. Validate canonical job via `job_validator`\\n8. If valid, hand off to VO\\n9. If invalid, fail explicitly with structured errors\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure behavior\\n\\n### PM must fail explicitly when:\\n- override payload is invalid\\n- PUB cannot be read and no safe fallback exists\\n- filtered constraints produce zero candidates\\n- direct target is unresolvable\\n- job artifact fails blocking validation\\n\\n### PM must not:\\n- silently fall back from `filtered_select` to unrestricted auto mode\\n- silently choose another target when `direct_select` fails\\n- hand off an invalid job to VO\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current implementation reality\\n\\nAt the time of this draft:\\n- deterministic PM substrate exists and is materially implemented\\n- PM contracts exist only partially\\n- PM is not yet realized as a real OpenClaw workspace/agent\\n- the job artifact and mode logic are ahead of the agent embodiment\\n\\nThis means the PM is currently stronger as substrate than as OpenClaw runtime entity.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Immediate implication for future work\\n\\nThe next correct move is:\\n- complete PM contract coverage\\n- create PM workspace/agent reality in OpenClaw\\n- bind the deterministic substrate to the PM supervisor identity\\n- then wire PM into VO through the canonical handoff contract\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_icTpCjr2NZTQGgJTlaSfpPmP|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd19dbf65c8190bce2b93f338cf13e","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\pm_selection_engine_contract.md","content":"# PM Selection Engine Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the mode-aware PM selection layer that resolves a production target and produces a validated job candidate._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n`selection_engine` is the deterministic PM component that turns:\n- a validated override payload\n- current PUB state\n- local account/channel config\n\ninto:\n- a resolved production target\n- a canonical PM job candidate\n- a structured result with reasoning, warnings, and errors\n\nIt is the PM's mode-aware execution layer.\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\n`selection_engine` should:\n- validate override payload before routing\n- route by mode (`auto_select`, `filtered_select`, `direct_select`)\n- call `read_pub` appropriately\n- apply post-read filters where needed\n- resolve the chosen target\n- build a job via `job_builder`\n- validate that job via `job_validator`\n- return a standardized result object\n\nIt should not:\n- parse natural language directly\n- write to Sheets\n- create run directories\n- fetch scripts\n- lock scripts\n- bypass PM authority rules\n\n---\n\n## Inputs\n\n### Required\n- `override`\n\n### Optional\n- `credential_path`\n- `today`\n- `job_sequence`\n\n---\n\n## Output shape\n\nSuggested top-level shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"mode\": \"auto_select\",\n  \"job\": {},\n  \"validation\": {\"valid\": true, \"errors\": []},\n  \"selection_reasoning\": \"auto_select: chose C004 FRA (runway=-17)\",\n  \"pub_summary\": {\"total_channels_configured\": 39, \"eligible\": 38, \"excluded\": 1, \"errors\": 0},\n  \"warnings\": [],\n  \"errors\": []\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Mode behavior\n\n## `auto_select`\n- validate override\n- read PUB\n- choose the top eligible channel by runway order\n- build job\n- validate job\n\nIf no eligible channels exist:\n- fail explicitly with `no_eligible_channels`\n\n## `filtered_select`\n- validate override\n- read PUB with `allowed_accounts` / `allowed_languages` where supported\n- apply `excluded_accounts` / `excluded_languages` post-read\n- choose the top candidate inside that subset\n- build job\n- validate job\n\nCritical rule:\n- if the filtered pool is empty, fail explicitly with `no_eligible_in_subset`\n- never silently fall back to unrestricted auto mode\n\n## `direct_select`\n- validate override\n- resolve the requested account/language target directly\n- use PUB for operational awareness when possible\n- if target is not in PUB, try local config resolution\n- build job\n- validate job\n\nCritical rule:\n- if direct target is invalid or unresolvable, fail explicitly\n- never silently choose another target\n\n---\n\n## Warning behavior\n\nThe selection engine may return warnings for operational but non-blocking concerns, including:\n- target exists but is not eligible in PUB\n- target has zero scripts remaining in a direct-select context\n- target could not be located in PUB but local config exists\n- validation warnings in cases where direct strategic authority still allows materialization\n\nWarnings should never be hidden.\n\n---\n\n## Error behavior\n\nThe selection engine should fail explicitly on:\n- override validation failure\n- PUB read failure\n- invalid direct target\n- empty filtered subset\n- blocking job validation failure\n- config resolution failure required to build a job\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n`selection_engine` depends on:\n- `override_validator`\n- `read_pub`\n- `job_builder`\n- `job_validator`\n\n---\n\n## Boundary rule\n\n`selection_engine` is not the PM supervisor itself.\nIt is a deterministic decision-execution component used by the PM supervisor.\n\nThe PM supervisor owns the broader decision context.\nThe selection engine owns the deterministic resolution of one selection request.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm\\\\pm_selection_engine_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# PM Selection Engine Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the mode-aware PM selection layer that resolves a production target and produces a validated job candidate._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\n`selection_engine` is the deterministic PM component that turns:\\n- a validated override payload\\n- current PUB state\\n- local account/channel config\\n\\ninto:\\n- a resolved production target\\n- a canonical PM job candidate\\n- a structured result with reasoning, warnings, and errors\\n\\nIt is the PM's mode-aware execution layer.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\n`selection_engine` should:\\n- validate override payload before routing\\n- route by mode (`auto_select`, `filtered_select`, `direct_select`)\\n- call `read_pub` appropriately\\n- apply post-read filters where needed\\n- resolve the chosen target\\n- build a job via `job_builder`\\n- validate that job via `job_validator`\\n- return a standardized result object\\n\\nIt should not:\\n- parse natural language directly\\n- write to Sheets\\n- create run directories\\n- fetch scripts\\n- lock scripts\\n- bypass PM authority rules\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Inputs\\n\\n### Required\\n- `override`\\n\\n### Optional\\n- `credential_path`\\n- `today`\\n- `job_sequence`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output shape\\n\\nSuggested top-level shape:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"success\\\": true,\\n  \\\"mode\\\": \\\"auto_select\\\",\\n  \\\"job\\\": {},\\n  \\\"validation\\\": {\\\"valid\\\": true, \\\"errors\\\": []},\\n  \\\"selection_reasoning\\\": \\\"auto_select: chose C004 FRA (runway=-17)\\\",\\n  \\\"pub_summary\\\": {\\\"total_channels_configured\\\": 39, \\\"eligible\\\": 38, \\\"excluded\\\": 1, \\\"errors\\\": 0},\\n  \\\"warnings\\\": [],\\n  \\\"errors\\\": []\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Mode behavior\\n\\n## `auto_select`\\n- validate override\\n- read PUB\\n- choose the top eligible channel by runway order\\n- build job\\n- validate job\\n\\nIf no eligible channels exist:\\n- fail explicitly with `no_eligible_channels`\\n\\n## `filtered_select`\\n- validate override\\n- read PUB with `allowed_accounts` / `allowed_languages` where supported\\n- apply `excluded_accounts` / `excluded_languages` post-read\\n- choose the top candidate inside that subset\\n- build job\\n- validate job\\n\\nCritical rule:\\n- if the filtered pool is empty, fail explicitly with `no_eligible_in_subset`\\n- never silently fall back to unrestricted auto mode\\n\\n## `direct_select`\\n- validate override\\n- resolve the requested account/language target directly\\n- use PUB for operational awareness when possible\\n- if target is not in PUB, try local config resolution\\n- build job\\n- validate job\\n\\nCritical rule:\\n- if direct target is invalid or unresolvable, fail explicitly\\n- never silently choose another target\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Warning behavior\\n\\nThe selection engine may return warnings for operational but non-blocking concerns, including:\\n- target exists but is not eligible in PUB\\n- target has zero scripts remaining in a direct-select context\\n- target could not be located in PUB but local config exists\\n- validation warnings in cases where direct strategic authority still allows materialization\\n\\nWarnings should never be hidden.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Error behavior\\n\\nThe selection engine should fail explicitly on:\\n- override validation failure\\n- PUB read failure\\n- invalid direct target\\n- empty filtered subset\\n- blocking job validation failure\\n- config resolution failure required to build a job\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Dependencies\\n\\n`selection_engine` depends on:\\n- `override_validator`\\n- `read_pub`\\n- `job_builder`\\n- `job_validator`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Boundary rule\\n\\n`selection_engine` is not the PM supervisor itself.\\nIt is a deterministic decision-execution component used by the PM supervisor.\\n\\nThe PM supervisor owns the broader decision context.\\nThe selection engine owns the deterministic resolution of one selection request.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_XENw5ulwdZ3aAKA5e44azBeb|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd19dbf66481908a39abcbf664a439","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\pm_job_builder_contract.md","content":"# PM Job Builder Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines how the PM constructs the canonical job artifact for VO handoff._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n`job_builder` takes the resolved PM channel target and local channel config and produces the canonical PM job artifact.\n\nThis job artifact is the main interface between PM and VO.\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\n`job_builder` should:\n- receive a resolved target channel dict\n- load the local YAML config for the account/language\n- generate a canonical `job_id`\n- combine operational PUB state with local static config\n- return a canonical job JSON object ready for validation\n\nIt should not:\n- decide which channel to produce\n- validate the final job\n- create run directories\n- fetch scripts\n\n---\n\n## Inputs\n\n### Required\n- `channel`\n  - must include at minimum: `account`, `language`\n\n### Optional\n- `priority_override`\n- `job_sequence`\n\n---\n\n## Job ID rule\n\nCanonical format:\n\n```text\nYYYY-MM-DD_{account}_{language}_{NNN}\n```\n\nExample:\n```text\n2026-03-30_004_fr_001\n```\n\n---\n\n## Source-of-truth split\n\n### Comes from local YAML config\n- `sheet_scripts_id`\n- `sheet_scripts_name`\n- `sheet_tracking_id`\n- `drive_folder_id`\n- `channel_url`\n- `v3_config`\n\n### Comes from current operational selection state\n- `account`\n- `language`\n- `channel_name` (with fallback allowed)\n- `runway_days`\n- `scripts_remaining`\n- `reason`\n- `pub_row`\n\n### Generated metadata\n- `job_id`\n- `created_at`\n- `priority_override`\n\n---\n\n## Required output fields\n\nAt minimum, the job should contain:\n- `job_id`\n- `account`\n- `language`\n- `channel_name`\n- `sheet_scripts_id`\n- `sheet_scripts_name`\n- `sheet_tracking_id`\n- `drive_folder_id`\n- `channel_url`\n- `v3_config`\n- `runway_days`\n- `scripts_remaining`\n- `reason`\n- `priority_override`\n- `created_at`\n- `pub_row`\n\n---\n\n## Failure behavior\n\n`job_builder` should fail explicitly if the local account/language config cannot be found.\n\nIt should not silently invent missing static config.\n\n---\n\n## Boundary rule\n\n`job_builder` is a canonical artifact-construction component.\nIt is not the PM decision layer and it is not the VO bootstrap layer.\n\nIts single job is to materialize the handoff artifact cleanly.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm\\\\pm_job_builder_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# PM Job Builder Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines how the PM constructs the canonical job artifact for VO handoff._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\n`job_builder` takes the resolved PM channel target and local channel config and produces the canonical PM job artifact.\\n\\nThis job artifact is the main interface between PM and VO.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\n`job_builder` should:\\n- receive a resolved target channel dict\\n- load the local YAML config for the account/language\\n- generate a canonical `job_id`\\n- combine operational PUB state with local static config\\n- return a canonical job JSON object ready for validation\\n\\nIt should not:\\n- decide which channel to produce\\n- validate the final job\\n- create run directories\\n- fetch scripts\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Inputs\\n\\n### Required\\n- `channel`\\n  - must include at minimum: `account`, `language`\\n\\n### Optional\\n- `priority_override`\\n- `job_sequence`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Job ID rule\\n\\nCanonical format:\\n\\n```text\\nYYYY-MM-DD_{account}_{language}_{NNN}\\n```\\n\\nExample:\\n```text\\n2026-03-30_004_fr_001\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Source-of-truth split\\n\\n### Comes from local YAML config\\n- `sheet_scripts_id`\\n- `sheet_scripts_name`\\n- `sheet_tracking_id`\\n- `drive_folder_id`\\n- `channel_url`\\n- `v3_config`\\n\\n### Comes from current operational selection state\\n- `account`\\n- `language`\\n- `channel_name` (with fallback allowed)\\n- `runway_days`\\n- `scripts_remaining`\\n- `reason`\\n- `pub_row`\\n\\n### Generated metadata\\n- `job_id`\\n- `created_at`\\n- `priority_override`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Required output fields\\n\\nAt minimum, the job should contain:\\n- `job_id`\\n- `account`\\n- `language`\\n- `channel_name`\\n- `sheet_scripts_id`\\n- `sheet_scripts_name`\\n- `sheet_tracking_id`\\n- `drive_folder_id`\\n- `channel_url`\\n- `v3_config`\\n- `runway_days`\\n- `scripts_remaining`\\n- `reason`\\n- `priority_override`\\n- `created_at`\\n- `pub_row`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure behavior\\n\\n`job_builder` should fail explicitly if the local account/language config cannot be found.\\n\\nIt should not silently invent missing static config.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Boundary rule\\n\\n`job_builder` is a canonical artifact-construction component.\\nIt is not the PM decision layer and it is not the VO bootstrap layer.\\n\\nIts single job is to materialize the handoff artifact cleanly.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Yko6RRDKorwBd6vbenRX6Hr0|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd19dbf66c819099231477814f0a37","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\pm_job_validator_contract.md","content":"# PM Job Validator Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic validation gate for PM jobs before VO handoff._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n`job_validator` is the deterministic gate that decides whether a PM job artifact is safe to hand to VO.\n\nIf validation fails, the PM job must not proceed downstream unless an explicitly documented exception applies.\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\n`job_validator` should:\n- verify required fields exist\n- verify required field types\n- verify non-empty required strings\n- verify coherent job structure\n- verify config existence where required\n- verify `scripts_remaining` consistency\n- return structured validation errors\n\nIt should not:\n- modify the job\n- fetch external data\n- silently repair invalid jobs\n- create downstream artifacts\n\n---\n\n## Validation layers\n\n### 1. Required field presence\nThe validator should fail if required fields are missing.\n\n### 2. Type validation\nThe validator should verify:\n- required string fields are non-empty strings\n- `runway_days` is numeric when not null\n- `scripts_remaining` is int when not null\n- `pub_row` is int when not null\n\n### 3. Coherence validation\nThe validator should verify:\n- `job_id` coherently includes `account` and `language`\n- expected local config exists\n- `scripts_remaining` is not non-positive in normal handoff scenarios\n\n---\n\n## Output shape\n\nSuggested shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"valid\": false,\n  \"errors\": [\n    {\n      \"code\": \"missing_field\",\n      \"field\": \"sheet_scripts_id\",\n      \"message\": \"Required field 'sheet_scripts_id' is missing\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error behavior\n\nValidation should be blocking by default.\n\n### Important nuance\nIf the PM's strategic mode later defines explicit non-blocking exception cases (for example in direct-select scenarios), that exception handling belongs to the PM supervisor/selection layer, not to the validator itself.\n\nThe validator remains deterministic and conservative.\n\n---\n\n## Boundary rule\n\n`job_validator` is not a strategy component.\nIt is a structural safety gate.\n\nIt protects VO from receiving malformed or incoherent PM jobs.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm\\\\pm_job_validator_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# PM Job Validator Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic validation gate for PM jobs before VO handoff._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\n`job_validator` is the deterministic gate that decides whether a PM job artifact is safe to hand to VO.\\n\\nIf validation fails, the PM job must not proceed downstream unless an explicitly documented exception applies.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\n`job_validator` should:\\n- verify required fields exist\\n- verify required field types\\n- verify non-empty required strings\\n- verify coherent job structure\\n- verify config existence where required\\n- verify `scripts_remaining` consistency\\n- return structured validation errors\\n\\nIt should not:\\n- modify the job\\n- fetch external data\\n- silently repair invalid jobs\\n- create downstream artifacts\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Validation layers\\n\\n### 1. Required field presence\\nThe validator should fail if required fields are missing.\\n\\n### 2. Type validation\\nThe validator should verify:\\n- required string fields are non-empty strings\\n- `runway_days` is numeric when not null\\n- `scripts_remaining` is int when not null\\n- `pub_row` is int when not null\\n\\n### 3. Coherence validation\\nThe validator should verify:\\n- `job_id` coherently includes `account` and `language`\\n- expected local config exists\\n- `scripts_remaining` is not non-positive in normal handoff scenarios\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output shape\\n\\nSuggested shape:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"valid\\\": false,\\n  \\\"errors\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"code\\\": \\\"missing_field\\\",\\n      \\\"field\\\": \\\"sheet_scripts_id\\\",\\n      \\\"message\\\": \\\"Required field 'sheet_scripts_id' is missing\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Error behavior\\n\\nValidation should be blocking by default.\\n\\n### Important nuance\\nIf the PM's strategic mode later defines explicit non-blocking exception cases (for example in direct-select scenarios), that exception handling belongs to the PM supervisor/selection layer, not to the validator itself.\\n\\nThe validator remains deterministic and conservative.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Boundary rule\\n\\n`job_validator` is not a strategy component.\\nIt is a structural safety gate.\\n\\nIt protects VO from receiving malformed or incoherent PM jobs.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_XfJIZJsRYD54LnTZF01QY8Xq|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd19dbf6788190ba5326251716f014","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\pm_to_vo_handoff_contract.md","content":"# PM to VO Handoff Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the boundary between the Production Manager and the Video Orchestrator._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis contract defines what the PM must deliver to VO and what VO is allowed to assume when receiving PM output.\n\nIt exists to prevent ambiguity at the exact point where production selection becomes run bootstrap.\n\n---\n\n## Boundary principle\n\n### PM owns\n- choosing/materializing the production target\n- building the canonical PM job\n- validating that job before handoff\n\n### VO owns\n- receiving a valid PM job\n- initializing the run directory\n- writing `job.json`\n- writing `run_metadata.json`\n- writing VO checkpoints\n- fetching and locking the script\n- producing `ready_for_s1` state\n\nPM must not absorb VO responsibilities.\nVO must not inherit malformed PM handoff assumptions.\n\n---\n\n## Canonical handoff artifact\n\nThe canonical PM -> VO handoff artifact is the validated PM job JSON.\n\nVO should treat that job as the upstream truth for run bootstrap.\n\n---\n\n## Minimum PM guarantees before handoff\n\nBefore handing off to VO, PM must guarantee:\n- a target was selected or directly materialized according to authority rules\n- the job artifact was built canonically\n- the job artifact passed blocking validation\n- warnings/errors are preserved in structured form\n\nPM must not hand off a job that failed structural validation.\n\n---\n\n## Minimum VO assumptions at handoff time\n\nWhen VO receives a valid PM job, it may assume:\n- required PM job fields exist\n- the job has already passed PM validation\n- account/language/config mapping is structurally coherent enough to bootstrap the run\n\nVO should still validate the job from VO's perspective before creating the run.\n\n---\n\n## Expected PM job fields for VO\n\nVO expects, at minimum, a PM job that contains:\n- `job_id`\n- `account`\n- `language`\n- `channel_name`\n- `sheet_scripts_id`\n- `sheet_scripts_name`\n- `sheet_tracking_id`\n- `drive_folder_id`\n- `v3_config`\n- `created_at`\n- `pub_row`\n\nAdditional operational fields may also be included:\n- `runway_days`\n- `scripts_remaining`\n- `reason`\n- `priority_override`\n- `channel_url`\n\n---\n\n## Success condition of PM handoff\n\nThe PM handoff is successful when:\n- PM returns `success=true`\n- PM returns a non-null `job`\n- PM validation is passing or explicitly accepted by documented PM authority rules\n- VO can consume the job without needing to infer missing structural fields\n\n---\n\n## Failure condition of PM handoff\n\nThe PM -> VO boundary is failed if:\n- PM could not resolve a valid target\n- PM job construction failed\n- PM job validation failed in a blocking way\n- PM returns no job artifact\n\nIn these cases VO must not be called as if handoff succeeded.\n\n---\n\n## Downstream implication\n\nThis contract is the core bridge needed before a real `PM -> VO -> S1` integration test can be trusted.\n\nIf this contract is weak, integration failures will look like S1 or VO problems when the real fault is upstream handoff ambiguity.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm\\\\pm_to_vo_handoff_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# PM to VO Handoff Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the boundary between the Production Manager and the Video Orchestrator._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThis contract defines what the PM must deliver to VO and what VO is allowed to assume when receiving PM output.\\n\\nIt exists to prevent ambiguity at the exact point where production selection becomes run bootstrap.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Boundary principle\\n\\n### PM owns\\n- choosing/materializing the production target\\n- building the canonical PM job\\n- validating that job before handoff\\n\\n### VO owns\\n- receiving a valid PM job\\n- initializing the run directory\\n- writing `job.json`\\n- writing `run_metadata.json`\\n- writing VO checkpoints\\n- fetching and locking the script\\n- producing `ready_for_s1` state\\n\\nPM must not absorb VO responsibilities.\\nVO must not inherit malformed PM handoff assumptions.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical handoff artifact\\n\\nThe canonical PM -> VO handoff artifact is the validated PM job JSON.\\n\\nVO should treat that job as the upstream truth for run bootstrap.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Minimum PM guarantees before handoff\\n\\nBefore handing off to VO, PM must guarantee:\\n- a target was selected or directly materialized according to authority rules\\n- the job artifact was built canonically\\n- the job artifact passed blocking validation\\n- warnings/errors are preserved in structured form\\n\\nPM must not hand off a job that failed structural validation.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Minimum VO assumptions at handoff time\\n\\nWhen VO receives a valid PM job, it may assume:\\n- required PM job fields exist\\n- the job has already passed PM validation\\n- account/language/config mapping is structurally coherent enough to bootstrap the run\\n\\nVO should still validate the job from VO's perspective before creating the run.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Expected PM job fields for VO\\n\\nVO expects, at minimum, a PM job that contains:\\n- `job_id`\\n- `account`\\n- `language`\\n- `channel_name`\\n- `sheet_scripts_id`\\n- `sheet_scripts_name`\\n- `sheet_tracking_id`\\n- `drive_folder_id`\\n- `v3_config`\\n- `created_at`\\n- `pub_row`\\n\\nAdditional operational fields may also be included:\\n- `runway_days`\\n- `scripts_remaining`\\n- `reason`\\n- `priority_override`\\n- `channel_url`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Success condition of PM handoff\\n\\nThe PM handoff is successful when:\\n- PM returns `success=true`\\n- PM returns a non-null `job`\\n- PM validation is passing or explicitly accepted by documented PM authority rules\\n- VO can consume the job without needing to infer missing structural fields\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure condition of PM handoff\\n\\nThe PM -> VO boundary is failed if:\\n- PM could not resolve a valid target\\n- PM job construction failed\\n- PM job validation failed in a blocking way\\n- PM returns no job artifact\\n\\nIn these cases VO must not be called as if handoff succeeded.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Downstream implication\\n\\nThis contract is the core bridge needed before a real `PM -> VO -> S1` integration test can be trusted.\\n\\nIf this contract is weak, integration failures will look like S1 or VO problems when the real fault is upstream handoff ambiguity.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_HL0GN1Qly07XVOcso9DAqUpz|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd19dbf6808190bd025028c5c23d44","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\pm_read_pub_contract.md","content":"# PM `read_pub` Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic PUB ingestion layer used by the Production Manager._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n`read_pub` is the PM's deterministic ingestion layer for the canonical PUB spreadsheet.\n\nIts job is to:\n- authenticate with the canonical Google service account\n- read the `PUB` tab from the canonical spreadsheet\n- normalize the rows relevant to production prioritization\n- filter out channels that are not eligible for production\n- compute runway per eligible channel\n- return a stable machine-consumable structure for PM decision-making\n\n`read_pub` does **not**:\n- choose the final production target when strategic authority is resolved above it\n- generate the PM -> VO job artifact\n- apply full mode-aware selection logic by itself\n- mutate Sheets or Drive\n\n---\n\n## Canonical source\n\n### Spreadsheet\n- **Sheet ID**: `1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc`\n- **Tab**: `PUB`\n\n### Credentials\n- **Credential model**: Google service account\n- **Canonical credential path**: `C:\\secrets\\content_factory\\google_service_account.json`\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\n`read_pub` should:\n- load the local channel registry/config mapping\n- read the target PUB tab\n- normalize each mapped row\n- compute eligibility and runway\n- return eligible channels sorted by urgency\n- return excluded rows and row-level errors in structured form\n\n---\n\n## Input model\n\n### Required runtime inputs\n- `credential_path`\n- `sheet_id`\n- `tab_name`\n- `today`\n\n### Optional runtime inputs\n- `allowed_accounts`\n- `allowed_languages`\n\n---\n\n## Required PUB columns\n\nMinimum columns currently required:\n- `ULT PUB` (date of last scheduled publication)\n- `PROGRAMAR` (videos already ready/scheduled)\n- `PROD` (active production flag)\n- `SCRIPTS` (`used/total`)\n\n`read_pub` must also retain row identity information sufficient to map each result to:\n- `pub_row`\n- `account`\n- `language`\n- `channel_name`\n\n---\n\n## Eligibility rules\n\nA row is eligible only if all of the following are true:\n1. `PROD = SIM`\n2. `scripts_remaining > 0`\n3. row/config mapping is valid\n4. required fields for runway calculation can be parsed\n\nRows that fail these rules must not appear in the eligible set.\nThey should instead appear in `excluded_rows` or `errors`.\n\n---\n\n## Runway rule\n\nCanonical formula:\n\n```text\nrunway_days = PROGRAMAR + (ULT_PUB - today)\n```\n\nWhere lower runway means higher urgency.\nNegative runway is valid and indicates deficit/urgency.\n\n---\n\n## Sorting rule\n\nBase output ordering should be:\n1. lowest `runway_days`\n2. lower account number as tiebreaker\n3. language as secondary tiebreaker when needed\n\n---\n\n## Output contract\n\nSuggested top-level shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"source\": {\n    \"sheet_id\": \"1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc\",\n    \"tab_name\": \"PUB\",\n    \"read_at\": \"2026-03-30T11:00:00-03:00\"\n  },\n  \"today\": \"2026-03-30\",\n  \"eligible_channels\": [],\n  \"excluded_rows\": [],\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"summary\": {}\n}\n```\n\n### Required eligible-channel fields\n- `pub_row`\n- `account`\n- `language`\n- `channel_name`\n- `ult_pub_raw`\n- `ult_pub_iso`\n- `programar`\n- `prod`\n- `scripts_raw`\n- `scripts_used`\n- `scripts_total`\n- `scripts_remaining`\n- `runway_days`\n- `eligible`\n- `reason`\n\n### Required excluded-row fields\nAt minimum:\n- `pub_row`\n- channel identity when available\n- `excluded_reason`\n- safe debugging fields when helpful\n\n### Required error fields\nAt minimum:\n- `code`\n- `message`\n- `scope`\n- `pub_row` when applicable\n\n---\n\n## Error handling\n\n### Fatal errors\nShould fail the whole call:\n- credential missing/unreadable\n- authentication failure\n- spreadsheet/tab not found\n- whole-request Google API failure\n\n### Row-level errors\nMay coexist with partial success:\n- invalid date parsing\n- malformed scripts field\n- invalid PROGRAMAR\n- unmapped row/account/language\n\nIf the sheet is readable and at least one valid eligible row exists, partial success is acceptable.\n\n---\n\n## Boundary rule\n\n`read_pub` is the deterministic ingestion layer of the PM.\nIt must not absorb the whole PM decision stack.\n\nSelection authority remains above it.\nJob creation remains downstream of it.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm\\\\pm_read_pub_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# PM `read_pub` Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic PUB ingestion layer used by the Production Manager._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\n`read_pub` is the PM's deterministic ingestion layer for the canonical PUB spreadsheet.\\n\\nIts job is to:\\n- authenticate with the canonical Google service account\\n- read the `PUB` tab from the canonical spreadsheet\\n- normalize the rows relevant to production prioritization\\n- filter out channels that are not eligible for production\\n- compute runway per eligible channel\\n- return a stable machine-consumable structure for PM decision-making\\n\\n`read_pub` does **not**:\\n- choose the final production target when strategic authority is resolved above it\\n- generate the PM -> VO job artifact\\n- apply full mode-aware selection logic by itself\\n- mutate Sheets or Drive\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical source\\n\\n### Spreadsheet\\n- **Sheet ID**: `1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc`\\n- **Tab**: `PUB`\\n\\n### Credentials\\n- **Credential model**: Google service account\\n- **Canonical credential path**: `C:\\\\secrets\\\\content_factory\\\\google_service_account.json`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\n`read_pub` should:\\n- load the local channel registry/config mapping\\n- read the target PUB tab\\n- normalize each mapped row\\n- compute eligibility and runway\\n- return eligible channels sorted by urgency\\n- return excluded rows and row-level errors in structured form\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Input model\\n\\n### Required runtime inputs\\n- `credential_path`\\n- `sheet_id`\\n- `tab_name`\\n- `today`\\n\\n### Optional runtime inputs\\n- `allowed_accounts`\\n- `allowed_languages`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Required PUB columns\\n\\nMinimum columns currently required:\\n- `ULT PUB` (date of last scheduled publication)\\n- `PROGRAMAR` (videos already ready/scheduled)\\n- `PROD` (active production flag)\\n- `SCRIPTS` (`used/total`)\\n\\n`read_pub` must also retain row identity information sufficient to map each result to:\\n- `pub_row`\\n- `account`\\n- `language`\\n- `channel_name`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Eligibility rules\\n\\nA row is eligible only if all of the following are true:\\n1. `PROD = SIM`\\n2. `scripts_remaining > 0`\\n3. row/config mapping is valid\\n4. required fields for runway calculation can be parsed\\n\\nRows that fail these rules must not appear in the eligible set.\\nThey should instead appear in `excluded_rows` or `errors`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Runway rule\\n\\nCanonical formula:\\n\\n```text\\nrunway_days = PROGRAMAR + (ULT_PUB - today)\\n```\\n\\nWhere lower runway means higher urgency.\\nNegative runway is valid and indicates deficit/urgency.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Sorting rule\\n\\nBase output ordering should be:\\n1. lowest `runway_days`\\n2. lower account number as tiebreaker\\n3. language as secondary tiebreaker when needed\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output contract\\n\\nSuggested top-level shape:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"source\\\": {\\n    \\\"sheet_id\\\": \\\"1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc\\\",\\n    \\\"tab_name\\\": \\\"PUB\\\",\\n    \\\"read_at\\\": \\\"2026-03-30T11:00:00-03:00\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"today\\\": \\\"2026-03-30\\\",\\n  \\\"eligible_channels\\\": [],\\n  \\\"excluded_rows\\\": [],\\n  \\\"errors\\\": [],\\n  \\\"summary\\\": {}\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Required eligible-channel fields\\n- `pub_row`\\n- `account`\\n- `language`\\n- `channel_name`\\n- `ult_pub_raw`\\n- `ult_pub_iso`\\n- `programar`\\n- `prod`\\n- `scripts_raw`\\n- `scripts_used`\\n- `scripts_total`\\n- `scripts_remaining`\\n- `runway_days`\\n- `eligible`\\n- `reason`\\n\\n### Required excluded-row fields\\nAt minimum:\\n- `pub_row`\\n- channel identity when available\\n- `excluded_reason`\\n- safe debugging fields when helpful\\n\\n### Required error fields\\nAt minimum:\\n- `code`\\n- `message`\\n- `scope`\\n- `pub_row` when applicable\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Error handling\\n\\n### Fatal errors\\nShould fail the whole call:\\n- credential missing/unreadable\\n- authentication failure\\n- spreadsheet/tab not found\\n- whole-request Google API failure\\n\\n### Row-level errors\\nMay coexist with partial success:\\n- invalid date parsing\\n- malformed scripts field\\n- invalid PROGRAMAR\\n- unmapped row/account/language\\n\\nIf the sheet is readable and at least one valid eligible row exists, partial success is acceptable.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Boundary rule\\n\\n`read_pub` is the deterministic ingestion layer of the PM.\\nIt must not absorb the whole PM decision stack.\\n\\nSelection authority remains above it.\\nJob creation remains downstream of it.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_UZ8EINbolgCr39uRycW56ikT|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd19dbf68881909b9b965579b65c8a","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\pm_override_contract.md","content":"# PM Override Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines how Tobias constrains or directs the Production Manager's selection behavior._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis contract defines the upstream override layer for the Production Manager (PM).\n\nPUB is the PM's operational input, but final production intent may be constrained or directed by Tobias.\n\nThis contract exists to make that explicit and implementation-safe.\n\n---\n\n## Core principle\n\n### PUB is operational truth, not strategic sovereignty\n\nThe PM uses PUB to understand reality:\n- which channels are active\n- how many scripts remain\n- how much runway each channel has\n- which channels are operationally urgent\n\nBut Tobias remains the higher-level strategic layer.\n\nThat means the PM must support three operating modes:\n1. `auto_select`\n2. `filtered_select`\n3. `direct_select`\n\n---\n\n## Operating modes\n\n## 1. `auto_select`\n\n### Meaning\nThe PM is asked to choose the best production target using its normal operational logic.\n\n### Behavior\n- read PUB\n- normalize rows\n- filter eligible channels\n- compute runway\n- sort by urgency\n- choose the top candidate using default prioritization rules\n\n### Decision authority\nPM decides within its normal rules.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `filtered_select`\n\n### Meaning\nThe PM must still choose using PUB/runway logic, but only inside a constrained subset imposed by Tobias.\n\n### Behavior\n- read PUB\n- normalize rows\n- apply upstream constraints first\n- compute runway only within the allowed subset\n- choose the best candidate inside that subset\n\n### Example constraints\n- allowed accounts only\n- allowed languages only\n- excluded accounts\n- excluded languages\n- monetized channels only\n- specific strategic cohort only\n\n### Decision authority\nTobias defines the selection frame.\nPM decides inside that frame.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `direct_select`\n\n### Meaning\nThe PM is not being asked to choose strategically.\nIt is being asked to materialize and validate a direct production target.\n\n### Behavior\n- resolve the requested account/language directly\n- validate that the target exists\n- validate operational viability where possible\n- build the canonical PM job for that target\n- report warnings if the direct target is unusual or operationally weak\n\n### Decision authority\nTobias decides the target.\nPM validates and materializes it.\n\n---\n\n## Priority order\n\nIf override information exists, PM should resolve authority in this order:\n1. `direct_select`\n2. `filtered_select`\n3. `auto_select`\n\n---\n\n## Contract shape\n\nSuggested shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"auto_select\",\n  \"reason\": \"Default PM selection\",\n  \"constraints\": null,\n  \"direct_target\": null,\n  \"requested_by\": \"tobias\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T12:00:00-03:00\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Validation rules\n\n### General\nEvery override object should validate:\n- supported `mode`\n- valid shape for that mode\n- no conflicting mode payloads\n\n### `filtered_select`\n- reject malformed account/language lists\n- reject empty constraints when mode is `filtered_select`\n- reject contradictory allowed/excluded constraints\n\n### `direct_select`\n- require `account`\n- require `language`\n- reject missing direct target\n\n---\n\n## Failure behavior\n\n### `auto_select`\nIf PUB cannot be read, PM fails normally.\n\n### `filtered_select`\nIf constraints produce zero eligible candidates:\n- PM should fail clearly with structured reason\n- PM must not silently fall back to unrestricted `auto_select`\n\n### `direct_select`\nIf the requested target is invalid/unresolvable:\n- PM should fail explicitly\n- PM must not silently choose another channel\n\nThis rule is critical.\nA direct order must never degrade into “I picked something else” without explicit Tobias approval.\n\n---\n\n## Non-goals for v1\n\nThis contract does not yet define:\n- natural-language parsing of overrides\n- override persistence lifetime/expiry\n- multi-step campaign scheduling\n- direct Lucca-to-PM conversation protocol\n\nThose may be added later.\n\n---\n\n## Boundary rule\n\nThe override contract does not replace the PM supervisor contract.\nIt defines the authority frame that the PM supervisor and selection engine must obey.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm\\\\pm_override_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# PM Override Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines how Tobias constrains or directs the Production Manager's selection behavior._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThis contract defines the upstream override layer for the Production Manager (PM).\\n\\nPUB is the PM's operational input, but final production intent may be constrained or directed by Tobias.\\n\\nThis contract exists to make that explicit and implementation-safe.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Core principle\\n\\n### PUB is operational truth, not strategic sovereignty\\n\\nThe PM uses PUB to understand reality:\\n- which channels are active\\n- how many scripts remain\\n- how much runway each channel has\\n- which channels are operationally urgent\\n\\nBut Tobias remains the higher-level strategic layer.\\n\\nThat means the PM must support three operating modes:\\n1. `auto_select`\\n2. `filtered_select`\\n3. `direct_select`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Operating modes\\n\\n## 1. `auto_select`\\n\\n### Meaning\\nThe PM is asked to choose the best production target using its normal operational logic.\\n\\n### Behavior\\n- read PUB\\n- normalize rows\\n- filter eligible channels\\n- compute runway\\n- sort by urgency\\n- choose the top candidate using default prioritization rules\\n\\n### Decision authority\\nPM decides within its normal rules.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 2. `filtered_select`\\n\\n### Meaning\\nThe PM must still choose using PUB/runway logic, but only inside a constrained subset imposed by Tobias.\\n\\n### Behavior\\n- read PUB\\n- normalize rows\\n- apply upstream constraints first\\n- compute runway only within the allowed subset\\n- choose the best candidate inside that subset\\n\\n### Example constraints\\n- allowed accounts only\\n- allowed languages only\\n- excluded accounts\\n- excluded languages\\n- monetized channels only\\n- specific strategic cohort only\\n\\n### Decision authority\\nTobias defines the selection frame.\\nPM decides inside that frame.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## 3. `direct_select`\\n\\n### Meaning\\nThe PM is not being asked to choose strategically.\\nIt is being asked to materialize and validate a direct production target.\\n\\n### Behavior\\n- resolve the requested account/language directly\\n- validate that the target exists\\n- validate operational viability where possible\\n- build the canonical PM job for that target\\n- report warnings if the direct target is unusual or operationally weak\\n\\n### Decision authority\\nTobias decides the target.\\nPM validates and materializes it.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Priority order\\n\\nIf override information exists, PM should resolve authority in this order:\\n1. `direct_select`\\n2. `filtered_select`\\n3. `auto_select`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Contract shape\\n\\nSuggested shape:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"mode\\\": \\\"auto_select\\\",\\n  \\\"reason\\\": \\\"Default PM selection\\\",\\n  \\\"constraints\\\": null,\\n  \\\"direct_target\\\": null,\\n  \\\"requested_by\\\": \\\"tobias\\\",\\n  \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"2026-03-30T12:00:00-03:00\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Validation rules\\n\\n### General\\nEvery override object should validate:\\n- supported `mode`\\n- valid shape for that mode\\n- no conflicting mode payloads\\n\\n### `filtered_select`\\n- reject malformed account/language lists\\n- reject empty constraints when mode is `filtered_select`\\n- reject contradictory allowed/excluded constraints\\n\\n### `direct_select`\\n- require `account`\\n- require `language`\\n- reject missing direct target\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure behavior\\n\\n### `auto_select`\\nIf PUB cannot be read, PM fails normally.\\n\\n### `filtered_select`\\nIf constraints produce zero eligible candidates:\\n- PM should fail clearly with structured reason\\n- PM must not silently fall back to unrestricted `auto_select`\\n\\n### `direct_select`\\nIf the requested target is invalid/unresolvable:\\n- PM should fail explicitly\\n- PM must not silently choose another channel\\n\\nThis rule is critical.\\nA direct order must never degrade into “I picked something else” without explicit Tobias approval.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Non-goals for v1\\n\\nThis contract does not yet define:\\n- natural-language parsing of overrides\\n- override persistence lifetime/expiry\\n- multi-step campaign scheduling\\n- direct Lucca-to-PM conversation protocol\\n\\nThose may be added later.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Boundary rule\\n\\nThe override contract does not replace the PM supervisor contract.\\nIt defines the authority frame that the PM supervisor and selection engine must obey.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":139,"output":6556,"cacheRead":150784,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":157479,"cost":{"input":0.00034750000000000004,"output":0.09834,"cacheRead":0.037696,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.1363835}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775049014958,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd19392b7c819083255ae4b2cd81ea"}}
