{"type":"message","id":"218f6442","parentId":"6055447b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:28:18.434Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou seguir com a consolidação do PM: resolver os contracts antigos da raiz, criar um doc de implementação/status do PM e preparar a base para a criação do workspace OpenClaw dele.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169cd1d6b6d188190a5f17f5a43ff3945\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_YP4r1OaKpbo0h2r4k9pypiIh|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1d7207488190a6a45a14cb25e2a1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem -File docs\\contracts | Select-Object Name,FullName","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"Get-ChildItem -File docs\\\\contracts | Select-Object Name,FullName\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":30}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_9M457goCfa0AdLHE0796Ya1W|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1d7207748190b9eecc35b0de3135","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\pm_supervisor_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm\\\\pm_supervisor_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_91F0BEgKLkTxvuRfa8KkEg2R|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1d7207848190af77c41a8067cddd","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\pm_to_vo_handoff_contract.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\pm\\\\pm_to_vo_handoff_contract.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_NTYYf1B9XO42aeSXYtUZ0FiE|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1d7207908190a8fb4393e64ed36a","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\implementation\\pm\\01_substrate_v1.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\implementation\\\\pm\\\\01_substrate_v1.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_XQn8gZJ73xYhSiu7OQCgirIv|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1d7207ac81908dc5503e258e1802","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\implementation\\pm\\02_override_modes_v1.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\implementation\\\\pm\\\\02_override_modes_v1.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_7Eor5AZdRMnLTwrzueqI2mKF|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1d7207b881908a2b363b345292b6","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\implementation\\pm\\03_integration_notes.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\implementation\\\\pm\\\\03_integration_notes.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":152158,"output":334,"cacheRead":1536,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":154028,"cost":{"input":0.38039500000000004,"output":0.00501,"cacheRead":0.000384,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.38578900000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775050081921,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd1d64a0248190b28f622e82f61257"}}
{"type":"message","id":"713c7d16","parentId":"218f6442","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:28:20.531Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_YP4r1OaKpbo0h2r4k9pypiIh|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1d7207488190a6a45a14cb25e2a1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Name                    FullName                                                                                       \r\n----                    --------                                                                                       \r\npm_override_contract.md C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm_override_co...\r\npm_read_pub_contract.md C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm_read_pub_co..."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":769,"aggregated":"Name                    FullName                                                                                       \r\n----                    --------                                                                                       \r\npm_override_contract.md C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm_override_co...\r\npm_read_pub_contract.md C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm_read_pub_co...","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775050100339}}
{"type":"message","id":"36351c02","parentId":"713c7d16","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:28:20.724Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_9M457goCfa0AdLHE0796Ya1W|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1d7207748190b9eecc35b0de3135","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PM Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the canonical role, authority, workflow, and component boundaries of the Production Manager._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Production Manager (PM) is the canonical upstream production-selection supervisor in the editing pipeline.\n\nIts job is to:\n- understand operational production state from the PUB sheet\n- interpret strategic constraints or direct orders from Tobias\n- choose or materialize the correct production target\n- build a canonical production job\n- validate that job before handoff\n- hand the validated job to the Video Orchestrator (VO)\n\nThe PM is an **OpenClaw supervisor/manager agent**.\nIt is not:\n- just a spreadsheet reader\n- just a deterministic script folder\n- the final owner of run bootstrap or script locking\n- a downstream sector executor\n\n---\n\n## Canonical authority\n\n### PM owns\n- production target selection within its authority frame\n- interpretation of PUB as operational truth\n- application of override mode rules\n- creation of canonical PM job artifacts\n- validation of those job artifacts before VO handoff\n- refusal to hand off invalid jobs\n\n### PM does not own\n- script fetching/locking\n- run directory initialization\n- S1 supervision\n- downstream sector execution\n- strategic sovereignty above Tobias\n\n### Core principle\nPUB is operational truth, not strategic sovereignty.\n\nThat means:\n- PM uses PUB to understand reality\n- Tobias can constrain or directly target production\n- PM obeys valid upstream authority while preserving operational safety\n\n---\n\n## Canonical operating model\n\nThe canonical PM model is:\n- **PM supervisor = decision brain of production target selection**\n- **deterministic PM runtime components = operational substrate**\n- **validated PM job artifact = handoff truth to VO**\n\nThe PM should reason over persisted/configured reality and structured override inputs, not hidden ad-hoc assumptions.\n\n---\n\n## Component classes inside PM\n\nThe PM sector is currently composed of three practical component classes.\n\n### 1. Canonical PM supervisor\n- future OpenClaw PM agent/workspace (not yet created at the time of this draft)\n\n### 2. Deterministic PM runtime components\n- `read_pub`\n- `pub_row_normalizer`\n- `override_validator`\n- `selection_engine`\n- `job_builder`\n- `job_validator`\n\n### 3. External integrations / supporting substrate\n- `runtime.integrations.google_sheets.GoogleSheetsClient`\n- local `accounts/registry.yaml`\n- per-channel YAML config files under `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n\n---\n\n## Canonical input model\n\nThe PM may be invoked with a structured override object that defines its authority frame.\n\n### Supported modes\n1. `auto_select`\n2. `filtered_select`\n3. `direct_select`\n\n### Priority order\nIf override information exists, the PM should resolve authority in this order:\n1. `direct_select`\n2. `filtered_select`\n3. `auto_select`\n\n---\n\n## Canonical output model\n\nThe canonical PM output is a **validated PM job artifact** suitable for VO handoff.\n\nAt minimum the PM should return:\n- selection success/failure\n- mode used\n- job artifact when successful\n- validation result\n- selection reasoning\n- warnings/errors\n- PUB summary when relevant\n\nThe PM should not claim success if the job fails validation.\n\n---\n\n## Authority map\n\n### Tobias owns\n- strategic production intent\n- high-level prioritization frame\n- direct target orders when desired\n\n### PM owns\n- operational interpretation of PUB\n- production target resolution within the active authority mode\n- job construction and validation\n- safe refusal when the requested result is structurally invalid or unresolvable\n\n### VO owns\n- run bootstrap after receiving a valid PM job\n- run directory initialization\n- script fetch/lock/persist\n- producing `ready_for_s1` state\n\n---\n\n## Canonical PM workflow\n\nThe canonical PM flow is:\n\n1. Receive structured override / production request\n2. Validate override payload via `override_validator`\n3. Read PUB via `read_pub`\n4. Apply mode-aware selection logic via `selection_engine`\n5. Resolve chosen production target\n6. Build canonical job via `job_builder`\n7. Validate canonical job via `job_validator`\n8. If valid, hand off to VO\n9. If invalid, fail explicitly with structured errors\n\n---\n\n## Failure behavior\n\n### PM must fail explicitly when:\n- override payload is invalid\n- PUB cannot be read and no safe fallback exists\n- filtered constraints produce zero candidates\n- direct target is unresolvable\n- job artifact fails blocking validation\n\n### PM must not:\n- silently fall back from `filtered_select` to unrestricted auto mode\n- silently choose another target when `direct_select` fails\n- hand off an invalid job to VO\n\n---\n\n## Current implementation reality\n\nAt the time of this draft:\n- deterministic PM substrate exists and is materially implemented\n- PM contracts exist only partially\n- PM is not yet realized as a real OpenClaw workspace/agent\n- the job artifact and mode logic are ahead of the agent embodiment\n\nThis means the PM is currently stronger as substrate than as OpenClaw runtime entity.\n\n---\n\n## Immediate implication for future work\n\nThe next correct move is:\n- complete PM contract coverage\n- create PM workspace/agent reality in OpenClaw\n- bind the deterministic substrate to the PM supervisor identity\n- then wire PM into VO through the canonical handoff contract\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775050100538}}
{"type":"message","id":"3bbd861e","parentId":"36351c02","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:28:20.918Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_91F0BEgKLkTxvuRfa8KkEg2R|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1d7207848190af77c41a8067cddd","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PM to VO Handoff Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the boundary between the Production Manager and the Video Orchestrator._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis contract defines what the PM must deliver to VO and what VO is allowed to assume when receiving PM output.\n\nIt exists to prevent ambiguity at the exact point where production selection becomes run bootstrap.\n\n---\n\n## Boundary principle\n\n### PM owns\n- choosing/materializing the production target\n- building the canonical PM job\n- validating that job before handoff\n\n### VO owns\n- receiving a valid PM job\n- initializing the run directory\n- writing `job.json`\n- writing `run_metadata.json`\n- writing VO checkpoints\n- fetching and locking the script\n- producing `ready_for_s1` state\n\nPM must not absorb VO responsibilities.\nVO must not inherit malformed PM handoff assumptions.\n\n---\n\n## Canonical handoff artifact\n\nThe canonical PM -> VO handoff artifact is the validated PM job JSON.\n\nVO should treat that job as the upstream truth for run bootstrap.\n\n---\n\n## Minimum PM guarantees before handoff\n\nBefore handing off to VO, PM must guarantee:\n- a target was selected or directly materialized according to authority rules\n- the job artifact was built canonically\n- the job artifact passed blocking validation\n- warnings/errors are preserved in structured form\n\nPM must not hand off a job that failed structural validation.\n\n---\n\n## Minimum VO assumptions at handoff time\n\nWhen VO receives a valid PM job, it may assume:\n- required PM job fields exist\n- the job has already passed PM validation\n- account/language/config mapping is structurally coherent enough to bootstrap the run\n\nVO should still validate the job from VO's perspective before creating the run.\n\n---\n\n## Expected PM job fields for VO\n\nVO expects, at minimum, a PM job that contains:\n- `job_id`\n- `account`\n- `language`\n- `channel_name`\n- `sheet_scripts_id`\n- `sheet_scripts_name`\n- `sheet_tracking_id`\n- `drive_folder_id`\n- `v3_config`\n- `created_at`\n- `pub_row`\n\nAdditional operational fields may also be included:\n- `runway_days`\n- `scripts_remaining`\n- `reason`\n- `priority_override`\n- `channel_url`\n\n---\n\n## Success condition of PM handoff\n\nThe PM handoff is successful when:\n- PM returns `success=true`\n- PM returns a non-null `job`\n- PM validation is passing or explicitly accepted by documented PM authority rules\n- VO can consume the job without needing to infer missing structural fields\n\n---\n\n## Failure condition of PM handoff\n\nThe PM -> VO boundary is failed if:\n- PM could not resolve a valid target\n- PM job construction failed\n- PM job validation failed in a blocking way\n- PM returns no job artifact\n\nIn these cases VO must not be called as if handoff succeeded.\n\n---\n\n## Downstream implication\n\nThis contract is the core bridge needed before a real `PM -> VO -> S1` integration test can be trusted.\n\nIf this contract is weak, integration failures will look like S1 or VO problems when the real fault is upstream handoff ambiguity.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775050100725}}
{"type":"message","id":"05acd3e8","parentId":"3bbd861e","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:28:21.126Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_NTYYf1B9XO42aeSXYtUZ0FiE|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1d7207908190a8fb4393e64ed36a","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PM Substrate v1 -- Documentacao de Implementacao\n\n**Data**: 30 Mar 2026\n**Status**: PRODUCTION\n**Testes**: 44 unitarios + 2 integracao = 46 total, todos passam\n\n---\n\n## 1. Arquitectura\n\nO PM Substrate v1 e composto por 5 modulos que formam um pipeline linear e deterministico (zero LLM):\n\n```\nPUB Sheet (Google Sheets)\n    |\n    v\ngoogle_sheets.py          Wrapper gspread (autenticacao + leitura)\n    |\n    v  raw rows (list[list[str]])\nread_pub.py               Ingestao: carrega registry, le sheet, normaliza, filtra, ordena\n    |\n    v  normalize cada row\npub_row_normalizer.py     Parsing: data, scripts, PROD, runway\n    |\n    v  eligible_channels ordenados\njob_builder.py            Monta job JSON canonico (carrega YAML config local)\n    |\n    v  job artifact\njob_validator.py          Valida campos, tipos, coerencia\n    |\n    v  {valid: true} -> pronto para VO\n```\n\n### Diagrama de fluxo completo\n\n```\nPUB Sheet\n    |\n    | GoogleSheetsClient.read_worksheet_raw()\n    v\nraw rows (2D list, todas as linhas da tab PUB)\n    |\n    | registry.yaml -> lista de channels com pub_row\n    | para cada channel: normalize_pub_row()\n    v\nnormalized rows (com eligible=true/false)\n    |\n    | filtrar eligible=true\n    | ordenar por (runway_days ASC, account ASC, language ASC)\n    v\neligible_channels (lista ordenada)\n    |\n    | escolher top (menor runway)\n    | carregar accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml\n    v\nbuild_job() -> job JSON canonico\n    |\n    | validate_job()\n    v\n{valid: true, errors: []}\n    |\n    v\nPronto para handoff ao Video Orchestrator (VO)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. Cada modulo em detalhe\n\n### 2.1 google_sheets.py\n\n- **Path**: `runtime/integrations/google_sheets.py`\n- **Responsabilidade**: Wrapper fino sobre gspread. Gere autenticacao via service account e expoe metodos de leitura (records, raw values, row, cell). Nao contem logica de negocio.\n- **O que NAO faz**: Nao normaliza dados, nao filtra, nao escreve na sheet.\n\n#### Interface publica\n\n```python\nclass GoogleSheetsClient:\n    def __init__(self, credential_path: Optional[Path] = None)\n    def open_sheet(self, sheet_id: str) -> gspread.Spreadsheet\n    def read_worksheet(self, sheet_id: str, tab_name: str) -> list[dict]\n    def read_worksheet_raw(self, sheet_id: str, tab_name: str) -> list[list[str]]\n    def read_row(self, sheet_id: str, tab_name: str, row_number: int) -> list[str]\n    def read_cell(self, sheet_id: str, tab_name: str, row: int, col: int) -> str\n```\n\n#### Input/Output\n\n| Metodo | Input | Output |\n|--------|-------|--------|\n| `read_worksheet_raw` | `sheet_id`, `tab_name` | `list[list[str]]` -- todas as linhas como listas de strings |\n| `read_worksheet` | `sheet_id`, `tab_name` | `list[dict]` -- records com headers como chaves |\n| `read_row` | `sheet_id`, `tab_name`, `row_number` (1-indexed) | `list[str]` |\n| `read_cell` | `sheet_id`, `tab_name`, `row`, `col` (1-indexed) | `str` |\n\n#### Detalhes tecnicos\n\n- Scopes: `spreadsheets.readonly` + `drive.readonly`\n- Credential default: `C:\\secrets\\content_factory\\google_service_account.json`\n- Lazy init: client so e criado no primeiro acesso (`_ensure_client`)\n- Excepcoes mapeadas: `SpreadsheetNotFound` -> `ValueError`, `APIError` -> `ConnectionError`, credential missing -> `FileNotFoundError`\n\n---\n\n### 2.2 read_pub.py\n\n- **Path**: `runtime/pm/read_pub.py`\n- **Responsabilidade**: Funcao principal do PM Substrate. Le a PUB sheet, carrega configs do registry, normaliza cada row, filtra por elegibilidade, ordena por runway, e devolve resultado contract-compliant. E o orquestrador do pipeline de leitura.\n- **O que NAO faz**: Nao cria o job artifact (isso e `job_builder`). Nao aplica overrides de NL. Nao escreve nada.\n\n#### Interface publica\n\n```python\ndef read_pub(\n    credential_path: Optional[Path] = None,\n    sheet_id: str = DEFAULT_SHEET_ID,\n    tab_name: str = DEFAULT_TAB,\n    today: Optional[date] = None,\n    allowed_accounts: Optional[list[str]] = None,\n    allowed_languages: Optional[list[str]] = None,\n) -> dict\n```\n\n#### Input/Output\n\n| Parametro | Tipo | Default | Descricao |\n|-----------|------|---------|-----------|\n| `credential_path` | `Optional[Path]` | `None` (usa default) | Path para service account JSON |\n| `sheet_id` | `str` | `1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc` | ID da PUB sheet |\n| `tab_name` | `str` | `\"PUB\"` | Nome da tab |\n| `today` | `Optional[date]` | `date.today()` | Data de referencia para runway |\n| `allowed_accounts` | `Optional[list[str]]` | `None` (todos) | Filtro por conta |\n| `allowed_languages` | `Optional[list[str]]` | `None` (todos) | Filtro por idioma |\n\n**Retorno**: dict contract-compliant (ver seccao 3).\n\n#### Funcoes internas\n\n- `_load_channel_configs() -> list[dict]`: Le `accounts/registry.yaml`, carrega cada YAML individual, devolve lista de channel configs com `pub_row`, IDs de sheets, etc.\n- `_fatal_error(code, message) -> dict`: Constroi resposta de erro fatal com a mesma shape do output normal.\n\n---\n\n### 2.3 pub_row_normalizer.py\n\n- **Path**: `runtime/pm/pub_row_normalizer.py`\n- **Responsabilidade**: Transforma uma row crua da PUB sheet numa estrutura normalizada. Faz parsing de datas (4 formatos + serial do Google), scripts (formato \"used/total\"), inteiros, e calcula runway. Deterministico, sem side effects.\n- **O que NAO faz**: Nao le sheets, nao decide elegibilidade global, nao carrega configs.\n\n#### Interface publica\n\n```python\ndef normalize_pub_row(\n    row_values: list[str],\n    pub_row: int,\n    account: str,\n    language: str,\n    channel_name: str,\n    today: date,\n) -> dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n#### Input/Output\n\n| Parametro | Tipo | Descricao |\n|-----------|------|-----------|\n| `row_values` | `list[str]` | Valores crus da linha (0-indexed) |\n| `pub_row` | `int` | Numero da linha na sheet (1-indexed) |\n| `account` | `str` | ID da conta (e.g. \"003\") |\n| `language` | `str` | Codigo do idioma (e.g. \"fr\") |\n| `channel_name` | `str` | Nome display do canal |\n| `today` | `date` | Data de referencia |\n\n**Retorno**: dict normalizado (ver seccao 3).\n\n#### Constantes de colunas (0-indexed)\n\n| Constante | Indice | Coluna Sheet | Conteudo |\n|-----------|--------|--------------|----------|\n| `COL_ULT_PUB` | 1 | B | Ultima publicacao |\n| `COL_PROGRAMAR` | 5 | F | Videos programados |\n| `COL_PROD` | 9 | J | Status producao (SIM/NAO) |\n| `COL_SCRIPTS` | 14 | O | Scripts usados/total |\n\n#### Funcoes de parsing internas\n\n| Funcao | Input | Output | Notas |\n|--------|-------|--------|-------|\n| `_safe_get(lst, index)` | lista, indice | `str` | Retorna `\"\"` se IndexError |\n| `_parse_date(value)` | `str` | `Optional[date]` | Suporta `dd/mm/yyyy`, `yyyy-mm-dd`, `dd-mm-yyyy`, `dd/mm/yy`, serial Google |\n| `_parse_int(value)` | `str` | `Optional[int]` | Empty = 0, float string aceite, invalido = None |\n| `_parse_scripts(value)` | `str` | `tuple[Optional[int], Optional[int]]` | Formato \"used/total\" |\n\n---\n\n### 2.4 job_builder.py\n\n- **Path**: `runtime/pm/job_builder.py`\n- **Responsabilidade**: Recebe o canal escolhido (do output de read_pub) e monta o job JSON canonico com tudo o que o VO precisa. Carrega o YAML local da conta para obter IDs de sheets/drives (source of truth para IDs). Gera job_id unico com data+conta+idioma+sequencia.\n- **O que NAO faz**: Nao decide qual canal produzir (isso e responsabilidade do PM). Nao valida o job (isso e `job_validator`).\n\n#### Interface publica\n\n```python\ndef build_job(\n    channel: dict[str, Any],\n    priority_override: Optional[str] = None,\n    job_sequence: int = 1,\n) -> dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n#### Input/Output\n\n| Parametro | Tipo | Default | Descricao |\n|-----------|------|---------|-----------|\n| `channel` | `dict` | -- | Um eligible_channel do output de read_pub |\n| `priority_override` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Override manual (e.g. \"Lucca: so conta 03\") |\n| `job_sequence` | `int` | `1` | Sequencia para jobs no mesmo dia |\n\n**Retorno**: Job JSON canonico (ver seccao 3).\n\n#### Formato do job_id\n\n```\n{YYYY-MM-DD}_{account}_{language}_{NNN}\nExemplo: 2026-03-30_004_fr_001\n```\n\n#### Funcao interna\n\n- `_load_channel_config(account, language) -> dict`: Carrega `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`. Raises `FileNotFoundError` se nao existir.\n\n---\n\n### 2.5 job_validator.py\n\n- **Path**: `runtime/pm/job_validator.py`\n- **Responsabilidade**: Validacao deterministica do job artifact. Verifica campos obrigatorios, tipos, coerencia interna (job_id contem account+language, config file existe, scripts_remaining > 0). Se validacao falhar, job NAO deve prosseguir para o VO.\n- **O que NAO faz**: Nao corrige erros, nao modifica o job, nao tem side effects.\n\n#### Interface publica\n\n```python\ndef validate_job(job: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n#### Input/Output\n\n| Parametro | Tipo | Descricao |\n|-----------|------|-----------|\n| `job` | `dict` | Job JSON canonico |\n\n**Retorno**:\n```python\n{\n    \"valid\": bool,\n    \"errors\": [{\"code\": str, \"field\": str, \"message\": str}, ...]\n}\n```\n\n#### Campos validados\n\n**Required string fields** (devem existir e ser strings nao-vazias):\n- `job_id`, `account`, `language`, `channel_name`\n- `sheet_scripts_id`, `sheet_tracking_id`, `drive_folder_id`\n- `v3_config`, `created_at`\n\n**Required fields** (devem existir, podem ser None em campos nullable):\n- Todos os string fields acima + `runway_days`, `scripts_remaining`, `pub_row`\n\n**Type checks**:\n- `runway_days`: numerico (`int` ou `float`)\n- `scripts_remaining`: `int`\n- `pub_row`: `int`\n\n**Coherence checks**:\n- `job_id` deve conter `_{account}_{language}_`\n- Config local `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml` deve existir no filesystem\n- `scripts_remaining` deve ser > 0\n\n---\n\n## 3. Estruturas de dados\n\n### 3.1 Normalized row (output de pub_row_normalizer)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"pub_row\": 16,\n  \"account\": \"003\",\n  \"language\": \"fr\",\n  \"channel_name\": \"C003 FRA (6) x\",\n  \"ult_pub_raw\": \"27/03/2026\",\n  \"ult_pub_iso\": \"2026-03-27\",\n  \"programar\": 0,\n  \"prod\": \"SIM\",\n  \"scripts_raw\": \"38/57\",\n  \"scripts_used\": 38,\n  \"scripts_total\": 57,\n  \"scripts_remaining\": 19,\n  \"runway_days\": 1,\n  \"eligible\": true,\n  \"normalization_errors\": []\n}\n```\n\n**Notas**:\n- `ult_pub_iso` e `null` se parsing da data falhar\n- `runway_days` e `null` se data ou programar nao puderem ser parsed\n- `eligible` = `true` apenas se: `prod == \"SIM\"` AND `scripts_remaining > 0` AND `len(errors) == 0` AND `runway_days is not None`\n- `normalization_errors` acumula todos os problemas de parsing (nao faz early return)\n\n### 3.2 read_pub output (top-level shape)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"source\": {\n    \"sheet_id\": \"1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc\",\n    \"tab_name\": \"PUB\",\n    \"read_at\": \"2026-03-30T15:16:06.123456+00:00\"\n  },\n  \"today\": \"2026-03-30\",\n  \"eligible_channels\": [\n    { \"...normalized row + reason field...\" }\n  ],\n  \"excluded_rows\": [\n    {\n      \"pub_row\": 5,\n      \"account\": \"001\",\n      \"language\": \"pt\",\n      \"channel_name\": \"C001 PT ...\",\n      \"excluded_reason\": \"No scripts remaining\",\n      \"raw_prod\": \"SIM\",\n      \"raw_scripts\": \"57/57\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"summary\": {\n    \"total_channels_configured\": 39,\n    \"eligible\": 38,\n    \"excluded\": 1,\n    \"errors\": 0\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Notas**:\n- `eligible_channels` ja vem ordenado por `(runway_days ASC, account ASC, language ASC)`\n- Cada eligible channel tem campo extra `reason` com texto legivel\n- `excluded_rows` tem `excluded_reason` explicativo\n- Em caso de erro fatal (credentials, sheet nao encontrada), `errors` tem um unico item com `scope: \"fatal\"` e todos os outros campos ficam vazios\n\n### 3.3 Job JSON (output de job_builder)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"account\": \"004\",\n  \"language\": \"fr\",\n  \"channel_name\": \"C004 FRA (CHRONIQUES) (9)\",\n  \"sheet_scripts_id\": \"...\",\n  \"sheet_scripts_name\": \"Pagina1\",\n  \"sheet_tracking_id\": \"...\",\n  \"drive_folder_id\": \"...\",\n  \"channel_url\": \"\",\n  \"v3_config\": \"accounts/004_dark_culture/configs/004-fr.yaml\",\n  \"runway_days\": -17,\n  \"scripts_remaining\": 15,\n  \"reason\": \"PROD=SIM, scripts_remaining=15, runway=-17\",\n  \"priority_override\": null,\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T15:16:06.635809+00:00\",\n  \"pub_row\": 25\n}\n```\n\n**Notas**:\n- IDs de sheets/drive vem do YAML local (source of truth), nao da PUB sheet\n- `priority_override` e `null` por defeito, preenchido apenas com override manual do CEO/PM\n- `created_at` em UTC com timezone info\n- `channel_name` vem do channel eligible (fallback para config YAML)\n\n### 3.4 Validation result (output de job_validator)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"valid\": true,\n  \"errors\": []\n}\n```\n\nOu em caso de falha:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"valid\": false,\n  \"errors\": [\n    {\n      \"code\": \"empty_or_invalid_type\",\n      \"field\": \"sheet_scripts_id\",\n      \"message\": \"Field 'sheet_scripts_id' must be a non-empty string, got: str=''\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"code\": \"no_scripts_remaining\",\n      \"field\": \"scripts_remaining\",\n      \"message\": \"scripts_remaining is 0 -- job should not have been created\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Codigos de erro**:\n| Codigo | Significado |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `missing_field` | Campo obrigatorio nao existe no dict |\n| `empty_or_invalid_type` | String field vazio ou tipo errado |\n| `invalid_type` | Campo numerico com tipo errado |\n| `incoherent_job_id` | job_id nao contem account+language |\n| `config_not_found` | YAML local da conta nao existe |\n| `no_scripts_remaining` | scripts_remaining <= 0 |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Logica de negocio\n\n### 4.1 PUB Sheet\n\n| Propriedade | Valor |\n|-------------|-------|\n| Sheet ID | `1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc` |\n| Tab | `PUB` |\n| Colunas usadas | B (ULT PUB), F (PROGRAMAR), J (PROD), O (SCRIPTS) |\n\nA sheet tem uma linha por canal. O mapeamento canal->linha e definido no `pub_row` de cada YAML de conta (via `registry.yaml`).\n\n### 4.2 Elegibilidade\n\nUm canal e elegivel se **todas** as condicoes forem verdadeiras:\n\n1. `PROD == \"SIM\"` (coluna J, case-insensitive, trimmed)\n2. `scripts_remaining > 0` (calculado como `total - used` da coluna O)\n3. Zero erros de normalizacao (parsing de data, scripts, etc.)\n4. `runway_days is not None` (data e programar devem ser validos)\n\n### 4.3 Formula de runway\n\n```\nrunway_days = PROGRAMAR + (ULT_PUB - today).days\n```\n\nOnde:\n- `PROGRAMAR` (coluna F) = numero de videos ja programados/agendados\n- `ULT_PUB` (coluna B) = data da ultima publicacao\n- `today` = data de referencia (parametro ou `date.today()`)\n\n**Exemplos**:\n- ULT_PUB=27/03, today=26/03, PROGRAMAR=3 -> runway = 3 + 1 = **4** (4 dias de folga)\n- ULT_PUB=25/03, today=26/03, PROGRAMAR=0 -> runway = 0 + (-1) = **-1** (1 dia atrasado)\n- ULT_PUB=10/03, today=30/03, PROGRAMAR=3 -> runway = 3 + (-20) = **-17** (urgente)\n\n**Runway negativo** = canal ja esta atrasado na publicacao. Quanto mais negativo, mais urgente.\n\n### 4.4 Ordenacao\n\nCanais elegiveis sao ordenados por:\n1. `runway_days` ASC (mais urgente primeiro)\n2. `account` ASC (tiebreaker)\n3. `language` ASC (tiebreaker)\n\nO PM escolhe o **top** da lista (menor runway) para produzir.\n\n### 4.5 Config loading\n\n```\naccounts/registry.yaml\n    |\n    | lista de entries com \"config\" path relativo\n    v\naccounts/{account}/{language}.yaml\n    |\n    | contem: account, language, channel_name, pub_row,\n    | sheet_scripts_id, sheet_scripts_name, sheet_tracking_id,\n    | drive_folder_id, channel_url, v3_config\n    v\nchannel config dict\n```\n\nCanais sem `pub_row` definido no YAML sao silenciosamente ignorados.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Validacao (job_validator)\n\n### 5.1 Camadas de validacao\n\nA validacao e executada em 3 camadas sequenciais:\n\n**Camada 1 -- Existencia de campos**:\n- Todos os `REQUIRED_FIELDS` devem existir no dict\n- Se algum faltar, retorna imediatamente (early return) sem verificar tipos/coerencia\n\n**Camada 2 -- Tipos e valores**:\n- String fields: devem ser `str` e nao-vazios apos `.strip()`\n- `runway_days`: deve ser `int` ou `float` (ou `None`)\n- `scripts_remaining`: deve ser `int` (ou `None`)\n- `pub_row`: deve ser `int` (ou `None`)\n\n**Camada 3 -- Coerencia**:\n- `job_id` deve conter `_{account}_{language}_` como substring\n- Config local `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml` deve existir no filesystem\n- `scripts_remaining` deve ser > 0 (se for `<= 0`, o job nunca deveria ter sido criado)\n\n### 5.2 Regra critica\n\n> **Se validacao falhar (valid=false), o job NAO DEVE prosseguir para o VO.**\n\nO PM deve tratar erros de validacao como blocking. Cada erro tem `code`, `field`, e `message` para debugging.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Testes\n\n### 6.1 Resumo\n\n| Suite | Ficheiro | Testes | Tipo |\n|-------|----------|--------|------|\n| TestParseDate | `test_pub_row_normalizer.py` | 5 | unit |\n| TestParseScripts | `test_pub_row_normalizer.py` | 5 | unit |\n| TestParseInt | `test_pub_row_normalizer.py` | 5 | unit |\n| TestNormalizePubRow | `test_pub_row_normalizer.py` | 9 | unit |\n| TestReadPubWithMockedSheet | `test_read_pub.py` | 4 | unit |\n| TestReadPubIntegration | `test_read_pub.py` | 1 | integration |\n| TestJobBuilder | `test_job_validator.py` | 6 | unit |\n| TestJobValidator | `test_job_validator.py` | 9 | unit |\n| TestEndToEnd | `test_job_validator.py` | 1+1 | unit + integration |\n| **Total** | | **44 unit + 2 integration** | **46** |\n\n### 6.2 Cobertura por area\n\n- **Date parsing** (5): dd/mm/yyyy, ISO, dd/mm/yy, invalido, vazio\n- **Scripts parsing** (5): valid, zero remaining, vazio, sem slash, invalido\n- **Int parsing** (5): valido, zero, vazio (=0), float string, invalido\n- **Normalizacao** (9): rows validos (fixture), PROD=NAO, scripts esgotados, data invalida, scripts invalidos, PROGRAMAR vazio, row curta, calculo runway positivo, runway negativo\n- **read_pub mock** (4): ordenacao por runway, rows invalidos excluidos, filtro por account, credentials missing\n- **Job builder** (6): builds valid job, job_id format, priority override, carrega config fields, config missing raises, created_at presente\n- **Job validator** (9): job valido passa, campo missing, string vazio, tipo errado runway, tipo errado scripts, zero scripts, job_id incoerente, config not found, erros multiplos\n- **E2E sample** (1): build_job + validate_job com SAMPLE_CHANNEL\n\n### 6.3 Fixtures\n\n| Ficheiro | Conteudo |\n|----------|----------|\n| `runtime/tests/fixtures/pm/pub_rows_valid.json` | 4 rows validos com dados realistas |\n| `runtime/tests/fixtures/pm/pub_rows_invalid.json` | 6 rows invalidos (PROD=NAO, scripts esgotados, data invalida, scripts invalidos, PROGRAMAR vazio, row curta) |\n| `runtime/tests/fixtures/pm/expected_read_pub_output.json` | Ordem esperada apos sort por runway |\n\n### 6.4 Execucao\n\n```bash\n# Todos os testes unitarios (44)\npytest runtime/tests/test_pub_row_normalizer.py runtime/tests/test_read_pub.py runtime/tests/test_job_validator.py\n\n# Com testes de integracao (requer credentials reais)\npytest -m integration runtime/tests/\n```\n\nTestes de integracao marcados com `@pytest.mark.integration`, skipped por defeito em CI.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Contract references\n\n| Documento | Conteudo |\n|-----------|----------|\n| `docs/contracts/pm_read_pub_contract.md` | Contrato formal do output de read_pub (shape, campos, garantias) |\n| `docs/10_PRODUCTION_MANAGER.md` | Documentacao geral do PM (responsabilidades, fluxo, decisoes) |\n\n---\n\n## 8. Resultado real (30 Mar 2026)\n\nExecucao real do pipeline contra a PUB sheet de producao:\n\n| Metrica | Valor |\n|---------|-------|\n| Total channels configured | 39 |\n| Eligible | 38 |\n| Excluded | 1 |\n| Errors | 0 |\n\n**Excluido**: C001 PT -- scripts esgotados (57/57, `scripts_remaining=0`)\n\n**Top 3 por urgencia** (menor runway):\n\n| # | Canal | Runway | Scripts remaining |\n|---|-------|--------|-------------------|\n| 1 | C004 FRA (CHRONIQUES) | -17 | 15 |\n| 2 | (segundo mais urgente) | ... | ... |\n| 3 | (terceiro mais urgente) | ... | ... |\n\n**Job gerado para o top**:\n- Job ID: `2026-03-30_004_fr_001`\n- Account: 004, Language: fr\n- Runway: -17 dias (17 dias atrasado)\n- Scripts remaining: 15\n- Validacao: **PASSED** (valid=true, 0 errors)\n- Status: Pronto para handoff ao VO\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775050100918}}
{"type":"message","id":"0e07ff76","parentId":"05acd3e8","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:28:21.313Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_XQn8gZJ73xYhSiu7OQCgirIv|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1d7207ac81908dc5503e258e1802","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PM Override Modes v1 — Implementacao\n\n_Status: implementado e testado. 30 Mar 2026._\n\n_Modulos: `override_validator.py`, `selection_engine.py`_\n\n_Contrato: `docs/contracts/pm_override_contract.md`_\n\n---\n\n## 1. Contexto\n\nO substrato PM ja esta funcional (Lote 1 + Lote 2):\n- `read_pub` le a PUB e normaliza linhas\n- `job_builder` constroi jobs canonicos\n- `job_validator` valida viabilidade operacional\n- 44 testes passam antes desta fase\n\nO problema que este lote resolve: ate agora o PM assume que **runway e a unica autoridade de decisao**. Na realidade, PUB e a **verdade operacional** — quantos scripts restam, qual o runway de cada canal, quais estao activos. Mas a **autoridade estrategica** esta acima do PM.\n\n**Tobias e a camada estrategica.** Ele define o que deve ser produzido. O PM e um executor inteligente que obedece, avisa, e recusa apenas quando algo e fisicamente impossivel.\n\nPara formalizar esta hierarquia, o PM suporta agora **3 modos de operacao** que controlam o grau de autonomia concedido.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Os 3 modos\n\n### 2.1 `auto_select` — \"Escolhe o mais urgente\"\n\nO PM tem autonomia total dentro da sua logica operacional.\n\n**Comportamento exacto:**\n1. Valida o override payload\n2. Le a PUB via `read_pub()`\n3. Obtem lista de canais elegiveis (ordenados por runway crescente)\n4. Escolhe o primeiro candidato (mais urgente)\n5. Constroi job via `build_job()`\n6. Valida job via `validate_job()`\n7. Retorna resultado com `selection_reasoning` explicando a escolha\n\n**Payload:**\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"auto_select\",\n  \"reason\": \"Choose the most urgent channel by runway\",\n  \"constraints\": null,\n  \"direct_target\": null,\n  \"requested_by\": \"tobias\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T12:00:00-03:00\"\n}\n```\n\n**Falha quando:**\n- PUB nao pode ser lida (`pub_read_failed`)\n- PUB retorna erros (`errors` nao vazio)\n- Zero canais elegiveis (`no_eligible_channels`)\n\n---\n\n### 2.2 `filtered_select` — \"So conta 03 hoje\"\n\nTobias define o frame de seleccao. O PM decide **dentro** desse frame.\n\n**Constraints suportadas:**\n| Campo | Tipo | Efeito |\n|-------|------|--------|\n| `allowed_accounts` | `list[str]` | Apenas estes accounts sao considerados |\n| `allowed_languages` | `list[str]` | Apenas estas linguas sao consideradas |\n| `excluded_accounts` | `list[str]` | Estes accounts sao removidos pos-filtro |\n| `excluded_languages` | `list[str]` | Estas linguas sao removidas pos-filtro |\n| `monetized_only` | `bool` | Apenas canais monetizados (sem implementacao real v1) |\n\n**Aplicacao dos filtros:**\n- `allowed_*` sao passados ao `read_pub()` como filtros nativos (pre-filtro)\n- `excluded_*` sao aplicados em post-filtro sobre os canais elegiveis retornados\n- Esta separacao e intencional: `read_pub` ja suporta `allowed_accounts`/`allowed_languages`\n\n**Comportamento exacto:**\n1. Valida o override payload (inclui validacao de constraints)\n2. Le a PUB com `allowed_accounts` e `allowed_languages` como parametros nativos\n3. Aplica `excluded_accounts` e `excluded_languages` como post-filtro\n4. Se **zero candidatos** apos filtros: **ERRO EXPLICITO** (`no_eligible_in_subset`)\n5. Se ha candidatos: escolhe o primeiro (mais urgente dentro do subset)\n6. Constroi e valida job normalmente\n\n**REGRA CRITICA:** Se os filtros produzem 0 candidatos, o PM **NAO** cai silenciosamente para `auto_select`. Retorna erro explicito com descricao dos constraints aplicados. Esta regra existe porque uma degradacao silenciosa violaria a intencao de Tobias.\n\n**Payload:**\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"filtered_select\",\n  \"reason\": \"Focus production on account 003 today\",\n  \"constraints\": {\n    \"allowed_accounts\": [\"003\"],\n    \"allowed_languages\": null,\n    \"excluded_accounts\": null,\n    \"excluded_languages\": null,\n    \"monetized_only\": false\n  },\n  \"direct_target\": null,\n  \"requested_by\": \"tobias\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T12:00:00-03:00\"\n}\n```\n\n**Falha quando:**\n- PUB nao pode ser lida\n- PUB retorna erros\n- Zero candidatos apos aplicacao de constraints (`no_eligible_in_subset`)\n- Constraints invalidos na validacao (contradicoes, tipos errados, constraints vazios)\n\n---\n\n### 2.3 `direct_select` — \"Produz 003 fr\"\n\nTobias decide o alvo exacto. O PM resolve, valida, e **obedece** — mas emite warnings quando ha problemas operacionais.\n\n**Comportamento exacto:**\n1. Valida o override payload (requer `direct_target` com `account` e `language`)\n2. Le a PUB para awareness operacional (nao para seleccao)\n3. Procura o canal alvo na PUB (canais elegiveis + linhas excluidas)\n4. **Se encontra na PUB:**\n   - Usa os dados PUB como base do channel dict\n   - Se canal nao e elegivel: emite warning `target_not_eligible`\n   - Se `scripts_remaining <= 0`: emite warning `target_no_scripts`\n5. **Se NAO encontra na PUB:**\n   - Tenta carregar config YAML local via `_load_channel_config(account, language)`\n   - Se config existe: constroi channel dict minimo, emite warning `target_not_in_pub`\n   - Se config NAO existe: **ERRO EXPLICITO** `target_not_found`\n6. Constroi job via `build_job()`\n7. Valida job — mas com regra especial (ver abaixo)\n\n**Regra especial de validacao em `direct_select`:**\nSe o `validate_job()` falha **apenas** por `no_scripts_remaining`, o PM converte esses erros em warnings e considera o job como valido. Razao: Tobias mandou produzir, o PM obedece mas avisa. O bloqueio so ocorre para erros verdadeiramente impeditivos (config nao encontrado, etc.).\n\n**REGRA CRITICA:** Se o alvo nao existe, o PM **NAO** escolhe outro alvo. Retorna erro explicito. Uma ordem directa nunca pode degradar silenciosamente para \"escolhi outra coisa\".\n\n**Payload:**\n```json\n{\n  \"mode\": \"direct_select\",\n  \"reason\": \"Lucca requested specific production target\",\n  \"constraints\": null,\n  \"direct_target\": {\n    \"account\": \"003\",\n    \"language\": \"fr\"\n  },\n  \"requested_by\": \"tobias\",\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-03-30T12:00:00-03:00\"\n}\n```\n\n**Falha quando:**\n- Alvo nao existe (nem na PUB, nem em config local): `target_not_found`\n- Config YAML do alvo nao pode ser carregada: `config_not_found`\n\n**Warnings possiveis:**\n- `target_not_eligible`: canal existe mas nao e elegivel na PUB\n- `target_no_scripts`: canal tem 0 scripts restantes\n- `target_not_in_pub`: canal nao encontrado na PUB, estado operacional desconhecido\n- `validation_warning_no_scripts_remaining`: validator reportou falta de scripts (convertido de erro)\n\n---\n\n## 3. Modulos implementados\n\n### 3.1 `override_validator.py`\n\n**Localizacao:** `runtime/pm/override_validator.py`\n\n**Responsabilidade:** Validar a shape e coerencia do override payload antes de qualquer operacao.\n\n**Interface:**\n```python\ndef validate_override(override: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns: {\"valid\": bool, \"errors\": [...], \"warnings\": [...]}\n    \"\"\"\n```\n\n**Validacoes executadas:**\n\n| Validacao | Codigo erro | Quando |\n|-----------|-------------|--------|\n| Payload nao e dict | `invalid_shape` | `override` nao e dicionario |\n| Campo obrigatorio em falta | `missing_field` | `mode` ou `requested_by` ausentes/vazios |\n| Modo invalido | `invalid_mode` | `mode` nao e `auto_select`, `filtered_select`, ou `direct_select` |\n| filtered_select sem constraints | `missing_constraints` | `constraints` e None ou nao e dict |\n| filtered_select constraints vazios | `empty_constraints` | Constraints existe mas todos os campos sao null/vazio |\n| Tipo de constraint invalido | `invalid_constraint_type` | Lista de accounts/languages nao e lista |\n| Valor de constraint invalido | `invalid_constraint_value` | Lista contem valores nao-string |\n| Constraints contraditorios | `contradictory_constraints` | Mesmo account ou language em allowed + excluded |\n| direct_select sem target | `missing_direct_target` | `direct_target` e None ou nao e dict |\n| direct_select sem account | `missing_target_account` | `direct_target.account` ausente |\n| direct_select sem language | `missing_target_language` | `direct_target.language` ausente |\n\n**Warnings emitidos:**\n\n| Warning | Codigo | Quando |\n|---------|--------|--------|\n| Constraints em auto_select | `unexpected_constraints` | `auto_select` tem `constraints` definidos (serao ignorados) |\n| direct_target em auto_select | `unexpected_direct_target` | `auto_select` tem `direct_target` definido (sera ignorado) |\n\n**Constantes:**\n```python\nVALID_MODES = {\"auto_select\", \"filtered_select\", \"direct_select\"}\nREQUIRED_TOP_FIELDS = [\"mode\", \"requested_by\"]\nCONSTRAINT_FIELDS = {\n    \"allowed_accounts\", \"allowed_languages\",\n    \"excluded_accounts\", \"excluded_languages\",\n    \"monetized_only\",\n}\n```\n\n**Nota de implementacao:** Quando o modo e invalido, a funcao retorna imediatamente sem executar validacoes mode-specific. Isto evita cascata de erros irrelevantes.\n\n---\n\n### 3.2 `selection_engine.py`\n\n**Localizacao:** `runtime/pm/selection_engine.py`\n\n**Responsabilidade:** Execucao mode-aware da seleccao PM. Recebe um override, encaminha para o handler do modo correcto, e retorna resultado padronizado.\n\n**Interface principal:**\n```python\ndef select_and_build_job(\n    override: dict[str, Any],\n    credential_path: Optional[Path] = None,\n    today: Optional[date] = None,\n    job_sequence: int = 1,\n) -> dict[str, Any]\n```\n\n**Shape do resultado:**\n```python\n{\n    \"success\": bool,\n    \"mode\": str,                    # \"auto_select\" | \"filtered_select\" | \"direct_select\"\n    \"job\": dict | None,             # Job canonico (quando success=True)\n    \"validation\": dict | None,      # Resultado do job_validator\n    \"selection_reasoning\": str,     # Explicacao textual da decisao\n    \"pub_summary\": dict | None,     # Resumo da PUB (total, eligible, excluded, errors)\n    \"warnings\": list[dict],         # Avisos operacionais\n    \"errors\": list[dict],           # Erros (quando success=False)\n}\n```\n\n**Fluxo interno:**\n\n```\nselect_and_build_job(override)\n  |\n  +-- validate_override(override) -- se falha, retorna imediatamente\n  |\n  +-- route por mode:\n      |\n      +-- auto_select   --> _auto_select()\n      |     read_pub() -> eligible[0] -> build_job() -> validate_job()\n      |\n      +-- filtered_select --> _filtered_select()\n      |     read_pub(allowed_*) -> post-filter(excluded_*) -> eligible[0] -> build_job() -> validate_job()\n      |\n      +-- direct_select  --> _direct_select()\n            read_pub() -> find target in PUB/excluded -> resolve from config if needed -> build_job() -> validate_job() [com relaxacao]\n```\n\n**Funcoes internas:**\n\n| Funcao | Papel |\n|--------|-------|\n| `_auto_select()` | Seleccao normal por runway |\n| `_filtered_select()` | Seleccao com constraints upstream |\n| `_direct_select()` | Resolucao directa de alvo |\n| `_build_and_validate()` | Comum: build_job + validate_job + tratamento de warnings |\n| `_read_pub_safe()` | Wrapper com try/except que retorna None em vez de exception |\n| `_excluded_to_channel()` | Converte entrada de `excluded_rows` para formato channel-like |\n| `_describe_constraints()` | String human-readable dos constraints activos |\n| `_result()` | Construtor do dict de resultado padronizado |\n\n**Integracao com modulos existentes:**\n- `override_validator.validate_override` — validacao do payload\n- `read_pub.read_pub` — leitura da PUB (suporta `allowed_accounts`, `allowed_languages`)\n- `job_builder.build_job` — construcao do job canonico\n- `job_validator.validate_job` — validacao de viabilidade do job\n\n---\n\n## 4. Decisoes implicitas tomadas\n\nEstas decisoes foram tomadas durante a implementacao e nao estavam explicitamente no contrato:\n\n### 4.1 `direct_select` com `scripts_remaining=0` gera WARNING, nao bloqueio\n\nO `validate_job()` pode falhar com `no_scripts_remaining`. Em `direct_select`, esta falha e convertida em warning e o job e considerado valido. Razao: Tobias mandou, PM obedece mas avisa. Se todos os erros de validacao forem do tipo `no_scripts_remaining`, o job passa.\n\n### 4.2 `filtered_select` aplica `allowed_*` no `read_pub` e `excluded_*` em post-filter\n\nDois estagios de filtragem:\n- **Pre-filtro** (nativo no `read_pub`): `allowed_accounts`, `allowed_languages`\n- **Post-filtro** (no selection engine): `excluded_accounts`, `excluded_languages`\n\nRazao: `read_pub` ja suporta filtros `allowed_*` nativamente, mas nao suporta `excluded_*`. Em vez de duplicar logica, o engine aplica exclusoes sobre o resultado.\n\n### 4.3 Override validator aceita `auto_select` com constraints mas emite warning\n\nUm payload `auto_select` com `constraints` definidos nao e erro — e um warning. Os constraints serao ignorados. Isto facilita transicoes entre modos sem rejeitar payloads prematuramente.\n\n### 4.4 Contradicoes em constraints sao erro\n\nSe o mesmo account aparece em `allowed_accounts` e `excluded_accounts`, e erro. O mesmo para languages. Nao ha logica de precedencia — a contradicao deve ser resolvida pelo caller.\n\n### 4.5 `direct_select` sem dados PUB constroi job minimo\n\nSe o `read_pub` falha ou o canal nao aparece na PUB, o PM tenta carregar config YAML local. Se existe, constroi um channel dict minimo com `runway_days=None` e `scripts_remaining=None`, e emite warning `target_not_in_pub`. O job e construido mas o caller sabe que o estado operacional e desconhecido.\n\n### 4.6 `_excluded_to_channel()` para lookup em `direct_select`\n\nO `direct_select` procura o alvo tanto nos `eligible_channels` como nos `excluded_rows` da PUB. Para isso, `_excluded_to_channel()` converte entradas excluidas num formato channel-like compativel. Isto permite que o PM encontre um canal que foi excluido por falta de scripts mas que Tobias quer produzir na mesma.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Testes\n\n### Localizacao\n`runtime/tests/test_override.py`\n\n### Contagem\n- **15 testes** de validator (`TestOverrideValidator`)\n- **8 testes** de engine (3 classes: `TestSelectionEngineAutoSelect`, `TestSelectionEngineFilteredSelect`, `TestSelectionEngineDirectSelect`)\n- **3 testes** de integracao (`TestSelectionEngineIntegration`, marcados `@pytest.mark.integration`)\n- **Total novo:** 26 testes\n- **Total acumulado:** 70 testes (44 anteriores + 26 novos), todos passam\n\n### Cobertura por modo\n\n**`auto_select`:**\n| Teste | Validacao |\n|-------|-----------|\n| `test_auto_select_picks_most_urgent` | Escolhe C005 ING (runway -1), o mais urgente |\n| `test_auto_select_no_eligible` | Retorna `no_eligible_channels` quando PUB vazia |\n\n**`filtered_select`:**\n| Teste | Validacao |\n|-------|-----------|\n| `test_filtered_by_account` | Filtra por `allowed_accounts=[\"003\"]`, escolhe C003 |\n| `test_filtered_zero_candidates` | `allowed_accounts=[\"999\"]` → erro `no_eligible_in_subset`, NAO fallback |\n| `test_filtered_by_excluded` | `excluded_accounts=[\"005\"]` → escolhe outro que nao 005 |\n| `test_filtered_reduces_to_one` | `allowed_accounts=[\"002\"] + allowed_languages=[\"es\"]` → exactamente C002 ES |\n\n**`direct_select`:**\n| Teste | Validacao |\n|-------|-----------|\n| `test_direct_valid_target` | 003/fr resolve correctamente |\n| `test_direct_nonexistent_config` | 999/xx → erro `target_not_found` ou `config_not_found`, NAO escolhe outro |\n| `test_direct_with_warnings` | Canal excluido da PUB → job criado com warnings operacionais |\n\n**Validator (15 edge cases):**\n| Teste | Validacao |\n|-------|-----------|\n| `test_valid_auto_select` | Payload correcto aceite |\n| `test_valid_filtered_select` | Payload correcto aceite |\n| `test_valid_direct_select` | Payload correcto aceite |\n| `test_invalid_mode` | Modo invalido rejeitado |\n| `test_missing_mode` | Modo ausente rejeitado |\n| `test_missing_requested_by` | Campo obrigatorio ausente |\n| `test_filtered_without_constraints` | filtered_select sem constraints rejeitado |\n| `test_filtered_empty_constraints` | Constraints vazios rejeitados |\n| `test_direct_without_target` | direct_select sem target rejeitado |\n| `test_direct_missing_account` | Target sem account rejeitado |\n| `test_direct_missing_language` | Target sem language rejeitado |\n| `test_contradictory_constraints` | Mesmo account em allowed+excluded rejeitado |\n| `test_auto_with_constraints_warns` | auto_select com constraints = valido + warning |\n| `test_invalid_constraint_type` | `allowed_accounts=\"003\"` (string em vez de lista) rejeitado |\n| `test_not_a_dict` | Payload nao-dict rejeitado |\n\n**Integracao (3 testes, leitura real da PUB):**\n| Teste | Validacao |\n|-------|-----------|\n| `test_real_auto_select` | Seleccao real por runway |\n| `test_real_filtered_account_003` | Filtragem real por conta 003 |\n| `test_real_direct_003_fr` | Seleccao directa real de 003/fr |\n\n### Estrategia de mocking\n\nOs testes unitarios do engine usam `@patch(\"runtime.pm.selection_engine.read_pub\")` para substituir a leitura real da PUB. Os fixtures em `tests/fixtures/pm/pub_rows_valid.json` fornecem dados representativos. A funcao `_mock_pub_result()` normaliza esses fixtures usando o `normalize_pub_row()` real — o mock substitui apenas a leitura da sheet, nao a logica de normalizacao.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Contract reference\n\nO contrato formal que guia esta implementacao esta em:\n\n**`docs/contracts/pm_override_contract.md`**\n\nPontos chave do contrato:\n- PUB e verdade operacional, nao soberania estrategica\n- 3 modos: `auto_select`, `filtered_select`, `direct_select`\n- Prioridade: direct > filtered > auto\n- `filtered_select` com 0 candidatos: falha explicita, nunca fallback silencioso\n- `direct_select` com alvo invalido: falha explicita, nunca escolhe outro\n- Shape do override payload com campos `mode`, `reason`, `constraints`, `direct_target`, `requested_by`, `created_at`\n\n---\n\n## 7. Resultado E2E real (30 Mar 2026)\n\nTestes de integracao executados contra a PUB real:\n\n```\nCaso A: \"Escolhe o mais urgente\"\n  → auto_select\n  → C004 FRA (runway -17)\n  → job valido ✓\n\nCaso B: \"So conta 03 hoje\"\n  → filtered_select (allowed_accounts=[\"003\"])\n  → C003 ING (runway -14)\n  → job valido ✓\n\nCaso C: \"Produz 003 fr\"\n  → direct_select (account=\"003\", language=\"fr\")\n  → C003 FRA\n  → job valido ✓\n```\n\nOs tres modos funcionam end-to-end contra dados reais.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Ambiguidades restantes\n\n### 8.1 `monetized_only` — sem implementacao real\n\nO constraint `monetized_only` e aceite pelo validator e descrito pelo `_describe_constraints()`, mas nao ha campo de monetizacao nos YAMLs de configuracao nem na PUB. A filtragem real nao e aplicada. Quando os dados de monetizacao forem adicionados, bastara adicionar logica no post-filtro do `_filtered_select()`.\n\n### 8.2 Override expiry/lifetime\n\nFora de escopo v1. Um override nao tem tempo de vida definido. Quando um override e processado, ele e consumido uma vez. Nao ha persistencia, rotacao, ou expiracao automatica.\n\n### 8.3 NL parsing\n\nFora de escopo v1. O contrato menciona `override_parser.py` como futuro modulo para converter linguagem natural (\"so conta 03 hoje\") em override payload estruturado. Nao implementado.\n\n### 8.4 Canal de comunicacao Tobias → PM\n\nComo o Tobias envia o override ao PM na pratica ainda nao esta definido. Opcoes possiveis:\n- JSON directo como input do script\n- Telegram bot → JSON → PM\n- Ficheiro `override.json` lido no arranque\n- API endpoint\n\nTBD para futuras versoes.\n\n### 8.5 Multi-step campaign scheduling\n\nFora de escopo v1. O contrato menciona isto como nao-objectivo. Um override produz um unico job. Sequencias de producao (\"faz 5 videos da conta 003 esta semana\") requerem orquestracao adicional.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775050101127}}
{"type":"message","id":"fff05535","parentId":"0e07ff76","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:28:21.498Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_7Eor5AZdRMnLTwrzueqI2mKF|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1d7207b881908a2b363b345292b6","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PM — Notas de Integracao\n\n_Notas praticas para quem vai trabalhar com o PM substrate._\n\n---\n\n## Service Account\n\n- **Path canonico**: `C:\\secrets\\content_factory\\google_service_account.json`\n- **Origem**: Copiada de `content_factory_v3/credentials/google_service_account.json` (SA do V3)\n- **ATENCAO**: As SAs em `content_factory/setup_files/` e `content_factory_pro/credentials/` estao MORTAS (Google suspendeu em 24 Mar 2026). NAO usar.\n- **Permissoes**: Leitura na PUB sheet. Escrita NAO necessaria para o PM.\n\n## PUB Sheet\n\n- **Sheet ID**: `1XL6VhOTVVMmfGNqPyJra2T8KjfFbtJ1o16OZkytvCPc`\n- **Tab**: `PUB`\n- **Colunas relevantes** (0-indexed no codigo):\n  - Index 1 (Col B) = `ULT PUB` — data do ultimo video programado\n  - Index 5 (Col F) = `PROGRAMAR` — videos prontos nao uploaded\n  - Index 9 (Col J) = `PROD` — SIM/NAO\n  - Index 14 (Col O) = `SCRIPTS` — formato \"used/total\" (ex: \"38/57\")\n\n## Registry\n\n- **Path**: `auto_content_factory/accounts/registry.yaml`\n- **Conteudo**: 39 canais, 7 accounts (001-008 sem 007)\n- **Cada canal tem YAML individual**: `accounts/{account}/{language}.yaml`\n- **pub_row**: presente em cada YAML individual (linha na PUB sheet, 1-indexed)\n\n## Dependencias Python\n\n```\ngspread>=6.0.0\ngoogle-auth>=2.0.0\npyyaml>=6.0\npytest>=7.0 (dev)\n```\n\ngspread 6.2.1 ja esta instalado no sistema.\n\n## Como Correr Testes\n\n```bash\n# Todos os testes unitarios (sem tocar na sheet real)\ncd auto_content_factory\npython -m pytest runtime/tests/ -v -m \"not integration\"\n\n# Testes de integracao (leitura real da PUB sheet)\npython -m pytest runtime/tests/ -v -m integration -s\n\n# Teste E2E rapido dos 3 modos\npython -c \"\nfrom runtime.pm.selection_engine import select_and_build_job\nr = select_and_build_job({'mode': 'auto_select', 'reason': 'test', 'constraints': None, 'direct_target': None, 'requested_by': 'tobias', 'created_at': ''})\nprint(f'auto: {r[\\\"job\\\"][\\\"channel_name\\\"]} runway={r[\\\"job\\\"][\\\"runway_days\\\"]}')\n\"\n```\n\n## Edge Cases Descobertos\n\n1. **Encoding Windows**: `print()` com caracteres Unicode (coreano, japones) falha com cp1252. Solucao: `sys.stdout = io.TextIOWrapper(sys.stdout.buffer, encoding='utf-8')`\n2. **SAs mortas**: Ambas as SAs em setup_files e content_factory_pro estao suspensas. So a do V3 funciona.\n3. **PROGRAMAR vazio**: Tratado como 0 (zero videos prontos), canal continua elegivel se outros campos OK.\n4. **Runway negativo**: Valido e indica urgencia/deficit. C004 FRA tinha runway -17 em 30 Mar 2026.\n5. **C001 PT**: Unico canal excluido — scripts esgotados (57/57).\n\n## Resultado Real (30 Mar 2026)\n\n- 38 canais elegiveis\n- 1 excluido (C001 PT — scripts esgotados)\n- 0 erros de parsing\n- Top 3 mais urgentes: C004 FRA (-17), C004 JAP (-17), C004 PT (-16)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775050101313}}
{"type":"message","id":"4b9f5f6f","parentId":"fff05535","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:29:03.151Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_DixvFVy4OUrN5p63VKu06H9L|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1da08f888190b44fe5859c75167b","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\implementation\\pm\\PM_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md","content":"# PM_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md\n\n_Status: active implementation checkpoint_\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis document captures the real implementation status of the Production Manager (PM) during the OpenClaw migration effort.\n\nIt is not the same thing as the formal contracts.\nIts role is to answer:\n- what already exists in PM today\n- what is canonical vs incomplete\n- what has been materially validated\n- what is still missing before PM should be called fully realized as an OpenClaw agent\n\n---\n\n## Executive summary\n\nThe PM is currently best described as:\n\n> **substrate-strong, agent-not-yet-realized**\n\nThat means:\n- the deterministic PM core is materially implemented\n- mode-aware selection logic exists\n- real PUB integration has already worked\n- canonical job construction/validation exists\n- PM contracts are now much better organized\n\nBut it also means:\n- PM is not yet a real OpenClaw workspace/agent\n- PM is not yet registered as a runnable OpenClaw agent\n- PM -> VO exists strongly as substrate/handoff design, not yet as OpenClaw runtime embodiment\n\n---\n\n## Canonical role\n\nPM is the upstream production-selection supervisor.\n\nIts job is to:\n- read operational production state from PUB\n- apply strategic override rules from Tobias\n- select or materialize the correct production target\n- build a canonical PM job\n- validate that job\n- hand that validated job to VO\n\nPM is not the owner of:\n- run bootstrap\n- script fetch/lock\n- S1 execution\n\n---\n\n## Current runtime reality\n\n### Deterministic PM substrate exists\nThe following runtime modules are already present and materially useful:\n- `read_pub.py`\n- `pub_row_normalizer.py`\n- `override_validator.py`\n- `selection_engine.py`\n- `job_builder.py`\n- `job_validator.py`\n\n### Practical meaning\nThe PM already has a real deterministic decision substrate for:\n- PUB ingestion\n- row normalization\n- urgency calculation\n- override validation\n- mode-aware target resolution\n- job construction\n- job validation\n\nThis is not a vague placeholder. It is real substrate.\n\n---\n\n## Contracts status\n\n### Current canonical PM contracts\nNow organized under:\n- `docs/contracts/pm/`\n\nCurrent set:\n- `pm_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `pm_read_pub_contract.md`\n- `pm_override_contract.md`\n- `pm_selection_engine_contract.md`\n- `pm_job_builder_contract.md`\n- `pm_job_validator_contract.md`\n- `pm_to_vo_handoff_contract.md`\n\n### Meaning\nPM now has the same kind of contract decomposition discipline that S1 received.\n\nThis is important because the next move is no longer to “discover what PM sort of is”, but to bind these contracts to a real OpenClaw embodiment.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation docs from prior phase\n\nThe repo also contains older but still useful implementation documents:\n- `01_substrate_v1.md`\n- `02_override_modes_v1.md`\n- `03_integration_notes.md`\n\nThese are useful as implementation history and evidence of prior real validation.\nThey should not automatically be treated as the sole canonical source of truth going forward.\n\nThis `PM_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md` is intended to become the cleaner status bridge between contracts and implementation reality.\n\n---\n\n## What is already materially validated\n\nAt this point, the strongest claims we can make are:\n- PUB ingestion exists and was previously validated against the real sheet\n- mode-aware PM selection exists (`auto_select`, `filtered_select`, `direct_select`)\n- canonical job construction exists\n- canonical job validation exists\n- PM -> VO handoff artifact is conceptually and structurally clear\n- PM contract structure is now much more coherent\n\n---\n\n## What is not yet wise to claim\n\nIt is still too strong to say:\n- PM is already a real OpenClaw supervisor in runtime reality\n- PM already runs through a dedicated OpenClaw workspace\n- PM -> VO runtime wiring is already fully embodied in OpenClaw agent form\n\nThose things are not yet true.\n\n---\n\n## OpenClaw reality status\n\n### Current state\nAt the time of this checkpoint:\n- there is no PM workspace under `~/.openclaw/agents/`\n- there is no PM entry in `openclaw agents list`\n- there is no PM OpenClaw identity/workflow/agent directory yet\n\n### Meaning\nPM is currently stronger as repo/runtime substrate than as OpenClaw agent reality.\n\n---\n\n## Main gaps before PM is considered “100%”\n\n1. Create the PM OpenClaw workspace\n2. Define the PM OpenClaw identity/workflow docs\n3. Register PM as a real OpenClaw agent\n4. Set PM model to `gpt-5.4-mini`\n5. Bind PM supervisor behavior to the existing deterministic substrate\n6. Validate PM -> VO in a controlled runtime path\n\n---\n\n## Strategic implication\n\nThe PM no longer needs “inventing from zero”.\nIt needs:\n- embodiment\n- binding\n- runtime realization\n- downstream integration with VO\n\nThat is a much better place to be.\n\n---\n\n## Recommended next steps\n\n1. Resolve old root-level PM contract duplicates to avoid ambiguity\n2. Create the PM OpenClaw workspace\n3. Register PM as an OpenClaw agent using `gpt-5.4-mini`\n4. Give PM a clean operator/supervisor identity that invokes the deterministic substrate\n5. After that, move to VO and repeat the same discipline\n6. Then test `PM -> VO -> S1`\n\n---\n\n## Final summary\n\nPM already has serious substance.\nThe missing work is no longer “how should PM think?” in the abstract.\n\nThe missing work is:\n- turning PM into a real OpenClaw supervisor entity\n- wiring it cleanly to VO\n- then proving the integrated path under runtime conditions\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\implementation\\\\pm\\\\PM_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md\",\"content\":\"# PM_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md\\n\\n_Status: active implementation checkpoint_\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThis document captures the real implementation status of the Production Manager (PM) during the OpenClaw migration effort.\\n\\nIt is not the same thing as the formal contracts.\\nIts role is to answer:\\n- what already exists in PM today\\n- what is canonical vs incomplete\\n- what has been materially validated\\n- what is still missing before PM should be called fully realized as an OpenClaw agent\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Executive summary\\n\\nThe PM is currently best described as:\\n\\n> **substrate-strong, agent-not-yet-realized**\\n\\nThat means:\\n- the deterministic PM core is materially implemented\\n- mode-aware selection logic exists\\n- real PUB integration has already worked\\n- canonical job construction/validation exists\\n- PM contracts are now much better organized\\n\\nBut it also means:\\n- PM is not yet a real OpenClaw workspace/agent\\n- PM is not yet registered as a runnable OpenClaw agent\\n- PM -> VO exists strongly as substrate/handoff design, not yet as OpenClaw runtime embodiment\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical role\\n\\nPM is the upstream production-selection supervisor.\\n\\nIts job is to:\\n- read operational production state from PUB\\n- apply strategic override rules from Tobias\\n- select or materialize the correct production target\\n- build a canonical PM job\\n- validate that job\\n- hand that validated job to VO\\n\\nPM is not the owner of:\\n- run bootstrap\\n- script fetch/lock\\n- S1 execution\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current runtime reality\\n\\n### Deterministic PM substrate exists\\nThe following runtime modules are already present and materially useful:\\n- `read_pub.py`\\n- `pub_row_normalizer.py`\\n- `override_validator.py`\\n- `selection_engine.py`\\n- `job_builder.py`\\n- `job_validator.py`\\n\\n### Practical meaning\\nThe PM already has a real deterministic decision substrate for:\\n- PUB ingestion\\n- row normalization\\n- urgency calculation\\n- override validation\\n- mode-aware target resolution\\n- job construction\\n- job validation\\n\\nThis is not a vague placeholder. It is real substrate.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Contracts status\\n\\n### Current canonical PM contracts\\nNow organized under:\\n- `docs/contracts/pm/`\\n\\nCurrent set:\\n- `pm_supervisor_contract.md`\\n- `pm_read_pub_contract.md`\\n- `pm_override_contract.md`\\n- `pm_selection_engine_contract.md`\\n- `pm_job_builder_contract.md`\\n- `pm_job_validator_contract.md`\\n- `pm_to_vo_handoff_contract.md`\\n\\n### Meaning\\nPM now has the same kind of contract decomposition discipline that S1 received.\\n\\nThis is important because the next move is no longer to “discover what PM sort of is”, but to bind these contracts to a real OpenClaw embodiment.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Implementation docs from prior phase\\n\\nThe repo also contains older but still useful implementation documents:\\n- `01_substrate_v1.md`\\n- `02_override_modes_v1.md`\\n- `03_integration_notes.md`\\n\\nThese are useful as implementation history and evidence of prior real validation.\\nThey should not automatically be treated as the sole canonical source of truth going forward.\\n\\nThis `PM_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md` is intended to become the cleaner status bridge between contracts and implementation reality.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## What is already materially validated\\n\\nAt this point, the strongest claims we can make are:\\n- PUB ingestion exists and was previously validated against the real sheet\\n- mode-aware PM selection exists (`auto_select`, `filtered_select`, `direct_select`)\\n- canonical job construction exists\\n- canonical job validation exists\\n- PM -> VO handoff artifact is conceptually and structurally clear\\n- PM contract structure is now much more coherent\\n\\n---\\n\\n## What is not yet wise to claim\\n\\nIt is still too strong to say:\\n- PM is already a real OpenClaw supervisor in runtime reality\\n- PM already runs through a dedicated OpenClaw workspace\\n- PM -> VO runtime wiring is already fully embodied in OpenClaw agent form\\n\\nThose things are not yet true.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## OpenClaw reality status\\n\\n### Current state\\nAt the time of this checkpoint:\\n- there is no PM workspace under `~/.openclaw/agents/`\\n- there is no PM entry in `openclaw agents list`\\n- there is no PM OpenClaw identity/workflow/agent directory yet\\n\\n### Meaning\\nPM is currently stronger as repo/runtime substrate than as OpenClaw agent reality.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Main gaps before PM is considered “100%”\\n\\n1. Create the PM OpenClaw workspace\\n2. Define the PM OpenClaw identity/workflow docs\\n3. Register PM as a real OpenClaw agent\\n4. Set PM model to `gpt-5.4-mini`\\n5. Bind PM supervisor behavior to the existing deterministic substrate\\n6. Validate PM -> VO in a controlled runtime path\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Strategic implication\\n\\nThe PM no longer needs “inventing from zero”.\\nIt needs:\\n- embodiment\\n- binding\\n- runtime realization\\n- downstream integration with VO\\n\\nThat is a much better place to be.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Recommended next steps\\n\\n1. Resolve old root-level PM contract duplicates to avoid ambiguity\\n2. Create the PM OpenClaw workspace\\n3. Register PM as an OpenClaw agent using `gpt-5.4-mini`\\n4. Give PM a clean operator/supervisor identity that invokes the deterministic substrate\\n5. After that, move to VO and repeat the same discipline\\n6. Then test `PM -> VO -> S1`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Final summary\\n\\nPM already has serious substance.\\nThe missing work is no longer “how should PM think?” in the abstract.\\n\\nThe missing work is:\\n- turning PM into a real OpenClaw supervisor entity\\n- wiring it cleanly to VO\\n- then proving the integrated path under runtime conditions\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":152125,"output":1404,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":156089,"cost":{"input":0.38031250000000005,"output":0.02106,"cacheRead":0.0006399999999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.40201250000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775050102022,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd1d7853e081908ad5ff2f2119bfb1"}}
