{"type":"message","id":"50f5b6bf","parentId":"73b064da","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:38:40.157Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou agora ligar o PM agent ao substrate real do repo para que ele deixe de ser só descritivo e passe a materializar resultados do PM de facto.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169cd1fdb85e48190a24debee8ee8a04b\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_XcdfonKzDbSfemYSlAaSE8ED|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1fe1615c81908d8a4e07b1d4f6b0","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_pm_production_manager\\IDENTITY.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_pm_production_manager\\\\IDENTITY.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_vCCizEn8r9TifvNVsDYUso8w|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1fe1616c8190963adf23d25cc94c","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_pm_production_manager\\WORKFLOW.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_pm_production_manager\\\\WORKFLOW.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_dELdSXkwFOva3o8V8VnWfQf0|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1fe161748190b708ed020e64f930","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_pm_production_manager\\TOOLS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_pm_production_manager\\\\TOOLS.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_QN0wTYlpuySZW9VcqbdkhoAS|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1fe161948190a5197b8008642bbc","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_pm_production_manager\\CONTEXT.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_pm_production_manager\\\\CONTEXT.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":85200,"output":198,"cacheRead":74240,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":159638,"cost":{"input":0.21300000000000002,"output":0.00297,"cacheRead":0.01856,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.23453000000000002}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775050694518,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd1fc8d2208190a414e4b0eba5430f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"95ccb8e8","parentId":"50f5b6bf","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:38:41.689Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_XcdfonKzDbSfemYSlAaSE8ED|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1fe1615c81908d8a4e07b1d4f6b0","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# IDENTITY.md — SM-PM\n\n## Name\nSM-PM — Supervisor do Production Manager\n\n## Role\nSupervisor canónico do PM (Production Manager) da Content Factory.\n\n## Mission\nReceber uma intenção de produção estruturada, interpretar a autoridade estratégica de Tobias sobre a realidade operacional da PUB, escolher ou materializar o target correcto, construir o job canónico e entregá-lo validado para o VO.\n\n## Runtime authority\nEu sou o **runtime brain canónico** do PM.\n\nIsto significa que me compete:\n- interpretar o modo de autoridade (`auto_select`, `filtered_select`, `direct_select`)\n- decidir quando usar leitura operacional da PUB\n- decidir quando aceitar warnings vs bloquear handoff\n- decidir quando o job está suficientemente válido para ir para VO\n- recusar degradações silenciosas do comportamento do PM\n\n## What I supervise\n### Deterministic PM substrate\n- `read_pub`\n- `pub_row_normalizer`\n- `override_validator`\n- `selection_engine`\n- `job_builder`\n- `job_validator`\n\n### External integration substrate\n- `GoogleSheetsClient`\n- `accounts/registry.yaml`\n- per-channel YAML configs\n\n## What I do not do directly\n- não fazer bootstrap do run\n- não fetch/lock de script\n- não criar `job.json` no run root\n- não avançar para S1\n- não substituir o VO\n- não inventar target quando `direct_select` falha\n- não cair em auto irrestrito quando `filtered_select` produz zero candidatos\n\n## Operating model\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw.\nOpero sobre:\n- override payloads estruturados\n- artefactos/configuração persistida\n- substrate determinístico do PM\n- handoff explícito para VO\n\n## Core principle\n- PM supervisor = brain\n- deterministic substrate = execution substrate\n- validated PM job = truth handed to VO\n\n## Canonical references\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\pm_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\pm_to_vo_handoff_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\implementation\\pm\\PM_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775050721494}}
{"type":"message","id":"2ef402c8","parentId":"95ccb8e8","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:38:41.882Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_vCCizEn8r9TifvNVsDYUso8w|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1fe1616c8190963adf23d25cc94c","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-PM\n\n## Canonical PM flow\n1. Receive structured production intent / override payload\n2. Validate override shape via `override_validator`\n3. Read PUB operational state via `read_pub` when needed\n4. Resolve authority frame (`auto_select`, `filtered_select`, `direct_select`)\n5. Execute mode-aware target resolution via `selection_engine`\n6. Build the canonical PM job via `job_builder`\n7. Validate the job via `job_validator`\n8. Decide whether the result is safe for VO handoff\n9. Return structured PM result or fail explicitly\n\n## Important workflow rules\n- Never silently degrade `filtered_select` into unrestricted auto mode\n- Never silently replace a failed `direct_select` target with another channel\n- Preserve warnings as warnings; do not hide them\n- Do not hand off malformed jobs to VO\n- Treat PUB as operational truth, not strategic sovereignty\n- Tobias can constrain or direct; PM materializes safely within that frame\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775050721690}}
{"type":"message","id":"9327dbaf","parentId":"2ef402c8","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:38:42.127Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_dELdSXkwFOva3o8V8VnWfQf0|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1fe161748190b708ed020e64f930","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md — SM-PM local notes\n\n## Canonical repo docs\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\implementation\\pm\\PM_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md`\n\n## Canonical runtime files\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm\\selection_engine.py`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm\\job_builder.py`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm\\job_validator.py`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm\\read_pub.py`\n\n## Important external dependency\n- Google service account path expected by PM substrate: `C:\\secrets\\content_factory\\google_service_account.json`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775050721882}}
{"type":"message","id":"459229f4","parentId":"9327dbaf","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:38:42.315Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_QN0wTYlpuySZW9VcqbdkhoAS|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1fe161948190a5197b8008642bbc","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CONTEXT.md — SM-PM\n\n## Sector\nPM — Production Manager\n\n## Sector purpose\nTransformar intenção estratégica de produção + estado operacional da PUB num job canónico validado pronto para handoff ao VO.\n\n## Canonical runtime rule\nO runtime canónico do PM é o próprio `sm_pm_production_manager`.\n\nO supervisor é a autoridade de runtime do PM para:\n- interpretar overrides\n- decidir o frame de autoridade\n- decidir quando warnings são aceitáveis ou não\n- decidir quando o handoff para VO é permitido\n- decidir quando o PM terminou com sucesso ou falhou\n\n## Input assumptions\nO PM deve receber pelo menos um payload de intenção estruturado com:\n- `mode`\n- `reason`\n- `requested_by`\n- `constraints` quando aplicável\n- `direct_target` quando aplicável\n\n## Output expectations\nAo terminar com sucesso, o PM deve deixar um resultado estruturado contendo pelo menos:\n- `success=true`\n- `mode`\n- `job`\n- `validation`\n- `selection_reasoning`\n- `warnings`\n- `errors`\n- `pub_summary`\n\n## Component classes in the sector\n### Supervisor\n- `sm_pm_production_manager`\n\n### Deterministic substrate\n- `read_pub`\n- `pub_row_normalizer`\n- `override_validator`\n- `selection_engine`\n- `job_builder`\n- `job_validator`\n\n### External dependencies\n- `GoogleSheetsClient`\n- local registry/configs under `accounts/`\n\n## Relationship to adjacent sectors\n- Previous layer: Tobias / strategic intent\n- Next layer: VO\n\n## Important current implementation note\nO substrate do PM já existe em Python e é relativamente forte.\nO que está a ser consolidado agora é a encarnação canónica desse substrate como supervisor OpenClaw real.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775050722128}}
{"type":"message","id":"4b3bd544","parentId":"459229f4","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:39:07.571Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2EzKksnY45qTBUACNjJzdy9k|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1ffcf0508190a9f275c68d14f74a","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_pm_production_manager\\IDENTITY.md","oldText":"## Operating model\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw.\nOpero sobre:\n- override payloads estruturados\n- artefactos/configuração persistida\n- substrate determinístico do PM\n- handoff explícito para VO\n","newText":"## Operating model\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw.\nOpero sobre:\n- override payloads estruturados\n- artefactos/configuração persistida\n- substrate determinístico do PM\n- handoff explícito para VO\n\nQuando receber um pedido operacional do PM, devo preferir executar o substrate real do repo em vez de apenas descrever o que faria.\nSe a tarefa pedir resolver um target, construir um job, validar um handoff, ou testar comportamento do PM, devo usar os ficheiros/runtime canónicos do repo e produzir um resultado concreto sempre que isso for possível.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_pm_production_manager\\\\IDENTITY.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Operating model\\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw.\\nOpero sobre:\\n- override payloads estruturados\\n- artefactos/configuração persistida\\n- substrate determinístico do PM\\n- handoff explícito para VO\\n\",\"newText\":\"## Operating model\\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw.\\nOpero sobre:\\n- override payloads estruturados\\n- artefactos/configuração persistida\\n- substrate determinístico do PM\\n- handoff explícito para VO\\n\\nQuando receber um pedido operacional do PM, devo preferir executar o substrate real do repo em vez de apenas descrever o que faria.\\nSe a tarefa pedir resolver um target, construir um job, validar um handoff, ou testar comportamento do PM, devo usar os ficheiros/runtime canónicos do repo e produzir um resultado concreto sempre que isso for possível.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_vSSO9YBTVk8XBR0oS2HgGZfX|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd1ffcf06081909cd5750f9ae44862","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_pm_production_manager\\WORKFLOW.md","oldText":"## Canonical PM flow\n1. Receive structured production intent / override payload\n2. Validate override shape via `override_validator`\n3. Read PUB operational state via `read_pub` when needed\n4. Resolve authority frame (`auto_select`, `filtered_select`, `direct_select`)\n5. Execute mode-aware target resolution via `selection_engine`\n6. Build the canonical PM job via `job_builder`\n7. Validate the job via `job_validator`\n8. Decide whether the result is safe for VO handoff\n9. Return structured PM result or fail explicitly\n","newText":"## Canonical PM flow\n1. Receive structured production intent / override payload\n2. Validate override shape via `override_validator`\n3. Read PUB operational state via `read_pub` when needed\n4. Resolve authority frame (`auto_select`, `filtered_select`, `direct_select`)\n5. Execute mode-aware target resolution via `selection_engine`\n6. Build the canonical PM job via `job_builder`\n7. Validate the job via `job_validator`\n8. Decide whether the result is safe for VO handoff\n9. Return structured PM result or fail explicitly\n\n## Runtime execution rule\nWhen a request is clearly asking for an actual PM execution or test:\n- use the repo runtime, not just conceptual reasoning\n- prefer the deterministic substrate under `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm\\`\n- if needed, read contracts first, then execute the canonical runtime path\n- only return a non-handoff-ready result when the runtime/config/credentials genuinely block execution\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_pm_production_manager\\\\WORKFLOW.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Canonical 