{"type":"message","id":"30e2296e","parentId":"29f264fa","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:53:45.729Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3CswaSqqMlMCOBa1tQ2tivUG|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a088190bf5a670be80c9add","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\job_input_validator.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\vo\\\\job_input_validator.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_OqrT7DAB29TVlYIAWxNQ3f1M|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a148190ab18de8548904d62","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\script_fetcher.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\vo\\\\script_fetcher.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_g8LwAIYZxAgERsIc7jsD6nqB|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a1c8190a7d4e27cd3e41e40","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\script_locker.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\vo\\\\script_locker.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_S0Uy23BHIAx30S5eHUtSYEOA|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a2481908656cf553f49e5e5","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\run_metadata_writer.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\vo\\\\run_metadata_writer.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_pvuVo4SDny8kOftqgSVEqwbO|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a2c8190af4d88d3e127e627","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\checkpoint_initializer.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\vo\\\\checkpoint_initializer.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6lqCC0VOp7tuG506AesKGQP7|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a348190be523ed2204a576e","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\script_metadata_writer.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\vo\\\\script_metadata_writer.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_XIrRqp01fSkOcIWZWfF9VRQS|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a3c819092eaf4fd1f3e59f8","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\script_checkpoint_writer.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\vo\\\\script_checkpoint_writer.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":197,"output":285,"cacheRead":163072,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":163554,"cost":{"input":0.0004925,"output":0.004275,"cacheRead":0.040768,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0455355}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775051613478,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd23604aa481908a78ec65f24b1444"}}
{"type":"message","id":"e34564d6","parentId":"30e2296e","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:53:47.761Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3CswaSqqMlMCOBa1tQ2tivUG|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a088190bf5a670be80c9add","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"VO Job Input Validator — validates PM job from VO perspective.\n\nIf validation fails, VO must NOT create any run directory.\nReturns structured errors for debugging.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\n# Fields that must exist and be non-empty strings\nREQUIRED_STRING_FIELDS = [\n    \"job_id\",\n    \"account\",\n    \"language\",\n    \"channel_name\",\n    \"sheet_scripts_id\",\n    \"sheet_tracking_id\",\n    \"drive_folder_id\",\n    \"v3_config\",\n    \"created_at\",\n]\n\n# All required fields (pub_row can be int or None)\nREQUIRED_FIELDS = REQUIRED_STRING_FIELDS + [\"pub_row\"]\n\n\ndef validate_job_input(job: dict[str, Any]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Validate a PM job as VO input.\n\n    Returns:\n        {\n            \"valid\": bool,\n            \"errors\": [{\"code\": str, \"field\": str, \"message\": str}, ...]\n        }\n    \"\"\"\n    errors: list[dict[str, str]] = []\n\n    # Check required fields exist\n    for field in REQUIRED_FIELDS:\n        if field not in job:\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"missing_field\",\n                \"field\": field,\n                \"message\": f\"Required field '{field}' is missing\",\n            })\n\n    # If critical fields missing, return early\n    if errors:\n        return {\"valid\": False, \"errors\": errors}\n\n    # Check required string fields are non-empty strings\n    for field in REQUIRED_STRING_FIELDS:\n        val = job.get(field)\n        if not isinstance(val, str) or not val.strip():\n            errors.append({\n                \"code\": \"empty_or_invalid_type\",\n                \"field\": field,\n                \"message\": f\"Field '{field}' must be a non-empty string, got: {type(val).__name__}={val!r}\",\n            })\n\n    # pub_row type check (must be int if present, can be None)\n    pub_row = job.get(\"pub_row\")\n    if pub_row is not None and not isinstance(pub_row, int):\n        errors.append({\n            \"code\": \"invalid_type\",\n            \"field\": \"pub_row\",\n            \"message\": f\"pub_row must be int or None, got: {type(pub_row).__name__}\",\n        })\n\n    return {\n        \"valid\": len(errors) == 0,\n        \"errors\": errors,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775051627581}}
{"type":"message","id":"6dcd665a","parentId":"e34564d6","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:53:47.943Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_OqrT7DAB29TVlYIAWxNQ3f1M|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a148190ab18de8548904d62","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"VO Script Fetcher — finds first eligible script from scripts sheet.\n\nFollows V3 semantics: first row where Status = \"to do\".\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\nfrom runtime.integrations.google_sheets import GoogleSheetsClient\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\n\ndef fetch_eligible_script(\n    sheet_scripts_id: str,\n    sheet_scripts_name: str,\n    credential_path: Optional[Path] = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Find first script with Status = 'to do'.\n\n    Returns:\n        {\"found\": True, \"row_number\": int, \"title\": str, \"description\": str,\n         \"script\": str, \"id\": str, \"status\": str}\n        or {\"found\": False, \"reason\": \"no_eligible_scripts\"}\n    \"\"\"\n    client = GoogleSheetsClient(credential_path=credential_path)\n    records = client.read_worksheet(sheet_scripts_id, sheet_scripts_name)\n\n    for idx, record in enumerate(records, start=2):  # Row 2 onwards (row 1 is header)\n        status = str(record.get(\"Status\", \"\")).strip().lower()\n        if status == \"to do\":\n            script_text = str(record.get(\"Script\", \"\")).strip()\n            if not script_text:\n                continue  # Skip rows with empty script\n\n            return {\n                \"found\": True,\n                \"row_number\": idx,\n                \"id\": str(record.get(\"ID\", \"\")).strip(),\n                \"title\": str(record.get(\"Title\", \"\")).strip(),\n                \"description\": str(record.get(\"Description\", \"\")).strip(),\n                \"script\": script_text,\n                \"status\": \"to do\",\n            }\n\n    return {\"found\": False, \"reason\": \"no_eligible_scripts\"}\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775051627762}}
{"type":"message","id":"edb085ed","parentId":"6dcd665a","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:53:48.158Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_g8LwAIYZxAgERsIc7jsD6nqB|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a1c8190a7d4e27cd3e41e40","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"VO Script Locker — applies lock on scripts sheet.\n\nV3 semantics: update Status to 'processing', write Processing_Started timestamp.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom typing import Any, Optional\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nimport gspread\nfrom google.oauth2.service_account import Credentials\n\nWRITE_SCOPES = [\n    \"https://www.googleapis.com/auth/spreadsheets\",\n    \"https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive\",\n]\n\nDEFAULT_CREDENTIAL_PATH = Path(r\"C:\\secrets\\content_factory\\google_service_account.json\")\n\n\ndef _get_write_client(credential_path: Optional[Path] = None) -> gspread.Client:\n    \"\"\"Build a gspread client with write scopes.\"\"\"\n    cred_path = Path(credential_path or DEFAULT_CREDENTIAL_PATH)\n    if not cred_path.exists():\n        raise FileNotFoundError(f\"Credentials not found: {cred_path}\")\n    credentials = Credentials.from_service_account_file(\n        str(cred_path), scopes=WRITE_SCOPES\n    )\n    return gspread.authorize(credentials)\n\n\ndef lock_script_row(\n    sheet_scripts_id: str,\n    sheet_scripts_name: str,\n    row_number: int,\n    credential_path: Optional[Path] = None,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Lock a script row by updating Status to 'processing'.\n\n    Returns:\n        {\"locked\": True, \"row_number\": int, \"locked_at\": str}\n        or {\"locked\": False, \"error\": str}\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        client = _get_write_client(credential_path)\n        spreadsheet = client.open_by_key(sheet_scripts_id)\n        worksheet = spreadsheet.worksheet(sheet_scripts_name)\n    except Exception as e:\n        return {\"locked\": False, \"error\": f\"Could not open sheet: {e}\"}\n\n    timestamp = datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()\n\n    # Update Status (column E) to 'processing'\n    try:\n        worksheet.update(f\"E{row_number}\", [[\"processing\"]])\n    except Exception as e:\n        return {\"locked\": False, \"error\": f\"Could not update Status: {e}\"}\n\n    # Update Processing_Started (column F) with timestamp\n    try:\n        worksheet.update(f\"F{row_number}\", [[timestamp]])\n    except Exception as e:\n        # Non-fatal: log warning but lock is still applied\n        pass\n\n    return {\n        \"locked\": True,\n        \"row_number\": row_number,\n        \"locked_at\": timestamp,\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775051627943}}
{"type":"message","id":"c01b5e9f","parentId":"edb085ed","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:53:48.342Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_S0Uy23BHIAx30S5eHUtSYEOA|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a2481908656cf553f49e5e5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"VO Run Metadata Writer — writes run_metadata.json to the run directory.\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef write_run_metadata(\n    video_root: Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Write run_metadata.json to the video root.\n\n    Args:\n        video_root: Path to the run directory.\n        job: Validated PM job dict.\n\n    Returns:\n        Absolute path to the written run_metadata.json.\n    \"\"\"\n    metadata = {\n        \"job_id\": job[\"job_id\"],\n        \"account\": job[\"account\"],\n        \"language\": job[\"language\"],\n        \"channel_name\": job[\"channel_name\"],\n        \"status\": \"initialized\",\n        \"current_stage\": \"vo_bootstrap\",\n        \"started_at\": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),\n        \"started_by\": \"vo_minimal\",\n        \"job_source\": \"pm_job\",\n        \"paths\": {\n            \"job_json\": str(video_root / \"job.json\"),\n            \"checkpoints\": str(video_root / \"checkpoints\"),\n            \"inputs\": str(video_root / \"inputs\"),\n            \"outputs\": str(video_root / \"outputs\"),\n            \"logs\": str(video_root / \"logs\"),\n            \"sectors\": str(video_root / \"sectors\"),\n        },\n    }\n\n    metadata_path = video_root / \"run_metadata.json\"\n    metadata_path.write_text(json.dumps(metadata, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return str(metadata_path)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775051628158}}
{"type":"message","id":"68508416","parentId":"c01b5e9f","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:53:48.523Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_pvuVo4SDny8kOftqgSVEqwbO|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a2c8190af4d88d3e127e627","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"VO Checkpoint Initializer — writes checkpoints/vo_init.json.\n\nRules:\n- Do NOT mark any sector as complete.\n- Do NOT invent progress.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef write_initial_checkpoint(\n    video_root: Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Write the initial checkpoint file.\n\n    Args:\n        video_root: Path to the run directory.\n        job: Validated PM job dict.\n\n    Returns:\n        Absolute path to the written vo_init.json.\n    \"\"\"\n    checkpoint = {\n        \"job_id\": job[\"job_id\"],\n        \"status\": \"initialized\",\n        \"current_stage\": \"vo_bootstrap\",\n        \"sectors_completed\": [],\n        \"next_step\": \"ready_for_script_fetch\",\n        \"created_at\": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),\n    }\n\n    checkpoint_path = video_root / \"checkpoints\" / \"vo_init.json\"\n    checkpoint_path.write_text(json.dumps(checkpoint, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return str(checkpoint_path)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775051628342}}
{"type":"message","id":"cf9d4381","parentId":"68508416","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:53:48.704Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_6lqCC0VOp7tuG506AesKGQP7|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a348190be523ed2204a576e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"VO Script Metadata Writer — persists script + metadata + lock locally.\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef write_script_artifacts(\n    video_root: Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    script_data: dict[str, Any],\n    lock_data: dict[str, Any],\n) -> dict[str, str]:\n    \"\"\"Write script_raw.txt, script_metadata.json, script_lock.json.\n\n    Returns dict of written paths.\n    \"\"\"\n    script_dir = Path(video_root) / \"inputs\" / \"script\"\n    script_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    # 1. script_raw.txt — exact text from sheet\n    script_path = script_dir / \"script_raw.txt\"\n    script_path.write_text(script_data[\"script\"], encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    # 2. script_metadata.json\n    script_text = script_data[\"script\"]\n    metadata = {\n        \"job_id\": job.get(\"job_id\", \"\"),\n        \"account\": job.get(\"account\", \"\"),\n        \"language\": job.get(\"language\", \"\"),\n        \"sheet_scripts_id\": job.get(\"sheet_scripts_id\", \"\"),\n        \"sheet_name\": job.get(\"sheet_scripts_name\", \"\"),\n        \"script_row\": script_data.get(\"row_number\"),\n        \"script_id\": script_data.get(\"id\", \"\"),\n        \"title\": script_data.get(\"title\", \"\"),\n        \"description\": script_data.get(\"description\", \"\"),\n        \"fetched_at\": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),\n        \"fetched_by\": \"vo_script_fetch\",\n        \"char_count\": len(script_text),\n        \"word_count\": len(script_text.split()),\n    }\n    metadata_path = script_dir / \"script_metadata.json\"\n    metadata_path.write_text(json.dumps(metadata, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    # 3. script_lock.json\n    lock_info = {\n        \"job_id\": job.get(\"job_id\", \"\"),\n        \"account\": job.get(\"account\", \"\"),\n        \"language\": job.get(\"language\", \"\"),\n        \"sheet_scripts_id\": job.get(\"sheet_scripts_id\", \"\"),\n        \"sheet_name\": job.get(\"sheet_scripts_name\", \"\"),\n        \"script_row\": script_data.get(\"row_number\"),\n        \"lock_status\": \"processing\",\n        \"locked_at\": lock_data.get(\"locked_at\", \"\"),\n        \"locked_by\": \"vo_script_fetch\",\n    }\n    lock_path = script_dir / \"script_lock.json\"\n    lock_path.write_text(json.dumps(lock_info, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return {\n        \"script_path\": str(script_path),\n        \"metadata_path\": str(metadata_path),\n        \"lock_path\": str(lock_path),\n    }\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775051628525}}
{"type":"message","id":"ce7e3714","parentId":"cf9d4381","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:53:48.892Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_XIrRqp01fSkOcIWZWfF9VRQS|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd236b0a3c819092eaf4fd1f3e59f8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"VO Script Checkpoint Writer — writes vo_script_ready.json.\"\"\"\n\nimport json\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom pathlib import Path\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\ndef write_script_checkpoint(\n    video_root: Path,\n    job: dict[str, Any],\n    script_data: dict[str, Any],\n    paths: dict[str, str],\n) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Write checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json.\n\n    Returns path to checkpoint file.\n    \"\"\"\n    checkpoint_dir = Path(video_root) / \"checkpoints\"\n    checkpoint_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\n\n    checkpoint = {\n        \"job_id\": job.get(\"job_id\", \"\"),\n        \"status\": \"script_ready\",\n        \"current_stage\": \"vo_script_fetch\",\n        \"script\": {\n            \"fetched\": True,\n            \"locked\": True,\n            \"script_path\": paths.get(\"script_path\", \"\"),\n            \"metadata_path\": paths.get(\"metadata_path\", \"\"),\n            \"lock_path\": paths.get(\"lock_path\", \"\"),\n            \"script_row\": script_data.get(\"row_number\"),\n        },\n        \"sectors_completed\": [],\n        \"next_step\": \"ready_for_s1\",\n        \"created_at\": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),\n    }\n\n    checkpoint_path = checkpoint_dir / \"vo_script_ready.json\"\n    checkpoint_path.write_text(json.dumps(checkpoint, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False), encoding=\"utf-8\")\n\n    return str(checkpoint_path)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775051628705}}
{"type":"message","id":"1cf0a56a","parentId":"ce7e3714","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:55:48.542Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Y7coJ3qBjrrkx4ygDPvVHnlM|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd23e5f00c819086af654ac7672e56","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\vo\\vo_supervisor_contract.md","content":"# VO Supervisor Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the canonical role, authority, workflow, and component boundaries of the Video Orchestrator._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Video Orchestrator (VO) is the canonical bootstrap-and-readiness supervisor between PM and S1.\n\nIts job is to:\n- receive a validated PM job\n- validate that job from the VO perspective\n- initialize the run directory and initial run artifacts\n- fetch and lock the next eligible script\n- persist local script artifacts\n- produce the exact run state required for S1 handoff\n\nThe VO is an **OpenClaw supervisor/manager agent** in the target architecture.\nIt is not:\n- the owner of strategic production selection\n- the owner of S1 execution\n- a downstream editing sector\n- a generic file helper without clear boundary responsibility\n\n---\n\n## Canonical authority\n\n### VO owns\n- validating PM handoff from the VO perspective\n- initializing the run directory\n- writing `job.json`\n- writing `run_metadata.json`\n- writing VO checkpoints\n- fetching the next eligible script\n- applying script lock on the scripts sheet\n- persisting script artifacts locally\n- deciding whether the run is truly `ready_for_s1`\n\n### VO does not own\n- upstream channel selection\n- strategic override interpretation\n- screenplay/polish generation\n- scene bible generation\n- downstream sector execution\n\n---\n\n## Canonical operating model\n\nThe canonical VO model is:\n- **VO supervisor = brain of run bootstrap and script readiness**\n- **deterministic VO substrate = execution substrate**\n- **persisted run artifacts = handoff truth to S1**\n\n---\n\n## Component classes inside VO\n\n### 1. Canonical VO supervisor\n- future OpenClaw VO agent/workspace (not yet created at the time of this draft)\n\n### 2. Deterministic VO runtime components\n- `job_input_validator`\n- `video_dir_initializer`\n- `run_metadata_writer`\n- `checkpoint_initializer`\n- `script_fetcher`\n- `script_locker`\n- `script_metadata_writer`\n- `script_checkpoint_writer`\n- `script_fetch_and_lock`\n- `vo_start`\n\n### 3. External integrations / supporting substrate\n- Google Sheets read access for script discovery\n- Google Sheets write access for script lock\n- local production filesystem\n- PM job artifact as upstream truth\n\n---\n\n## Canonical input model\n\nThe VO should receive a validated PM job artifact as its upstream handoff truth.\n\nThe VO may assume PM already performed PM-side job validation, but it should still validate the job from the VO boundary perspective before creating the run.\n\n---\n\n## Canonical output model\n\nThe canonical VO output is a run state that is safe for S1 to consume.\n\nThis means the VO should leave behind, at minimum:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_init.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\n---\n\n## Authority map\n\n### PM owns\n- choosing/materializing the production target\n- building the canonical PM job\n- validating PM-side handoff readiness\n\n### VO owns\n- converting the PM job into a real initialized run\n- acquiring and locking the script\n- producing `ready_for_s1` state\n\n### S1 owns\n- consuming the VO-prepared run\n- transforming script into canonical pre-production artifacts\n\n---\n\n## Canonical VO workflow\n\n1. Receive validated PM job\n2. Validate job via `job_input_validator`\n3. Bootstrap run via `vo_start`\n4. Create run directory + write initial artifacts\n5. Fetch next eligible script via `script_fetcher`\n6. Lock script row via `script_locker`\n7. Persist script artifacts locally via `script_metadata_writer`\n8. Write `vo_script_ready.json`\n9. Hand off to S1\n\n---\n\n## Failure behavior\n\n### VO must fail explicitly when:\n- PM job is structurally invalid for VO\n- run directory already exists\n- script fetch fails\n- script lock fails\n- required local artifacts cannot be persisted\n- checkpointing required for readiness fails\n\n### VO must not\n- invent run readiness when artifacts are missing\n- mark sectors complete before they actually ran\n- silently skip required lock/persist steps\n- hand off to S1 without the required script artifacts/checkpoint\n\n---\n\n## Current implementation reality\n\nAt the time of this draft:\n- deterministic VO substrate exists and is materially implemented\n- VO implementation notes exist from the earlier phase\n- VO contracts are only now being formalized canonically\n- VO is not yet realized as a real OpenClaw workspace/agent\n\nThis means VO is currently stronger as runtime substrate than as OpenClaw runtime entity.\n\n---\n\n## Immediate implication for future work\n\nThe next correct move is:\n- complete VO contract coverage\n- create the VO OpenClaw workspace/agent\n- bind the deterministic VO substrate to that supervisor identity\n- then validate PM -> VO and PM -> VO -> S1 under runtime conditions\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\vo\\\\vo_supervisor_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# VO Supervisor Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the canonical role, authority, workflow, and component boundaries of the Video Orchestrator._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThe Video Orchestrator (VO) is the canonical bootstrap-and-readiness supervisor between PM and S1.\\n\\nIts job is to:\\n- receive a validated PM job\\n- validate that job from the VO perspective\\n- initialize the run directory and initial run artifacts\\n- fetch and lock the next eligible script\\n- persist local script artifacts\\n- produce the exact run state required for S1 handoff\\n\\nThe VO is an **OpenClaw supervisor/manager agent** in the target architecture.\\nIt is not:\\n- the owner of strategic production selection\\n- the owner of S1 execution\\n- a downstream editing sector\\n- a generic file helper without clear boundary responsibility\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical authority\\n\\n### VO owns\\n- validating PM handoff from the VO perspective\\n- initializing the run directory\\n- writing `job.json`\\n- writing `run_metadata.json`\\n- writing VO checkpoints\\n- fetching the next eligible script\\n- applying script lock on the scripts sheet\\n- persisting script artifacts locally\\n- deciding whether the run is truly `ready_for_s1`\\n\\n### VO does not own\\n- upstream channel selection\\n- strategic override interpretation\\n- screenplay/polish generation\\n- scene bible generation\\n- downstream sector execution\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical operating model\\n\\nThe canonical VO model is:\\n- **VO supervisor = brain of run bootstrap and script readiness**\\n- **deterministic VO substrate = execution substrate**\\n- **persisted run artifacts = handoff truth to S1**\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Component classes inside VO\\n\\n### 1. Canonical VO supervisor\\n- future OpenClaw VO agent/workspace (not yet created at the time of this draft)\\n\\n### 2. Deterministic VO runtime components\\n- `job_input_validator`\\n- `video_dir_initializer`\\n- `run_metadata_writer`\\n- `checkpoint_initializer`\\n- `script_fetcher`\\n- `script_locker`\\n- `script_metadata_writer`\\n- `script_checkpoint_writer`\\n- `script_fetch_and_lock`\\n- `vo_start`\\n\\n### 3. External integrations / supporting substrate\\n- Google Sheets read access for script discovery\\n- Google Sheets write access for script lock\\n- local production filesystem\\n- PM job artifact as upstream truth\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical input model\\n\\nThe VO should receive a validated PM job artifact as its upstream handoff truth.\\n\\nThe VO may assume PM already performed PM-side job validation, but it should still validate the job from the VO boundary perspective before creating the run.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical output model\\n\\nThe canonical VO output is a run state that is safe for S1 to consume.\\n\\nThis means the VO should leave behind, at minimum:\\n- `job.json`\\n- `run_metadata.json`\\n- `checkpoints/vo_init.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Authority map\\n\\n### PM owns\\n- choosing/materializing the production target\\n- building the canonical PM job\\n- validating PM-side handoff readiness\\n\\n### VO owns\\n- converting the PM job into a real initialized run\\n- acquiring and locking the script\\n- producing `ready_for_s1` state\\n\\n### S1 owns\\n- consuming the VO-prepared run\\n- transforming script into canonical pre-production artifacts\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical VO workflow\\n\\n1. Receive validated PM job\\n2. Validate job via `job_input_validator`\\n3. Bootstrap run via `vo_start`\\n4. Create run directory + write initial artifacts\\n5. Fetch next eligible script via `script_fetcher`\\n6. Lock script row via `script_locker`\\n7. Persist script artifacts locally via `script_metadata_writer`\\n8. Write `vo_script_ready.json`\\n9. Hand off to S1\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure behavior\\n\\n### VO must fail explicitly when:\\n- PM job is structurally invalid for VO\\n- run directory already exists\\n- script fetch fails\\n- script lock fails\\n- required local artifacts cannot be persisted\\n- checkpointing required for readiness fails\\n\\n### VO must not\\n- invent run readiness when artifacts are missing\\n- mark sectors complete before they actually ran\\n- silently skip required lock/persist steps\\n- hand off to S1 without the required script artifacts/checkpoint\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current implementation reality\\n\\nAt the time of this draft:\\n- deterministic VO substrate exists and is materially implemented\\n- VO implementation notes exist from the earlier phase\\n- VO contracts are only now being formalized canonically\\n- VO is not yet realized as a real OpenClaw workspace/agent\\n\\nThis means VO is currently stronger as runtime substrate than as OpenClaw runtime entity.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Immediate implication for future work\\n\\nThe next correct move is:\\n- complete VO contract coverage\\n- create the VO OpenClaw workspace/agent\\n- bind the deterministic VO substrate to that supervisor identity\\n- then validate PM -> VO and PM -> VO -> S1 under runtime conditions\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2MP6gGN2SDS19429I79WSSq8|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd23e5f024819090d202dfcda6472b","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\vo\\vo_job_input_validator_contract.md","content":"# VO Job Input Validator Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic validation gate for PM job input at the VO boundary._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n`job_input_validator` verifies that the PM job is structurally acceptable for VO bootstrap.\n\nIf validation fails, VO must not create any run directory or initial artifacts.\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\n`job_input_validator` should:\n- verify required fields exist\n- verify required string fields are non-empty\n- verify `pub_row` is either `int` or `None`\n- return structured validation errors\n\nIt should not:\n- modify the job\n- create filesystem artifacts\n- fetch scripts\n- perform PM-side strategic validation\n\n---\n\n## Required fields\n\nRequired non-empty string fields:\n- `job_id`\n- `account`\n- `language`\n- `channel_name`\n- `sheet_scripts_id`\n- `sheet_tracking_id`\n- `drive_folder_id`\n- `v3_config`\n- `created_at`\n\nRequired additional field:\n- `pub_row` (may be `int` or `None`)\n\n---\n\n## Output shape\n\nSuggested shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"valid\": false,\n  \"errors\": [\n    {\n      \"code\": \"missing_field\",\n      \"field\": \"job_id\",\n      \"message\": \"Required field 'job_id' is missing\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Failure rule\n\nIf validation fails, VO must not create a run directory.\nNo bootstrap side effects are allowed after validation failure.\n\n---\n\n## Boundary rule\n\nThis validator protects the PM -> VO boundary.\nIt is not a replacement for PM-side validation and it is not a downstream runtime orchestrator.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\vo\\\\vo_job_input_validator_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# VO Job Input Validator Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic validation gate for PM job input at the VO boundary._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\n`job_input_validator` verifies that the PM job is structurally acceptable for VO bootstrap.\\n\\nIf validation fails, VO must not create any run directory or initial artifacts.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\n`job_input_validator` should:\\n- verify required fields exist\\n- verify required string fields are non-empty\\n- verify `pub_row` is either `int` or `None`\\n- return structured validation errors\\n\\nIt should not:\\n- modify the job\\n- create filesystem artifacts\\n- fetch scripts\\n- perform PM-side strategic validation\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Required fields\\n\\nRequired non-empty string fields:\\n- `job_id`\\n- `account`\\n- `language`\\n- `channel_name`\\n- `sheet_scripts_id`\\n- `sheet_tracking_id`\\n- `drive_folder_id`\\n- `v3_config`\\n- `created_at`\\n\\nRequired additional field:\\n- `pub_row` (may be `int` or `None`)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output shape\\n\\nSuggested shape:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"valid\\\": false,\\n  \\\"errors\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"code\\\": \\\"missing_field\\\",\\n      \\\"field\\\": \\\"job_id\\\",\\n      \\\"message\\\": \\\"Required field 'job_id' is missing\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure rule\\n\\nIf validation fails, VO must not create a run directory.\\nNo bootstrap side effects are allowed after validation failure.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Boundary rule\\n\\nThis validator protects the PM -> VO boundary.\\nIt is not a replacement for PM-side validation and it is not a downstream runtime orchestrator.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_RAgBbhWwQfoQYa3DwrrxH1d5|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd23e5f0308190ba68022f18dd1688","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\vo\\vo_video_dir_initializer_contract.md","content":"# VO Video Directory Initializer Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic creation of the run directory structure._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n`video_dir_initializer` creates the canonical run directory structure for a video production run and writes the copied `job.json` into the run root.\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\n`video_dir_initializer` should:\n- derive the run path deterministically from `account`, `language`, and `job_id`\n- create the run root\n- create canonical subdirectories\n- write `job.json`\n- fail explicitly if the run already exists\n\nIt should not:\n- validate the PM job itself\n- fetch scripts\n- write `run_metadata.json`\n- write checkpoints beyond its own artifact creation\n\n---\n\n## Canonical path rule\n\nDeterministic path:\n\n```text\nproduction/{account}_{language}/{job_id}/\n```\n\n---\n\n## Canonical subdirectories\n\nAt minimum:\n- `checkpoints/`\n- `inputs/`\n- `outputs/`\n- `logs/`\n- `sectors/`\n\n---\n\n## Required artifact\n\nThe initializer must write:\n- `job.json`\n\nThis should be a copied persisted representation of the PM job artifact.\n\n---\n\n## Failure rule\n\nIf the target run directory already exists:\n- fail explicitly with `run_already_exists`\n- do not mix old and new run state\n- do not silently reuse the directory\n\n---\n\n## Output shape\n\nSuggested shape:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"video_root\": \"C:\\\\...\\\\production\\\\004_fr\\\\2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"subdirs_created\": [\"...\"],\n  \"job_json_path\": \"C:\\\\...\\\\job.json\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Boundary rule\n\nThis component is a filesystem bootstrap primitive for VO.\nIt is not the VO supervisor and it is not a generic rerun/recovery manager.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\vo\\\\vo_video_dir_initializer_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# VO Video Directory Initializer Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic creation of the run directory structure._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\n`video_dir_initializer` creates the canonical run directory structure for a video production run and writes the copied `job.json` into the run root.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\n`video_dir_initializer` should:\\n- derive the run path deterministically from `account`, `language`, and `job_id`\\n- create the run root\\n- create canonical subdirectories\\n- write `job.json`\\n- fail explicitly if the run already exists\\n\\nIt should not:\\n- validate the PM job itself\\n- fetch scripts\\n- write `run_metadata.json`\\n- write checkpoints beyond its own artifact creation\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical path rule\\n\\nDeterministic path:\\n\\n```text\\nproduction/{account}_{language}/{job_id}/\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical subdirectories\\n\\nAt minimum:\\n- `checkpoints/`\\n- `inputs/`\\n- `outputs/`\\n- `logs/`\\n- `sectors/`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Required artifact\\n\\nThe initializer must write:\\n- `job.json`\\n\\nThis should be a copied persisted representation of the PM job artifact.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure rule\\n\\nIf the target run directory already exists:\\n- fail explicitly with `run_already_exists`\\n- do not mix old and new run state\\n- do not silently reuse the directory\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output shape\\n\\nSuggested shape:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"video_root\\\": \\\"C:\\\\\\\\...\\\\\\\\production\\\\\\\\004_fr\\\\\\\\2026-03-30_004_fr_001\\\",\\n  \\\"subdirs_created\\\": [\\\"...\\\"],\\n  \\\"job_json_path\\\": \\\"C:\\\\\\\\...\\\\\\\\job.json\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Boundary rule\\n\\nThis component is a filesystem bootstrap primitive for VO.\\nIt is not the VO supervisor and it is not a generic rerun/recovery manager.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_09PDBbFdTsbUYbxzFnJpF7G1|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd23e5f05c819080814bea99be4b08","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\vo\\vo_bootstrap_contract.md","content":"# VO Bootstrap Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the canonical run bootstrap phase of the Video Orchestrator._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe VO bootstrap phase converts a valid PM job into a real initialized run on disk.\n\nIt is the phase that produces the initial run root and marks the run as ready for script fetch.\n\n---\n\n## Responsibilities\n\nThe bootstrap phase should:\n1. validate PM job from the VO perspective\n2. initialize the run directory\n3. write `job.json`\n4. write `run_metadata.json`\n5. write `checkpoints/vo_init.json`\n6. return a structured result\n\n---\n\n## Success condition\n\nBootstrap succeeds when:\n- PM job validation passes\n- run directory is created\n- `job.json` exists\n- `run_metadata.json` exists\n- `checkpoints/vo_init.json` exists\n- result state is `initialized`\n- next step is `ready_for_script_fetch`\n\n---\n\n## Failure condition\n\nBootstrap fails if:\n- job validation fails\n- run directory already exists\n- any required initial artifact cannot be written\n\nIn that case the result must clearly communicate failure and no false readiness may be emitted.\n\n---\n\n## Output expectations\n\nSuggested success result:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"video_root\": \"C:\\\\...\",\n  \"paths\": {\n    \"job_json\": \"C:\\\\...\\\\job.json\",\n    \"run_metadata\": \"C:\\\\...\\\\run_metadata.json\",\n    \"checkpoint_init\": \"C:\\\\...\\\\checkpoints\\\\vo_init.json\"\n  },\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"next_step\": \"ready_for_script_fetch\",\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Boundary rule\n\nBootstrap creates the run skeleton.\nIt does not yet make the run `ready_for_s1`.\nThat requires successful script fetch + lock + local persistence.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\vo\\\\vo_bootstrap_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# VO Bootstrap Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the canonical run bootstrap phase of the Video Orchestrator._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThe VO bootstrap phase converts a valid PM job into a real initialized run on disk.\\n\\nIt is the phase that produces the initial run root and marks the run as ready for script fetch.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Responsibilities\\n\\nThe bootstrap phase should:\\n1. validate PM job from the VO perspective\\n2. initialize the run directory\\n3. write `job.json`\\n4. write `run_metadata.json`\\n5. write `checkpoints/vo_init.json`\\n6. return a structured result\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Success condition\\n\\nBootstrap succeeds when:\\n- PM job validation passes\\n- run directory is created\\n- `job.json` exists\\n- `run_metadata.json` exists\\n- `checkpoints/vo_init.json` exists\\n- result state is `initialized`\\n- next step is `ready_for_script_fetch`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure condition\\n\\nBootstrap fails if:\\n- job validation fails\\n- run directory already exists\\n- any required initial artifact cannot be written\\n\\nIn that case the result must clearly communicate failure and no false readiness may be emitted.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output expectations\\n\\nSuggested success result:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"success\\\": true,\\n  \\\"job_id\\\": \\\"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\\\",\\n  \\\"video_root\\\": \\\"C:\\\\\\\\...\\\",\\n  \\\"paths\\\": {\\n    \\\"job_json\\\": \\\"C:\\\\\\\\...\\\\\\\\job.json\\\",\\n    \\\"run_metadata\\\": \\\"C:\\\\\\\\...\\\\\\\\run_metadata.json\\\",\\n    \\\"checkpoint_init\\\": \\\"C:\\\\\\\\...\\\\\\\\checkpoints\\\\\\\\vo_init.json\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"initialized\\\",\\n  \\\"next_step\\\": \\\"ready_for_script_fetch\\\",\\n  \\\"errors\\\": [],\\n  \\\"warnings\\\": []\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Boundary rule\\n\\nBootstrap creates the run skeleton.\\nIt does not yet make the run `ready_for_s1`.\\nThat requires successful script fetch + lock + local persistence.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0j89KPb4WZEcpPH0zDC0uw6y|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd23e5f0688190a631e5618d70d176","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\vo\\vo_script_fetch_contract.md","content":"# VO Script Fetch Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic script acquisition rule used by VO._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n`script_fetcher` finds the next eligible script from the scripts sheet for the current run.\n\nIt follows the operational semantics inherited from the V3 pipeline.\n\n---\n\n## Eligibility rule\n\nA script is eligible when:\n- `Status = \"to do\"` (case-insensitive, trimmed)\n- script text is non-empty\n- it is the first row matching those conditions when scanning top-to-bottom from row 2\n\nRows with empty script text must be skipped.\n\n---\n\n## Required sheet semantics\n\nExpected columns:\n- `ID`\n- `Title`\n- `Description`\n- `Script`\n- `Status`\n- `Processing_Started`\n- `Processing_Completed`\n- `Account_Used`\n\nThe fetcher should use the scripts sheet ID and tab name from the PM job / local config context.\n\n---\n\n## Output shape\n\nIf found:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"found\": true,\n  \"row_number\": 6,\n  \"id\": \"FR-005\",\n  \"title\": \"Les Enfants de la Creuse\",\n  \"description\": \"...\",\n  \"script\": \"...\",\n  \"status\": \"to do\"\n}\n```\n\nIf not found:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"found\": false,\n  \"reason\": \"no_eligible_scripts\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Failure behavior\n\nThe fetcher may raise or propagate read/integration failures, but the orchestrator above it must convert those to structured VO errors.\n\n---\n\n## Boundary rule\n\nThe fetcher only finds the script.\nIt does not lock the row and it does not persist local artifacts.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\vo\\\\vo_script_fetch_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# VO Script Fetch Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the deterministic script acquisition rule used by VO._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\n`script_fetcher` finds the next eligible script from the scripts sheet for the current run.\\n\\nIt follows the operational semantics inherited from the V3 pipeline.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Eligibility rule\\n\\nA script is eligible when:\\n- `Status = \\\"to do\\\"` (case-insensitive, trimmed)\\n- script text is non-empty\\n- it is the first row matching those conditions when scanning top-to-bottom from row 2\\n\\nRows with empty script text must be skipped.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Required sheet semantics\\n\\nExpected columns:\\n- `ID`\\n- `Title`\\n- `Description`\\n- `Script`\\n- `Status`\\n- `Processing_Started`\\n- `Processing_Completed`\\n- `Account_Used`\\n\\nThe fetcher should use the scripts sheet ID and tab name from the PM job / local config context.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output shape\\n\\nIf found:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"found\\\": true,\\n  \\\"row_number\\\": 6,\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"FR-005\\\",\\n  \\\"title\\\": \\\"Les Enfants de la Creuse\\\",\\n  \\\"description\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n  \\\"script\\\": \\\"...\\\",\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"to do\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nIf not found:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"found\\\": false,\\n  \\\"reason\\\": \\\"no_eligible_scripts\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure behavior\\n\\nThe fetcher may raise or propagate read/integration failures, but the orchestrator above it must convert those to structured VO errors.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Boundary rule\\n\\nThe fetcher only finds the script.\\nIt does not lock the row and it does not persist local artifacts.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5MLAPoTvarz3VbKFfkW6RTES|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd23e5f0708190b3fc3882d859e3ed","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\vo\\vo_script_lock_contract.md","content":"# VO Script Lock Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines how VO applies a script lock in the scripts sheet._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\n`script_locker` applies the operational lock that prevents the chosen script from remaining available as `to do` for another run.\n\n---\n\n## Lock semantics\n\nAt minimum the lock must:\n- update `Status` to `processing`\n- write a UTC ISO timestamp into `Processing_Started` when possible\n\n---\n\n## Permissions model\n\nThe locker requires write-capable Google Sheets scopes.\nReadonly client access is not sufficient.\n\nExpected write scopes include:\n- `spreadsheets`\n- `drive`\n\n---\n\n## Output shape\n\nSuccess:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"locked\": true,\n  \"row_number\": 6,\n  \"locked_at\": \"2026-03-30T14:25:13.456789+00:00\"\n}\n```\n\nFailure:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"locked\": false,\n  \"error\": \"Could not update Status: ...\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Failure behavior\n\nIf the locker cannot apply the status update, the lock fails.\nThe orchestrator must treat this as blocking.\n\nIf the timestamp write fails after status was already updated, the lock may still be treated as operationally valid.\nThat is a tolerated but non-ideal state.\n\n---\n\n## Boundary rule\n\nThe locker only applies the sheet-side lock.\nIt does not persist local script artifacts and it does not declare the run `ready_for_s1` by itself.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\vo\\\\vo_script_lock_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# VO Script Lock Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines how VO applies a script lock in the scripts sheet._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\n`script_locker` applies the operational lock that prevents the chosen script from remaining available as `to do` for another run.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Lock semantics\\n\\nAt minimum the lock must:\\n- update `Status` to `processing`\\n- write a UTC ISO timestamp into `Processing_Started` when possible\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Permissions model\\n\\nThe locker requires write-capable Google Sheets scopes.\\nReadonly client access is not sufficient.\\n\\nExpected write scopes include:\\n- `spreadsheets`\\n- `drive`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output shape\\n\\nSuccess:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"locked\\\": true,\\n  \\\"row_number\\\": 6,\\n  \\\"locked_at\\\": \\\"2026-03-30T14:25:13.456789+00:00\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nFailure:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"locked\\\": false,\\n  \\\"error\\\": \\\"Could not update Status: ...\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure behavior\\n\\nIf the locker cannot apply the status update, the lock fails.\\nThe orchestrator must treat this as blocking.\\n\\nIf the timestamp write fails after status was already updated, the lock may still be treated as operationally valid.\\nThat is a tolerated but non-ideal state.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Boundary rule\\n\\nThe locker only applies the sheet-side lock.\\nIt does not persist local script artifacts and it does not declare the run `ready_for_s1` by itself.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_JCKs1Tk2BDget1Ss9XFbjYiT|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd23e5f0a08190915d67b770d0f678","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\vo\\vo_script_fetch_and_lock_contract.md","content":"# VO Script Fetch and Lock Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the canonical VO sequence that fetches, locks, persists, and checkpoints script readiness._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis contract defines the VO sequence that turns an initialized run into a `ready_for_s1` run.\n\n---\n\n## Canonical sequence\n\n1. Fetch next eligible script\n2. Lock the script row in the sheet\n3. Persist local artifacts:\n   - `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n   - `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n   - `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n4. Write `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n5. Return `next_step = ready_for_s1`\n\n---\n\n## Success condition\n\nSuccess requires all of the following:\n- an eligible script was found\n- the row was locked\n- all local script artifacts were written\n- the readiness checkpoint was written\n\nOnly then may the VO claim the run is `ready_for_s1`.\n\n---\n\n## Failure condition\n\nThe sequence fails if any of the following happens:\n- script fetch fails\n- no eligible scripts exist\n- lock fails\n- local artifact persistence fails\n- readiness checkpoint write fails\n\nThe VO must not claim script readiness if any of these failed.\n\n---\n\n## Output shape\n\nSuggested success result:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"job_id\": \"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\",\n  \"status\": \"script_ready\",\n  \"current_stage\": \"vo_script_fetch\",\n  \"script_row\": 6,\n  \"title\": \"Les Enfants de la Creuse\",\n  \"script_path\": \"C:\\\\...\\\\script_raw.txt\",\n  \"metadata_path\": \"C:\\\\...\\\\script_metadata.json\",\n  \"lock_path\": \"C:\\\\...\\\\script_lock.json\",\n  \"checkpoint_path\": \"C:\\\\...\\\\vo_script_ready.json\",\n  \"next_step\": \"ready_for_s1\",\n  \"errors\": [],\n  \"warnings\": []\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Boundary rule\n\nThis contract is the operational bridge from VO bootstrap to S1 handoff.\nIt should be treated as a canonical readiness gate, not an optional convenience step.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\vo\\\\vo_script_fetch_and_lock_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# VO Script Fetch and Lock Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the canonical VO sequence that fetches, locks, persists, and checkpoints script readiness._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThis contract defines the VO sequence that turns an initialized run into a `ready_for_s1` run.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical sequence\\n\\n1. Fetch next eligible script\\n2. Lock the script row in the sheet\\n3. Persist local artifacts:\\n   - `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\\n   - `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\\n   - `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\\n4. Write `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\\n5. Return `next_step = ready_for_s1`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Success condition\\n\\nSuccess requires all of the following:\\n- an eligible script was found\\n- the row was locked\\n- all local script artifacts were written\\n- the readiness checkpoint was written\\n\\nOnly then may the VO claim the run is `ready_for_s1`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure condition\\n\\nThe sequence fails if any of the following happens:\\n- script fetch fails\\n- no eligible scripts exist\\n- lock fails\\n- local artifact persistence fails\\n- readiness checkpoint write fails\\n\\nThe VO must not claim script readiness if any of these failed.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Output shape\\n\\nSuggested success result:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"success\\\": true,\\n  \\\"job_id\\\": \\\"2026-03-30_004_fr_001\\\",\\n  \\\"status\\\": \\\"script_ready\\\",\\n  \\\"current_stage\\\": \\\"vo_script_fetch\\\",\\n  \\\"script_row\\\": 6,\\n  \\\"title\\\": \\\"Les Enfants de la Creuse\\\",\\n  \\\"script_path\\\": \\\"C:\\\\\\\\...\\\\\\\\script_raw.txt\\\",\\n  \\\"metadata_path\\\": \\\"C:\\\\\\\\...\\\\\\\\script_metadata.json\\\",\\n  \\\"lock_path\\\": \\\"C:\\\\\\\\...\\\\\\\\script_lock.json\\\",\\n  \\\"checkpoint_path\\\": \\\"C:\\\\\\\\...\\\\\\\\vo_script_ready.json\\\",\\n  \\\"next_step\\\": \\\"ready_for_s1\\\",\\n  \\\"errors\\\": [],\\n  \\\"warnings\\\": []\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Boundary rule\\n\\nThis contract is the operational bridge from VO bootstrap to S1 handoff.\\nIt should be treated as a canonical readiness gate, not an optional convenience step.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Q1jyVW3RIARLCF0oHxtDaZf1|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd23e5f0ac8190ad274c8f27840151","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\vo\\vo_to_s1_handoff_contract.md","content":"# VO to S1 Handoff Contract\n\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the boundary between the Video Orchestrator and S1._\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis contract defines what VO must leave behind for S1 and what S1 is allowed to assume when it begins.\n\nIt exists to eliminate ambiguity at the exact point where run bootstrap ends and pre-production begins.\n\n---\n\n## Boundary principle\n\n### VO owns\n- run bootstrap\n- script fetch and lock\n- persistence of initial script artifacts\n- declaration of `ready_for_s1`\n\n### S1 owns\n- consuming the ready run\n- screenplay generation\n- polish generation\n- scene bible build\n- S1 checkpoints and completion\n\nVO must not pretend to perform S1 responsibilities.\nS1 must not need to infer missing VO prerequisites.\n\n---\n\n## Minimum VO guarantees before handoff\n\nBefore handing off to S1, VO must guarantee the presence of at least:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\n---\n\n## Minimum S1 assumptions at handoff time\n\nWhen S1 receives a run from VO, it may assume:\n- PM/VO handoff already happened\n- the run root exists\n- script artifacts exist locally\n- the script row was locked upstream\n- the run is explicitly marked `ready_for_s1`\n\nS1 should still run its own preflight rather than trusting blindly.\n\n---\n\n## Success condition of handoff\n\nThe VO -> S1 handoff is successful when:\n- VO finished script fetch and lock successfully\n- all required local artifacts exist\n- `vo_script_ready.json` exists and points to the next step as `ready_for_s1`\n\n---\n\n## Failure condition of handoff\n\nThe handoff is failed if:\n- script artifacts are missing\n- readiness checkpoint is missing\n- run state is only partially initialized\n- lock/persistence sequence failed\n\nIn those cases S1 must not be treated as ready to start.\n\n---\n\n## Downstream implication\n\nThis contract is the direct bridge needed before a true `PM -> VO -> S1` runtime validation can be trusted.\nIf this boundary is weak, S1 failures may actually be hidden VO failures.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\vo\\\\vo_to_s1_handoff_contract.md\",\"content\":\"# VO to S1 Handoff Contract\\n\\n_Status: v1 draft. Defines the boundary between the Video Orchestrator and S1._\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThis contract defines what VO must leave behind for S1 and what S1 is allowed to assume when it begins.\\n\\nIt exists to eliminate ambiguity at the exact point where run bootstrap ends and pre-production begins.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Boundary principle\\n\\n### VO owns\\n- run bootstrap\\n- script fetch and lock\\n- persistence of initial script artifacts\\n- declaration of `ready_for_s1`\\n\\n### S1 owns\\n- consuming the ready run\\n- screenplay generation\\n- polish generation\\n- scene bible build\\n- S1 checkpoints and completion\\n\\nVO must not pretend to perform S1 responsibilities.\\nS1 must not need to infer missing VO prerequisites.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Minimum VO guarantees before handoff\\n\\nBefore handing off to S1, VO must guarantee the presence of at least:\\n- `job.json`\\n- `run_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Minimum S1 assumptions at handoff time\\n\\nWhen S1 receives a run from VO, it may assume:\\n- PM/VO handoff already happened\\n- the run root exists\\n- script artifacts exist locally\\n- the script row was locked upstream\\n- the run is explicitly marked `ready_for_s1`\\n\\nS1 should still run its own preflight rather than trusting blindly.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Success condition of handoff\\n\\nThe VO -> S1 handoff is successful when:\\n- VO finished script fetch and lock successfully\\n- all required local artifacts exist\\n- `vo_script_ready.json` exists and points to the next step as `ready_for_s1`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Failure condition of handoff\\n\\nThe handoff is failed if:\\n- script artifacts are missing\\n- readiness checkpoint is missing\\n- run state is only partially initialized\\n- lock/persistence sequence failed\\n\\nIn those cases S1 must not be treated as ready to start.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Downstream implication\\n\\nThis contract is the direct bridge needed before a true `PM -> VO -> S1` runtime validation can be trusted.\\nIf this boundary is weak, S1 failures may actually be hidden VO failures.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":81536,"output":4805,"cacheRead":78336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":164677,"cost":{"input":0.20384000000000002,"output":0.072075,"cacheRead":0.019584,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.295499}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775051629574,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd23700b9c8190b9aa32eeaaf2e9d9"}}
