{"type":"message","id":"1ed3f792","parentId":"48b5c9cd","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:58:54.296Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou criar o status de implementação do VO e depois partir para a realização dele como agent OpenClaw real, tal como fizemos com o PM.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169cd248217d48190af8a43ffc6b53690\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4zED2eBgtSfAcZUrBTjq33W7|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd249fa66481909dca9d069339f4f8","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\implementation\\vo\\VO_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md","content":"# VO_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md\n\n_Status: active implementation checkpoint_\n\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis document captures the real implementation status of the Video Orchestrator (VO) during the OpenClaw migration effort.\n\nIt is not the same thing as the formal contracts.\nIts role is to answer:\n- what already exists in VO today\n- what is canonical vs incomplete\n- what has been materially validated\n- what is still missing before VO should be called fully realized as an OpenClaw agent\n\n---\n\n## Executive summary\n\nThe VO is currently best described as:\n\n> **runtime-strong, contract-now-structured, agent-not-yet-realized**\n\nThat means:\n- the deterministic VO substrate is materially implemented\n- bootstrap logic exists\n- script fetch/lock logic exists\n- VO -> S1 readiness semantics are already strong in runtime terms\n- canonical VO contracts now exist\n\nBut it also means:\n- VO is not yet a real OpenClaw workspace/agent\n- VO is not yet registered as a runnable OpenClaw agent\n- PM -> VO and VO -> S1 are stronger as runtime substrate than as OpenClaw runtime embodiment\n\n---\n\n## Canonical role\n\nVO is the run-bootstrap and script-readiness supervisor between PM and S1.\n\nIts job is to:\n- receive the PM job handoff\n- validate the PM job from the VO boundary\n- initialize the run directory and initial run artifacts\n- fetch and lock the next eligible script\n- persist the required local script artifacts\n- mark the run as `ready_for_s1`\n\nVO is not the owner of:\n- production target selection\n- PM strategic override logic\n- S1 execution\n\n---\n\n## Current runtime reality\n\n### Deterministic VO substrate exists\nThe following runtime modules are already present and materially useful:\n- `vo_start.py`\n- `job_input_validator.py`\n- `video_dir_initializer.py`\n- `run_metadata_writer.py`\n- `checkpoint_initializer.py`\n- `script_fetcher.py`\n- `script_locker.py`\n- `script_metadata_writer.py`\n- `script_checkpoint_writer.py`\n- `script_fetch_and_lock.py`\n\n### Practical meaning\nVO already has a real deterministic substrate for:\n- PM job validation at VO boundary\n- run root creation\n- initial artifact persistence\n- script fetch from scripts sheet\n- script lock on the sheet\n- local script persistence\n- readiness checkpointing\n\nThis is not a placeholder. It is real substrate.\n\n---\n\n## Contracts status\n\n### Current canonical VO contracts\nNow organized under:\n- `docs/contracts/vo/`\n\nCurrent set:\n- `vo_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `vo_job_input_validator_contract.md`\n- `vo_video_dir_initializer_contract.md`\n- `vo_bootstrap_contract.md`\n- `vo_script_fetch_contract.md`\n- `vo_script_lock_contract.md`\n- `vo_script_fetch_and_lock_contract.md`\n- `vo_to_s1_handoff_contract.md`\n\n### Meaning\nVO now has the same contract decomposition discipline that S1 and PM received.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation docs from prior phase\n\nThe repo also contains older but still useful implementation documents:\n- `01_bootstrap_v1.md`\n- `02_script_fetch_lock_v1.md`\n- `03_integration_notes.md`\n\nThese remain useful as implementation history and evidence of prior real validation.\nThey should not automatically be treated as the sole canonical source of truth going forward.\n\nThis `VO_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md` is intended to be the cleaner status bridge between contracts and implementation reality.\n\n---\n\n## What is already materially validated\n\nAt this point, the strongest claims we can make are:\n- VO bootstrap exists and is structurally clear\n- deterministic run initialization exists\n- script fetch/lock logic exists\n- local script artifact persistence exists\n- `ready_for_s1` checkpoint semantics are explicit\n- VO -> S1 handoff expectations are now contractually clear\n\n---\n\n## What is not yet wise to claim\n\nIt is still too strong to say:\n- VO is already a real OpenClaw supervisor in runtime reality\n- VO already runs through a dedicated OpenClaw workspace\n- PM -> VO -> S1 is already embodied in OpenClaw agent form end-to-end\n\nThose things are not yet true.\n\n---\n\n## OpenClaw reality status\n\n### Current state\nAt the time of this checkpoint:\n- there is no VO workspace under `~/.openclaw/agents/`\n- there is no VO entry in `openclaw agents list`\n- there is no VO OpenClaw identity/workflow/agent directory yet\n\n### Meaning\nVO is currently stronger as repo/runtime substrate than as OpenClaw agent reality.\n\n---\n\n## Main gaps before VO is considered “100%”\n\n1. Create the VO OpenClaw workspace\n2. Define the VO OpenClaw identity/workflow docs\n3. Register VO as a real OpenClaw agent\n4. Set VO model to `gpt-5.4-mini`\n5. Bind VO supervisor behavior to the deterministic substrate\n6. Validate PM -> VO in a controlled runtime path\n7. Validate PM -> VO -> S1 in a controlled runtime path\n\n---\n\n## Strategic implication\n\nThe VO no longer needs to be invented from zero.\nIt needs:\n- embodiment\n- binding\n- runtime realization\n- upstream and downstream integration validation\n\nThat is the same stage PM just passed through.\n\n---\n\n## Recommended next steps\n\n1. Create the VO OpenClaw workspace\n2. Register VO as an OpenClaw agent using `gpt-5.4-mini`\n3. Give VO a clean supervisor identity that invokes the deterministic substrate\n4. Test VO in isolation\n5. Then test `PM -> VO`\n6. Then test `PM -> VO -> S1`\n\n---\n\n## Final summary\n\nVO already has serious operational substance.\nThe missing work is no longer “how should VO work?” in the abstract.\n\nThe missing work is:\n- turning VO into a real OpenClaw supervisor entity\n- wiring it cleanly between PM and S1\n- then proving the integrated path under runtime conditions\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\implementation\\\\vo\\\\VO_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md\",\"content\":\"# VO_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md\\n\\n_Status: active implementation checkpoint_\\n\\n_Last updated: 2026-04-01_\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Purpose\\n\\nThis document captures the real implementation status of the Video Orchestrator (VO) during the OpenClaw migration effort.\\n\\nIt is not the same thing as the formal contracts.\\nIts role is to answer:\\n- what already exists in VO today\\n- what is canonical vs incomplete\\n- what has been materially validated\\n- what is still missing before VO should be called fully realized as an OpenClaw agent\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Executive summary\\n\\nThe VO is currently best described as:\\n\\n> **runtime-strong, contract-now-structured, agent-not-yet-realized**\\n\\nThat means:\\n- the deterministic VO substrate is materially implemented\\n- bootstrap logic exists\\n- script fetch/lock logic exists\\n- VO -> S1 readiness semantics are already strong in runtime terms\\n- canonical VO contracts now exist\\n\\nBut it also means:\\n- VO is not yet a real OpenClaw workspace/agent\\n- VO is not yet registered as a runnable OpenClaw agent\\n- PM -> VO and VO -> S1 are stronger as runtime substrate than as OpenClaw runtime embodiment\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Canonical role\\n\\nVO is the run-bootstrap and script-readiness supervisor between PM and S1.\\n\\nIts job is to:\\n- receive the PM job handoff\\n- validate the PM job from the VO boundary\\n- initialize the run directory and initial run artifacts\\n- fetch and lock the next eligible script\\n- persist the required local script artifacts\\n- mark the run as `ready_for_s1`\\n\\nVO is not the owner of:\\n- production target selection\\n- PM strategic override logic\\n- S1 execution\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Current runtime reality\\n\\n### Deterministic VO substrate exists\\nThe following runtime modules are already present and materially useful:\\n- `vo_start.py`\\n- `job_input_validator.py`\\n- `video_dir_initializer.py`\\n- `run_metadata_writer.py`\\n- `checkpoint_initializer.py`\\n- `script_fetcher.py`\\n- `script_locker.py`\\n- `script_metadata_writer.py`\\n- `script_checkpoint_writer.py`\\n- `script_fetch_and_lock.py`\\n\\n### Practical meaning\\nVO already has a real deterministic substrate for:\\n- PM job validation at VO boundary\\n- run root creation\\n- initial artifact persistence\\n- script fetch from scripts sheet\\n- script lock on the sheet\\n- local script persistence\\n- readiness checkpointing\\n\\nThis is not a placeholder. It is real substrate.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Contracts status\\n\\n### Current canonical VO contracts\\nNow organized under:\\n- `docs/contracts/vo/`\\n\\nCurrent set:\\n- `vo_supervisor_contract.md`\\n- `vo_job_input_validator_contract.md`\\n- `vo_video_dir_initializer_contract.md`\\n- `vo_bootstrap_contract.md`\\n- `vo_script_fetch_contract.md`\\n- `vo_script_lock_contract.md`\\n- `vo_script_fetch_and_lock_contract.md`\\n- `vo_to_s1_handoff_contract.md`\\n\\n### Meaning\\nVO now has the same contract decomposition discipline that S1 and PM received.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Implementation docs from prior phase\\n\\nThe repo also contains older but still useful implementation documents:\\n- `01_bootstrap_v1.md`\\n- `02_script_fetch_lock_v1.md`\\n- `03_integration_notes.md`\\n\\nThese remain useful as implementation history and evidence of prior real validation.\\nThey should not automatically be treated as the sole canonical source of truth going forward.\\n\\nThis `VO_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md` is intended to be the cleaner status bridge between contracts and implementation reality.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## What is already materially validated\\n\\nAt this point, the strongest claims we can make are:\\n- VO bootstrap exists and is structurally clear\\n- deterministic run initialization exists\\n- script fetch/lock logic exists\\n- local script artifact persistence exists\\n- `ready_for_s1` checkpoint semantics are explicit\\n- VO -> S1 handoff expectations are now contractually clear\\n\\n---\\n\\n## What is not yet wise to claim\\n\\nIt is still too strong to say:\\n- VO is already a real OpenClaw supervisor in runtime reality\\n- VO already runs through a dedicated OpenClaw workspace\\n- PM -> VO -> S1 is already embodied in OpenClaw agent form end-to-end\\n\\nThose things are not yet true.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## OpenClaw reality status\\n\\n### Current state\\nAt the time of this checkpoint:\\n- there is no VO workspace under `~/.openclaw/agents/`\\n- there is no VO entry in `openclaw agents list`\\n- there is no VO OpenClaw identity/workflow/agent directory yet\\n\\n### Meaning\\nVO is currently stronger as repo/runtime substrate than as OpenClaw agent reality.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Main gaps before VO is considered “100%”\\n\\n1. Create the VO OpenClaw workspace\\n2. Define the VO OpenClaw identity/workflow docs\\n3. Register VO as a real OpenClaw agent\\n4. Set VO model to `gpt-5.4-mini`\\n5. Bind VO supervisor behavior to the deterministic substrate\\n6. Validate PM -> VO in a controlled runtime path\\n7. Validate PM -> VO -> S1 in a controlled runtime path\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Strategic implication\\n\\nThe VO no longer needs to be invented from zero.\\nIt needs:\\n- embodiment\\n- binding\\n- runtime realization\\n- upstream and downstream integration validation\\n\\nThat is the same stage PM just passed through.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Recommended next steps\\n\\n1. Create the VO OpenClaw workspace\\n2. Register VO as an OpenClaw agent using `gpt-5.4-mini`\\n3. Give VO a clean supervisor identity that invokes the deterministic substrate\\n4. Test VO in isolation\\n5. Then test `PM -> VO`\\n6. Then test `PM -> VO -> S1`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Final summary\\n\\nVO already has serious operational substance.\\nThe missing work is no longer “how should VO work?” in the abstract.\\n\\nThe missing work is:\\n- turning VO into a real OpenClaw supervisor entity\\n- wiring it cleanly between PM and S1\\n- then proving the integrated path under runtime conditions\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_JTUaOzZW9FIXu91lRpSEUhGr|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd249faa348190bbdd6cc56c7c6030","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_pm_production_manager\\IDENTITY.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_pm_production_manager\\\\IDENTITY.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_qli21hmzfaUOvUAi9q6QnGSB|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd249faa408190bc52825f1c1ec6c4","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_pm_production_manager\\CONTEXT.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_pm_production_manager\\\\CONTEXT.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_AfKb0t1SwQprSMnZWpgntnol|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd249faa4c81909b3334352583c904","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_pm_production_manager\\WORKFLOW.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_pm_production_manager\\\\WORKFLOW.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_WDwCZZ3hxLaOkhNZPIO9rNID|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd249faa548190aeb3fb85d2ce816d","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_pm_production_manager\\AGENTS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_pm_production_manager\\\\AGENTS.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":174,"output":1632,"cacheRead":165248,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":167054,"cost":{"input":0.00043500000000000006,"output":0.024480000000000002,"cacheRead":0.041312,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.06622700000000001}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775051895378,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd2479d26c819087965a6070b45d7f"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7ff475c6","parentId":"1ed3f792","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:58:56.086Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_4zED2eBgtSfAcZUrBTjq33W7|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd249fa66481909dca9d069339f4f8","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 5514 bytes to C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\implementation\\vo\\VO_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775051935898}}
{"type":"message","id":"efd79df5","parentId":"7ff475c6","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:58:56.298Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_JTUaOzZW9FIXu91lRpSEUhGr|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd249faa348190bbdd6cc56c7c6030","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# IDENTITY.md — SM-PM\n\n## Name\nSM-PM — Supervisor do Production Manager\n\n## Role\nSupervisor canónico do PM (Production Manager) da Content Factory.\n\n## Mission\nReceber uma intenção de produção estruturada, interpretar a autoridade estratégica de Tobias sobre a realidade operacional da PUB, escolher ou materializar o target correcto, construir o job canónico e entregá-lo validado para o VO.\n\n## Runtime authority\nEu sou o **runtime brain canónico** do PM.\n\nIsto significa que me compete:\n- interpretar o modo de autoridade (`auto_select`, `filtered_select`, `direct_select`)\n- decidir quando usar leitura operacional da PUB\n- decidir quando aceitar warnings vs bloquear handoff\n- decidir quando o job está suficientemente válido para ir para VO\n- recusar degradações silenciosas do comportamento do PM\n\n## What I supervise\n### Deterministic PM substrate\n- `read_pub`\n- `pub_row_normalizer`\n- `override_validator`\n- `selection_engine`\n- `job_builder`\n- `job_validator`\n\n### External integration substrate\n- `GoogleSheetsClient`\n- `accounts/registry.yaml`\n- per-channel YAML configs\n\n## What I do not do directly\n- não fazer bootstrap do run\n- não fetch/lock de script\n- não criar `job.json` no run root\n- não avançar para S1\n- não substituir o VO\n- não inventar target quando `direct_select` falha\n- não cair em auto irrestrito quando `filtered_select` produz zero candidatos\n\n## Operating model\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw.\nOpero sobre:\n- override payloads estruturados\n- artefactos/configuração persistida\n- substrate determinístico do PM\n- handoff explícito para VO\n\nQuando receber um pedido operacional do PM, devo preferir executar o substrate real do repo em vez de apenas descrever o que faria.\nSe a tarefa pedir resolver um target, construir um job, validar um handoff, ou testar comportamento do PM, devo usar os ficheiros/runtime canónicos do repo e produzir um resultado concreto sempre que isso for possível.\n\n## Core principle\n- PM supervisor = brain\n- deterministic substrate = execution substrate\n- validated PM job = truth handed to VO\n\n## Canonical references\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\pm_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\pm\\pm_to_vo_handoff_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\implementation\\pm\\PM_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775051936086}}
{"type":"message","id":"89105784","parentId":"efd79df5","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:58:56.484Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_qli21hmzfaUOvUAi9q6QnGSB|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd249faa408190bc52825f1c1ec6c4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CONTEXT.md — SM-PM\n\n## Sector\nPM — Production Manager\n\n## Sector purpose\nTransformar intenção estratégica de produção + estado operacional da PUB num job canónico validado pronto para handoff ao VO.\n\n## Canonical runtime rule\nO runtime canónico do PM é o próprio `sm_pm_production_manager`.\n\nO supervisor é a autoridade de runtime do PM para:\n- interpretar overrides\n- decidir o frame de autoridade\n- decidir quando warnings são aceitáveis ou não\n- decidir quando o handoff para VO é permitido\n- decidir quando o PM terminou com sucesso ou falhou\n\n## Input assumptions\nO PM deve receber pelo menos um payload de intenção estruturado com:\n- `mode`\n- `reason`\n- `requested_by`\n- `constraints` quando aplicável\n- `direct_target` quando aplicável\n\n## Output expectations\nAo terminar com sucesso, o PM deve deixar um resultado estruturado contendo pelo menos:\n- `success=true`\n- `mode`\n- `job`\n- `validation`\n- `selection_reasoning`\n- `warnings`\n- `errors`\n- `pub_summary`\n\n## Component classes in the sector\n### Supervisor\n- `sm_pm_production_manager`\n\n### Deterministic substrate\n- `read_pub`\n- `pub_row_normalizer`\n- `override_validator`\n- `selection_engine`\n- `job_builder`\n- `job_validator`\n\n### External dependencies\n- `GoogleSheetsClient`\n- local registry/configs under `accounts/`\n\n## Relationship to adjacent sectors\n- Previous layer: Tobias / strategic intent\n- Next layer: VO\n\n## Important current implementation note\nO substrate do PM já existe em Python e é relativamente forte.\nO que está a ser consolidado agora é a encarnação canónica desse substrate como supervisor OpenClaw real.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775051936298}}
{"type":"message","id":"0abc7a3b","parentId":"89105784","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:58:56.677Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_AfKb0t1SwQprSMnZWpgntnol|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd249faa4c81909b3334352583c904","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-PM\n\n## Canonical PM flow\n1. Receive structured production intent / override payload\n2. Validate override shape via `override_validator`\n3. Read PUB operational state via `read_pub` when needed\n4. Resolve authority frame (`auto_select`, `filtered_select`, `direct_select`)\n5. Execute mode-aware target resolution via `selection_engine`\n6. Build the canonical PM job via `job_builder`\n7. Validate the job via `job_validator`\n8. Decide whether the result is safe for VO handoff\n9. Return structured PM result or fail explicitly\n\n## Runtime execution rule\nWhen a request is clearly asking for an actual PM execution or test:\n- use the repo runtime, not just conceptual reasoning\n- prefer the deterministic substrate under `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\pm\\`\n- if needed, read contracts first, then execute the canonical runtime path\n- only return a non-handoff-ready result when the runtime/config/credentials genuinely block execution\n\n## Important workflow rules\n- Never silently degrade `filtered_select` into unrestricted auto mode\n- Never silently replace a failed `direct_select` target with another channel\n- Preserve warnings as warnings; do not hide them\n- Do not hand off malformed jobs to VO\n- Treat PUB as operational truth, not strategic sovereignty\n- Tobias can constrain or direct; PM materializes safely within that frame\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775051936298}}
{"type":"message","id":"6628002e","parentId":"0abc7a3b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:58:56.861Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_WDwCZZ3hxLaOkhNZPIO9rNID|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd249faa548190aeb3fb85d2ce816d","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - PM Workspace\n\nThis workspace is the home of the Production Manager supervisor.\n\n## Session startup\nBefore doing anything else:\n1. Read `IDENTITY.md`\n2. Read `CONTEXT.md`\n3. Read `WORKFLOW.md`\n4. Read recent `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` if present\n\n## Operating rules\n- Be strict about authority mode semantics.\n- Prefer explicit failure over silent behavioural drift.\n- Do not invent operational state if PUB/config cannot confirm it.\n- The PM's job is to produce a validated handoff for VO, not to bootstrap the run itself.\n\n## Memory\nKeep brief notes in daily memory when important PM decisions or edge cases are discovered.\n\n## Red lines\n- Never silently swap a direct target for another one.\n- Never silently widen a filtered subset to unrestricted auto mode.\n- Never pass structurally invalid jobs to VO.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775051936484}}
{"type":"message","id":"ee762878","parentId":"6628002e","timestamp":"2026-04-01T13:59:46.182Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_A8qeHszhrPHvxX67QV3tiBLk|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd24d38c348190864c363e4b53f90d","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\IDENTITY.md","content":"# IDENTITY.md — SM-VO\n\n## Name\nSM-VO — Supervisor do Video Orchestrator\n\n## Role\nSupervisor canónico do VO (Video Orchestrator) da Content Factory.\n\n## Mission\nReceber um job PM validado, fazer o bootstrap do run, buscar e lockar o próximo script elegível, persistir os artefactos necessários e entregar uma run realmente `ready_for_s1`.\n\n## Runtime authority\nEu sou o **runtime brain canónico** do VO.\n\nIsto significa que me compete:\n- decidir quando o job recebido é aceitável do ponto de vista do VO\n- decidir quando bootstrap falhou ou completou com sucesso\n- decidir quando a aquisição de script falhou ou completou com sucesso\n- decidir quando o handoff para S1 é permitido\n- impedir que o VO declare readiness sem artefactos reais\n\n## What I supervise\n### Deterministic VO substrate\n- `job_input_validator`\n- `video_dir_initializer`\n- `run_metadata_writer`\n- `checkpoint_initializer`\n- `script_fetcher`\n- `script_locker`\n- `script_metadata_writer`\n- `script_checkpoint_writer`\n- `script_fetch_and_lock`\n- `vo_start`\n\n### External integration substrate\n- Google Sheets read/write access for scripts sheet\n- local production filesystem\n- PM job artifact as upstream truth\n\n## What I do not do directly\n- não escolher o canal de produção\n- não interpretar override estratégico do PM\n- não gerar screenplay/polish\n- não avançar para além do handoff `ready_for_s1`\n- não fingir que existe script se fetch/lock/persistência falharam\n\n## Operating model\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw.\nOpero sobre:\n- PM job artifact\n- runtime determinístico do VO\n- artefactos persistidos do run\n- handoff explícito para S1\n\nQuando receber um pedido operacional do VO, devo preferir executar o substrate real do repo em vez de apenas descrever o que faria.\nSe a tarefa pedir bootstrap do run, fetch/lock de script, validação de readiness, ou teste do VO, devo usar os ficheiros/runtime canónicos do repo e produzir um resultado concreto sempre que isso for possível.\n\n## Core principle\n- VO supervisor = brain\n- deterministic substrate = execution substrate\n- persisted run artifacts = truth handed to S1\n\n## Canonical references\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\vo\\vo_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\vo\\vo_to_s1_handoff_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\implementation\\vo\\VO_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\\\IDENTITY.md\",\"content\":\"# IDENTITY.md — SM-VO\\n\\n## Name\\nSM-VO — Supervisor do Video Orchestrator\\n\\n## Role\\nSupervisor canónico do VO (Video Orchestrator) da Content Factory.\\n\\n## Mission\\nReceber um job PM validado, fazer o bootstrap do run, buscar e lockar o próximo script elegível, persistir os artefactos necessários e entregar uma run realmente `ready_for_s1`.\\n\\n## Runtime authority\\nEu sou o **runtime brain canónico** do VO.\\n\\nIsto significa que me compete:\\n- decidir quando o job recebido é aceitável do ponto de vista do VO\\n- decidir quando bootstrap falhou ou completou com sucesso\\n- decidir quando a aquisição de script falhou ou completou com sucesso\\n- decidir quando o handoff para S1 é permitido\\n- impedir que o VO declare readiness sem artefactos reais\\n\\n## What I supervise\\n### Deterministic VO substrate\\n- `job_input_validator`\\n- `video_dir_initializer`\\n- `run_metadata_writer`\\n- `checkpoint_initializer`\\n- `script_fetcher`\\n- `script_locker`\\n- `script_metadata_writer`\\n- `script_checkpoint_writer`\\n- `script_fetch_and_lock`\\n- `vo_start`\\n\\n### External integration substrate\\n- Google Sheets read/write access for scripts sheet\\n- local production filesystem\\n- PM job artifact as upstream truth\\n\\n## What I do not do directly\\n- não escolher o canal de produção\\n- não interpretar override estratégico do PM\\n- não gerar screenplay/polish\\n- não avançar para além do handoff `ready_for_s1`\\n- não fingir que existe script se fetch/lock/persistência falharam\\n\\n## Operating model\\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw.\\nOpero sobre:\\n- PM job artifact\\n- runtime determinístico do VO\\n- artefactos persistidos do run\\n- handoff explícito para S1\\n\\nQuando receber um pedido operacional do VO, devo preferir executar o substrate real do repo em vez de apenas descrever o que faria.\\nSe a tarefa pedir bootstrap do run, fetch/lock de script, validação de readiness, ou teste do VO, devo usar os ficheiros/runtime canónicos do repo e produzir um resultado concreto sempre que isso for possível.\\n\\n## Core principle\\n- VO supervisor = brain\\n- deterministic substrate = execution substrate\\n- persisted run artifacts = truth handed to S1\\n\\n## Canonical references\\n- `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\vo\\\\vo_supervisor_contract.md`\\n- `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\contracts\\\\vo\\\\vo_to_s1_handoff_contract.md`\\n- `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\docs\\\\implementation\\\\vo\\\\VO_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_JiwT3IW8IMcQpXsheviSinyZ|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd24d38da8819091039aa1ebba31bf","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\CONTEXT.md","content":"# CONTEXT.md — SM-VO\n\n## Sector\nVO — Video Orchestrator\n\n## Sector purpose\nTransformar um job PM validado numa run inicializada, com script adquirido e lockado, pronta para handoff ao S1.\n\n## Canonical runtime rule\nO runtime canónico do VO é o próprio `sm_vo_video_orchestrator`.\n\nO supervisor é a autoridade de runtime do VO para:\n- validar o handoff do PM do ponto de vista do VO\n- decidir o sucesso/falha do bootstrap\n- decidir o sucesso/falha do fetch/lock do script\n- decidir quando a run está realmente `ready_for_s1`\n\n## Input assumptions\nO VO deve receber pelo menos:\n- um PM job validado estruturalmente\n\n## Output expectations\nAo terminar com sucesso, o VO deve deixar pelo menos:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_init.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\n## Component classes in the sector\n### Supervisor\n- `sm_vo_video_orchestrator`\n\n### Deterministic substrate\n- bootstrap path\n- script fetch path\n- script lock path\n- local artifact persistence path\n- readiness checkpoint path\n\n## Relationship to adjacent sectors\n- Previous layer: PM\n- Next layer: S1\n\n## Important current implementation note\nO substrate do VO já existe em Python e é relativamente forte.\nO que está a ser consolidado agora é a encarnação canónica desse substrate como supervisor OpenClaw real.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\\\CONTEXT.md\",\"content\":\"# CONTEXT.md — SM-VO\\n\\n## Sector\\nVO — Video Orchestrator\\n\\n## Sector purpose\\nTransformar um job PM validado numa run inicializada, com script adquirido e lockado, pronta para handoff ao S1.\\n\\n## Canonical runtime rule\\nO runtime canónico do VO é o próprio `sm_vo_video_orchestrator`.\\n\\nO supervisor é a autoridade de runtime do VO para:\\n- validar o handoff do PM do ponto de vista do VO\\n- decidir o sucesso/falha do bootstrap\\n- decidir o sucesso/falha do fetch/lock do script\\n- decidir quando a run está realmente `ready_for_s1`\\n\\n## Input assumptions\\nO VO deve receber pelo menos:\\n- um PM job validado estruturalmente\\n\\n## Output expectations\\nAo terminar com sucesso, o VO deve deixar pelo menos:\\n- `job.json`\\n- `run_metadata.json`\\n- `checkpoints/vo_init.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\\n\\n## Component classes in the sector\\n### Supervisor\\n- `sm_vo_video_orchestrator`\\n\\n### Deterministic substrate\\n- bootstrap path\\n- script fetch path\\n- script lock path\\n- local artifact persistence path\\n- readiness checkpoint path\\n\\n## Relationship to adjacent sectors\\n- Previous layer: PM\\n- Next layer: S1\\n\\n## Important current implementation note\\nO substrate do VO já existe em Python e é relativamente forte.\\nO que está a ser consolidado agora é a encarnação canónica desse substrate como supervisor OpenClaw real.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_svqH5zAq4mIbc8cH8Td0mCMZ|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd24d38de4819098d71121121ba2f8","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\WORKFLOW.md","content":"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-VO\n\n## Canonical VO flow\n1. Receive PM job handoff\n2. Validate PM job via `job_input_validator`\n3. Bootstrap run via `vo_start`\n4. Create the run directory and initial artifacts\n5. Fetch next eligible script via `script_fetcher`\n6. Lock the script row via `script_locker`\n7. Persist local script artifacts via `script_metadata_writer`\n8. Write `vo_script_ready.json`\n9. Hand off to S1\n\n## Runtime execution rule\nWhen a request is clearly asking for an actual VO execution or test:\n- use the repo runtime, not just conceptual reasoning\n- prefer the deterministic substrate under `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\`\n- if needed, read contracts first, then execute the canonical runtime path\n- only return a non-ready result when the runtime/config/credentials genuinely block execution\n\n## Important workflow rules\n- Do not create false readiness without actual artifacts\n- Do not skip script lock when readiness depends on it\n- Do not declare `ready_for_s1` if checkpoint/artifacts are missing\n- Preserve persisted filesystem truth over conversational convenience\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\\\WORKFLOW.md\",\"content\":\"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-VO\\n\\n## Canonical VO flow\\n1. Receive PM job handoff\\n2. Validate PM job via `job_input_validator`\\n3. Bootstrap run via `vo_start`\\n4. Create the run directory and initial artifacts\\n5. Fetch next eligible script via `script_fetcher`\\n6. Lock the script row via `script_locker`\\n7. Persist local script artifacts via `script_metadata_writer`\\n8. Write `vo_script_ready.json`\\n9. Hand off to S1\\n\\n## Runtime execution rule\\nWhen a request is clearly asking for an actual VO execution or test:\\n- use the repo runtime, not just conceptual reasoning\\n- prefer the deterministic substrate under `C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\vo\\\\`\\n- if needed, read contracts first, then execute the canonical runtime path\\n- only return a non-ready result when the runtime/config/credentials genuinely block execution\\n\\n## Important workflow rules\\n- Do not create false readiness without actual artifacts\\n- Do not skip script lock when readiness depends on it\\n- Do not declare `ready_for_s1` if checkpoint/artifacts are missing\\n- Preserve persisted filesystem truth over conversational convenience\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_vXrnsC6OTru3p91u9q5thX6g|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd24d38df8819094cfba49df85b004","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\AGENTS.md","content":"# AGENTS.md - VO Workspace\n\nThis workspace is the home of the Video Orchestrator supervisor.\n\n## Session startup\nBefore doing anything else:\n1. Read `IDENTITY.md`\n2. Read `CONTEXT.md`\n3. Read `WORKFLOW.md`\n4. Read recent `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` if present\n\n## Operating rules\n- Prefer concrete runtime execution over abstract summaries when asked to test or run VO.\n- Do not invent readiness.\n- The VO's job is to deliver a real `ready_for_s1` run, not to merely describe how bootstrap should work.\n\n## Memory\nKeep brief notes in daily memory when important VO decisions or edge cases are discovered.\n\n## Red lines\n- Never declare `ready_for_s1` without the required artifacts/checkpoints.\n- Never skip blocking validation of PM job input.\n- Never hide script-fetch or lock failure behind optimistic prose.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\\\AGENTS.md\",\"content\":\"# AGENTS.md - VO Workspace\\n\\nThis workspace is the home of the Video Orchestrator supervisor.\\n\\n## Session startup\\nBefore doing anything else:\\n1. Read `IDENTITY.md`\\n2. Read `CONTEXT.md`\\n3. Read `WORKFLOW.md`\\n4. Read recent `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` if present\\n\\n## Operating rules\\n- Prefer concrete runtime execution over abstract summaries when asked to test or run VO.\\n- Do not invent readiness.\\n- The VO's job is to deliver a real `ready_for_s1` run, not to merely describe how bootstrap should work.\\n\\n## Memory\\nKeep brief notes in daily memory when important VO decisions or edge cases are discovered.\\n\\n## Red lines\\n- Never declare `ready_for_s1` without the required artifacts/checkpoints.\\n- Never skip blocking validation of PM job input.\\n- Never hide script-fetch or lock failure behind optimistic prose.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4srCD0o31QCJuIumjPRvgb4C|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd24d38e0881908acd7e973f7dee33","name":"write","argumen