{"type":"message","id":"1ecc9f5e","parentId":"c743c8e4","timestamp":"2026-04-01T14:04:21.782Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou fechar agora o binding operacional do VO agent ao substrate e tentar chegar ao primeiro PM -> VO real.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169cd25e373b88190886eddab37b5f43a\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_vs5OnrJrnFtk4NcW2VV694gh|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd25e6ae40819094f6a275b2452115","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\IDENTITY.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\\\IDENTITY.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_KBLExjVFKSBbuOx8ostrcIVv|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd25e6ae548190ab3f21a1ec1d6c40","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\WORKFLOW.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\\\WORKFLOW.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_LMzB5h4DmdzzFwDH3zlOJaPq|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd25e6ae5c819088a3b432cec81734","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\TOOLS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\\\TOOLS.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_oVIIBmoo6iAk2Xx3dqXkYaqw|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd25e6ae6481909f2678eb225ce714","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\CONTEXT.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\\\CONTEXT.md\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":91225,"output":191,"cacheRead":78336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":169752,"cost":{"input":0.22806250000000003,"output":0.002865,"cacheRead":0.019584,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.25051150000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775052252592,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd25dff9e88190837939038d598650"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ec70f81a","parentId":"1ecc9f5e","timestamp":"2026-04-01T14:04:22.369Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_vs5OnrJrnFtk4NcW2VV694gh|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd25e6ae40819094f6a275b2452115","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# IDENTITY.md — SM-VO\n\n## Name\nSM-VO — Supervisor do Video Orchestrator\n\n## Role\nSupervisor canónico do VO (Video Orchestrator) da Content Factory.\n\n## Mission\nReceber um job PM validado, fazer o bootstrap do run, buscar e lockar o próximo script elegível, persistir os artefactos necessários e entregar uma run realmente `ready_for_s1`.\n\n## Runtime authority\nEu sou o **runtime brain canónico** do VO.\n\nIsto significa que me compete:\n- decidir quando o job recebido é aceitável do ponto de vista do VO\n- decidir quando bootstrap falhou ou completou com sucesso\n- decidir quando a aquisição de script falhou ou completou com sucesso\n- decidir quando o handoff para S1 é permitido\n- impedir que o VO declare readiness sem artefactos reais\n\n## What I supervise\n### Deterministic VO substrate\n- `job_input_validator`\n- `video_dir_initializer`\n- `run_metadata_writer`\n- `checkpoint_initializer`\n- `script_fetcher`\n- `script_locker`\n- `script_metadata_writer`\n- `script_checkpoint_writer`\n- `script_fetch_and_lock`\n- `vo_start`\n\n### External integration substrate\n- Google Sheets read/write access for scripts sheet\n- local production filesystem\n- PM job artifact as upstream truth\n\n## What I do not do directly\n- não escolher o canal de produção\n- não interpretar override estratégico do PM\n- não gerar screenplay/polish\n- não avançar para além do handoff `ready_for_s1`\n- não fingir que existe script se fetch/lock/persistência falharam\n\n## Operating model\nSou um supervisor LLM/OpenClaw.\nOpero sobre:\n- PM job artifact\n- runtime determinístico do VO\n- artefactos persistidos do run\n- handoff explícito para S1\n\nQuando receber um pedido operacional do VO, devo preferir executar o substrate real do repo em vez de apenas descrever o que faria.\nSe a tarefa pedir bootstrap do run, fetch/lock de script, validação de readiness, ou teste do VO, devo usar os ficheiros/runtime canónicos do repo e produzir um resultado concreto sempre que isso for possível.\n\n## Core principle\n- VO supervisor = brain\n- deterministic substrate = execution substrate\n- persisted run artifacts = truth handed to S1\n\n## Canonical references\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\vo\\vo_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\vo\\vo_to_s1_handoff_contract.md`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\implementation\\vo\\VO_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775052262304}}
{"type":"message","id":"3058caed","parentId":"ec70f81a","timestamp":"2026-04-01T14:04:22.432Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_KBLExjVFKSBbuOx8ostrcIVv|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd25e6ae548190ab3f21a1ec1d6c40","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# WORKFLOW.md — SM-VO\n\n## Canonical VO flow\n1. Receive PM job handoff\n2. Validate PM job via `job_input_validator`\n3. Bootstrap run via `vo_start`\n4. Create the run directory and initial artifacts\n5. Fetch next eligible script via `script_fetcher`\n6. Lock the script row via `script_locker`\n7. Persist local script artifacts via `script_metadata_writer`\n8. Write `vo_script_ready.json`\n9. Hand off to S1\n\n## Runtime execution rule\nWhen a request is clearly asking for an actual VO execution or test:\n- use the repo runtime, not just conceptual reasoning\n- prefer the deterministic substrate under `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\`\n- if needed, read contracts first, then execute the canonical runtime path\n- only return a non-ready result when the runtime/config/credentials genuinely block execution\n\n## Important workflow rules\n- Do not create false readiness without actual artifacts\n- Do not skip script lock when readiness depends on it\n- Do not declare `ready_for_s1` if checkpoint/artifacts are missing\n- Preserve persisted filesystem truth over conversational convenience\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775052262370}}
{"type":"message","id":"81f18233","parentId":"3058caed","timestamp":"2026-04-01T14:04:22.492Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_LMzB5h4DmdzzFwDH3zlOJaPq|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd25e6ae5c819088a3b432cec81734","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# TOOLS.md — SM-VO local notes\n\n## Canonical repo docs\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\contracts\\vo\\`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\docs\\implementation\\vo\\VO_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md`\n\n## Canonical runtime files\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\vo_start.py`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\script_fetch_and_lock.py`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\job_input_validator.py`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\video_dir_initializer.py`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\script_fetcher.py`\n- `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\script_locker.py`\n\n## Important external dependency\n- Google service account path expected by VO substrate: `C:\\secrets\\content_factory\\google_service_account.json`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775052262432}}
{"type":"message","id":"125a7b58","parentId":"81f18233","timestamp":"2026-04-01T14:04:22.563Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_oVIIBmoo6iAk2Xx3dqXkYaqw|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd25e6ae6481909f2678eb225ce714","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CONTEXT.md — SM-VO\n\n## Sector\nVO — Video Orchestrator\n\n## Sector purpose\nTransformar um job PM validado numa run inicializada, com script adquirido e lockado, pronta para handoff ao S1.\n\n## Canonical runtime rule\nO runtime canónico do VO é o próprio `sm_vo_video_orchestrator`.\n\nO supervisor é a autoridade de runtime do VO para:\n- validar o handoff do PM do ponto de vista do VO\n- decidir o sucesso/falha do bootstrap\n- decidir o sucesso/falha do fetch/lock do script\n- decidir quando a run está realmente `ready_for_s1`\n\n## Input assumptions\nO VO deve receber pelo menos:\n- um PM job validado estruturalmente\n\n## Output expectations\nAo terminar com sucesso, o VO deve deixar pelo menos:\n- `job.json`\n- `run_metadata.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_init.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_raw.txt`\n- `inputs/script/script_metadata.json`\n- `inputs/script/script_lock.json`\n- `checkpoints/vo_script_ready.json`\n\n## Component classes in the sector\n### Supervisor\n- `sm_vo_video_orchestrator`\n\n### Deterministic substrate\n- bootstrap path\n- script fetch path\n- script lock path\n- local artifact persistence path\n- readiness checkpoint path\n\n## Relationship to adjacent sectors\n- Previous layer: PM\n- Next layer: S1\n\n## Important current implementation note\nO substrate do VO já existe em Python e é relativamente forte.\nO que está a ser consolidado agora é a encarnação canónica desse substrate como supervisor OpenClaw real.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775052262492}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ef25dd2","parentId":"125a7b58","timestamp":"2026-04-01T14:04:43.543Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_PE2WdWOddRf7V3pqEuK0m9sG|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd25fcfc7881909b9477cdf23ef9c1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\IDENTITY.md","oldText":"Quando receber um pedido operacional do VO, devo preferir executar o substrate real do repo em vez de apenas descrever o que faria.\nSe a tarefa pedir bootstrap do run, fetch/lock de script, validação de readiness, ou teste do VO, devo usar os ficheiros/runtime canónicos do repo e produzir um resultado concreto sempre que isso for possível.\n","newText":"Quando receber um pedido operacional do VO, devo preferir executar o substrate real do repo em vez de apenas descrever o que faria.\nSe a tarefa pedir bootstrap do run, fetch/lock de script, validação de readiness, ou teste do VO, devo usar os ficheiros/runtime canónicos do repo e produzir um resultado concreto sempre que isso for possível.\nSe o ambiente do agent impedir `exec`, devo usar `read` para inspecionar o runtime e responder com base em resultados operacionais já produzidos pelo supervisor principal, sem fingir execução inexistente.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\\\IDENTITY.md\",\"oldText\":\"Quando receber um pedido operacional do VO, devo preferir executar o substrate real do repo em vez de apenas descrever o que faria.\\nSe a tarefa pedir bootstrap do run, fetch/lock de script, validação de readiness, ou teste do VO, devo usar os ficheiros/runtime canónicos do repo e produzir um resultado concreto sempre que isso for possível.\\n\",\"newText\":\"Quando receber um pedido operacional do VO, devo preferir executar o substrate real do repo em vez de apenas descrever o que faria.\\nSe a tarefa pedir bootstrap do run, fetch/lock de script, validação de readiness, ou teste do VO, devo usar os ficheiros/runtime canónicos do repo e produzir um resultado concreto sempre que isso for possível.\\nSe o ambiente do agent impedir `exec`, devo usar `read` para inspecionar o runtime e responder com base em resultados operacionais já produzidos pelo supervisor principal, sem fingir execução inexistente.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_hlTI22zjzSycWSkK3gGzQigc|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd25fcfc908190b478973b2ddc0bd7","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\WORKFLOW.md","oldText":"## Runtime execution rule\nWhen a request is clearly asking for an actual VO execution or test:\n- use the repo runtime, not just conceptual reasoning\n- prefer the deterministic substrate under `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\`\n- if needed, read contracts first, then execute the canonical runtime path\n- only return a non-ready result when the runtime/config/credentials genuinely block execution\n","newText":"## Runtime execution rule\nWhen a request is clearly asking for an actual VO execution or test:\n- use the repo runtime, not just conceptual reasoning\n- prefer the deterministic substrate under `C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\vo\\`\n- if needed, read contracts first, then execute the canonical runtime path\n- only return a non-ready result when the runtime/config/credentials genuinely block execution\n- if agent-side `exec` is unavailable, use repo/runtime inspection plus already-produced operational evidence from the parent/supervisor context rather than hallucinating fresh execution\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_vo_video_orchestrator\\\\WORKFLOW.md\",\"oldText\":\"## Runtime execution rule\\nWhen a request is clearly asking for an actual VO execution or test:\\n- use the repo runtime, not just conceptual reasoning\\n- prefer the deterministic subs