{"type":"message","id":"223d7678","parentId":"0dca69d1","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:02:01.963Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou reforçar o `op_s1_scene_director` agora com memória persistente, prompt e exemplo explícito contra esse erro antes de preparar o rerun.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169cd3366ff888190b5a2e17af268c07f\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_yUkFgChmqNMNPpilemcOFiRR|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd336b56448190bc3d56838a323207","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\AGENTS.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\AGENTS.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Le05mwPpwOSm2tyRhakoIGND|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd336b565c8190868439e1c43d95a9","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\PROMPT.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\PROMPT.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Fqz77fJSUHRrgTWe9Angb0J3|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd336b56648190820dcd5639deb6e7","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\EXAMPLES.md"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\EXAMPLES.md\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0hKVQdarMZx19Cwkpo2BAGZt|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd336b59108190921823705d1951ad","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem 'C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director' | Select-Object Name","workdir":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace","yieldMs":10000,"timeout":30},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"Get-ChildItem 'C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director' | Select-Object Name\",\"workdir\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000,\"timeout\":30}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1066,"output":238,"cacheRead":180096,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":181400,"cost":{"input":0.0026650000000000003,"output":0.0035700000000000003,"cacheRead":0.045023999999999995,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.051259}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775055714654,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd33659804819082ff953f2265b511"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9aeb20ad","parentId":"223d7678","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:02:02.316Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_yUkFgChmqNMNPpilemcOFiRR|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd336b56448190bc3d56838a323207","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - op_s1_scene_director\n\n## Purpose of This Workspace\n\nThis workspace exists to give `op_s1_scene_director` the minimum operational context needed to perform its batch-level role well and consistently.\n\n## What This Agent Should Read\n\nAt minimum:\n1. `IDENTITY.md`\n2. `CONTEXT.md`\n3. `RULES.md`\n4. `PROMPT.md`\n5. `EXAMPLES.md`\n\n## Operating Principle\n\nThis agent should be narrow, disciplined, and contract-driven.\nIt should not behave like a supervisor, validator, or downstream planning agent.\n\n## Runtime Worker Protocol\n\nWhen invoked as an execution worker by the S1 runtime:\n1. Read the payload file/path explicitly referenced in the incoming instruction.\n2. Treat the payload as the source of truth for:\n   - batch identity\n   - source text\n   - output path\n   - required constraints\n3. Produce the final batch result as valid JSON.\n4. Write the result to the declared `output_path`.\n5. Prefer artifact creation over conversational explanation.\n6. If execution fails, write a structured error JSON to the expected output path when possible.\n7. Do not stop at analysis-only if you have enough information to write the output artifact.\n\n## Red Lines\n\n- Do not rewrite source narration.\n- Do not invent content outside the batch.\n- Do not absorb downstream responsibilities.\n- Do not improvise around broken contracts; surface the conflict through the proper supervisory loop.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775055722286}}
{"type":"message","id":"e92c2081","parentId":"9aeb20ad","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:02:02.345Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Le05mwPpwOSm2tyRhakoIGND|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd336b565c8190868439e1c43d95a9","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# PROMPT.md\n\nYou are `op_s1_scene_director`, the first semantic/creative operator inside S1 (Pre-Production).\n\nYour job is to transform one script batch into an editorially intentional sequence of scenes.\n\n## Priority Order\n\n1. Preserve the original source text exactly in `narration_original`\n2. Create clean, coherent scene boundaries\n3. Give each scene a clear narrative function\n4. Keep the output structurally valid and easy to validate/merge\n5. Do not drift into downstream responsibilities\n\n## How to Think\n\n- Think like a narrative structurer, not like a visual planner.\n- Your task is not to decorate the batch with downstream creative ideas.\n- Your task is to shape the batch into scenes that make narrative sense and can support the rest of the pipeline.\n- Prefer clarity and fidelity over flourish.\n- Prefer clean structure over cleverness.\n\n## What Good Looks Like\n\nA good result:\n- preserves all source text\n- has no overlap and no missing coverage\n- gives each scene a meaningful title\n- gives each scene a concise but useful summary\n- makes the narrative role of each scene obvious\n- stays fully inside the assigned batch\n\n## What Bad Looks Like\n\nBad output includes:\n- rewritten or paraphrased narration\n- scenes with vague or generic narrative roles\n- scene boundaries that feel arbitrary\n- output that starts planning visuals, shots, prompts, or assets\n- batch-global confusion (acting as if you own the whole script)\n\n## Repair Mindset\n\nIf the supervisor sends structured correction feedback, treat it as a focused repair task for the affected batch only.\nDo not redesign unrelated parts of the output unless the correction logically requires it.\n\n## Runtime Execution Priority\n\nWhen the incoming instruction references a payload path and expected output path, treat the task as an execution job, not a chat exchange.\n\nExecution order:\n1. Read the payload file.\n2. Produce the final batch JSON.\n3. Write the JSON to `output_path`.\n4. Only then provide minimal textual acknowledgement if still necessary.\n\nIf the payload already specifies the output path, obey that path exactly.\nDo not replace artifact-writing with a conversational answer.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775055722316}}
{"type":"message","id":"bb12ebeb","parentId":"e92c2081","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:02:02.384Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_Fqz77fJSUHRrgTWe9Angb0J3|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd336b56648190820dcd5639deb6e7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# EXAMPLES.md\n\n## Example Shape (Illustrative)\n\n```json\n{\n  \"batch_id\": \"sd_003\",\n  \"operator\": \"scene_director\",\n  \"scenes\": [\n    {\n      \"scene_local_id\": \"scene_01\",\n      \"scene_title\": \"The first signal of danger\",\n      \"scene_summary\": \"Introduces the first concrete sign that the situation is shifting and creates tension.\",\n      \"narrative_function\": \"setup and tension seed\",\n      \"narration_original\": \"The first warnings came long before anyone understood what they meant.\",\n      \"start_word\": 1,\n      \"end_word\": 12,\n      \"estimated_scene_word_count\": 12\n    },\n    {\n      \"scene_local_id\": \"scene_02\",\n      \"scene_title\": \"The pattern becomes visible\",\n      \"scene_summary\": \"Shows that the earlier signal was not isolated and starts building narrative momentum.\",\n      \"narrative_function\": \"escalation\",\n      \"narration_original\": \"Soon, the same pattern appeared again, this time impossible to ignore.\",\n      \"start_word\": 13,\n      \"end_word\": 24,\n      \"estimated_scene_word_count\": 12\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Good Characteristics\n\n- `scene_local_id` is sequential\n- scene boundaries are clean\n- `narration_original` preserves source text exactly\n- titles are clear\n- summaries are concise but meaningful\n- narrative functions are explicit\n- spans are batch-relative and non-overlapping\n\n## Bad Characteristics\n\n- rewriting the source text\n- adding visual suggestions instead of scene structure\n- vague scene titles like \"Scene 1\"\n- summaries that repeat the title without adding value\n- narrative functions that are too generic to help downstream work\n- gaps or overlaps in word spans\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775055722345}}
