{"type":"message","id":"cb180f57","parentId":"5f3cfb3a","timestamp":"2026-04-01T15:02:41.231Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_pvdbgiKx1Wc4HpZ3P298aHIn|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd3392a7508190b74f91efc0a7acc6","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\MEMORY.md","content":"# MEMORY.md — op_s1_scene_director\n\n## Critical lessons\n\n### Batch-relative coordinates are mandatory\nWhen executing one scene_director batch:\n- `start_word` and `end_word` must always be **batch-relative**\n- the first word in the current batch is always `1`\n- never output global script coordinates\n- never use `batch.start_word` as an output offset\n\n### `narration_original` must match the declared span exactly\nFor every scene:\n- `narration_original` must correspond exactly to the source text covered by `start_word`..`end_word`\n- do not paraphrase\n- do not merge or trim text in ways that break span alignment\n\n## Failure mode already observed\nA real integrated `PM -> VO -> S1` test failed because:\n- batches `sd_002` to `sd_005` returned global coordinates instead of local batch coordinates\n- `sd_001` also had narration/span mismatch\n- this produced validator errors including:\n  - `invalid_scene_span`\n  - `missing_coverage_detected`\n  - `narration_source_mismatch`\n\n## Non-negotiable rule\nNever repeat this mistake.\nIf the batch starts at global word 718 in the source script, the first local word in the output is still `1`.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\MEMORY.md\",\"content\":\"# MEMORY.md — op_s1_scene_director\\n\\n## Critical lessons\\n\\n### Batch-relative coordinates are mandatory\\nWhen executing one scene_director batch:\\n- `start_word` and `end_word` must always be **batch-relative**\\n- the first word in the current batch is always `1`\\n- never output global script coordinates\\n- never use `batch.start_word` as an output offset\\n\\n### `narration_original` must match the declared span exactly\\nFor every scene:\\n- `narration_original` must correspond exactly to the source text covered by `start_word`..`end_word`\\n- do not paraphrase\\n- do not merge or trim text in ways that break span alignment\\n\\n## Failure mode already observed\\nA real integrated `PM -> VO -> S1` test failed because:\\n- batches `sd_002` to `sd_005` returned global coordinates instead of local batch coordinates\\n- `sd_001` also had narration/span mismatch\\n- this produced validator errors including:\\n  - `invalid_scene_span`\\n  - `missing_coverage_detected`\\n  - `narration_source_mismatch`\\n\\n## Non-negotiable rule\\nNever repeat this mistake.\\nIf the batch starts at global word 718 in the source script, the first local word in the output is still `1`.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ccNUCYSpCB8KE2uOfAMYzftv|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd3392a7648190ab6eae7a56e85ff4","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\AGENTS.md","oldText":"At minimum:\n1. `IDENTITY.md`\n2. `CONTEXT.md`\n3. `RULES.md`\n4. `PROMPT.md`\n5. `EXAMPLES.md`\n","newText":"At minimum:\n1. `IDENTITY.md`\n2. `CONTEXT.md`\n3. `RULES.md`\n4. `PROMPT.md`\n5. `EXAMPLES.md`\n6. `MEMORY.md`\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\AGENTS.md\",\"oldText\":\"At minimum:\\n1. `IDENTITY.md`\\n2. `CONTEXT.md`\\n3. `RULES.md`\\n4. `PROMPT.md`\\n5. `EXAMPLES.md`\\n\",\"newText\":\"At minimum:\\n1. `IDENTITY.md`\\n2. `CONTEXT.md`\\n3. `RULES.md`\\n4. `PROMPT.md`\\n5. `EXAMPLES.md`\\n6. `MEMORY.md`\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Q3lWfj1GoMJTJXiSK8ATvQhS|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd3392a77481908710104115458862","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\PROMPT.md","oldText":"A good result:\n- preserves all source text\n- has no overlap and no missing coverage\n- gives each scene a meaningful title\n- gives each scene a concise but useful summary\n- makes the narrative role of each scene obvious\n- stays fully inside the assigned batch\n","newText":"A good result:\n- preserves all source text\n- has no overlap and no missing coverage\n- gives each scene a meaningful title\n- gives each scene a concise but useful summary\n- makes the narrative role of each scene obvious\n- stays fully inside the assigned batch\n- uses strictly batch-relative word coordinates\n- keeps `narration_original` exactly aligned to the declared span\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\PROMPT.md\",\"oldText\":\"A good result:\\n- preserves all source text\\n- has no overlap and no missing coverage\\n- gives each scene a meaningful title\\n- gives each scene a concise but useful summary\\n- makes the narrative role of each scene obvious\\n- stays fully inside the assigned batch\\n\",\"newText\":\"A good result:\\n- preserves all source text\\n- has no overlap and no missing coverage\\n- gives each scene a meaningful title\\n- gives each scene a concise but useful summary\\n- makes the narrative role of each scene obvious\\n- stays fully inside the assigned batch\\n- uses strictly batch-relative word coordinates\\n- keeps `narration_original` exactly aligned to the declared span\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_MiKdRfoYrOZVnR9L4ELRRQRo|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd3392a78081908521de9ffecc5055","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\PROMPT.md","oldText":"Bad output includes:\n- rewritten or paraphrased narration\n- scenes with vague or generic narrative roles\n- scene boundaries that feel arbitrary\n- output that starts planning visuals, shots, prompts, or assets\n- batch-global confusion (acting as if you own the whole script)\n","newText":"Bad output includes:\n- rewritten or paraphrased narration\n- scenes with vague or generic narrative roles\n- scene boundaries that feel arbitrary\n- output that starts planning visuals, shots, prompts, or assets\n- batch-global confusion (acting as if you own the whole script)\n- using global script word coordinates instead of local batch coordinates\n- `narration_original` text that does not exactly match the declared span\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\PROMPT.md\",\"oldText\":\"Bad output includes:\\n- rewritten or paraphrased narration\\n- scenes with vague or generic narrative roles\\n- scene boundaries that feel arbitrary\\n- output that starts planning visuals, shots, prompts, or assets\\n- batch-global confusion (acting as if you own the whole script)\\n\",\"newText\":\"Bad output includes:\\n- rewritten or paraphrased narration\\n- scenes with vague or generic narrative roles\\n- scene boundaries that feel arbitrary\\n- output that starts planning visuals, shots, prompts, or assets\\n- batch-global confusion (acting as if you own the whole script)\\n- using global script word coordinates instead of local batch coordinates\\n- `narration_original` text that does not exactly match the declared span\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6T0qQMbHxo3lkEorirPfA4KE|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd3392a78c8190b0b014960045c286","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\PROMPT.md","oldText":"Execution order:\n1. Read the payload file.\n2. Produce the final batch JSON.\n3. Write the JSON to `output_path`.\n4. Only then provide minimal textual acknowledgement if still necessary.\n\nIf the payload already specifies the output path, obey that path exactly.\nDo not replace artifact-writing with a conversational answer.\n","newText":"Execution order:\n1. Read the payload file.\n2. Produce the final batch JSON.\n3. Verify that every scene span is batch-relative.\n4. Verify that `narration_original` exactly matches the source text implied by that span.\n5. Write the JSON to `output_path`.\n6. Only then provide minimal textual acknowledgement if still necessary.\n\nIf the payload already specifies the output path, obey that path exactly.\nDo not replace artifact-writing with a conversational answer.\n\n## Absolute coordinate rule\nIf a batch payload says:\n- `batch.start_word = 718`\n- `batch.end_word = 1466`\n- `word_count = 749`\n\nthat does **not** mean your output should start at 718.\nIt means the batch covers a global window of the script, but your output coordinates must still run locally from `1` to `749`.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\PROMPT.md\",\"oldText\":\"Execution order:\\n1. Read the payload file.\\n2. Produce the final batch JSON.\\n3. Write the JSON to `output_path`.\\n4. Only then provide minimal textual acknowledgement if still necessary.\\n\\nIf the payload already specifies the output path, obey that path exactly.\\nDo not replace artifact-writing with a conversational answer.\\n\",\"newText\":\"Execution order:\\n1. Read the payload file.\\n2. Produce the final batch JSON.\\n3. Verify that every scene span is batch-relative.\\n4. Verify that `narration_original` exactly matches the source text implied by that span.\\n5. Write the JSON to `output_path`.\\n6. Only then provide minimal textual acknowledgement if still necessary.\\n\\nIf the payload already specifies the output path, obey that path exactly.\\nDo not replace artifact-writing with a conversational answer.\\n\\n## Absolute coordinate rule\\nIf a batch payload says:\\n- `batch.start_word = 718`\\n- `batch.end_word = 1466`\\n- `word_count = 749`\\n\\nthat does **not** mean your output should start at 718.\\nIt means the batch covers a global window of the script, but your output coordinates must still run locally from `1` to `749`.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_dO41jND4D844V4YpETYcBfMq|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd3392a79c8190b902f44f03e