{"type":"message","id":"cd7c4628","parentId":"cf070368","timestamp":"2026-04-01T16:59:12.552Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_mSrm3HjXcrwQObN62sLKzTKb|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd4edfe56c81909cec2b68b6e0e7cf","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\sm_s1_pre_production\\WORKFLOW.md","oldText":"7. Validate each batch.\n8. Merge approved outputs.\n9. Validate full screenplay.\n","newText":"7. Normalize scene_director outputs deterministically when needed.\n8. Validate each batch.\n9. Merge approved outputs.\n10. Validate full screenplay.\n\n## Important scene_director lane rule\nThe scene_director lane is now hybrid:\n- operator owns semantic grouping and scene meaning\n- deterministic substrate owns more of the mechanical span/alignment normalization\n- localized boundary issues should be treated as repair candidates, not immediate proof that the whole lane design is wrong\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\sm_s1_pre_production\\\\WORKFLOW.md\",\"oldText\":\"7. Validate each batch.\\n8. Merge approved outputs.\\n9. Validate full screenplay.\\n\",\"newText\":\"7. Normalize scene_director outputs deterministically when needed.\\n8. Validate each batch.\\n9. Merge approved outputs.\\n10. Validate full screenplay.\\n\\n## Important scene_director lane rule\\nThe scene_director lane is now hybrid:\\n- operator owns semantic grouping and scene meaning\\n- deterministic substrate owns more of the mechanical span/alignment normalization\\n- localized boundary issues should be treated as repair candidates, not immediate proof that the whole lane design is wrong\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_sVX156m8W4fNMkYPnbYE5EFq|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd4edfe824819081eab6ba9c9945f2","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\agents\\op_s1_scene_director\\PROMPT.md","oldText":"A good result:\n- preserves all source text\n- has no overlap and no missing coverage\n- gives each scene a meaningful title\n- gives each scene a concise but useful summary\n- makes the narrative role of each scene obvious\n- stays fully inside the assigned batch\n- uses strictly batch-relative word coordinates\n- keeps `narration_original` exactly aligned to the declared span\n","newText":"A good result:\n- preserves all source text\n- gives each scene a meaningful title\n- gives each scene a concise but useful summary\n- makes the narrative role of each scene obvious\n- stays fully inside the assigned batch\n- keeps scene boundaries semantically clean\n- avoids letting one scene swallow the opening sentence of the next scene\n\nImportant: the runtime may normalize exact spans/text alignment downstream. Your main job is to produce correct semantic grouping and faithful scene content, not to behave like a word-counter.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\agents\\\\op_s1_scene_director\\\\PROMPT.md\",\"oldText\":\"A good result:\\n- preserves all source text\\n- has no overlap and no missing coverage\\n- gives each scene a meaningful title\\n- gives each scene a concise but useful summary\\n- makes the narrative role of each scene obvious\\n- stays fully inside the assigned batch\\n- uses strictly batch-relative word coordinates\\n- keeps `narration_original` exactly aligned to the declared span\\n\",\"newText\":\"A good result:\\n- preserves all source text\\n- gives each scene a meaningful title\\n- gives each scene a concise but useful summary\\n- makes the narrative role of each scene obvious\\n- stays fully inside the assigned batch\\n- keeps scene boundaries semantically clean\\n- avoids letting one scene swallow the opening sentence of the next scene\\n\\nImportant: the runtime may normalize exact spans/text alignment downstream. Your main job is to produce correct semantic grouping and faithful scene content, not to behave like a word-counter.\\n\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_FVAYwKmZ