{"type":"message","id":"a3ee1d58","parentId":"de053be7","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:20:28.542Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_R9yt7r7bFHAlMQOoQyZv9IYK|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd53db22f481908f2223426cf21fd7","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Select-String : N�o � poss�vel localizar um par�metro que coincida com o nome de par�metro 'Recurse'.\r\nNo linha:1 caractere:184\r\n+ ... efine|evaluator|word_count|scene_count' -SimpleMatch -Recurse -ErrorA ...\r\n+                                                          ~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : InvalidArgument: (:) [Select-String], ParameterBindingException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NamedParameterNotFound,Microsoft.PowerShell.Commands.SelectStringCommand\n\n(Command exited with code 1)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":1,"durationMs":730,"aggregated":"Select-String : N�o � poss�vel localizar um par�metro que coincida com o nome de par�metro 'Recurse'.\r\nNo linha:1 caractere:184\r\n+ ... efine|evaluator|word_count|scene_count' -SimpleMatch -Recurse -ErrorA ...\r\n+                                                          ~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : InvalidArgument: (:) [Select-String], ParameterBindingException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : NamedParameterNotFound,Microsoft.PowerShell.Commands.SelectStringCommand\n\n(Command exited with code 1)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775064028426}}
{"type":"message","id":"d217c535","parentId":"a3ee1d58","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:20:38.609Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_8AiosNRIEOGjuBgBt7zTdB1L|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd53e652bc8190a0934e93bba36c9e","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\shared\\processors\\scene_word_count_checker.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\content_factory_v3\\\\shared\\\\processors\\\\scene_word_count_checker.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_W4d5W5Yk4KonxpdCc2H4pb9O|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd53e652d0819099e448f2a09f609f","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\shared\\processors\\scene_text_validator.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\content_factory_v3\\\\shared\\\\processors\\\\scene_text_validator.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5rERSrRRhgvW9yVjMPyQ8c76|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd53e652d88190b33477efea4634b5","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\shared\\processors\\scene_reconstructor.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\content_factory_v3\\\\shared\\\\processors\\\\scene_reconstructor.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3GMMEYmoTeTet0etgI9ShumG|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd53e652e08190aef8397cfc7ace03","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\shared\\agents\\refinement_loop.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\content_factory_v3\\\\shared\\\\agents\\\\refinement_loop.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_NmjdtABSkCqLIXALUxfQO2SV|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd53e652e88190a2271fe26037377b","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\shared\\agents\\evaluator_agent.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\content_factory_v3\\\\shared\\\\agents\\\\evaluator_agent.py\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ohXPPFpQgEd88MWmpuqNO9Ky|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd53e652f08190bb1ef4ce7edcc4e7","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\content_factory_v3\\shared\\processors\\parallel_screenplay.py"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\content_factory_v3\\\\shared\\\\processors\\\\parallel_screenplay.py\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":13905,"output":255,"cacheRead":204288,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":218448,"cost":{"input":0.0347625,"output":0.0038250000000000003,"cacheRead":0.051072,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0896595}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775064029365,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd53de49488190841dccfc2206e026"}}
{"type":"message","id":"07629ac5","parentId":"d217c535","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:20:39.889Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8AiosNRIEOGjuBgBt7zTdB1L|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd53e652bc8190a0934e93bba36c9e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\r\nScene Word Count Pre-Check — deterministic Python validator.\r\n\r\nRuns BEFORE the LLM evaluator to catch word count violations for free.\r\nGenerates specific feedback for the screenplay agent to fix violations in 1 retry.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Optional, Tuple\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _count_units(text: str, language: str) -> int:\r\n    \"\"\"Count content units: characters for CJK, words for alphabetic.\"\"\"\r\n    if language in (\"ja\", \"ko\"):\r\n        return len(text.strip())\r\n    return len(text.split())\r\n\r\n\r\ndef check_scene_word_counts(\r\n    scenes: List[Dict],\r\n    min_words: int,\r\n    max_words: int,\r\n    tolerance: int = 3,\r\n    language: str = \"en\",\r\n) -> Tuple[bool, Optional[Dict]]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Check word counts of all scenes and generate feedback if violations found.\r\n\r\n    Args:\r\n        scenes: List of scene dicts with \"text\", \"word_count\", \"scene_number\"\r\n        min_words: Minimum words per scene (from LANGUAGE_WORD_LIMITS)\r\n        max_words: Maximum words per scene (from LANGUAGE_WORD_LIMITS)\r\n        tolerance: Accept scenes within [min - tolerance, max + tolerance]\r\n        language: Language code (ja/ko use character count)\r\n\r\n    Returns:\r\n        (True, None) if all scenes are within acceptable range\r\n        (False, feedback_dict) if violations found — feedback ready for agent retry\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if not scenes:\r\n        return True, None\r\n\r\n    effective_min = min_words - tolerance\r\n    effective_max = max_words + tolerance\r\n    unit_name = \"characters\" if language in (\"ja\", \"ko\") else \"words\"\r\n\r\n    violations = []\r\n\r\n    for scene in scenes:\r\n        text = scene.get(\"text\", \"\")\r\n        actual_count = _count_units(text, language)\r\n        scene_num = scene.get(\"scene_number\", \"?\")\r\n\r\n        if actual_count < effective_min:\r\n            violations.append({\r\n                \"scene_number\": scene_num,\r\n                \"current_count\": actual_count,\r\n                \"min_required\": min_words,\r\n                \"action\": f\"MERGE with adjacent scene - this scene has only {actual_count} {unit_name} (minimum {min_words})\",\r\n                \"suggestion\": f\"Combine scene {scene_num} with the previous or next scene that shares thematic connection. The merged scene must stay under {max_words} {unit_name}.\",\r\n            })\r\n        elif actual_count > effective_max:\r\n            violations.append({\r\n                \"scene_number\": scene_num,\r\n                \"current_count\": actual_count,\r\n                \"max_allowed\": max_words,\r\n                \"action\": f\"SPLIT at sentence boundary - this scene has {actual_count} {unit_name} (maximum {max_words})\",\r\n                \"suggestion\": f\"Split scene {scene_num} into two scenes at a natural sentence boundary. Each resulting scene must have at least {min_words} {unit_name}.\",\r\n            })\r\n\r\n    if not violations:\r\n        return True, None\r\n\r\n    feedback = {\r\n        \"is_retry\": True,\r\n        \"word_count_fix_required\": True,\r\n        \"scenes_to_fix\": violations,\r\n        \"total_violations\": len(violations),\r\n        \"instruction\": (\r\n            f\"Fix ONLY the {len(violations)} word count violation(s) listed below. \"\r\n            f\"Keep all other scenes UNCHANGED. Preserve ALL metadata fields \"\r\n            f\"(faction_shown, interpretation_mode, emotional_tone, reasoning). \"\r\n            f\"Valid range: {min_words}-{max_words} {unit_name} per scene.\"\r\n        ),\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    return False, feedback\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775064039738}}
{"type":"message","id":"7a428c2b","parentId":"07629ac5","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:20:40.016Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_W4d5W5Yk4KonxpdCc2H4pb9O|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd53e652d0819099e448f2a09f609f","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\r\nScene Text Validator — deterministic Python validator.\r\n\r\nReplaces the LLM screenplay evaluator for text-coverage checks.\r\nValidates: missing_text, duplicate_text, empty_scenes, scene_order.\r\nGenerates specific feedback for the screenplay agent to fix violations in 1 retry.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport re\r\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Optional, Tuple\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _split_sentences(text: str) -> List[str]:\r\n    \"\"\"Split text into sentences using punctuation boundaries.\"\"\"\r\n    # Split on sentence-ending punctuation followed by space or end of string\r\n    raw = re.split(r'(?<=[.!?;])\\s+', text.strip())\r\n    # Normalize whitespace and filter empty\r\n    return [s.strip() for s in raw if s.strip()]\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _normalize(text: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Normalize text for comparison: lowercase, collapse whitespace.\"\"\"\r\n    return re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text.strip().lower())\r\n\r\n\r\ndef validate_scene_text(\r\n    scenes: List[Dict],\r\n    original_text: str,\r\n) -> Tuple[bool, Optional[Dict]]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Validate scene text coverage and integrity.\r\n\r\n    Checks:\r\n    1. empty_scenes: no scene has empty or whitespace-only text\r\n    2. duplicate_text: no sentence appears in more than one scene\r\n    3. missing_text: major chunks of original text missing from scenes\r\n    4. scene_order: scene_numbers are sequential starting from expected value\r\n\r\n    Args:\r\n        scenes: List of scene dicts with \"text\" and \"scene_number\"\r\n        original_text: The original batch text that was split into scenes\r\n\r\n    Returns:\r\n        (True, None) if all checks pass\r\n        (False, feedback_dict) if violations found — feedback ready for agent retry\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if not scenes:\r\n        return False, {\r\n            \"is_retry\": True,\r\n            \"text_validation_required\": True,\r\n            \"issues\": [{\"type\": \"no_scenes\", \"detail\": \"No scenes were generated\"}],\r\n            \"total_violations\": 1,\r\n            \"instruction\": \"You returned no scenes. Split the input text into scenes.\",\r\n        }\r\n\r\n    issues = []\r\n\r\n    # --- 1. Empty scenes ---\r\n    for scene in scenes:\r\n        text = scene.get(\"text\", \"\").strip()\r\n        scene_num = scene.get(\"scene_number\", \"?\")\r\n        if not text:\r\n            issues.append({\r\n                \"type\": \"empty_scene\",\r\n                \"scene_number\": scene_num,\r\n                \"detail\": f\"Scene {scene_num} has empty text\",\r\n                \"action\": f\"Remove scene {scene_num} or merge it with an adjacent scene\",\r\n            })\r\n\r\n    # --- 2. Duplicate text ---\r\n    scene_texts_normalized = []\r\n    for scene in scenes:\r\n        text = scene.get(\"text\", \"\").strip()\r\n        if text:\r\n            scene_texts_normalized.append((scene.get(\"scene_number\", \"?\"), _normalize(text)))\r\n\r\n    for i in range(len(scene_texts_normalized)):\r\n        for j in range(i + 1, len(scene_texts_normalized)):\r\n            num_i, text_i = scene_texts_normalized[i]\r\n            num_j, text_j = scene_texts_normalized[j]\r\n            # Check for exact duplicates or high overlap (one contains the other)\r\n            if text_i == text_j:\r\n                issues.append({\r\n                    \"type\": \"duplicate_text\",\r\n                    \"scene_numbers\": [num_i, num_j],\r\n                    \"detail\": f\"Scene {num_i} and scene {num_j} have identical text\",\r\n                    \"action\": f\"Remove duplicate scene {num_j} and redistribute text\",\r\n                })\r\n            elif len(text_i) > 20 and len(text_j) > 20:\r\n                # Check if one scene contains 80%+ of the other\r\n                shorter, longer = (text_i, text_j) if len(text_i) < len(text_j) else (text_j, text_i)\r\n                if shorter in longer:\r\n                    issues.append({\r\n                        \"type\": \"duplicate_text\",\r\n                        \"scene_numbers\": [num_i, num_j],\r\n                        \"detail\": f\"Scene {num_i} text is contained within scene {num_j} (or vice versa)\",\r\n                        \"action\": f\"Remove the overlapping text from one of the scenes\",\r\n                    })\r\n\r\n    # --- 3. Missing text ---\r\n    # Check that all sentences from original text appear in at least one scene\r\n    original_sentences = _split_sentences(original_text)\r\n    combined_scene_text = _normalize(\" \".join(s.get(\"text\", \"\") for s in scenes))\r\n\r\n    missing_sentences = []\r\n    for sentence in original_sentences:\r\n        norm_sentence = _normalize(sentence)\r\n        # Skip very short fragments (< 3 words)\r\n        if len(norm_sentence.split()) < 3:\r\n            continue\r\n        if norm_sentence not in combined_scene_text:\r\n            missing_sentences.append(sentence)\r\n\r\n    if missing_sentences:\r\n        # Only flag if significant text is missing (> 10% of sentences)\r\n        missing_ratio = len(missing_sentences) / max(len(original_sentences), 1)\r\n        if missing_ratio > 0.10:\r\n            issues.append({\r\n                \"type\": \"missing_text\",\r\n                \"missing_count\": len(missing_sentences),\r\n                \"total_sentences\": len(original_sentences),\r\n                \"missing_ratio\": f\"{missing_ratio:.0%}\",\r\n                \"examples\": missing_sentences[:3],\r\n                \"detail\": f\"{len(missing_sentences)}/{len(original_sentences)} sentences from the original text are missing from scenes\",\r\n                \"action\": \"Include ALL sentences from the original text. Do not skip or summarize any content.\",\r\n            })\r\n\r\n    # --- 4. Scene order ---\r\n    scene_numbers = [s.get(\"scene_number\") for s in scenes if s.get(\"scene_number\") is not None]\r\n    if scene_numbers:\r\n        for i in range(1, len(scene_numbers)):\r\n            if scene_numbers[i] != scene_numbers[i - 1] + 1:\r\n                issues.append({\r\n                    \"type\": \"scene_order\",\r\n                    \"detail\": f\"Scene numbers are not sequential: ...{scene_numbers[i-1]}, {scene_numbers[i]}...\",\r\n                    \"action\": \"Number scenes sequentially without gaps\",\r\n                })\r\n                break  # Only report once\r\n\r\n    if not issues:\r\n        return True, None\r\n\r\n    feedback = {\r\n        \"is_retry\": True,\r\n        \"text_validation_required\": True,\r\n        \"issues\": issues,\r\n        \"total_violations\": len(issues),\r\n        \"instruction\": (\r\n            f\"Fix the {len(issues)} text validation issue(s) listed below. \"\r\n            f\"The original text must be fully covered by the scenes — do not skip or summarize content. \"\r\n            f\"Keep all metadata fields (faction_shown, interpretation_mode, emotional_tone, reasoning).\"\r\n        ),\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    return False, feedback\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775064039890}}
{"type":"message","id":"07afdd4b","parentId":"7a428c2b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:20:40.124Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_5rERSrRRhgvW9yVjMPyQ8c76|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd53e652d88190b33477efea4634b5","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\r\nScene Reconstructor — deterministic Python auto-correction for screenplay scenes.\r\n\r\nReplaces LLM-based retries (word count + text validator) with pure Python fixes.\r\nTwo paths:\r\n  1. Text matches original → fix word counts by moving whole sentences between scenes\r\n  2. Text corrupted → reconstruct ALL scenes from original text\r\n\r\nZero LLM calls. Handles all 13 languages (CJK character counting, full-width punctuation).\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport re\r\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Optional, Tuple\r\n\r\nfrom loguru import logger\r\n\r\n\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# Language helpers\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n_CJK_LANGUAGES = {\"ja\", \"ko\"}\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _count_units(text: str, language: str) -> int:\r\n    \"\"\"Count content units: characters for CJK (excluding whitespace), words for alphabetic.\"\"\"\r\n    if language in _CJK_LANGUAGES:\r\n        # Remove ALL whitespace before counting — CJK doesn't use spaces as separators\r\n        return len(re.sub(r'\\s+', '', text))\r\n    return len(text.split())\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _split_sentences(text: str, language: str) -> List[str]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Split text into sentences using language-aware punctuation boundaries.\r\n\r\n    CJK (ja, ko): splits on full-width AND half-width sentence-ending punctuation.\r\n    Alphabetic: splits on .!? followed by whitespace.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if language in _CJK_LANGUAGES:\r\n        parts = re.split(r'(?<=[。！？.!?])\\s*|\\n+', text)\r\n    else:\r\n        parts = re.split(r'(?<=[.!?])\\s+', text)\r\n    return [s.strip() for s in parts if s.strip()]\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _join_sentences(sentences: List[str], language: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Join sentences back into text, language-aware.\"\"\"\r\n    if language in _CJK_LANGUAGES:\r\n        # No separator for CJK — sentences end with punctuation (。！？)\r\n        return \"\".join(sentences)\r\n    return \" \".join(sentences)\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _normalize_for_compare(text: str, language: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Normalize text for comparison.\r\n\r\n    Alphabetic: lowercase + collapse whitespace.\r\n    CJK: strip + remove ALL whitespace (CJK doesn't use spaces as word separators).\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if language in _CJK_LANGUAGES:\r\n        # Remove all whitespace for CJK — spaces/newlines are not significant\r\n        return re.sub(r'\\s+', '', text.strip())\r\n    return re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text.strip()).lower()\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _texts_match(scenes: List[Dict], original_text: str, language: str) -> bool:\r\n    \"\"\"Check if concatenated scene texts match the original text.\"\"\"\r\n    joiner = \" \"  # use space for comparison regardless of language\r\n    combined = joiner.join(s.get(\"text\", \"\").strip() for s in scenes if s.get(\"text\", \"\").strip())\r\n    norm_combined = _normalize_for_compare(combined, language)\r\n    norm_original = _normalize_for_compare(original_text, language)\r\n    return norm_combined == norm_original\r\n\r\n\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# Path 1: Fix word counts by moving sentences\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\ndef _extract_scene_sentences(scenes: List[Dict], language: str) -> List[List[str]]:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract sentences from each scene, preserving scene boundaries.\"\"\"\r\n    result = []\r\n    for scene in scenes:\r\n        text = scene.get(\"text\", \"\").strip()\r\n        if text:\r\n            result.append(_split_sentences(text, language))\r\n        else:\r\n            result.append([])\r\n    return result\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _fix_word_counts(\r\n    scene_sentences: List[List[str]],\r\n    min_units: int,\r\n    max_units: int,\r\n    language: str,\r\n) -> List[List[str]]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Redistribute whole sentences between adjacent scenes to fix word count violations.\r\n\r\n    Iterates up to 10 passes to stabilize. Each pass scans left-to-right:\r\n    - Scene too long: move last sentence(s) to next scene\r\n    - Scene too short: pull first sentence from next scene\r\n\r\n    Returns the fixed scene_sentences list.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    max_passes = 10\r\n\r\n    for pass_num in range(max_passes):\r\n        changed = False\r\n\r\n        for i in range(len(scene_sentences)):\r\n            if not scene_sentences[i]:\r\n                continue\r\n\r\n            current_text = _join_sentences(scene_sentences[i], language)\r\n            current_count = _count_units(current_text, language)\r\n\r\n            # --- Too long: move last sentence(s) to next scene ---\r\n            if current_count > max_units and len(scene_sentences[i]) > 1:\r\n                # Move last sentence to next scene (create new scene if last)\r\n                if i < len(scene_sentences) - 1:\r\n                    # Move to existing next scene\r\n                    moved = scene_sentences[i].pop()\r\n                    scene_sentences[i + 1].insert(0, moved)\r\n                    changed = True\r\n                elif i > 0:\r\n                    # Last scene, too long — try moving first sentence to previous\r\n                    moved = scene_sentences[i].pop(0)\r\n                    scene_sentences[i - 1].append(moved)\r\n                    changed = True\r\n\r\n            # --- Too short: pull first sentence from next scene ---\r\n            elif current_count < min_units and i < len(scene_sentences) - 1:\r\n                if scene_sentences[i + 1]:\r\n                    # Only pull if next scene won't become empty\r\n                    if len(scene_sentences[i + 1]) > 1:\r\n                        pulled = scene_sentences[i + 1].pop(0)\r\n                        scene_sentences[i].append(pulled)\r\n                        changed = True\r\n                    elif len(scene_sentences[i + 1]) == 1:\r\n                        # Next scene has only 1 sentence — merge entirely\r\n                        pulled = scene_sentences[i + 1].pop(0)\r\n                        scene_sentences[i].append(pulled)\r\n                        changed = True\r\n\r\n        # Remove empty scenes\r\n        scene_sentences = [s for s in scene_sentences if s]\r\n\r\n        if not changed:\r\n            break\r\n\r\n    # Final pass: merge last scene into previous if absurdly short (< min // 2)\r\n    if len(scene_sentences) >= 2:\r\n        last_text = _join_sentences(scene_sentences[-1], language)\r\n        last_count = _count_units(last_text, language)\r\n        prev_text = _join_sentences(scene_sentences[-2], language)\r\n        prev_count = _count_units(prev_text, language)\r\n        # Only merge if last scene is absurdly short AND merged result won't exceed max\r\n        if last_count < min_units // 2 and (prev_count + last_count) <= max_units:\r\n            scene_sentences[-2].extend(scene_sentences[-1])\r\n            scene_sentences.pop()\r\n\r\n    return scene_sentences\r\n\r\n\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# Path 2: Rebuild from scratch\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\ndef _rebuild_from_scratch(\r\n    original_text: str,\r\n    min_units: int,\r\n    max_units: int,\r\n    start_scene_number: int,\r\n    language: str,\r\n) -> List[Dict]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Reconstruct scenes from original text using greedy sentence distribution.\r\n\r\n    Algorithm: fill each scene with sentences until reaching the target\r\n    (midpoint of min/max). Cut when >= target and sentence ends with punctuation.\r\n    Hard cut at max_units.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    sentences = _split_sentences(original_text, language)\r\n    if not sentences:\r\n        return []\r\n\r\n    target = (min_units + max_units) // 2\r\n    scenes = []\r\n    current_sentences: List[str] = []\r\n    current_count = 0\r\n    scene_number = start_scene_number\r\n\r\n    for sentence in sentences:\r\n        sentence_units = _count_units(sentence, language)\r\n\r\n        # Would exceed max? Start new scene (if we have content)\r\n        if current_count + sentence_units > max_units and current_sentences:\r\n            scene_text = _join_sentences(current_sentences, language)\r\n            scenes.append({\r\n                \"scene_number\": scene_number,\r\n                \"text\": scene_text,\r\n                \"word_count\": _count_units(scene_text, language),\r\n                \"scene_type\": \"narrative\",\r\n            })\r\n            scene_number += 1\r\n            current_sentences = [sentence]\r\n            current_count = sentence_units\r\n        else:\r\n            current_sentences.append(sentence)\r\n            current_count += sentence_units\r\n\r\n            # Reached target? Start new scene\r\n            if current_count >= target:\r\n                scene_text = _join_sentences(current_sentences, language)\r\n                scenes.append({\r\n                    \"scene_number\": scene_number,\r\n                    \"text\": scene_text,\r\n                    \"word_count\": _count_units(scene_text, language),\r\n                    \"scene_type\": \"narrative\",\r\n                })\r\n                scene_number += 1\r\n                current_sentences = []\r\n                current_count = 0\r\n\r\n    # Last scene\r\n    if current_sentences:\r\n        scene_text = _join_sentences(current_sentences, language)\r\n        scenes.append({\r\n            \"scene_number\": scene_number,\r\n            \"text\": scene_text,\r\n            \"word_count\": _count_units(scene_text, language),\r\n            \"scene_type\": \"narrative\",\r\n        })\r\n\r\n    return scenes\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _rebuild_and_fix(\r\n    original_text: str,\r\n    min_units: int,\r\n    max_units: int,\r\n    start_scene_number: int,\r\n    language: str,\r\n) -> List[Dict]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Rebuild from scratch + fix word counts via sentence redistribution.\r\n\r\n    _rebuild_from_scratch() uses a greedy algorithm that can create scenes\r\n    exceeding max (single long sentence) or below min (short remainder).\r\n    This wrapper applies _fix_word_counts() after rebuild to ensure compliance.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    rebuilt = _rebuild_from_scratch(original_text, min_units, max_units, start_scene_number, language)\r\n    if not rebuilt:\r\n        return rebuilt\r\n\r\n    # Apply same fix_word_counts as match_fix path\r\n    scene_sentences = _extract_scene_sentences(rebuilt, language)\r\n    fixed_sentences = _fix_word_counts(scene_sentences, min_units, max_units, language)\r\n\r\n    # Rebuild scene dicts\r\n    fixed_scenes = []\r\n    scene_num = start_scene_number\r\n    for sentences in fixed_sentences:\r\n        text = _join_sentences(sentences, language)\r\n        fixed_scenes.append({\r\n            \"scene_number\": scene_num,\r\n            \"text\": text,\r\n            \"word_count\": _count_units(text, language),\r\n            \"scene_type\": \"narrative\",\r\n        })\r\n        scene_num += 1\r\n\r\n    return fixed_scenes\r\n\r\n\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# Main entry point\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\ndef reconstruct_scenes(\r\n    scenes: List[Dict],\r\n    original_text: str,\r\n    min_words: int,\r\n    max_words: int,\r\n    start_scene_number: int,\r\n    language: str = \"en\",\r\n) -> Tuple[List[Dict], Dict]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Validate + auto-fix scenes from screenplay agent. Zero LLM calls.\r\n\r\n    Two paths:\r\n      1. Text matches original → fix word counts by moving sentences (\"match_fix\")\r\n      2. Text corrupted → rebuild all scenes from original text (\"reconstruct\")\r\n      3. Everything OK → return as-is (\"passthrough\")\r\n\r\n    Args:\r\n        scenes: List of scene dicts from screenplay agent (need \"text\" key)\r\n        original_text: The original batch text that was split into scenes\r\n        min_words: Minimum units per scene (words or chars for CJK)\r\n        max_words: Maximum units per scene\r\n        start_scene_number: Starting scene number for sequential numbering\r\n        language: Language code (en, ja, ko, etc.)\r\n\r\n    Returns:\r\n        (fixed_scenes, report) where report contains:\r\n        - path: \"match_fix\" | \"reconstruct\" | \"passthrough\"\r\n        - changes_made: list of change descriptions\r\n        - original_scene_count: int\r\n        - final_scene_count: int\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    report = {\r\n        \"path\": \"passthrough\",\r\n        \"changes_made\": [],\r\n        \"original_scene_count\": len(scenes),\r\n        \"final_scene_count\": len(scenes),\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    # Edge case: empty input\r\n    if not original_text or not original_text.strip():\r\n        logger.warning(\"[Reconstructor] Empty original text\")\r\n        report[\"path\"] = \"passthrough\"\r\n        return [], report\r\n\r\n    # Edge case: no scenes from agent\r\n    if not scenes:\r\n        logger.warning(\"[Reconstructor] No scenes from agent, rebuilding from scratch\")\r\n        rebuilt = _rebuild_and_fix(original_text, min_words, max_words, start_scene_number, language)\r\n        report[\"path\"] = \"reconstruct\"\r\n        report[\"changes_made\"].append(\"no_scenes_from_agent\")\r\n        report[\"final_scene_count\"] = len(rebuilt)\r\n        return rebuilt, report\r\n\r\n    # Check if text matches original\r\n    if _texts_match(scenes, original_text, language):\r\n        # Path 1: Text matches — check if word counts need fixing\r\n        needs_fix = False\r\n        for scene in scenes:\r\n            text = scene.get(\"text\", \"\").strip()\r\n            count = _count_units(text, language)\r\n            if count < min_words or count > max_words:\r\n                needs_fix = True\r\n                break\r\n\r\n        if not needs_fix:\r\n            # Everything is fine — passthrough (but still renumber sequentially)\r\n            report[\"path\"] = \"passthrough\"\r\n            scene_num = start_scene_number\r\n            for s in scenes:\r\n                s[\"scene_number\"] = scene_num\r\n                scene_num += 1\r\n            return scenes, report\r\n\r\n        # Fix word counts by redistributing sentences\r\n        logger.info(\"[Reconstructor] Text matches, fixing word counts...\")\r\n        scene_sentences = _extract_scene_sentences(scenes, language)\r\n        original_counts = [_count_units(_join_sentences(ss, language), language) for ss in scene_sentences]\r\n\r\n        fixed_sentences = _fix_word_counts(scene_sentences, min_words, max_words, language)\r\n\r\n        # Build fixed scenes\r\n        fixed_scenes = []\r\n        scene_num = start_scene_number\r\n        for sentences in fixed_sentences:\r\n            text = _join_sentences(sentences, language)\r\n            fixed_scenes.append({\r\n                \"scene_number\": scene_num,\r\n                \"text\": text,\r\n                \"word_count\": _count_units(text, language),\r\n                \"scene_type\": \"narrative\",\r\n            })\r\n            scene_num += 1\r\n\r\n        # Merge absurdly short last scene into previous (< min_words // 2)\r\n        if len(fixed_scenes) >= 2:\r\n            last_wc = fixed_scenes[-1][\"word_count\"]\r\n            prev_wc = fixed_scenes[-2][\"word_count\"]\r\n            if last_wc < min_words // 2 and (prev_wc + last_wc) <= max_words:\r\n                prev = fixed_scenes[-2]\r\n                last = fixed_scenes[-1]\r\n                joiner = \"\" if language in _CJK_LANGUAGES else \" \"\r\n                merged_text = prev[\"text\"] + joiner + last[\"text\"]\r\n                prev[\"text\"] = merged_text\r\n                prev[\"word_count\"] = _count_units(merged_text, language)\r\n                fixed_scenes.pop()\r\n                report[\"changes_made\"].append(\r\n                    f\"merged_short_last_scene: {last_wc}w into scene {prev['scene_number']}\"\r\n                )\r\n\r\n        # Check if fix actually resolved all violations (except last scene which can be short)\r\n        still_violated = False\r\n        for idx, s in enumerate(fixed_scenes):\r\n            is_last = (idx == len(fixed_scenes) - 1)\r\n            wc = s[\"word_count\"]\r\n            if wc > max_words:\r\n                still_violated = True\r\n                break\r\n            if wc < min_words and not is_last:\r\n                still_violated = True\r\n                break\r\n\r\n        if still_violated:\r\n            # Sentence redistribution couldn't fix it — rebuild from scratch\r\n            logger.warning(\r\n                \"[Reconstructor] Sentence redistribution couldn't fix all violations, \"\r\n                \"rebuilding from scratch.\"\r\n            )\r\n            rebuilt = _rebuild_and_fix(\r\n                original_text, min_words, max_words, start_scene_number, language\r\n            )\r\n            report[\"path\"] = \"reconstruct\"\r\n            report[\"changes_made\"].append(\r\n                f\"redistribution_failed: {original_counts} -> rebuild\"\r\n            )\r\n            report[\"final_scene_count\"] = len(rebuilt)\r\n            return rebuilt, report\r\n\r\n        # Log changes\r\n        new_counts = [s[\"word_count\"] for s in fixed_scenes]\r\n        if len(original_counts) != len(new_counts) or original_counts != new_counts:\r\n            report[\"changes_made\"].append(\r\n                f\"word_counts: {original_counts} -> {new_counts}\"\r\n            )\r\n\r\n        report[\"path\"] = \"match_fix\"\r\n        report[\"final_scene_count\"] = len(fixed_scenes)\r\n        return fixed_scenes, report\r\n\r\n    else:\r\n        # Path 2: Text doesn't match — reconstruct from scratch\r\n        combined = \" \".join(s.get(\"text\", \"\").strip() for s in scenes)\r\n        orig_units = _count_units(original_text, language)\r\n        scene_units = _count_units(combined, language)\r\n        logger.warning(\r\n            f\"[Reconstructor] Text mismatch! \"\r\n            f\"Original: {orig_units} units, Scenes: {scene_units} units. \"\r\n            f\"Rebuilding from scratch.\"\r\n        )\r\n\r\n        rebuilt = _rebuild_and_fix(original_text, min_words, max_words, start_scene_number, language)\r\n\r\n        report[\"path\"] = \"reconstruct\"\r\n        report[\"changes_made\"].append(\r\n            f\"text_mismatch: original={orig_units} units, scenes={scene_units} units\"\r\n        )\r\n        report[\"final_scene_count\"] = len(rebuilt)\r\n        return rebuilt, report\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775064040016}}
{"type":"message","id":"bf327d04","parentId":"07afdd4b","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:20:40.239Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_3GMMEYmoTeTet0etgI9ShumG|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd53e652e08190aef8397cfc7ace03","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Refinement Loop - Generate → Evaluate → Refine workflow.\r\n\r\nThis module provides a reusable refinement loop that:\r\n1. Calls the main agent to generate output\r\n2. Evaluates the output using an EvaluatorAgent\r\n3. If evaluation fails, refines with feedback\r\n4. Returns the best version\r\n\r\nThe loop is limited to MAX_REFINEMENTS to prevent cost explosion.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import Any, Callable, Dict, List, Optional, Tuple\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\n\r\nfrom loguru import logger\r\n\r\nfrom .evaluator_agent import EvaluatorAgent, EvaluationResult\r\n\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass RefinementStats:\r\n    \"\"\"Statistics from a refinement cycle.\"\"\"\r\n    original_score: int\r\n    final_score: int\r\n    refinement_count: int\r\n    improved: bool\r\n    evaluation_history: List[EvaluationResult]\r\n\r\n    def to_dict(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:\r\n        \"\"\"Convert to dictionary.\"\"\"\r\n        return {\r\n            \"original_score\": self.original_score,\r\n            \"final_score\": self.final_score,\r\n            \"refinement_count\": self.refinement_count,\r\n            \"improved\": self.improved,\r\n            \"score_history\": [e.score for e in self.evaluation_history],\r\n        }\r\n\r\n\r\nclass RefinementLoop:\r\n    \"\"\"Orchestrates the generate → evaluate → refine cycle.\r\n\r\n    Usage:\r\n        loop = RefinementLoop(\r\n            evaluator=EvaluatorAgent(\"screenplay\", account_id=\"001\"),\r\n            max_refinements=1,\r\n        )\r\n\r\n        result, stats = loop.run(\r\n            generate_fn=lambda: agent.generate(input_data),\r\n            refine_fn=lambda output, feedback: agent.generate_with_feedback(input_data, output, feedback),\r\n            input_data={\"segments\": segments},\r\n            context={\"characters\": characters},\r\n        )\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n\r\n    def __init__(\r\n        self,\r\n        evaluator: EvaluatorAgent,\r\n        max_refinements: int = 2,\r\n        log_dir: Optional[Path] = None,\r\n    ):\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Initialize refinement loop.\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            evaluator: The EvaluatorAgent to use for evaluation\r\n            max_refinements: Maximum refinement iterations (default: 1)\r\n            log_dir: Directory to save evaluation logs (optional)\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        self.evaluator = evaluator\r\n        self.max_refinements = max_refinements\r\n        self.log_dir = log_dir\r\n\r\n    def run(\r\n        self,\r\n        generate_fn: Callable[[], Dict[str, Any]],\r\n        refine_fn: Callable[[Dict[str, Any], str], Dict[str, Any]],\r\n        input_data: Dict[str, Any],\r\n        context: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\r\n        batch_id: Optional[str] = None,\r\n    ) -> Tuple[Dict[str, Any], RefinementStats]:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Run the generate → evaluate → refine cycle.\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            generate_fn: Function that generates initial output (no args)\r\n            refine_fn: Function that refines output given (previous_output, feedback)\r\n            input_data: Original input data for evaluation context\r\n            context: Additional context for evaluation\r\n            batch_id: Optional batch identifier for logging\r\n\r\n        Returns:\r\n            Tuple of (best_output, refinement_stats)\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        evaluation_history: List[EvaluationResult] = []\r\n        outputs: List[Dict[str, Any]] = []\r\n\r\n        # Step 1: Generate initial output\r\n        logger.info(f\"[REFINEMENT] Generating initial output...\")\r\n        output_v1 = generate_fn()\r\n        outputs.append(output_v1)\r\n\r\n        # Step 2: Evaluate V1\r\n        logger.info(f\"[REFINEMENT] Evaluating V1...\")\r\n        eval_v1 = self.evaluator.evaluate(input_data, output_v1, context)\r\n        evaluation_history.append(eval_v1)\r\n\r\n        logger.info(f\"[EVAL] V1 Score: {eval_v1.score}/100, passed={eval_v1.passed}\")\r\n\r\n        # Check if refinement needed\r\n        if not self.evaluator.should_refine(eval_v1):\r\n            logger.info(f\"[REFINEMENT] V1 passed evaluation, no refinement needed\")\r\n            stats = RefinementStats(\r\n                original_score=eval_v1.score,\r\n                final_score=eval_v1.score,\r\n                refinement_count=0,\r\n                improved=False,\r\n                evaluation_history=evaluation_history,\r\n            )\r\n            self._save_log(input_data, outputs, evaluation_history, batch_id)\r\n            return output_v1, stats\r\n\r\n        # Step 3: Refinement loop\r\n        current_output = output_v1\r\n        current_eval = eval_v1\r\n        refinement_count = 0\r\n\r\n        while refinement_count < self.max_refinements:\r\n            refinement_count += 1\r\n            logger.info(f\"[REFINEMENT] Refinement iteration {refinement_count}/{self.max_refinements}...\")\r\n\r\n            # Generate feedback for refinement\r\n            feedback = current_eval.get_feedback_for_refinement()\r\n            logger.debug(f\"[FEEDBACK] {feedback[:500]}...\")\r\n\r\n            # Refine with feedback\r\n            logger.info(f\"[REFINEMENT] Generating refined output V{refinement_count + 1}...\")\r\n            refined_output = refine_fn(current_output, feedback)\r\n            outputs.append(refined_output)\r\n\r\n            # Evaluate refined output\r\n            logger.info(f\"[REFINEMENT] Evaluating V{refinement_count + 1}...\")\r\n            refined_eval = self.evaluator.evaluate(input_data, refined_output, context)\r\n            evaluation_history.append(refined_eval)\r\n\r\n            logger.info(\r\n                f\"[EVAL] V{refinement_count + 1} Score: {refined_eval.score}/100, \"\r\n                f\"passed={refined_eval.passed} (was {current_eval.score})\"\r\n            )\r\n\r\n            # Update current best if improved\r\n            if refined_eval.score > current_eval.score:\r\n                current_output = refined_output\r\n                current_eval = refined_eval\r\n                logger.info(f\"[REFINEMENT] Score improved: {eval_v1.score} -> {refined_eval.score}\")\r\n            else:\r\n                logger.info(f\"[REFINEMENT] Score did not improve, keeping previous version\")\r\n\r\n            # Check if we've reached passing threshold\r\n            if not self.evaluator.should_refine(current_eval):\r\n                logger.info(f\"[REFINEMENT] Reached passing threshold, stopping\")\r\n                break\r\n\r\n        # Final stats\r\n        final_output = current_output\r\n        final_score = current_eval.score\r\n\r\n        stats = RefinementStats(\r\n            original_score=eval_v1.score,\r\n            final_score=final_score,\r\n            refinement_count=refinement_count,\r\n            improved=final_score > eval_v1.score,\r\n            evaluation_history=evaluation_history,\r\n        )\r\n\r\n        logger.info(\r\n            f\"[REFINEMENT] Complete: {eval_v1.score} -> {final_score} \"\r\n            f\"({refinement_count} refinement(s), improved={stats.improved})\"\r\n        )\r\n\r\n        self._save_log(input_data, outputs, evaluation_history, batch_id)\r\n\r\n        return final_output, stats\r\n\r\n    def _save_log(\r\n        self,\r\n        input_data: Dict[str, Any],\r\n        outputs: List[Dict[str, Any]],\r\n        evaluations: List[EvaluationResult],\r\n        batch_id: Optional[str] = None,\r\n    ) -> None:\r\n        \"\"\"Save evaluation log to file.\"\"\"\r\n        if not self.log_dir:\r\n            return\r\n\r\n        try:\r\n            self.log_dir.mkdir(parents=True, exist_ok=True)\r\n\r\n            timestamp = datetime.now().strftime(\"%Y%m%d_%H%M%S\")\r\n            batch_suffix = f\"_{batch_id}\" if batch_id else \"\"\r\n            filename = f\"eval_{self.evaluator.agent_type}{batch_suffix}_{timestamp}.json\"\r\n\r\n            log_data = {\r\n                \"timestamp\": timestamp,\r\n                \"agent_type\": self.evaluator.agent_type,\r\n                \"batch_id\": batch_id,\r\n                \"evaluator_stats\": self.evaluator.get_stats(),\r\n                \"input_summary\": {\r\n                    \"type\": type(input_data).__name__,\r\n                    \"keys\": list(input_data.keys()) if isinstance(input_data, dict) else None,\r\n                },\r\n                \"evaluations\": [e.to_dict() for e in evaluations],\r\n                \"score_progression\": [e.score for e in evaluations],\r\n                \"final_score\": evaluations[-1].score if evaluations else 0,\r\n                \"refinement_count\": len(evaluations) - 1,\r\n            }\r\n\r\n            log_path = self.log_dir / filename\r\n            with open(log_path, \"w\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\r\n                json.dump(log_data, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)\r\n\r\n            logger.debug(f\"[REFINEMENT] Saved evaluation log: {log_path}\")\r\n\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            logger.warning(f\"[REFINEMENT] Failed to save log: {e}\")\r\n\r\n\r\ndef create_refinement_loop(\r\n    agent_type: str,\r\n    language: Optional[str] = None,\r\n    account_id: Optional[str] = None,\r\n    log_dir: Optional[Path] = None,\r\n    max_refinements: int = 1,\r\n    score_threshold: int = 85,\r\n) -> RefinementLoop:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Factory function to create a RefinementLoop with appropriate evaluator.\r\n\r\n    Args:\r\n        agent_type: Type of agent (tts_polish, character, screenplay, prompt_gen)\r\n        language: Language for TTS Polish evaluator\r\n        account_id: Account ID for account-specific evaluators\r\n        log_dir: Directory for evaluation logs\r\n        max_refinements: Maximum refinement iterations\r\n        score_threshold: Minimum score to pass\r\n\r\n    Returns:\r\n        Configured RefinementLoop instance\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    evaluator = EvaluatorAgent(\r\n        agent_type=agent_type,\r\n        language=language,\r\n        account_id=account_id,\r\n        score_threshold=score_threshold,\r\n        max_refinements=max_refinements,\r\n    )\r\n\r\n    return RefinementLoop(\r\n        evaluator=evaluator,\r\n        max_refinements=max_refinements,\r\n        log_dir=log_dir,\r\n    )\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775064040128}}
{"type":"message","id":"0cfbc50d","parentId":"bf327d04","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:20:40.353Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_NmjdtABSkCqLIXALUxfQO2SV|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd53e652e88190a2271fe26037377b","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Evaluator Agent - Generic evaluator for quality validation and refinement.\r\n\r\nThis module provides a base evaluator agent that can assess outputs from various\r\nagents (TTS Polish, Character, Screenplay, Prompt Gen) and provide structured\r\nfeedback for refinement.\r\n\r\nThe evaluator uses language-specific or account-specific prompts to ensure\r\nevaluation criteria match the original agent's requirements.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nfrom dataclasses import dataclass, field\r\nfrom enum import Enum\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\r\n\r\nfrom loguru import logger\r\nfrom openai import OpenAI\r\nfrom tenacity import retry, stop_after_attempt, wait_exponential\r\n\r\nfrom ..config import config\r\n\r\n\r\nclass Severity(str, Enum):\r\n    \"\"\"Issue severity levels.\"\"\"\r\n    CRITICAL = \"critical\"\r\n    MAJOR = \"major\"\r\n    MINOR = \"minor\"\r\n\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass EvaluationIssue:\r\n    \"\"\"A single issue found during evaluation.\"\"\"\r\n    severity: Severity\r\n    category: str\r\n    problem: str\r\n    current: str = \"\"\r\n    expected: str = \"\"\r\n    suggestion: str = \"\"\r\n    field: str = \"\"\r\n    index: int = -1  # chunk_index, group_index, etc.\r\n    reasoning: str = \"\"\r\n\r\n    def to_dict(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:\r\n        \"\"\"Convert to dictionary for JSON serialization.\"\"\"\r\n        return {\r\n            \"severity\": self.severity.value,\r\n            \"category\": self.category,\r\n            \"problem\": self.problem,\r\n            \"current\": self.current,\r\n            \"expected\": self.expected,\r\n            \"suggestion\": self.suggestion,\r\n            \"field\": self.field,\r\n            \"index\": self.index,\r\n            \"reasoning\": self.reasoning,\r\n        }\r\n\r\n    @classmethod\r\n    def from_dict(cls, data: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"EvaluationIssue\":\r\n        \"\"\"Create from dictionary.\"\"\"\r\n        return cls(\r\n            severity=Severity(data.get(\"severity\", \"minor\")),\r\n            category=data.get(\"category\", \"\"),\r\n            problem=data.get(\"problem\", \"\"),\r\n            current=data.get(\"current\", \"\"),\r\n            expected=data.get(\"expected\", \"\"),\r\n            suggestion=data.get(\"suggestion\", \"\"),\r\n            field=data.get(\"field\", \"\"),\r\n            index=data.get(\"index\", data.get(\"chunk_index\", data.get(\"group_index\", -1))),\r\n            reasoning=data.get(\"reasoning\", \"\"),\r\n        )\r\n\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass EvaluationResult:\r\n    \"\"\"Result of an evaluation.\"\"\"\r\n    score: int  # 0-100\r\n    passed: bool\r\n    issues: List[EvaluationIssue] = field(default_factory=list)\r\n    summary: str = \"\"\r\n    notes: str = \"\"  # director_notes, gemini_expert_notes, etc.\r\n    refinement_needed: bool = False\r\n    raw_response: Dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)\r\n    checklists: Dict[str, Dict[str, bool]] = field(default_factory=dict)\r\n    statistics: Dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)\r\n\r\n    def to_dict(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:\r\n        \"\"\"Convert to dictionary for JSON serialization.\"\"\"\r\n        return {\r\n            \"score\": self.score,\r\n            \"passed\": self.passed,\r\n            \"issues\": [issue.to_dict() for issue in self.issues],\r\n            \"summary\": self.summary,\r\n            \"notes\": self.notes,\r\n            \"refinement_needed\": self.refinement_needed,\r\n            \"checklists\": self.checklists,\r\n            \"statistics\": self.statistics,\r\n        }\r\n\r\n    @classmethod\r\n    def from_dict(cls, data: Dict[str, Any]) -> \"EvaluationResult\":\r\n        \"\"\"Create from dictionary (API response).\"\"\"\r\n        issues = []\r\n        for issue_data in data.get(\"issues\", []):\r\n            issues.append(EvaluationIssue.from_dict(issue_data))\r\n\r\n        return cls(\r\n            score=data.get(\"score\", 0),\r\n            passed=data.get(\"passed\", False),\r\n            issues=issues,\r\n            summary=data.get(\"summary\", \"\"),\r\n            notes=data.get(\"director_notes\", data.get(\"gemini_expert_notes\", data.get(\"notes\", \"\"))),\r\n            refinement_needed=data.get(\"refinement_needed\", False),\r\n            raw_response=data,\r\n            checklists={\r\n                k: v for k, v in data.items()\r\n                if k.endswith(\"_checklist\") and isinstance(v, dict)\r\n            },\r\n            statistics=data.get(\"statistics\", {}),\r\n        )\r\n\r\n    def get_critical_issues(self) -> List[EvaluationIssue]:\r\n        \"\"\"Get only critical issues.\"\"\"\r\n        return [i for i in self.issues if i.severity == Severity.CRITICAL]\r\n\r\n    def get_feedback_for_refinement(self) -> str:\r\n        \"\"\"Generate feedback string for refinement prompt.\"\"\"\r\n        if not self.issues:\r\n            return \"No specific issues found.\"\r\n\r\n        feedback_parts = []\r\n\r\n        # Group issues by severity\r\n        critical = [i for i in self.issues if i.severity == Severity.CRITICAL]\r\n        major = [i for i in self.issues if i.severity == Severity.MAJOR]\r\n\r\n        if critical:\r\n            feedback_parts.append(\"CRITICAL ISSUES (must fix):\")\r\n            for i, issue in enumerate(critical, 1):\r\n                feedback_parts.append(f\"  {i}. [{issue.category}] {issue.problem}\")\r\n                if issue.current:\r\n                    current_str = str(issue.current)\r\n                    feedback_parts.append(f\"     Current: {current_str[:200]}...\")\r\n                if issue.suggestion:\r\n                    suggestion_str = str(issue.suggestion)\r\n                    feedback_parts.append(f\"     Fix: {suggestion_str[:200]}...\")\r\n\r\n        if major:\r\n            feedback_parts.append(\"\\nMAJOR ISSUES (should fix):\")\r\n            for i, issue in enumerate(major, 1):\r\n                feedback_parts.append(f\"  {i}. [{issue.category}] {issue.problem}\")\r\n                if issue.suggestion:\r\n                    suggestion_str = str(issue.suggestion)\r\n                    feedback_parts.append(f\"     Suggestion: {suggestion_str[:200]}...\")\r\n\r\n        if self.notes:\r\n            feedback_parts.append(f\"\\nEVALUATOR NOTES: {self.notes}\")\r\n\r\n        return \"\\n\".join(feedback_parts)\r\n\r\n\r\nclass EvaluatorAgent:\r\n    \"\"\"Generic evaluator agent for quality validation.\r\n\r\n    Supports different agent types:\r\n    - tts_polish: Evaluates TTS text polishing (language-specific, shared)\r\n    - character: Evaluates character definitions (account-specific)\r\n    - screenplay: Evaluates screenplay groupings (account-specific)\r\n    - prompt_gen: Evaluates image prompts (account-specific)\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n\r\n    AGENT_TYPES = [\"tts_polish\", \"character\", \"screenplay\", \"prompt_gen\", \"mansion_dna\"]\r\n\r\n    def __init__(\r\n        self,\r\n        agent_type: str,\r\n        language: Optional[str] = None,\r\n        account_id: Optional[str] = None,\r\n        model: str = \"gpt-4.1-mini\",\r\n        temperature: float = 0.3,\r\n        api_key: Optional[str] = None,\r\n        score_threshold: int = 85,\r\n        max_refinements: int = 2,\r\n    ):\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Initialize Evaluator Agent.\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            agent_type: Type of agent to evaluate (tts_polish, character, screenplay, prompt_gen)\r\n            language: Language code for TTS Polish evaluator (pt, en, es, etc.)\r\n            account_id: Account ID for account-specific evaluators (001, 003, etc.)\r\n            model: OpenAI model to use (default: gpt-4.1-mini)\r\n            temperature: Sampling temperature (default: 0.3 for consistency)\r\n            api_key: OpenAI API key (default: from config)\r\n            score_threshold: Minimum score to pass (default: 85)\r\n            max_refinements: Maximum refinement iterations (default: 1)\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if agent_type not in self.AGENT_TYPES:\r\n            raise ValueError(f\"Invalid agent_type: {agent_type}. Must be one of {self.AGENT_TYPES}\")\r\n\r\n        self.agent_type = agent_type\r\n        self.language = language.lower() if language else None\r\n        self.account_id = account_id\r\n        self.model = model\r\n        self.temperature = temperature\r\n        self.score_threshold = score_threshold\r\n        self.max_refinements = max_refinements\r\n\r\n        # Validate parameters based on agent type\r\n        if agent_type == \"tts_polish\" and not language:\r\n            raise ValueError(\"language is required for tts_polish evaluator\")\r\n        if agent_type in [\"character\", \"screenplay\", \"prompt_gen\", \"mansion_dna\"] and not account_id:\r\n            raise ValueError(f\"account_id is required for {agent_type} evaluator\")\r\n\r\n        self.api_key = api_key or config.openai_api_key\r\n        if not self.api_key:\r\n            raise ValueError(\"OpenAI API key not configured for Evaluator Agent\")\r\n\r\n        self.client = OpenAI(api_key=self.api_key)\r\n        self.system_prompt = self._load_evaluator_prompt()\r\n\r\n        logger.info(\r\n            f\"Evaluator Agent initialized: type={agent_type}, \"\r\n            f\"language={language}, account={account_id}, model={model}\"\r\n        )\r\n\r\n    def _load_evaluator_prompt(self) -> str:\r\n        \"\"\"Load the appropriate evaluator prompt based on agent type.\"\"\"\r\n        base_path = Path(__file__).parent.parent\r\n\r\n        if self.agent_type == \"tts_polish\":\r\n            # Shared prompt: shared/prompts/evaluators/tts_polish/tts_polish_evaluator_{lang}_system.txt\r\n            prompt_path = (\r\n                base_path / \"prompts\" / \"evaluators\" / \"tts_polish\" /\r\n                f\"tts_polish_evaluator_{self.language}_system.txt\"\r\n            )\r\n        else:\r\n            # Account-specific prompt\r\n            # accounts/{account_id}/prompts/evaluators/{agent_type}_evaluator_{account_id}_system.txt\r\n            accounts_base = base_path.parent / \"accounts\"\r\n            account_dir = self._find_account_dir(accounts_base)\r\n            if account_dir:\r\n                prompt_path = (\r\n                    account_dir / \"prompts\" / \"evaluators\" /\r\n                    f\"{self.agent_type}_evaluator_{self.account_id}_system.txt\"\r\n                )\r\n            else:\r\n                prompt_path = Path(\"nonexistent\")  # Will trigger fallback\r\n\r\n        if prompt_path.exists():\r\n            logger.info(f\"Loading evaluator prompt: {prompt_path.name}\")\r\n            return prompt_path.read_text(encoding=\"utf-8\")\r\n\r\n        logger.warning(f\"Evaluator prompt not found at {prompt_path}, using fallback\")\r\n        return self._get_fallback_prompt()\r\n\r\n    def _find_account_dir(self, accounts_base: Path) -> Optional[Path]:\r\n        \"\"\"Find account directory by ID (e.g., 001 -> 001_money_and_entrepreneurship).\"\"\"\r\n        if not accounts_base.exists():\r\n            return None\r\n\r\n        for item in accounts_base.iterdir():\r\n            if item.is_dir() and item.name.startswith(f\"{self.account_id}_\"):\r\n                return item\r\n\r\n        return None\r\n\r\n    def _get_fallback_prompt(self) -> str:\r\n        \"\"\"Generate a basic fallback prompt if specific prompt file is not found.\"\"\"\r\n        return f\"\"\"You are a quality evaluator for the {self.agent_type} agent.\r\n\r\nYour task is to evaluate the output and provide structured feedback.\r\n\r\nEVALUATION OUTPUT FORMAT (JSON only):\r\n{{\r\n    \"score\": 0-100,\r\n    \"passed\": true/false,\r\n    \"issues\": [\r\n        {{\r\n            \"severity\": \"critical|major|minor\",\r\n            \"category\": \"category_name\",\r\n            \"problem\": \"description of the problem\",\r\n            \"current\": \"current problematic content\",\r\n            \"suggestion\": \"how to fix it\"\r\n        }}\r\n    ],\r\n    \"summary\": \"brief summary of evaluation\",\r\n    \"refinement_needed\": true/false\r\n}}\r\n\r\nSCORING:\r\n- 100: Perfect, no issues\r\n- 85-99: Minor issues only, acceptable\r\n- 70-84: Some issues need attention\r\n- Below 70: Significant problems\r\n\r\nSet refinement_needed=true if score < 85 AND there are critical issues.\"\"\"\r\n\r\n    @retry(\r\n        stop=stop_after_attempt(3),\r\n        wait=wait_exponential(multiplier=1, min=4, max=10),\r\n        reraise=True,\r\n    )\r\n    def evaluate(\r\n        self,\r\n        input_data: Dict[str, Any],\r\n        output_data: Dict[str, Any],\r\n        context: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\r\n    ) -> EvaluationResult:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Evaluate output against input and return structured feedback.\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            input_data: Original input to the agent\r\n            output_data: Output produced by the agent\r\n            context: Additional context (characters, scene_context, etc.)\r\n\r\n        Returns:\r\n            EvaluationResult with score, issues, and refinement flag\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        user_prompt = self._build_evaluation_prompt(input_data, output_data, context)\r\n\r\n        try:\r\n            response = self.client.chat.completions.create(\r\n                model=self.model,\r\n                messages=[\r\n                    {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": self.system_prompt},\r\n                    {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_prompt},\r\n                ],\r\n                temperature=self.temperature,\r\n                response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"},\r\n                timeout=120,\r\n            )\r\n\r\n            content = response.choices[0].message.content\r\n\r\n            # Log token usage\r\n            if hasattr(response, 'usage') and response.usage:\r\n                logger.debug(\r\n                    f\"Evaluator API usage: {response.usage.prompt_tokens} prompt + \"\r\n                    f\"{response.usage.completion_tokens} completion tokens\"\r\n                )\r\n\r\n            # Parse response\r\n            try:\r\n                result_data = json.loads(content)\r\n            except json.JSONDecodeError as e:\r\n                logger.error(f\"JSON parsing failed: {e}\")\r\n                logger.error(f\"Raw response: {content[:500]}\")\r\n                return EvaluationResult(\r\n                    score=0,\r\n                    passed=False,\r\n                    summary=f\"Evaluation failed: invalid JSON response\",\r\n                    refinement_needed=True,\r\n                )\r\n\r\n            result = EvaluationResult.from_dict(result_data)\r\n\r\n            # Apply threshold logic\r\n            if result.score >= self.score_threshold:\r\n                result.passed = True\r\n                result.refinement_needed = False\r\n            else:\r\n                result.passed = False\r\n                # Only refine if there are critical issues\r\n                has_critical = any(i.severity == Severity.CRITICAL for i in result.issues)\r\n                result.refinement_needed = has_critical\r\n\r\n            logger.info(\r\n                f\"Evaluation complete: score={result.score}/100, \"\r\n                f\"passed={result.passed}, refinement_needed={result.refinement_needed}\"\r\n            )\r\n\r\n            return result\r\n\r\n        except Exception as e:\r\n            logger.error(f\"Evaluation failed: {e}\")\r\n            raise\r\n\r\n    def _build_evaluation_prompt(\r\n        self,\r\n        input_data: Dict[str, Any],\r\n        output_data: Dict[str, Any],\r\n        context: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\r\n    ) -> str:\r\n        \"\"\"Build the user prompt for evaluation.\"\"\"\r\n        prompt_parts = [\r\n            \"Evaluate the following output against the input.\\n\",\r\n            \"=\" * 50,\r\n            \"\\nINPUT DATA:\",\r\n            json.dumps(input_data, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)[:5000],\r\n            \"\\n\" + \"=\" * 50,\r\n            \"\\nOUTPUT DATA:\",\r\n            json.dumps(output_data, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)[:8000],\r\n        ]\r\n\r\n        if context:\r\n            prompt_parts.extend([\r\n                \"\\n\" + \"=\" * 50,\r\n                \"\\nCONTEXT:\",\r\n                json.dumps(context, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False)[:3000],\r\n            ])\r\n\r\n        prompt_parts.extend([\r\n            \"\\n\" + \"=\" * 50,\r\n            \"\\nProvide your evaluation as JSON following the format in the system prompt.\",\r\n        ])\r\n\r\n        return \"\\n\".join(prompt_parts)\r\n\r\n    def should_refine(self, evaluation: EvaluationResult) -> bool:\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        Determine if refinement is needed based on evaluation result.\r\n\r\n        Args:\r\n            evaluation: The evaluation result\r\n\r\n        Returns:\r\n            True if refinement should be attempted\r\n        \"\"\"\r\n        if evaluation.score >= self.score_threshold:\r\n            return False\r\n\r\n        # Must have critical issues to warrant refinement\r\n        has_critical = any(i.severity == Severity.CRITICAL for i in evaluation.issues)\r\n        return has_critical\r\n\r\n    def get_stats(self) -> Dict[str, Any]:\r\n        \"\"\"Get agent statistics.\"\"\"\r\n        return {\r\n            \"agent_type\": self.agent_type,\r\n            \"language\": self.language,\r\n            \"account_id\": self.account_id,\r\n            \"model\": self.model,\r\n            \"temperature\": self.temperature,\r\n            \"score_threshold\": self.score_threshold,\r\n            \"max_refinements\": self.max_refinements,\r\n        }\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775064040239}}
{"type":"message","id":"34649b0e","parentId":"0cfbc50d","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:20:40.478Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_ohXPPFpQgEd88MWmpuqNO9Ky|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd53e652f08190bb1ef4ce7edcc4e7","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"Async parallel screenplay batch processor using KMS.\"\"\"\n\nimport asyncio\nimport json\n\nfrom loguru import logger\nfrom openai import AsyncOpenAI\n\nfrom shared.clients.centralized_key_client import CentralizedKeyClient\n\n\nclass ParallelScreenplayProcessor:\n    \"\"\"Process all screenplay batches in parallel using KMS key pool.\n\n    Uses CentralizedKeyClient (async) with Semaphore(8) for parallel batches.\n    Each batch: acquire key via KMS -> call OpenAI -> return raw JSON response.\n    Scene reconstruction is NOT done here (orchestrator handles it per-batch).\n    \"\"\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        kms_url: str,\n        machine_id: str,\n        system_prompt: str,\n        video_context: dict,\n        scene_min_words: int,\n        scene_max_words: int,\n        language: str,\n        account_code: str | None = None,\n        video_name: str = \"\",\n    ):\n        self.kms_url = kms_url\n        self.machine_id = machine_id\n        self.system_prompt = system_prompt\n        self.video_context = video_context\n        self.scene_min_words = scene_min_words\n        self.scene_max_words = scene_max_words\n        self.language = language\n        self.account_code = account_code\n        self.video_name = video_name\n\n    async def run(self, batches: list[str]) -> list[dict]:\n        \"\"\"Process all batches in parallel. Returns list of parsed JSON responses (in order).\n\n        Args:\n            batches: List of text strings (one per batch)\n\n        Returns:\n            List of parsed agent output dicts, each containing \"scenes\" key.\n            Order matches input batches.\n        \"\"\"\n        async with CentralizedKeyClient(self.kms_url, self.machine_id) as kms:\n            sem = asyncio.Semaphore(8)  # Allow up to 8 concurrent batches\n\n            async def process_one(batch_idx: int, batch_text: str) -> dict:\n                async with sem:\n                    return await self._process_batch(kms, batch_idx, batch_text, len(batches))\n\n            results = await asyncio.gather(\n                *[process_one(i, b) for i, b in enumerate(batches)],\n                return_exceptions=True,\n            )\n\n        # Check for errors\n        errors = [(i, r) for i, r in enumerate(results) if isinstance(r, Exception)]\n        if errors:\n            for i, e in errors:\n                logger.error(f\"Screenplay batch {i + 1} failed: {type(e).__name__}: {e}\")\n            raise RuntimeError(\n                f\"Parallel screenplay failed: {len(errors)}/{len(batches)} batches errored. \"\n                f\"First error: {errors[0][1]}\"\n            ) from errors[0][1]\n\n        return results  # List of parsed JSON dicts, in order\n\n    async def _process_batch(\n        self,\n        kms: CentralizedKeyClient,\n        batch_idx: int,\n        batch_text: str,\n        total_batches: int,\n    ) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Process a single batch using KMS for key acquisition.\"\"\"\n        batch_number = batch_idx + 1  # 1-based for agent input\n\n        is_cjk = self.language in (\"ja\", \"ko\")\n        batch_units = len(batch_text.strip()) if is_cjk else len(batch_text.split())\n        unit_label = \"chars\" if is_cjk else \"words\"\n\n        agent_input = {\n            \"input_type\": \"TEXT_BATCH\",\n            \"batch_number\": batch_number,\n            \"total_batches\": total_batches,\n            \"video_context\": self.video_context,\n            \"data\": {\n                \"text\": batch_text,\n                \"word_count\": batch_units,\n            },\n            \"constraints\": {\n                f\"min_{unit_label}_per_scene\": self.scene_min_words,\n                f\"max_{unit_label}_per_scene\": self.scene_max_words,\n                \"counting_unit\": \"characters\" if is_cjk else \"words\",\n                \"start_scene_number\": 1,  # Will be re-numbered by orchestrator\n            },\n            \"feedback\": None,\n        }\n\n        logger.info(\n            f\"  [KMS] Batch {batch_number}/{total_batches}: \"\n            f\"sending to GPT-4.1-mini ({batch_units} {unit_label})\"\n        )\n        import time\n        _t0 = time.monotonic()\n\n        async def call_fn(api_key: str):\n            client = AsyncOpenAI(api_key=api_key)\n            try:\n                response = await client.chat.completions.create(\n                    model=\"gpt-4.1-mini\",\n                    messages=[\n                        {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": self.system_prompt},\n                        {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": json.dumps(agent_input, ensure_ascii=False)},\n                    ],\n                    temperature=0.4,\n                    response_format={\"type\": \"json_object\"},\n                    timeout=120,\n                )\n                usage = {\n                    \"input_tokens\": response.usage.prompt_tokens,\n                    \"output_tokens\": response.usage.completion_tokens,\n                    \"agent_name\": \"screenplay_agent\",\n                    \"step_name\": \"bloco1_screenplay\",\n                    \"account_code\": self.account_code,\n                    \"language\": self.language,\n                    \"system_name\": \"bloco1\",\n                    \"video_title\": self.video_name,\n                }\n                raw_content = response.choices[0].message.content\n                return raw_content, usage\n            finally:\n                await client.close()\n\n        raw_json = await kms.call_with_resilience(\"gpt-4.1-mini\", call_fn)\n        agent_output = json.loads(raw_json)\n\n        scenes = agent_output.get(\"scenes\", [])\n        elapsed = time.monotonic() - _t0\n        logger.success(\n            f\"  [KMS] Batch {batch_number}/{total_batches}: \"\n            f\"{len(scenes)} scenes ({elapsed:.1f}s)\"\n        )\n\n        return agent_output\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775064040353}}
{"type":"message","id":"79d5516b","parentId":"34649b0e","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:21:03.983Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Sim — boa. Isso foi uma pista muito boa.\n\n# O que encontrei no V3\nTemos sinais fortes de que o V3 já seguia uma filosofia muito próxima do que estamos a descobrir agora:\n\n## 1. Separação entre trabalho semântico e trabalho mecânico\nNo V3, o “screenplay agent” parece estar mais focado em:\n- devolver `scenes`\n- agrupamento narrativo\n- output bruto por batch\n\nE depois existe camada Python a tratar de refinamento/checagem/reconstrução.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Existe lógica de checagem de word count / reconstrução\nEncontrei no V3 ficheiros como:\n\n- `shared/processors/scene_word_count_checker.py`\n- `shared/processors/scene_text_validator.py`\n- `shared/processors/scene_reconstructor.py`\n\nSó pelos nomes e pelo padrão, isso já é muito alinhado com a hipótese que estamos a seguir:\n- agent propõe\n- código valida/reconstrói/normaliza\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existe também loop de refine/evaluate\nEncontrei:\n\n- `shared/agents/refinement_loop.py`\n- `shared/agents/evaluator_agent.py`\n\nIsto é relevante porque mostra que no V3 já existia mentalidade de:\n\n### generate → evaluate → refine\ne não só:\n### generate once and trust forever\n\n---\n\n## 4. Existe processamento paralelo de screenplay por batch\nTambém achei:\n\n- `shared/processors/parallel_screenplay.py`\n\nE ele mostra explicitamente:\n- batches paralelos\n- resposta JSON do agent\n- reconstrução de cenas **não acontece ali**, fica para o orchestrator depois\n\n### Isso é muito importante\nPorque reforça exactamente a ideia de que:\n> o agent não precisa ser a única fonte de verdade de tudo\n\n---\n\n# O que isso significa para nós\n## Confirma uma direção\nO que estamos a tentar agora no OpenClaw S1 não é uma loucura nova.\n\nNa verdade, parece que o V3 já tinha percebido isto:\n\n### o screenplay/scene agent sozinho não deve carregar toda a precisão mecânica\nPrecisa de:\n- checagem\n- reconstrução\n- refinamento\n- orquestração\n\n---\n\n# Minha leitura estratégica\n## O V3 está a dar um sinal muito forte de que:\no caminho mais promissor não é forçar o `scene_director` a acertar tudo no braço.\n\nE sim:\n- agent faz agrupamento semântico\n- código reconstrói e valida\n- evaluator/refinement loop corrige quando necessário\n\n---\n\n# O que eu ainda não fiz\nAinda não li a fundo o conteúdo interno desses 3 processadores para te dizer:\n\n- exactamente como faziam a normalização\n- se fundiam cenas pequenas\n- se resegmentavam por word_count\n- ou se só validavam e mandavam refinar\n\nMas já dá para dizer com boa confiança:\n\n## Sim:\no V3 parece ter uma solução mais madura nesse eixo do que o que estávamos a improvisar aqui.\n\n---\n\n# Minha recomendação objectiva agora\nAntes de continuar inventando heurística local do zero, eu acho que o passo certo é:\n\n## puxar a lógica relevante do V3\nprincipalmente destas peças:\n- `scene_word_count_checker.py`\n- `scene_text_validator.py`\n- `scene_reconstructor.py`\n\nPorque há boa chance de já existir ali:\n- a resposta exacta ou quase exacta para este gargalo\n\n---\n\n# Resumo curto\n## Sim:\nfoi uma excelente ideia olhar o V3.\n\n## O que encontrei:\nsinais fortes de que o V3 já separava:\n- geração semântica\n- reconstrução/validação/refino em Python\n\n## O que isso sugere:\n**em vez de continuar improvisando muito no S1 novo, provavelmente vale importar/adaptar a lógica madura do V3.**\n\nSe quiser, o próximo passo certo é eu abrir esses 3 ficheiros do V3 com calma e te dizer:\n### exactamente qual lógica deles vale a pena portar para o S1 actual.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169cd53ef5bf08190b16bed24fcb169c8\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":7955,"output":851,"cacheRead":206592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":215398,"cost":{"input":0.019887500000000002,"output":0.012765,"cacheRead":0.051648,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0843005}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775064041165,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd53ec459c8190a1957e5c103cede2"}}
