{"type":"message","id":"c480326f","parentId":"7861fbe1","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:41:57.543Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_eKANKXErfmGOUxA8CFViTWrn|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd58e426c081908721774baceb9315","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\r\nScene Word Count Pre-Check — deterministic Python validator.\r\n\r\nRuns BEFORE the LLM evaluator to catch word count violations for free.\r\nGenerates specific feedback for the screenplay agent to fix violations in 1 retry.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Optional, Tuple\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _count_units(text: str, language: str) -> int:\r\n    \"\"\"Count content units: characters for CJK, words for alphabetic.\"\"\"\r\n    if language in (\"ja\", \"ko\"):\r\n        return len(text.strip())\r\n    return len(text.split())\r\n\r\n\r\ndef check_scene_word_counts(\r\n    scenes: List[Dict],\r\n    min_words: int,\r\n    max_words: int,\r\n    tolerance: int = 3,\r\n    language: str = \"en\",\r\n) -> Tuple[bool, Optional[Dict]]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Check word counts of all scenes and generate feedback if violations found.\r\n\r\n    Args:\r\n        scenes: List of scene dicts with \"text\", \"word_count\", \"scene_number\"\r\n        min_words: Minimum words per scene (from LANGUAGE_WORD_LIMITS)\r\n        max_words: Maximum words per scene (from LANGUAGE_WORD_LIMITS)\r\n        tolerance: Accept scenes within [min - tolerance, max + tolerance]\r\n        language: Language code (ja/ko use character count)\r\n\r\n    Returns:\r\n        (True, None) if all scenes are within acceptable range\r\n        (False, feedback_dict) if violations found — feedback ready for agent retry\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if not scenes:\r\n        return True, None\r\n\r\n    effective_min = min_words - tolerance\r\n    effective_max = max_words + tolerance\r\n    unit_name = \"characters\" if language in (\"ja\", \"ko\") else \"words\"\r\n\r\n    violations = []\r\n\r\n    for scene in scenes:\r\n        text = scene.get(\"text\", \"\")\r\n        actual_count = _count_units(text, language)\r\n        scene_num = scene.get(\"scene_number\", \"?\")\r\n\r\n        if actual_count < effective_min:\r\n            violations.append({\r\n                \"scene_number\": scene_num,\r\n                \"current_count\": actual_count,\r\n                \"min_required\": min_words,\r\n                \"action\": f\"MERGE with adjacent scene - this scene has only {actual_count} {unit_name} (minimum {min_words})\",\r\n                \"suggestion\": f\"Combine scene {scene_num} with the previous or next scene that shares thematic connection. The merged scene must stay under {max_words} {unit_name}.\",\r\n            })\r\n        elif actual_count > effective_max:\r\n            violations.append({\r\n                \"scene_number\": scene_num,\r\n                \"current_count\": actual_count,\r\n                \"max_allowed\": max_words,\r\n                \"action\": f\"SPLIT at sentence boundary - this scene has {actual_count} {unit_name} (maximum {max_words})\",\r\n                \"suggestion\": f\"Split scene {scene_num} into two scenes at a natural sentence boundary. Each resulting scene must have at least {min_words} {unit_name}.\",\r\n            })\r\n\r\n    if not violations:\r\n        return True, None\r\n\r\n    feedback = {\r\n        \"is_retry\": True,\r\n        \"word_count_fix_required\": True,\r\n        \"scenes_to_fix\": violations,\r\n        \"total_violations\": len(violations),\r\n        \"instruction\": (\r\n            f\"Fix ONLY the {len(violations)} word count violation(s) listed below. \"\r\n            f\"Keep all other scenes UNCHANGED. Preserve ALL metadata fields \"\r\n            f\"(faction_shown, interpretation_mode, emotional_tone, reasoning). \"\r\n            f\"Valid range: {min_words}-{max_words} {unit_name} per scene.\"\r\n        ),\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    return False, feedback\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775065317432}}
{"type":"message","id":"3f553f65","parentId":"c480326f","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:41:57.658Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_MUQRAtn2mCX045r7enowEda0|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd58e429208190a3e3b21c8c97efda","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\r\nScene Text Validator — deterministic Python validator.\r\n\r\nReplaces the LLM screenplay evaluator for text-coverage checks.\r\nValidates: missing_text, duplicate_text, empty_scenes, scene_order.\r\nGenerates specific feedback for the screenplay agent to fix violations in 1 retry.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport re\r\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Optional, Tuple\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _split_sentences(text: str) -> List[str]:\r\n    \"\"\"Split text into sentences using punctuation boundaries.\"\"\"\r\n    # Split on sentence-ending punctuation followed by space or end of string\r\n    raw = re.split(r'(?<=[.!?;])\\s+', text.strip())\r\n    # Normalize whitespace and filter empty\r\n    return [s.strip() for s in raw if s.strip()]\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _normalize(text: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Normalize text for comparison: lowercase, collapse whitespace.\"\"\"\r\n    return re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text.strip().lower())\r\n\r\n\r\ndef validate_scene_text(\r\n    scenes: List[Dict],\r\n    original_text: str,\r\n) -> Tuple[bool, Optional[Dict]]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Validate scene text coverage and integrity.\r\n\r\n    Checks:\r\n    1. empty_scenes: no scene has empty or whitespace-only text\r\n    2. duplicate_text: no sentence appears in more than one scene\r\n    3. missing_text: major chunks of original text missing from scenes\r\n    4. scene_order: scene_numbers are sequential starting from expected value\r\n\r\n    Args:\r\n        scenes: List of scene dicts with \"text\" and \"scene_number\"\r\n        original_text: The original batch text that was split into scenes\r\n\r\n    Returns:\r\n        (True, None) if all checks pass\r\n        (False, feedback_dict) if violations found — feedback ready for agent retry\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if not scenes:\r\n        return False, {\r\n            \"is_retry\": True,\r\n            \"text_validation_required\": True,\r\n            \"issues\": [{\"type\": \"no_scenes\", \"detail\": \"No scenes were generated\"}],\r\n            \"total_violations\": 1,\r\n            \"instruction\": \"You returned no scenes. Split the input text into scenes.\",\r\n        }\r\n\r\n    issues = []\r\n\r\n    # --- 1. Empty scenes ---\r\n    for scene in scenes:\r\n        text = scene.get(\"text\", \"\").strip()\r\n        scene_num = scene.get(\"scene_number\", \"?\")\r\n        if not text:\r\n            issues.append({\r\n                \"type\": \"empty_scene\",\r\n                \"scene_number\": scene_num,\r\n                \"detail\": f\"Scene {scene_num} has empty text\",\r\n                \"action\": f\"Remove scene {scene_num} or merge it with an adjacent scene\",\r\n            })\r\n\r\n    # --- 2. Duplicate text ---\r\n    scene_texts_normalized = []\r\n    for scene in scenes:\r\n        text = scene.get(\"text\", \"\").strip()\r\n        if text:\r\n            scene_texts_normalized.append((scene.get(\"scene_number\", \"?\"), _normalize(text)))\r\n\r\n    for i in range(len(scene_texts_normalized)):\r\n        for j in range(i + 1, len(scene_texts_normalized)):\r\n            num_i, text_i = scene_texts_normalized[i]\r\n            num_j, text_j = scene_texts_normalized[j]\r\n            # Check for exact duplicates or high overlap (one contains the other)\r\n            if text_i == text_j:\r\n                issues.append({\r\n                    \"type\": \"duplicate_text\",\r\n                    \"scene_numbers\": [num_i, num_j],\r\n                    \"detail\": f\"Scene {num_i} and scene {num_j} have identical text\",\r\n                    \"action\": f\"Remove duplicate scene {num_j} and redistribute text\",\r\n                })\r\n            elif len(text_i) > 20 and len(text_j) > 20:\r\n                # Check if one scene contains 80%+ of the other\r\n                shorter, longer = (text_i, text_j) if len(text_i) < len(text_j) else (text_j, text_i)\r\n                if shorter in longer:\r\n                    issues.append({\r\n                        \"type\": \"duplicate_text\",\r\n                        \"scene_numbers\": [num_i, num_j],\r\n                        \"detail\": f\"Scene {num_i} text is contained within scene {num_j} (or vice versa)\",\r\n                        \"action\": f\"Remove the overlapping text from one of the scenes\",\r\n                    })\r\n\r\n    # --- 3. Missing text ---\r\n    # Check that all sentences from original text appear in at least one scene\r\n    original_sentences = _split_sentences(original_text)\r\n    combined_scene_text = _normalize(\" \".join(s.get(\"text\", \"\") for s in scenes))\r\n\r\n    missing_sentences = []\r\n    for sentence in original_sentences:\r\n        norm_sentence = _normalize(sentence)\r\n        # Skip very short fragments (< 3 words)\r\n        if len(norm_sentence.split()) < 3:\r\n            continue\r\n        if norm_sentence not in combined_scene_text:\r\n            missing_sentences.append(sentence)\r\n\r\n    if missing_sentences:\r\n        # Only flag if significant text is missing (> 10% of sentences)\r\n        missing_ratio = len(missing_sentences) / max(len(original_sentences), 1)\r\n        if missing_ratio > 0.10:\r\n            issues.append({\r\n                \"type\": \"missing_text\",\r\n                \"missing_count\": len(missing_sentences),\r\n                \"total_sentences\": len(original_sentences),\r\n                \"missing_ratio\": f\"{missing_ratio:.0%}\",\r\n                \"examples\": missing_sentences[:3],\r\n                \"detail\": f\"{len(missing_sentences)}/{len(original_sentences)} sentences from the original text are missing from scenes\",\r\n                \"action\": \"Include ALL sentences from the original text. Do not skip or summarize any content.\",\r\n            })\r\n\r\n    # --- 4. Scene order ---\r\n    scene_numbers = [s.get(\"scene_number\") for s in scenes if s.get(\"scene_number\") is not None]\r\n    if scene_numbers:\r\n        for i in range(1, len(scene_numbers)):\r\n            if scene_numbers[i] != scene_numbers[i - 1] + 1:\r\n                issues.append({\r\n                    \"type\": \"scene_order\",\r\n                    \"detail\": f\"Scene numbers are not sequential: ...{scene_numbers[i-1]}, {scene_numbers[i]}...\",\r\n                    \"action\": \"Number scenes sequentially without gaps\",\r\n                })\r\n                break  # Only report once\r\n\r\n    if not issues:\r\n        return True, None\r\n\r\n    feedback = {\r\n        \"is_retry\": True,\r\n        \"text_validation_required\": True,\r\n        \"issues\": issues,\r\n        \"total_violations\": len(issues),\r\n        \"instruction\": (\r\n            f\"Fix the {len(issues)} text validation issue(s) listed below. \"\r\n            f\"The original text must be fully covered by the scenes — do not skip or summarize content. \"\r\n            f\"Keep all metadata fields (faction_shown, interpretation_mode, emotional_tone, reasoning).\"\r\n        ),\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    return False, feedback\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775065317544}}
{"type":"message","id":"ed31a066","parentId":"3f553f65","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:41:57.777Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_KaWC9G16hntJ0O3oxWrAUatd|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd58e4293081909b68f28a2efe22f2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\"\"\"\r\nScene Reconstructor — deterministic Python auto-correction for screenplay scenes.\r\n\r\nReplaces LLM-based retries (word count + text validator) with pure Python fixes.\r\nTwo paths:\r\n  1. Text matches original → fix word counts by moving whole sentences between scenes\r\n  2. Text corrupted → reconstruct ALL scenes from original text\r\n\r\nZero LLM calls. Handles all 13 languages (CJK character counting, full-width punctuation).\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport re\r\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Optional, Tuple\r\n\r\nfrom loguru import logger\r\n\r\n\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# Language helpers\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n_CJK_LANGUAGES = {\"ja\", \"ko\"}\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _count_units(text: str, language: str) -> int:\r\n    \"\"\"Count content units: characters for CJK (excluding whitespace), words for alphabetic.\"\"\"\r\n    if language in _CJK_LANGUAGES:\r\n        # Remove ALL whitespace before counting — CJK doesn't use spaces as separators\r\n        return len(re.sub(r'\\s+', '', text))\r\n    return len(text.split())\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _split_sentences(text: str, language: str) -> List[str]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Split text into sentences using language-aware punctuation boundaries.\r\n\r\n    CJK (ja, ko): splits on full-width AND half-width sentence-ending punctuation.\r\n    Alphabetic: splits on .!? followed by whitespace.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if language in _CJK_LANGUAGES:\r\n        parts = re.split(r'(?<=[。！？.!?])\\s*|\\n+', text)\r\n    else:\r\n        parts = re.split(r'(?<=[.!?])\\s+', text)\r\n    return [s.strip() for s in parts if s.strip()]\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _join_sentences(sentences: List[str], language: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"Join sentences back into text, language-aware.\"\"\"\r\n    if language in _CJK_LANGUAGES:\r\n        # No separator for CJK — sentences end with punctuation (。！？)\r\n        return \"\".join(sentences)\r\n    return \" \".join(sentences)\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _normalize_for_compare(text: str, language: str) -> str:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Normalize text for comparison.\r\n\r\n    Alphabetic: lowercase + collapse whitespace.\r\n    CJK: strip + remove ALL whitespace (CJK doesn't use spaces as word separators).\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    if language in _CJK_LANGUAGES:\r\n        # Remove all whitespace for CJK — spaces/newlines are not significant\r\n        return re.sub(r'\\s+', '', text.strip())\r\n    return re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text.strip()).lower()\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _texts_match(scenes: List[Dict], original_text: str, language: str) -> bool:\r\n    \"\"\"Check if concatenated scene texts match the original text.\"\"\"\r\n    joiner = \" \"  # use space for comparison regardless of language\r\n    combined = joiner.join(s.get(\"text\", \"\").strip() for s in scenes if s.get(\"text\", \"\").strip())\r\n    norm_combined = _normalize_for_compare(combined, language)\r\n    norm_original = _normalize_for_compare(original_text, language)\r\n    return norm_combined == norm_original\r\n\r\n\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# Path 1: Fix word counts by moving sentences\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\ndef _extract_scene_sentences(scenes: List[Dict], language: str) -> List[List[str]]:\r\n    \"\"\"Extract sentences from each scene, preserving scene boundaries.\"\"\"\r\n    result = []\r\n    for scene in scenes:\r\n        text = scene.get(\"text\", \"\").strip()\r\n        if text:\r\n            result.append(_split_sentences(text, language))\r\n        else:\r\n            result.append([])\r\n    return result\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _fix_word_counts(\r\n    scene_sentences: List[List[str]],\r\n    min_units: int,\r\n    max_units: int,\r\n    language: str,\r\n) -> List[List[str]]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Redistribute whole sentences between adjacent scenes to fix word count violations.\r\n\r\n    Iterates up to 10 passes to stabilize. Each pass scans left-to-right:\r\n    - Scene too long: move last sentence(s) to next scene\r\n    - Scene too short: pull first sentence from next scene\r\n\r\n    Returns the fixed scene_sentences list.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    max_passes = 10\r\n\r\n    for pass_num in range(max_passes):\r\n        changed = False\r\n\r\n        for i in range(len(scene_sentences)):\r\n            if not scene_sentences[i]:\r\n                continue\r\n\r\n            current_text = _join_sentences(scene_sentences[i], language)\r\n            current_count = _count_units(current_text, language)\r\n\r\n            # --- Too long: move last sentence(s) to next scene ---\r\n            if current_count > max_units and len(scene_sentences[i]) > 1:\r\n                # Move last sentence to next scene (create new scene if last)\r\n                if i < len(scene_sentences) - 1:\r\n                    # Move to existing next scene\r\n                    moved = scene_sentences[i].pop()\r\n                    scene_sentences[i + 1].insert(0, moved)\r\n                    changed = True\r\n                elif i > 0:\r\n                    # Last scene, too long — try moving first sentence to previous\r\n                    moved = scene_sentences[i].pop(0)\r\n                    scene_sentences[i - 1].append(moved)\r\n                    changed = True\r\n\r\n            # --- Too short: pull first sentence from next scene ---\r\n            elif current_count < min_units and i < len(scene_sentences) - 1:\r\n                if scene_sentences[i + 1]:\r\n                    # Only pull if next scene won't become empty\r\n                    if len(scene_sentences[i + 1]) > 1:\r\n                        pulled = scene_sentences[i + 1].pop(0)\r\n                        scene_sentences[i].append(pulled)\r\n                        changed = True\r\n                    elif len(scene_sentences[i + 1]) == 1:\r\n                        # Next scene has only 1 sentence — merge entirely\r\n                        pulled = scene_sentences[i + 1].pop(0)\r\n                        scene_sentences[i].append(pulled)\r\n                        changed = True\r\n\r\n        # Remove empty scenes\r\n        scene_sentences = [s for s in scene_sentences if s]\r\n\r\n        if not changed:\r\n            break\r\n\r\n    # Final pass: merge last scene into previous if absurdly short (< min // 2)\r\n    if len(scene_sentences) >= 2:\r\n        last_text = _join_sentences(scene_sentences[-1], language)\r\n        last_count = _count_units(last_text, language)\r\n        prev_text = _join_sentences(scene_sentences[-2], language)\r\n        prev_count = _count_units(prev_text, language)\r\n        # Only merge if last scene is absurdly short AND merged result won't exceed max\r\n        if last_count < min_units // 2 and (prev_count + last_count) <= max_units:\r\n            scene_sentences[-2].extend(scene_sentences[-1])\r\n            scene_sentences.pop()\r\n\r\n    return scene_sentences\r\n\r\n\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# Path 2: Rebuild from scratch\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\ndef _rebuild_from_scratch(\r\n    original_text: str,\r\n    min_units: int,\r\n    max_units: int,\r\n    start_scene_number: int,\r\n    language: str,\r\n) -> List[Dict]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Reconstruct scenes from original text using greedy sentence distribution.\r\n\r\n    Algorithm: fill each scene with sentences until reaching the target\r\n    (midpoint of min/max). Cut when >= target and sentence ends with punctuation.\r\n    Hard cut at max_units.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    sentences = _split_sentences(original_text, language)\r\n    if not sentences:\r\n        return []\r\n\r\n    target = (min_units + max_units) // 2\r\n    scenes = []\r\n    current_sentences: List[str] = []\r\n    current_count = 0\r\n    scene_number = start_scene_number\r\n\r\n    for sentence in sentences:\r\n        sentence_units = _count_units(sentence, language)\r\n\r\n        # Would exceed max? Start new scene (if we have content)\r\n        if current_count + sentence_units > max_units and current_sentences:\r\n            scene_text = _join_sentences(current_sentences, language)\r\n            scenes.append({\r\n                \"scene_number\": scene_number,\r\n                \"text\": scene_text,\r\n                \"word_count\": _count_units(scene_text, language),\r\n                \"scene_type\": \"narrative\",\r\n            })\r\n            scene_number += 1\r\n            current_sentences = [sentence]\r\n            current_count = sentence_units\r\n        else:\r\n            current_sentences.append(sentence)\r\n            current_count += sentence_units\r\n\r\n            # Reached target? Start new scene\r\n            if current_count >= target:\r\n                scene_text = _join_sentences(current_sentences, language)\r\n                scenes.append({\r\n                    \"scene_number\": scene_number,\r\n                    \"text\": scene_text,\r\n                    \"word_count\": _count_units(scene_text, language),\r\n                    \"scene_type\": \"narrative\",\r\n                })\r\n                scene_number += 1\r\n                current_sentences = []\r\n                current_count = 0\r\n\r\n    # Last scene\r\n    if current_sentences:\r\n        scene_text = _join_sentences(current_sentences, language)\r\n        scenes.append({\r\n            \"scene_number\": scene_number,\r\n            \"text\": scene_text,\r\n            \"word_count\": _count_units(scene_text, language),\r\n            \"scene_type\": \"narrative\",\r\n        })\r\n\r\n    return scenes\r\n\r\n\r\ndef _rebuild_and_fix(\r\n    original_text: str,\r\n    min_units: int,\r\n    max_units: int,\r\n    start_scene_number: int,\r\n    language: str,\r\n) -> List[Dict]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Rebuild from scratch + fix word counts via sentence redistribution.\r\n\r\n    _rebuild_from_scratch() uses a greedy algorithm that can create scenes\r\n    exceeding max (single long sentence) or below min (short remainder).\r\n    This wrapper applies _fix_word_counts() after rebuild to ensure compliance.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    rebuilt = _rebuild_from_scratch(original_text, min_units, max_units, start_scene_number, language)\r\n    if not rebuilt:\r\n        return rebuilt\r\n\r\n    # Apply same fix_word_counts as match_fix path\r\n    scene_sentences = _extract_scene_sentences(rebuilt, language)\r\n    fixed_sentences = _fix_word_counts(scene_sentences, min_units, max_units, language)\r\n\r\n    # Rebuild scene dicts\r\n    fixed_scenes = []\r\n    scene_num = start_scene_number\r\n    for sentences in fixed_sentences:\r\n        text = _join_sentences(sentences, language)\r\n        fixed_scenes.append({\r\n            \"scene_number\": scene_num,\r\n            \"text\": text,\r\n            \"word_count\": _count_units(text, language),\r\n            \"scene_type\": \"narrative\",\r\n        })\r\n        scene_num += 1\r\n\r\n    return fixed_scenes\r\n\r\n\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n# Main entry point\r\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\ndef reconstruct_scenes(\r\n    scenes: List[Dict],\r\n    original_text: str,\r\n    min_words: int,\r\n    max_words: int,\r\n    start_scene_number: int,\r\n    language: str = \"en\",\r\n) -> Tuple[List[Dict], Dict]:\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Validate + auto-fix scenes from screenplay agent. Zero LLM calls.\r\n\r\n    Two paths:\r\n      1. Text matches original → fix word counts by moving sentences (\"match_fix\")\r\n      2. Text corrupted → rebuild all scenes from original text (\"reconstruct\")\r\n      3. Everything OK → return as-is (\"passthrough\")\r\n\r\n    Args:\r\n        scenes: List of scene dicts from screenplay agent (need \"text\" key)\r\n        original_text: The original batch text that was split into scenes\r\n        min_words: Minimum units per scene (words or chars for CJK)\r\n        max_words: Maximum units per scene\r\n        start_scene_number: Starting scene number for sequential numbering\r\n        language: Language code (en, ja, ko, etc.)\r\n\r\n    Returns:\r\n        (fixed_scenes, report) where report contains:\r\n        - path: \"match_fix\" | \"reconstruct\" | \"passthrough\"\r\n        - changes_made: list of change descriptions\r\n        - original_scene_count: int\r\n        - final_scene_count: int\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    report = {\r\n        \"path\": \"passthrough\",\r\n        \"changes_made\": [],\r\n        \"original_scene_count\": len(scenes),\r\n        \"final_scene_count\": len(scenes),\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    # Edge case: empty input\r\n    if not original_text or not original_text.strip():\r\n        logger.warning(\"[Reconstructor] Empty original text\")\r\n        report[\"path\"] = \"passthrough\"\r\n        return [], report\r\n\r\n    # Edge case: no scenes from agent\r\n    if not scenes:\r\n        logger.warning(\"[Reconstructor] No scenes from agent, rebuilding from scratch\")\r\n        rebuilt = _rebuild_and_fix(original_text, min_words, max_words, start_scene_number, language)\r\n        report[\"path\"] = \"reconstruct\"\r\n        report[\"changes_made\"].append(\"no_scenes_from_agent\")\r\n        report[\"final_scene_count\"] = len(rebuilt)\r\n        return rebuilt, report\r\n\r\n    # Check if text matches original\r\n    if _texts_match(scenes, original_text, language):\r\n        # Path 1: Text matches — check if word counts need fixing\r\n        needs_fix = False\r\n        for scene in scenes:\r\n            text = scene.get(\"text\", \"\").strip()\r\n            count = _count_units(text, language)\r\n            if count < min_words or count > max_words:\r\n                needs_fix = True\r\n                break\r\n\r\n        if not needs_fix:\r\n            # Everything is fine — passthrough (but still renumber sequentially)\r\n            report[\"path\"] = \"passthrough\"\r\n            scene_num = start_scene_number\r\n            for s in scenes:\r\n                s[\"scene_number\"] = scene_num\r\n                scene_num += 1\r\n            return scenes, report\r\n\r\n        # Fix word counts by redistributing sentences\r\n        logger.info(\"[Reconstructor] Text matches, fixing word counts...\")\r\n        scene_sentences = _extract_scene_sentences(scenes, language)\r\n        original_counts = [_count_units(_join_sentences(ss, language), language) for ss in scene_sentences]\r\n\r\n        fixed_sentences = _fix_word_counts(scene_sentences, min_words, max_words, language)\r\n\r\n        # Build fixed scenes\r\n        fixed_scenes = []\r\n        scene_num = start_scene_number\r\n        for sentences in fixed_sentences:\r\n            text = _join_sentences(sentences, language)\r\n            fixed_scenes.append({\r\n                \"scene_number\": scene_num,\r\n                \"text\": text,\r\n                \"word_count\": _count_units(text, language),\r\n                \"scene_type\": \"narrative\",\r\n            })\r\n            scene_num += 1\r\n\r\n        # Merge absurdly short last scene into previous (< min_words // 2)\r\n        if len(fixed_scenes) >= 2:\r\n            last_wc = fixed_scenes[-1][\"word_count\"]\r\n            prev_wc = fixed_scenes[-2][\"word_count\"]\r\n            if last_wc < min_words // 2 and (prev_wc + last_wc) <= max_words:\r\n                prev = fixed_scenes[-2]\r\n                last = fixed_scenes[-1]\r\n                joiner = \"\" if language in _CJK_LANGUAGES else \" \"\r\n                merged_text = prev[\"text\"] + joiner + last[\"text\"]\r\n                prev[\"text\"] = merged_text\r\n                prev[\"word_count\"] = _count_units(merged_text, language)\r\n                fixed_scenes.pop()\r\n                report[\"changes_made\"].append(\r\n                    f\"merged_short_last_scene: {last_wc}w into scene {prev['scene_number']}\"\r\n                )\r\n\r\n        # Check if fix actually resolved all violations (except last scene which can be short)\r\n        still_violated = False\r\n        for idx, s in enumerate(fixed_scenes):\r\n            is_last = (idx == len(fixed_scenes) - 1)\r\n            wc = s[\"word_count\"]\r\n            if wc > max_words:\r\n                still_violated = True\r\n                break\r\n            if wc < min_words and not is_last:\r\n                still_violated = True\r\n                break\r\n\r\n        if still_violated:\r\n            # Sentence redistribution couldn't fix it — rebuild from scratch\r\n            logger.warning(\r\n                \"[Reconstructor] Sentence redistribution couldn't fix all violations, \"\r\n                \"rebuilding from scratch.\"\r\n            )\r\n            rebuilt = _rebuild_and_fix(\r\n                original_text, min_words, max_words, start_scene_number, language\r\n            )\r\n            report[\"path\"] = \"reconstruct\"\r\n            report[\"changes_made\"].append(\r\n                f\"redistribution_failed: {original_counts} -> rebuild\"\r\n            )\r\n            report[\"final_scene_count\"] = len(rebuilt)\r\n            return rebuilt, report\r\n\r\n        # Log changes\r\n        new_counts = [s[\"word_count\"] for s in fixed_scenes]\r\n        if len(original_counts) != len(new_counts) or original_counts != new_counts:\r\n            report[\"changes_made\"].append(\r\n                f\"word_counts: {original_counts} -> {new_counts}\"\r\n            )\r\n\r\n        report[\"path\"] = \"match_fix\"\r\n        report[\"final_scene_count\"] = len(fixed_scenes)\r\n        return fixed_scenes, report\r\n\r\n    else:\r\n        # Path 2: Text doesn't match — reconstruct from scratch\r\n        combined = \" \".join(s.get(\"text\", \"\").strip() for s in scenes)\r\n        orig_units = _count_units(original_text, language)\r\n        scene_units = _count_units(combined, language)\r\n        logger.warning(\r\n            f\"[Reconstructor] Text mismatch! \"\r\n            f\"Original: {orig_units} units, Scenes: {scene_units} units. \"\r\n            f\"Rebuilding from scratch.\"\r\n        )\r\n\r\n        rebuilt = _rebuild_and_fix(original_text, min_words, max_words, start_scene_number, language)\r\n\r\n        report[\"path\"] = \"reconstruct\"\r\n        report[\"changes_made\"].append(\r\n            f\"text_mismatch: original={orig_units} units, scenes={scene_units} units\"\r\n        )\r\n        report[\"final_scene_count\"] = len(rebuilt)\r\n        return rebuilt, report\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775065317658}}
{"type":"message","id":"203138f2","parentId":"ed31a066","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:42:36.979Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Perfeito. Li os 3, e agora dá para te trazer uma proposta bem mais concreta.\n\n# Leitura profunda do V3\nA tua intuição estava **certíssima**.\n\n## O V3 já tinha exactamente a filosofia que está a fazer falta aqui:\n- agent faz a parte semântica\n- Python faz a parte mecânica\n- e, se necessário, reconstrói ou refina\n\n---\n\n# O que cada peça faz no V3\n\n## 1. `scene_word_count_checker.py`\n### O que ele faz\nÉ um **pré-check determinístico** de quantidade de palavras por cena.\n\nEle:\n- mede o tamanho real de cada cena\n- compara com `min_words` / `max_words`\n- permite pequena tolerância\n- se encontrar cena curta demais ou longa demais:\n  - não tenta resolver sozinho\n  - gera **feedback estruturado** para retry\n\n### Tipo de feedback\nAlgo como:\n- cena X está curta demais → merge com vizinha\n- cena Y está longa demais → split em boundary natural\n\n## O que isso significa\nEle funciona mais como:\n- **detector + gerador de instrução de repair**\ndo que como reconstrutor final.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `scene_text_validator.py`\n### O que ele faz\nÉ outro validator determinístico.\n\nEle checa:\n- cenas vazias\n- duplicação de texto\n- texto faltando\n- ordem das cenas\n\n### Mecanismo\nEle compara as frases do texto original com o texto combinado das cenas.\n\nSe faltar coisa demais ou houver duplicação/overlap importante:\n- gera feedback estruturado para retry\n\n## O que isso significa\nÉ um guardião de:\n- cobertura total do texto\n- integridade textual\n- ordem\n\n---\n\n## 3. `scene_reconstructor.py`\n### Este é o ouro.\nÉ claramente a peça mais importante para o nosso problema.\n\n---\n\n# O que o `scene_reconstructor.py` faz\nEle implementa **duas estratégias principais**:\n\n## Path 1 — `match_fix`\nSe o texto das cenas ainda bate com o original:\n- ele **não chama LLM**\n- extrai sentenças por cena\n- redistribui sentenças entre cenas vizinhas\n- corrige word counts\n- funde cena curta\n- divide cena longa\n- reconstrói as cenas\n\n### Tradução\nSe o screenplay está “quase certo”, ele corrige **deterministicamente**.\n\n---\n\n## Path 2 — `reconstruct`\nSe o texto do agent já não bate com o original:\n- ele considera o output semanticamente/textualmente corrompido\n- e **reconstrói tudo do zero** a partir do texto original\n- usando split por sentença + distribuição gulosa dentro do range\n\n### Tradução\nSe o agent estragou demais,\no código assume o controlo e remonta tudo.\n\n---\n\n# Isto é extremamente importante\nPorque o V3 já resolveu o dilema que estamos a viver agora:\n\n## dilema\n“Até onde confiar no agent e até onde puxar para Python?”\n\n## resposta do V3\n- se o agent está bom o suficiente → **fix deterministicamente**\n- se não está → **rebuild deterministicamente**\n\n---\n\n# O que isso muda no nosso S1 actual\nMuda muito.\n\n## Hoje no nosso S1 novo\nO nosso normalizer está ainda muito simplista.\nEle tenta:\n- alinhar sequencialmente `narration_original`\n- rederivar spans\n\nMas ele **ainda não tem**:\n- lógica de merge/split por sentença\n- lógica de rebalanço de scene size\n- fallback sério de reconstruct\n\n---\n\n# Proposta concreta de porting para o S1 actual\n\nAgora vou te dizer exactamente o que eu portaria.\n\n---\n\n## Peça 1 — portar a filosofia do `scene_reconstructor.py`\n### Prioridade máxima\nEu criaria no S1 novo algo como:\n\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/scene_reconstructor.py`\n\n### Papel\nReceber:\n- output bruto do `scene_director`\n- texto original do batch\n- min/max words por cena\n- scene numbering start\n- language\n\nE decidir:\n\n### Caminho A — match_fix\nSe o texto ainda casa com o original:\n- ajustar tamanhos de cena via frases\n- mover frases entre cenas\n- fundir cenas curtas\n- reconstruir word counts e spans\n\n### Caminho B — reconstruct\nSe o texto já não casa bem:\n- ignorar a estrutura do agent\n- reconstruir cenas deterministicamente a partir do batch text\n\n---\n\n## Peça 2 — portar parte do `scene_text_validator.py`\n### Prioridade alta\nCriar algo como:\n- `scene_text_integrity_checker.py`\n\nPara checar:\n- missing text\n- duplicate text\n- scene order\n- vazio\n\n### Por quê?\nPorque isso permite decidir:\n- ainda dá para fixar?\n- ou já precisa reconstruct?\n\n---\n\n## Peça 3 — portar parte do `scene_word_count_checker.py`\n### Prioridade alta\nCriar um checker determinístico para:\n- detectar violações de tamanho\n- e orientar o reconstructor/fixer\n\n### Observação importante\nEu **não copiaria cegamente** o modelo do V3 de “gerar feedback para retry” como primeira opção.\n\nNo nosso estado actual, eu faria assim:\n- primeiro tentar **corrigir deterministicamente**\n- só se não der, gerar repair/retry supervisor-driven\n\n---\n\n# Como eu redesenharia o lane no S1 novo\n## Pipeline ideal\n### Step 1 — agent\n`scene_director` devolve:\n- scene grouping\n- title\n- summary\n- narrative function\n- texto da cena\n\n### Step 2 — deterministic text integrity check\nVer:\n- bate com o texto original?\n- está completo?\n- sem duplicações?\n\n### Step 3 — deterministic reconstruction/fix\nSe precisar:\n- split/merge por sentença\n- rebalance de word count\n- rebuild total se necessário\n\n### Step 4 — derive exact spans\nAqui sim:\n- `start_word`\n- `end_word`\n- `estimated_scene_word_count`\n\n### Step 5 — validator final\nValida o artefacto já reconstruído\n\n### Step 6 — só então retry semântico\nSe até isso falhar,\naí sim faz sentido um repair supervisor-driven para o agent\n\n---\n\n# O que eu portaria 1:1 e o que eu adaptaria\n\n## Portaria quase 1:1\n### do `scene_reconstructor.py`\n- `_count_units`\n- `_split_sentences`\n- `_join_sentences`\n- `_normalize_for_compare`\n- `_texts_match`\n- `_extract_scene_sentences`\n- `_fix_word_counts`\n- `_rebuild_from_scratch`\n- `_rebuild_and_fix`\n- `reconstruct_scenes`\n\n### Adaptando nomes/campos\nPorque no nosso S1 actual os campos são mais como:\n- `narration_original`\n- `scene_local_id`\n- etc.\n\n---\n\n## Adaptaria\n### do `scene_text_validator.py`\nA ideia geral sim, mas ajustando para:\n- `narration_original`\n- batch-local semantics\n- integração com validator final actual\n\n---\n\n## Não copiaria literalmente\n### do `scene_word_count_checker.py`\nA parte de “gerar feedback para o agent” eu não trataria como primeira resposta.\n\nEu portaria mais:\n- a lógica de detecção\n- e deixaria a resposta padrão ser:\n  - fix deterministicamente primeiro\n\n---\n\n# Minha recomendação objectiva\n## O melhor próximo passo técnico agora é:\n### parar de expandir o nosso normalizer improvisado\ne substituí-lo por um **scene_reconstructor inspirado diretamente no V3**.\n\n---\n\n# Em uma frase\n## O V3 já tinha a solução conceptual certa:\n**se o output do agent ainda é aproveitável, Python corrige; se não é, Python reconstrói.**\n\nE eu acho que esse é o caminho exacto que devemos trazer para o S1 novo.\n\n---\n\n# Proposta de ordem de implementação\n## Ordem prática\n1. criar `scene_reconstructor.py` no S1 novo, inspirado no V3  \n2. ligar ele logo após o output do `scene_director`  \n3. usar o reconstructor antes do validator final  \n4. só depois pensar em repair supervisor-driven mais sofisticado\n\nPorque isso deve eliminar uma parte enorme da fragilidade.\n\n---\n\nSe quiser, eu posso agora já começar a:\n### portar/adaptar o `scene_reconstructor.py` do V3 para o S1 actual.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169cd58ea625081908139078607cbeb13\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":11170,"output":1795,"cacheRead":207360,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":220325,"cost":{"input":0.027925000000000002,"output":0.026925,"cacheRead":0.05184,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.10669000000000001}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775065318542,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd58e789fc8190992237ade465bb1b"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5842c7e4","parentId":"203138f2","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:43:31.671Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-04-01 14:43:23 GMT-3] Reminder: this is a 5-minute progress update reminder for the current PM -> VO -> S1 controlled test. Check the current run state, identify the exact step reached (PM, VO bootstrap, VO script_ready, or S1/b1_*), summarize progress briefly, and tell Lucca what has completed, what is currently running or blocked, and the next expected checkpoint.\n\nA scheduled reminder has been triggered. The reminder content is:\n\nReminder: this is a 5-minute progress update reminder for the current PM -> VO -> S1 controlled test. Check the current run state, identify the exact step reached (PM, VO bootstrap, VO script_ready, or S1/b1_*), summarize progress briefly, and tell Lucca what has completed, what is currently running or blocked, and the next expected checkpoint.\n\nHandle this reminder internally. Do not relay it to the user unless explicitly requested.\nCurrent time: Wednesday, April 1st, 2026 — 14:43 (America/Sao_Paulo) / 2026-04-01 17:43 UTC"}],"timestamp":1775065411606}}
{"type":"message","id":"2e8fd77b","parentId":"5842c7e4","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:43:44.969Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Update de 5 min:\n\n## Não está rodando agora\nSem execução activa.\n\n---\n\n# Estado do pipeline\n## PM ✅\nValidado.\n\n## VO ✅\nValidado.\n\n## S1 / scene_director ❌\nContinua o gargalo.\n\n---\n\n# O que avançou na investigação\nA leitura profunda do V3 ficou muito valiosa.\n\n## Descoberta principal\nO V3 já tinha um desenho muito mais maduro para este problema:\n\n- `scene_word_count_checker.py`\n- `scene_text_validator.py`\n- `scene_reconstructor.py`\n\n### O insight central\nNo V3:\n- se o output do agent ainda é aproveitável → Python corrige\n- se o output está corrompido → Python reconstrói\n\n---\n\n# Leitura actual\nIsso encaixa exactamente com o nosso problema actual no S1 novo.\n\n## Então a hipótese mais forte agora é:\no caminho certo não é insistir mais no prompt,\ne sim:\n- portar/adaptar a lógica do `scene_reconstructor.py`\n- e complementar com validação/checks do V3\n\n---\n\n# Próximo checkpoint esperado\nA próxima etapa realmente útil será:\n- começar o port/adaptação dessa lógica do V3 para o S1 actual\n- e só depois voltar a testar\n\n---\n\n# Resumo curto\n## Agora:\n- nada rodando\n- PM e VO já estão bons\n- `scene_director` ainda trava o S1\n- o caminho mais promissor agora é adaptar o reconstructor/validators maduros do V3","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169cd594a1e88819084215a1cad4b90f7\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":13016,"output":327,"cacheRead":206336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":219679,"cost":{"input":0.03254,"output":0.0049050000000000005,"cacheRead":0.051584,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.089029}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775065413019,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd59465a6c81908ec22b883863dee1"}}
