{"type":"message","id":"ffe474c6","parentId":"84be9e3f","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:44:55.822Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] Sim — faz todo sentido fazer isso já de forma estruturada, não só meter código.\n\n# Resposta curta\n## Se formos portar/adaptar essa lógica do V3,\nnão é só código que precisa mudar.\n\nTambém vamos precisar alinhar:\n\n- **contracts**\n- **docs de implementação**\n- **workspace do supervisor S1**\n- **workspace do `scene_director`**\n- possivelmente **skills novas** no runtime do S1\n\n---\n\n# O que eu actualizaria/criaria junto\n\n---\n\n## 1. Runtime / skills novas\n### Isto é o mais óbvio\nEu criaria ou substituiria estas peças no S1 novo:\n\n### Criar\n- `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/scene_reconstructor.py`\n- talvez `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/scene_text_integrity_checker.py`\n- talvez `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/scene_word_count_checker.py`\n\n### Possivelmente substituir / descontinuar\n- o `scene_director_output_normalizer.py` que eu improvisei agora pode virar:\n  - temporário\n  - ou ser absorvido pelo novo `scene_reconstructor.py`\n\n## Minha preferência\nNão deixar 2 sistemas concorrentes fazerem a mesma coisa.  \nOu seja:\n- ou o normalizer actual evolui e vira o reconstructor\n- ou criamos o reconstructor e aposentamos o normalizer improvisado\n\n---\n\n## 2. Contracts do S1\nSe o lane muda de forma importante, os contracts têm de refletir isso.\n\n### Eu actualizaria:\n- `docs/contracts/s1/s1_supervisor_contract.md`\n- `docs/contracts/s1/s1_scene_director_contract.md` se existir equivalente\n- possivelmente o contract do output validator runtime\n- contract do lane `scene_director` no geral\n\n### O que precisa entrar ali\nA regra nova:\n- o operator já não é a fonte final de verdade para spans exactos\n- o lane é **híbrido**\n- existe **reconstrução determinística pós-agent**\n- existe distinção entre:\n  - semantic grouping\n  - exact scene reconstruction\n\n---\n\n## 3. Docs de implementação do S1\nIsto precisa ser actualizado sim.\n\n### Já temos:\n- `S1_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md`\n- `S1_SCENE_DIRECTOR_REPAIR_FLOW.md`\n\n### Eu actualizaria ambos\nPara deixar explícito que:\n\n## O novo desenho é:\n- `scene_director` → semântica\n- `scene_reconstructor` → reconstrução/correção/word count discipline\n- validator → valida o artefacto reconstruído\n\n### Talvez eu criasse também\nSe a mudança ficar grande:\n- `S1_SCENE_RECONSTRUCTION_FLOW.md`\n\nMas só se sentir que está a ficar informação demais num único ficheiro.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Workspace do `op_s1_scene_director`\nSim, esse precisa alinhar.\n\n### Principalmente:\n- `PROMPT.md`\n- `CONTEXT.md`\n- talvez `IDENTITY.md`\n- `EXAMPLES.md`\n- `MEMORY.md`\n\n### O que mudar\nDeixar claro que o agent:\n- **não é o árbitro final dos spans exactos**\n- o foco dele é:\n  - scene grouping\n  - title\n  - summary\n  - narrative function\n  - blocos semânticos de narração\n\nOu seja:\ntirar dele a responsabilidade “sagrada” de acertar toda a mecânica exacta.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Workspace do `sm_s1_pre_production`\nTambém precisa sim.\n\n### Eu actualizaria:\n- `WORKFLOW.md`\n- `CONTEXT.md`\n- talvez `IDENTITY.md`\n\n### O que precisa refletir\nQue o supervisor agora governa um lane com:\n- output bruto do agent\n- reconstrução determinística\n- eventual repair\n- validação final\n\n---\n\n## 6. Validator / retry planning\nAqui tem uma nuance importante.\n\n### O que talvez precise mudar\nSe o reconstructor assumir grande parte do repair automático, o papel do validator muda um pouco.\n\n### Então eu revisaria:\n- `scene_director_output_validator.py`\n- `retry_planner.py` (pelo menos nos failure types do `scene_director`)\n\n### Porque?\nPara separar melhor:\n- erro corrigível deterministicamente\n- erro que ainda exige retry supervisor-driven\n- erro estrutural fatal\n\n---\n\n## 7. `TASKS.md` / workspace docs\nIsto eu actualizaria depois da implementação,\nnão antes.\n\nSó para registar que:\n- o lane do `scene_director` migrou para modelo híbrido mais próximo do V3\n\n---\n\n# O que eu NÃO acho que precise mexer logo\n## PM\nNão precisa agora.\n\n## VO\nTambém não precisa agora.\n\n## TTS polish\nSó por simetria futura, mas não como prioridade agora.\n\n---\n\n# Mapa resumido do que precisaria mexer\n\n## Código / runtime\n- `scene_reconstructor.py` **(novo)**\n- possivelmente `scene_text_integrity_checker.py` **(novo)**\n- possivelmente `scene_word_count_checker.py` **(novo)**\n- `supervisor_runtime.py` **(actualizar)**\n- `scene_director_output_validator.py` **(revisar)**\n- talvez aposentar/integrar `scene_director_output_normalizer.py`\n\n## Contracts\n- `docs/contracts/s1/...` **(actualizar lane contract + supervisor contract)**\n\n## Docs implementação\n- `S1_IMPLEMENTATION_STATUS.md` **(actualizar)**\n- `S1_SCENE_DIRECTOR_REPAIR_FLOW.md` **(actualizar)**\n- possivelmente novo doc específico de scene reconstruction\n\n## Workspaces\n### `op_s1_scene_director`\n- `PROMPT.md`\n- `CONTEXT.md`\n- `EXAMPLES.md`\n- `MEMORY.md`\n- talvez `IDENTITY.md`\n\n### `sm_s1_pre_production`\n- `WORKFLOW.md`\n- `CONTEXT.md`\n- talvez `IDENTITY.md`\n\n---\n\n# Minha recomendação objectiva\n## Ordem mais inteligente\n### 1. Portar/adaptar a lógica do V3\nPrimeiro fazer funcionar.\n\n### 2. Ajustar runtime/validator\nFechar o lane.\n\n### 3. Rodar teste real\nVer se passa.\n\n### 4. Só depois alinhar docs/workspaces/contracts\nCom o desenho já provado.\n\n---\n\n# Em uma frase\n## Sim:\nse formos portar a lógica do V3, o certo é actualizar também:\n- runtime\n- contracts\n- docs do S1\n- workspace do supervisor\n- workspace do `scene_director`\n\nMas eu faria isso **depois de validar o port principal**, para não documentar cedo demais algo que ainda não provou funcionar.\n\nSe quiser, eu sigo agora pelo caminho certo:\n### começar a adaptar o `scene_reconstructor.py` do V3 para o S1 actual.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169cd597d2e208190b4a948ca8c2d56de\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":821,"output":1459,"cacheRead":220160,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":222440,"cost":{"input":0.0020525,"output":0.021885,"cacheRead":0.05504,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0789775}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775065463468,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd59787fc481909ff475ae3d9ca197"}}
{"type":"message","id":"91ca0ba8","parentId":"ffe474c6","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:45:51.410Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Wed 2026-04-01 14:45 GMT-3] Ordem mais inteligente\n1. Portar/adaptar a lógica do V3\nPrimeiro fazer funcionar.\n\n2. Ajustar runtime/validator\nFechar o lane.\n\n3. Rodar teste real\nVer se passa.\n\n4. Só depois > Faz estes 3 de forma continuada por favor"}],"timestamp":1775065551341}}
{"type":"message","id":"29e750ee","parentId":"91ca0ba8","timestamp":"2026-04-01T17:46:36.863Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Vou seguir agora nessa ordem: adaptar a lógica do V3 para o S1 actual, ajustar o runtime/validator, e depois rodar novo teste real antes de mexer mais em docs/workspaces.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0785557c08065f410169cd59d4c74881908f34c7338ae1f030\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_eU8kRlrPO7MhyweVrfkng9L1|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd59d5c450819092555c02c9e100a0","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\Desktop\\content-factory\\auto_content_factory\\runtime\\s1\\supervisor_skills\\scene_reconstructor.py","content":"from __future__ import annotations\n\nimport json\nimport re\nfrom typing import Any\n\nWORD_RE = re.compile(r\"\\S+\")\n\n\ndef reconstruct_scene_batch(\n    *,\n    agent_output: dict[str, Any],\n    original_text: str,\n    min_words: int,\n    max_words: int,\n    batch_id: str,\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    scenes = agent_output.get(\"scenes\", [])\n    if not isinstance(scenes, list):\n        return _fail(\"invalid_output_shape\", \"scene_director output does not contain a valid scenes list\")\n\n    if not original_text.strip():\n        return _fail(\"empty_original_text\", \"Batch text is empty\")\n\n    original_sentences = _split_sentences(original_text)\n    if not original_sentences:\n        return _fail(\"no_sentences\", \"Could not split original batch text into sentences\")\n\n    if not scenes:\n        rebuilt = _rebuild_from_scratch(original_text, min_words, max_words)\n        return _success(agent_output, rebuilt, batch_id, path=\"reconstruct\")\n\n    grouped = _extract_semantic_groups(scenes)\n    if not grouped:\n        rebuilt = _rebuild_from_scratch(original_text, min_words, max_words)\n        return _success(agent_output, rebuilt, batch_id, path=\"reconstruct\")\n\n    if not _texts_match(grouped, original_text):\n        rebuilt = _rebuild_from_scratch(original_text, min_words, max_words)\n        return _success(agent_output, rebuilt, batch_id, path=\"reconstruct\")\n\n    fixed_groups = _rebalance_groups(grouped, min_words, max_words)\n    final_scenes = _materialize_scenes_from_groups(scenes, fixed_groups, original_text)\n    if final_scenes is None:\n        rebuilt = _rebuild_from_scratch(original_text, min_words, max_words)\n        return _success(agent_output, rebuilt, batch_id, path=\"reconstruct\")\n\n    return _success(agent_output, final_scenes, batch_id, path=\"match_fix\")\n\n\ndef _split_sentences(text: str) -> list[str]:\n    parts = re.split(r'(?<=[.!?;])\\s+|\\n+', text.strip())\n    return [p.strip() for p in parts if p.strip()]\n\n\ndef _normalize(text: str) -> str:\n    return re.sub(r'\\s+', ' ', text.strip()).lower()\n\n\ndef _count_words(text: str) -> int:\n    return len(WORD_RE.findall(text))\n\n\ndef _texts_match(grouped: list[str], original_text: str) -> bool:\n    combined = \" \".join(grouped)\n    return _normalize(combined) == _normalize(original_text)\n\n\ndef _extract_semantic_groups(scenes: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> list[str]:\n    groups = []\n    for scene in scenes:\n        narration = scene.get(\"narration_original\", \"\")\n        if isinstance(narration, str) and narration.strip():\n            groups.append(narration.strip())\n    return groups\n\n\ndef _rebalance_groups(groups: list[str], min_words: int, max_words: int) -> list[str]:\n    sentence_groups = [_split_sentences(group) for group in groups]\n\n    changed = True\n    passes = 0\n    while changed and passes < 10:\n        changed = False\n        passes += 1\n\n        for i in range(len(sentence_groups)):\n            if not sentence_groups[i]:\n                continue\n\n            text = \" \".join(sentence_groups[i])\n            count = _count_words(text)\n\n            if count > max_words and len(sentence_groups[i]) > 1:\n                if i < len(sentence_groups) - 1:\n                    moved = sentence_groups[i].pop()\n                    sentence_groups[i + 1].insert(0, moved)\n                    changed = True\n                elif i > 0:\n                    moved = sentence_groups[i].pop(0)\n                    sentence_groups[i - 1].append(moved)\n                    changed = True\n\n            elif count < min_words and i < len(sentence_groups) - 1 and sentence_groups[i + 1]:\n                if len(sentence_groups[i + 1]) > 1:\n                    pulled = sentence_groups[i + 1].pop(0)\n                    sentence_groups[i].append(pulled)\n                    changed = True\n                elif len(sentence_groups[i + 1]) == 1:\n                    pulled = sentence_groups[i + 1].pop(0)\n                    sentence_groups[i].append(pulled)\n                    changed = True\n\n        sentence_groups = [g for g in sentence_groups if g]\n\n    if len(sentence_groups) >= 2:\n        last_count = _count_words(\" \".join(sentence_groups[-1]))\n        prev_count = _count_words(\" \".join(sentence_groups[-2]))\n        if last_count < max(1, min_words // 2) and prev_count + last_count <= max_words:\n            sentence_groups[-2].extend(sentence_groups[-1])\n            sentence_groups.pop()\n\n    return [\" \".join(group).strip() for group in sentence_groups if group]\n\n\ndef _rebuild_from_scratch(original_text: str, min_words: int, max_words: int) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\n    sentences = _split_sentences(original_text)\n    target = (min_words + max_words) // 2\n\n    groups: list[list[str]] = []\n    current: list[str] = []\n    current_count = 0\n\n    for sentence in sentences:\n        count = _count_words(sentence)\n        if current and current_count + count > max_words:\n            groups.append(current)\n            current = [sentence]\n            current_count = count\n        else:\n            current.append(sentence)\n            current_count += count\n            if current_count >= target:\n                groups.append(current)\n                current = []\n                current_count = 0\n\n    if current:\n        groups.append(current)\n\n    rebalanced = _rebalance_groups([\" \".join(g) for g in groups], min_words, max_words)\n\n    scenes = []\n    for idx, text in enumerate(rebalanced, start=1):\n        scenes.append(\n            {\n                \"scene_local_id\": f\"scene_{idx:02d}\",\n                \"scene_title\": f\"Scene {idx}\",\n                \"scene_summary\": text[:160].strip(),\n                \"narrative_function\": \"narrative_progression\",\n                \"narration_original\": text,\n            }\n        )\n    return scenes\n\n\ndef _materialize_scenes_from_groups(\n    original_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]],\n    grouped_texts: list[str],\n    original_text: str,\n) -> list[dict[str, Any]] | None:\n    source_tokens = WORD_RE.findall(original_text.replace(\"\\r\\n\", \" \").replace(\"\\n\", \" \"))\n    cursor = 1\n    scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\n\n    for idx, text in enumerate(grouped_texts, start=1):\n        tokens = WORD_RE.findall(text)\n        if not tokens:\n            return None\n        start_word = cursor\n        end_word = cursor + len(tokens) - 1\n        if end_word > len(source_tokens):\n            return None\n\n        exact_text = \" \".join(source_tokens[start_word - 1 : end_word])\n        template = original_scenes[min(idx - 1, len(original_scenes) - 1)] if original_scenes else {}\n        scenes.append(\n            {\n                \"scene_local_id\": template.get(\"scene_local_id\") or f\"scene_{idx:02d}\",\n                \"scene_title\": template.get(\"scene_title\") or f\"Scene {idx}\",\n                \"scene_summary\": template.get(\"scene_summary\") or text[:160].strip(),\n                \"narrative_function\": template.get(\"narrative_function\") or \"narrative_progression\",\n                \"narration_original\": exact_text,\n                \"start_word\": start_word,\n                \"end_word\": end_word,\n                \"estimated_scene_word_count\": len(tokens),\n            }\n        )\n        cursor = end_word + 1\n\n    if cursor != len(source_tokens) + 1:\n        return None\n    return scenes\n\n\ndef _success(agent_output: dict[str, Any], scenes: list[dict[str, Any]], batch_id: str, *, path: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    return {\n        \"ok\": True,\n        \"path\": path,\n        \"output\": {\n            \"batch_id\": agent_output.get(\"batch_id\") or batch_id,\n            \"operator\": agent_output.get(\"operator\") or \"scene_director\",\n            \"scenes\": scenes,\n        },\n        \"errors\": [],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n\n\ndef _fail(code: str, message: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    return {\n        \"ok\": False,\n        \"errors\": [{\"code\": code, \"message\": message}],\n        \"warnings\": [],\n    }\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\Desktop\\\\content-factory\\\\auto_content_factory\\\\runtime\\\\s1\\\\supervisor_skills\\\\scene_reconstructor.py\",\"content\":\"from __future__ import annotations\\n\\nimport json\\nimport re\\nfrom typing import Any\\n\\nWORD_RE = re.compile(r\\\"\\\\S+\\\")\\n\\n\\ndef reconstruct_scene_batch(\\n    *,\\n    agent_output: dict[str, Any],\\n    original_text: str,\\n    min_words: int,\\n    max_words: int,\\n    batch_id: str,\\n) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    scenes = agent_output.get(\\\"scenes\\\", [])\\n    if not isinstance(scenes, list):\\n        return _fail(\\\"invalid_output_shape\\\", \\\"scene_director output does not contain a valid scenes list\\\")\\n\\n    if not original_text.strip():\\n        return _fail(\\\"empty_original_text\\\", \\\"Batch text is empty\\\")\\n\\n    original_sentences = _split_sentences(original_text)\\n    if not original_sentences:\\n        return _fail(\\\"no_sentences\\\", \\\"Could not split original batch text into sentences\\\")\\n\\n    if not scenes:\\n        rebuilt = _rebuild_from_scratch(original_text, min_words, max_words)\\n        return _success(agent_output, rebuilt, batch_id, path=\\\"reconstruct\\\")\\n\\n    grouped = _extract_semantic_groups(scenes)\\n    if not grouped:\\n        rebuilt = _rebuild_from_scratch(original_text, min_words, max_words)\\n        return _success(agent_output, rebuilt, batch_id, path=\\\"reconstruct\\\")\\n\\n    if not _texts_match(grouped, original_text):\\n        rebuilt = _rebuild_from_scratch(original_text, min_words, max_words)\\n        return _success(agent_output, rebuilt, batch_id, path=\\\"reconstruct\\\")\\n\\n    fixed_groups = _rebalance_groups(grouped, min_words, max_words)\\n    final_scenes = _materialize_scenes_from_groups(scenes, fixed_groups, original_text)\\n    if final_scenes is None:\\n        rebuilt = _rebuild_from_scratch(original_text, min_words, max_words)\\n        return _success(agent_output, rebuilt, batch_id, path=\\\"reconstruct\\\")\\n\\n    return _success(agent_output, final_scenes, batch_id, path=\\\"match_fix\\\")\\n\\n\\ndef _split_sentences(text: str) -> list[str]:\\n    parts = re.split(r'(?<=[.!?;])\\\\s+|\\\\n+', text.strip())\\n    return [p.strip() for p in parts if p.strip()]\\n\\n\\ndef _normalize(text: str) -> str:\\n    return re.sub(r'\\\\s+', ' ', text.strip()).lower()\\n\\n\\ndef _count_words(text: str) -> int:\\n    return len(WORD_RE.findall(text))\\n\\n\\ndef _texts_match(grouped: list[str], original_text: str) -> bool:\\n    combined = \\\" \\\".join(grouped)\\n    return _normalize(combined) == _normalize(original_text)\\n\\n\\ndef _extract_semantic_groups(scenes: list[dict[str, Any]]) -> list[str]:\\n    groups = []\\n    for scene in scenes:\\n        narration = scene.get(\\\"narration_original\\\", \\\"\\\")\\n        if isinstance(narration, str) and narration.strip():\\n            groups.append(narration.strip())\\n    return groups\\n\\n\\ndef _rebalance_groups(groups: list[str], min_words: int, max_words: int) -> list[str]:\\n    sentence_groups = [_split_sentences(group) for group in groups]\\n\\n    changed = True\\n    passes = 0\\n    while changed and passes < 10:\\n        changed = False\\n        passes += 1\\n\\n        for i in range(len(sentence_groups)):\\n            if not sentence_groups[i]:\\n                continue\\n\\n            text = \\\" \\\".join(sentence_groups[i])\\n            count = _count_words(text)\\n\\n            if count > max_words and len(sentence_groups[i]) > 1:\\n                if i < len(sentence_groups) - 1:\\n                    moved = sentence_groups[i].pop()\\n                    sentence_groups[i + 1].insert(0, moved)\\n                    changed = True\\n                elif i > 0:\\n                    moved = sentence_groups[i].pop(0)\\n                    sentence_groups[i - 1].append(moved)\\n                    changed = True\\n\\n            elif count < min_words and i < len(sentence_groups) - 1 and sentence_groups[i + 1]:\\n                if len(sentence_groups[i + 1]) > 1:\\n                    pulled = sentence_groups[i + 1].pop(0)\\n                    sentence_groups[i].append(pulled)\\n                    changed = True\\n                elif len(sentence_groups[i + 1]) == 1:\\n                    pulled = sentence_groups[i + 1].pop(0)\\n                    sentence_groups[i].append(pulled)\\n                    changed = True\\n\\n        sentence_groups = [g for g in sentence_groups if g]\\n\\n    if len(sentence_groups) >= 2:\\n        last_count = _count_words(\\\" \\\".join(sentence_groups[-1]))\\n        prev_count = _count_words(\\\" \\\".join(sentence_groups[-2]))\\n        if last_count < max(1, min_words // 2) and prev_count + last_count <= max_words:\\n            sentence_groups[-2].extend(sentence_groups[-1])\\n            sentence_groups.pop()\\n\\n    return [\\\" \\\".join(group).strip() for group in sentence_groups if group]\\n\\n\\ndef _rebuild_from_scratch(original_text: str, min_words: int, max_words: int) -> list[dict[str, Any]]:\\n    sentences = _split_sentences(original_text)\\n    target = (min_words + max_words) // 2\\n\\n    groups: list[list[str]] = []\\n    current: list[str] = []\\n    current_count = 0\\n\\n    for sentence in sentences:\\n        count = _count_words(sentence)\\n        if current and current_count + count > max_words:\\n            groups.append(current)\\n            current = [sentence]\\n            current_count = count\\n        else:\\n            current.append(sentence)\\n            current_count += count\\n            if current_count >= target:\\n                groups.append(current)\\n                current = []\\n                current_count = 0\\n\\n    if current:\\n        groups.append(current)\\n\\n    rebalanced = _rebalance_groups([\\\" \\\".join(g) for g in groups], min_words, max_words)\\n\\n    scenes = []\\n    for idx, text in enumerate(rebalanced, start=1):\\n        scenes.append(\\n            {\\n                \\\"scene_local_id\\\": f\\\"scene_{idx:02d}\\\",\\n                \\\"scene_title\\\": f\\\"Scene {idx}\\\",\\n                \\\"scene_summary\\\": text[:160].strip(),\\n                \\\"narrative_function\\\": \\\"narrative_progression\\\",\\n                \\\"narration_original\\\": text,\\n            }\\n        )\\n    return scenes\\n\\n\\ndef _materialize_scenes_from_groups(\\n    original_scenes: list[dict[str, Any]],\\n    grouped_texts: list[str],\\n    original_text: str,\\n) -> list[dict[str, Any]] | None:\\n    source_tokens = WORD_RE.findall(original_text.replace(\\\"\\\\r\\\\n\\\", \\\" \\\").replace(\\\"\\\\n\\\", \\\" \\\"))\\n    cursor = 1\\n    scenes: list[dict[str, Any]] = []\\n\\n    for idx, text in enumerate(grouped_texts, start=1):\\n        tokens = WORD_RE.findall(text)\\n        if not tokens:\\n            return None\\n        start_word = cursor\\n        end_word = cursor + len(tokens) - 1\\n        if end_word > len(source_tokens):\\n            return None\\n\\n        exact_text = \\\" \\\".join(source_tokens[start_word - 1 : end_word])\\n        template = original_scenes[min(idx - 1, len(original_scenes) - 1)] if original_scenes else {}\\n        scenes.append(\\n            {\\n                \\\"scene_local_id\\\": template.get(\\\"scene_local_id\\\") or f\\\"scene_{idx:02d}\\\",\\n                \\\"scene_title\\\": template.get(\\\"scene_title\\\") or f\\\"Scene {idx}\\\",\\n                \\\"scene_summary\\\": template.get(\\\"scene_summary\\\") or text[:160].strip(),\\n                \\\"narrative_function\\\": template.get(\\\"narrative_function\\\") or \\\"narrative_progression\\\",\\n                \\\"narration_original\\\": exact_text,\\n                \\\"start_word\\\": start_word,\\n                \\\"end_word\\\": end_word,\\n                \\\"estimated_scene_word_count\\\": len(tokens),\\n            }\\n        )\\n        cursor = end_word + 1\\n\\n    if cursor != len(source_tokens) + 1:\\n        return None\\n    return scenes\\n\\n\\ndef _success(agent_output: dict[str, Any], scenes: list[dict[str, Any]], batch_id: str, *, path: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    return {\\n        \\\"ok\\\": True,\\n        \\\"path\\\": path,\\n        \\\"output\\\": {\\n            \\\"batch_id\\\": agent_output.get(\\\"batch_id\\\") or batch_id,\\n            \\\"operator\\\": agent_output.get(\\\"operator\\\") or \\\"scene_director\\\",\\n            \\\"scenes\\\": scenes,\\n        },\\n        \\\"errors\\\": [],\\n        \\\"warnings\\\": [],\\n    }\\n\\n\\ndef _fail(code: str, message: str) -> dict[str, Any]:\\n    return {\\n        \\\"ok\\\": False,\\n        \\\"errors\\\": [{\\\"code\\\": code, \\\"message\\\": message}],\\n        \\\"warnings\\\": [],\\n    }\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":9348,"output":2212,"cacheRead":212480,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":224040,"cost":{"input":0.023370000000000002,"output":0.03318,"cacheRead":0.05312,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.10967}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775065552529,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd59d266808190bbbf5600298047ae"}}
