{"type":"message","id":"a4d855a8","parentId":"995f5168","timestamp":"2026-04-01T18:01:46.340Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_i8L5o6L69OkGLmNM6zI26frN|fc_0785557c08065f410169cd5d7adb788190a0b979961fbcb098","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\User-OEM\\.openclaw\\workspace\\TASKS.md","oldText":"### Priority 1 — Finalize S1 as integration-ready\nGoal: treat S1 as strong enough for upstream integration, while keeping one last runtime-quality mindset.\n\nCurrent status:\n- tests green\n- schema/contracts/workspaces substantially aligned\n- runtime substantially stronger than before\n- still worth validating inside upstream flow before calling it fully done\n\nRemaining S1 objectives:\n- validate controlled runtime path with real upstream-shaped inputs\n- inspect real S1 output quality, not only tests\n- keep note of any integration-only bugs that appear once PM/VO feed the sector\n\n### Priority 2 — PM and VO operational diagnosis + OpenClaw realisation\nAfter freezing S1 as integration-ready, move to PM and VO.\n\nDesired outcome:\n- PM and VO become real OpenClaw agents\n- PM and VO have proper workspaces in OpenClaw\n- PM and VO run on `gpt-5.4-mini`\n- PM -> VO -> S1 canonical workflow runs end-to-end on a controlled test\n\nLikely areas to inspect:\n- `docs/contracts/`\n- `runtime/pm`\n- current PM/VO contracts, skills, runtime wiring, and OpenClaw registration state\n\n## Execution rule\nDo not rely on chat memory for this mission. Continue from this file + repo state until the human returns or a hard blocker is reached.\n","newText":"### Priority 1 — Finish the S1 scene_director lane\nGoal: get the S1 scene_director lane to pass robustly under the canonical PM -> VO -> S1 flow.\n\nCurrent status:\n- PM is realized and functional as a real OpenClaw agent\n- VO is realized and functional as a real OpenClaw agent\n- `PM -> VO -> ready_for_s1` is proven in runtime reality\n- the remaining bottleneck is the S1 `scene_director` lane\n\nWhat has already been done:\n- added `--local` for scene_director batch isolation\n- tested/reinforced operator workspace and supervisor message\n- identified residual boundary and over-segmentation failures\n- inspected V3 and found mature reference logic in:\n  - `scene_word_count_checker.py`\n  - `scene_text_validator.py`\n  - `scene_reconstructor.py`\n- started port/adaptation of V3-style reconstruction into the S1 runtime\n- added `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/scene_reconstructor.py`\n- adapted `supervisor_runtime.py` to use the reconstructor before final validation\n- fixed one robustness issue where missing batch output caused `FileNotFoundError`\n\nImmediate next objectives:\n- inspect the result of the latest full S1 rerun from scratch\n- if still failing, identify whether failure is:\n  - reconstructor logic\n  - validator mismatch\n  - missing batch output / operator execution\n  - screenplay semantic validation\n- continue iterating until S1 reaches `b1_complete`\n\n### Priority 2 — Only after S1 is truly stable\nOnce S1 is stable under real PM -> VO -> S1 flow:\n- align any remaining contracts/docs/workspaces to the proven design\n- only then move focus downstream/upstream again\n\n## Execution rule\nDo not rely on chat memory for this mission. Continue from this file + repo state until the human returns or a hard blocker is reached.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"C:\\\\Users\\\\User-OEM\\\\.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\TASKS.md\",\"oldText\":\"### Priority 1 — Finalize S1 as integration-ready\\nGoal: treat S1 as strong enough for upstream integration, while keeping one last runtime-quality mindset.\\n\\nCurrent status:\\n- tests green\\n- schema/contracts/workspaces substantially aligned\\n- runtime substantially stronger than before\\n- still worth validating inside upstream flow before calling it fully done\\n\\nRemaining S1 objectives:\\n- validate controlled runtime path with real upstream-shaped inputs\\n- inspect real S1 output quality, not only tests\\n- keep note of any integration-only bugs that appear once PM/VO feed the sector\\n\\n### Priority 2 — PM and VO operational diagnosis + OpenClaw realisation\\nAfter freezing S1 as integration-ready, move to PM and VO.\\n\\nDesired outcome:\\n- PM and VO become real OpenClaw agents\\n- PM and VO have proper workspaces in OpenClaw\\n- PM and VO run on `gpt-5.4-mini`\\n- PM -> VO -> S1 canonical workflow runs end-to-end on a controlled test\\n\\nLikely areas to inspect:\\n- `docs/contracts/`\\n- `runtime/pm`\\n- current PM/VO contracts, skills, runtime wiring, and OpenClaw registration state\\n\\n## Execution rule\\nDo not rely on chat memory for this mission. Continue from this file + repo state until the human returns or a hard blocker is reached.\\n\",\"newText\":\"### Priority 1 — Finish the S1 scene_director lane\\nGoal: get the S1 scene_director lane to pass robustly under the canonical PM -> VO -> S1 flow.\\n\\nCurrent status:\\n- PM is realized and functional as a real OpenClaw agent\\n- VO is realized and functional as a real OpenClaw agent\\n- `PM -> VO -> ready_for_s1` is proven in runtime reality\\n- the remaining bottleneck is the S1 `scene_director` lane\\n\\nWhat has already been done:\\n- added `--local` for scene_director batch isolation\\n- tested/reinforced operator workspace and supervisor message\\n- identified residual boundary and over-segmentation failures\\n- inspected V3 and found mature reference logic in:\\n  - `scene_word_count_checker.py`\\n  - `scene_text_validator.py`\\n  - `scene_reconstructor.py`\\n- started port/adaptation of V3-style reconstruction into the S1 runtime\\n- added `runtime/s1/supervisor_skills/scene_reconstructor.py`\\n- adapted `supervisor_runtime.py` to use the reconstructor before final validation\\n- fixed one robustness issue where missing batch output caused `FileNotFoundError`\\n\\nImmediate next objectives:\\n- inspect the result of the latest full S1 rerun from scratch\\n- if still failing, identify whether failure is:\\n  - reconstructor logic\\n  - validator mismatch\\n  - missing batch output / operator execution\\n  - screenplay semantic validation\\n- continue iterating until S1 reaches `b1_complete`\\n\\n### Priority 2 — Only after S1 is truly stable\\nOnce S1 is stable under real PM -> VO -> S1 flow:\\n- align any remaining contracts/docs/workspaces to the proven design\\n- only then move focus downstream/upstream again\\n\\n## Execution rule\\nDo not rely on chat memory for this mission. Continue from this file + repo state until the human returns or a hard blocker is reached.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":108,"output":747,"cacheRead":235008,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":235863,"cost":{"input":0.00027,"output":0.011205,"cacheRead":0.058752,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.070227}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775066487611,"responseId":"resp_0785557c08065f410169cd5d78a1e88190a62a88764b509fa4"}}
